		"B-boying or breaking, also called breakdancing, is a style of street dance that originated primarily among African American and Puerto Rican youth, many former members of the Black Spades, the Young Spades, and the Baby Spades, during the mid 1970s. The dance spread worldwide due to popularity in the media, especially in regions such as the United Kingdom, Canada, Japan, Germany, France, Russia, and South Korea."@en ,
		"La breakdance \\u00E8 una danza acrobatica sviluppata dalle comunit\\u00E0 giovanili afro-americane e America Latina nel Bronx a partire dal 1968. Dj Kool Herc coni\\u00F2 il termine b-boy per identificare i giovani che ballavano scendendo \\"a terra\\", durante i suoi breaks musicali nelle feste di strada del 1972."@it ,
		"Le ou la breakdance, \\u00E9galement appel\\u00E9(e) break dance, break, breaking, breakdancing, b-boying \\u2014 terme privil\\u00E9gi\\u00E9 aux \\u00C9tats-Unis \\u2014 est un style de danse d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 \\u00E0 New York dans les ann\\u00E9es 1970, caract\\u00E9ris\\u00E9 par son aspect acrobatique et ses figures au sol. Un danseur de breakdance est appel\\u00E9 breaker, breakdancer, Bboy ou b-boy (pour un homme), Bgirl  ou b-girl (pour une femme).Il y a souvent un amalgame entre la breakdance et d\'autres danses."@fr ,
		"\\u30D6\\u30EC\\u30A4\\u30AF\\u30C0\\u30F3\\u30B9\\uFF08breakin\'\\uFF09\\u306F\\u30AA\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u30C9\\u30B9\\u30AF\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30D2\\u30C3\\u30D7\\u30DB\\u30C3\\u30D7\\u306B\\u5206\\u985E\\u3055\\u308C\\u308B\\u30B9\\u30C8\\u30EA\\u30FC\\u30C8\\u30C0\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u306E\\u4E00\\u3064\\u3002\\u65E5\\u672C\\u8A9E\\u3067\\u306F\\u30D6\\u30EC\\u30A4\\u30AF\\u3068\\u7565\\u3055\\u308C\\u305F\\u308A\\u3001\\u539F\\u8A9E\\u306E\\u30D6\\u30EC\\u30A4\\u30AD\\u30F3\\uFF08breakin\'\\uFF09\\u3068\\u3082\\u547C\\u3070\\u308C\\u308B\\u3002B-boying\\u3068\\u3082\\u547C\\u3070\\u308C\\u3001\\u3053\\u306E\\u30C0\\u30F3\\u30B5\\u30FC\\u3092B-boy\\u3084B-girl\\u3068\\u547C\\u3076\\u3002B-boy\\u3001B-girl\\u306E\\u201CB\\u201D\\u306Fbad\\uFF08\\u4E0D\\u826F\\uFF09\\u3084black\\uFF08\\u9ED2\\u4EBA\\uFF09\\u306E\\u201CB\\u201D\\u3068\\u8A8D\\u8B58\\u3055\\u308C\\u304C\\u3061\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u304C\\u3001\\u3053\\u308C\\u306F\\u9593\\u9055\\u3044\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002B-boy\\u3068\\u306Fbreaks\\uFF08breakbeats)\\u3067\\u8E0A\\u308Bboy\\u306E\\u4E8B\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u300C\\u30D6\\u30EC\\u30A4\\u30AF\\u30C0\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u300D\\u3068\\u3044\\u3046\\u65E5\\u672C\\u3067\\u306E\\u547C\\u79F0\\u306F\\u30011984\\u5E74\\u306E\\u6620\\u753B\\u300E\\u30D6\\u30EC\\u30A4\\u30AF\\u30C0\\u30F3\\u30B9\\uFF08\\u539F\\u984C\\uFF1ABreakin\'\\uFF09\\u300F\\u516C\\u958B\\u306B\\u4F34\\u3044\\u3001\\u4E00\\u822C\\u306B\\u6D78\\u900F\\u3057\\u305F\\u3002\\u30D2\\u30C3\\u30D7\\u30DB\\u30C3\\u30D7\\u56DB\\u5927\\u8981\\u7D20\\u306E\\u4E00\\u3064\\u3002\\u73FE\\u5728\\u4E16\\u754C\\u3067\\u4E00\\u756A\\u30C0\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u4EBA\\u53E3\\u304C\\u591A\\u3044\\u30B8\\u30E3\\u30F3\\u30EB\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Break-dance \\u0438\\u043B\\u0438 b-boying (\\u0430\\u043D\\u0433\\u043B. breakdance)\\u2014 \\u0443\\u043B\\u0438\\u0447\\u043D\\u044B\\u0439 \\u0442\\u0430\\u043D\\u0435\\u0446, \\u043E\\u0434\\u043D\\u043E \\u0438\\u0437 \\u0442\\u0435\\u0447\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0439 \\u0445\\u0438\\u043F-\\u0445\\u043E\\u043F \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u044B. \\u0421\\u0435\\u0433\\u043E\\u0434\\u043D\\u044F \\u0432\\u044B\\u0434\\u0435\\u043B\\u044F\\u044E\\u0442 \\u0434\\u0432\\u0430 \\u043E\\u0441\\u043D\\u043E\\u0432\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u0432\\u0438\\u0434\\u0430 \\u044D\\u0442\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0442\\u0430\\u043D\\u0446\\u0430: \\u043D\\u0438\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u0439 \\u044D\\u043A\\u0441\\u0442\\u0440\\u0438\\u043C \\u2013 \\u0442\\u0430\\u043D\\u0446\\u043E\\u0440 \\u0438\\u0441\\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u043D\\u044F\\u0435\\u0442 \\u0432 \\u043E\\u0441\\u043D\\u043E\\u0432\\u043D\\u043E\\u043C \\u0430\\u043A\\u0440\\u043E\\u0431\\u0430\\u0442\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0435 \\u0438 \\u0441\\u0438\\u043B\\u043E\\u0432\\u044B\\u0435 \\u0442\\u0440\\u044E\\u043A\\u0438 \\u043D\\u0430 \\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u0443; 		"Breakdance, ook bekend als breaking of b-boying, is een dansstijl. Breakdance vormt samen met rap, graffiti en dj-en de vier elementaire onderdelen van hiphop. Het dansen zelf wordt breakdancen of breakdansen genoemd."@nl ,
		"Breakdance (tamb\\u00E9m conhecido como breaking ou b - boying em alguns lugares) \\u00E9 um estilo de dan\\u00E7a de rua, parte da cultura do Hip-Hop criada por afro-americanos e latinos na d\\u00E9cada de 1970 em Nova Iorque, Estados Unidos. Normalmente \\u00E9 dan\\u00E7ada ao som do Hip-Hop ou de Electro."@pt ,
		"Breakdance, Breaking, B-Boying bzw. B-Girling ist eine urspr\\u00FCnglich auf der Stra\\u00DFe getanzte Tanzform, die als Teil der Hip-Hop-Bewegung unter afroamerikanischen Jugendlichen in Manhattan und der s\\u00FCdlichen Bronx im New York der fr\\u00FChen 1970er Jahre entstanden ist. Getanzt wird zu Pop, Funk oder Hip-Hop.F\\u00FCr viele Jugendliche bot B-Boying, wie es in den 1970er und fr\\u00FChen 1980er Jahren genannt wurde, eine Alternative zur Gewalt der st\\u00E4dtischen Stra\\u00DFen-Gangs."@de ,
		"El Break Dance o Breaking es una danza urbana que forma parte de la cultura Hip-Hop surgida en las comunidades afro-americanas de los barrios  neoyorquinos como Bronx y Brooklyn en los 70.Si bien es cierto que alcanzar\\u00EDa un reconocimiento m\\u00E1s alto en la d\\u00E9cada de los 80, gracias a la influencia de diversos artistas como James Brown o Michael Jackson, y pel\\u00EDculas como Breakin\' y Beat Street que extendieron el movimiento hacia los pa\\u00EDses europeos y Latinoam\\u00E9rica."@es .

Das College wird von Studenten aus 36 US-amerikanischen Staaten und 34 L\\u00E4ndern besucht. Im Jahr 2013 besuchten 364 Studenten das College. Studienschwerpunkt ist die Human\\u00F6kologie."@de .
dbr:Black_Arts_Movement	rdfs:label	"Black Arts Movement"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Black Arts Movement, Black Aesthetics Movement or BAM  is the artistic branch of the Black Power movement. It was started in Harlem by writer and activist Amiri Baraka (born Everett LeRoi Jones). Time magazine describes the Black Arts Movement as the \\"single most controversial movement in the history of African-American literature \\u2013 possibly in American literature as a whole.\\" The Black Arts Repertory Theatre is a key institution of the Black Arts Movement."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"I poeti Black Mountain, talvolta definiti projectivist poets, sono stati un gruppo di poeti statunitensi di avanguardia o postmoderni della met\\u00E0 del XX secolo, aventi quale riferimento il Black Mountain College."@it ,
		"Os poetas de Black Mountain  ( Black Mountain poets),  tamb\\u00E9m conhecidos  como poetas projetivistas (projectivist poets), foram um grupo de poetas dos Estados Unidos do per\\u00EDodo p\\u00F3s Segunda Guerra Mundial, mais especificamente surgido nos anos de 1950, sendo considerados poetas pertencentes a uma segunda onda de poetas vanguardistas ou p\\u00F3smodernos, reunidos em torno do Black Mountain College,  uma universidade experimental da Carolina do Norte que colocava em pr\\u00E1tica a pedagogia de John Dewey e onde atuavam como professores nomes como William Carlos Williams e John Cage.Em 1950, Charles Olson publicou seu ensaio, verso projetivo. "@pt ,
		"The Black Mountain poets, sometimes called projectivist poets, were a group of mid 20th century American avant-garde or postmodern poets centered on Black Mountain College in North Carolina."@en ,
		"L\'\\u00E9ph\\u00E9mere Black Mountain Review (7 num\\u00E9ros entre 1954 et 1957) rentre dans l\'histoire litt\\u00E9raire en 1960, quand l\'\\u00E9pith\\u00E8te \\u201CBlack Mountain School\\u201D est fabriqu\\u00E9 pour d\\u00E9crire certains auteurs qui publient dans la revue, qu\'ils aient ou pas fr\\u00E9quent\\u00E9s Black Mountain College."@fr .

dbr:Celtic_Revival	rdfs:label	"Renascen\\u00E7a c\\u00E9ltica"@pt ,

		"Irische Renaissance"@de ,
		"Odrodzenie Irlandzkie w literaturze"@pl ;
	rdfs:comment	"Celtic Revival covers a variety of movements and trends, mostly in the 19th and 20th centuries, which drew on the traditions of Celtic literature and Celtic art, or in fact more often what art historians call Insular art, the Early Medieval style of Ireland and Britain."@en ,
		"Als irische Renaissance (englisch  Irish Renaissance, auch Irish Revival oder f\\u00E4lschlich Celtic Revival, Celtic Dawn, irisch Athbheochan Cheilteach ) wird eine Vielzahl von Bestrebungen, Bewegungen und einzelnen Personen zusammengefasst, die Ende des 19. Jahrhunderts und Anfang des 20. Jahrhunderts im weitesten Sinne eine Wiedererweckung der irischen Identit\\u00E4t und Kultur zum Ziel hatten."@de ,
		"El Renacimiento C\\u00E9ltico (Celtic Revival, en ingl\\u00E9s; tambi\\u00E9n conocido como Irish Literary Revival (\\"Renacimiento literario irland\\u00E9s\\"), tiene su origen en un grupo de autores que impulsaron una nueva apreciaci\\u00F3n de la literatura y la poes\\u00EDa en ga\\u00E9lico a finales del siglo XIX y principios del siglo XX. Entre otros, destacan los siguientes: Lady Gregory, Samuel Ferguson, Standish Halles O\'Grady, Douglas Hyde, Thomas McDonagh, Aubrey de Vere, Percy French, George William Russell, Oliver St."@es ,
		"Renascen\\u00E7a c\\u00E9ltica (Celtic Revival, em ingl\\u00EAs; tamb\\u00E9m conhecido como Irish Literary Revival, \\"Renacemento liter\\u00E1rio irland\\u00EAs\\"), tem a sua origem num grupo de autores que impulsionaram uma nova aprecia\\u00E7\\u00E3o da literatura e a poesia de tem\\u00E1tica celtica em meados do s\\u00E9culo XVII e princ\\u00EDpios do s\\u00E9culo XIX."@pt ,
		"De Ierse Renaissance, in ruimere zin ook wel de Keltische Renaissance (Engels: Celtic Revival) genoemd, was een periode aan het eind van de 19e en het begin van de 20e eeuw waarin de Ierse literatuur, folklore en kunst, die eerder in verval waren geraakt, een sterke heropleving doormaakten. Dit ging gepaard met een opleving van het nationalisme."@nl ,
		"Odrodzenie Irlandzkie w literaturze (ang. Irish Literary Revival, Irish Literary Renaissance) lub Odrodzenie Celtyckie (ang. Celtic Revival) \\u2013 zapocz\\u0105tkowany w latach 80. XIX wieku zwrot irlandzkiej literatury ku tradycji celtyckich mit\\u00F3w, poda\\u0144 i legend, kt\\u00F3re sta\\u0142y si\\u0119 osnow\\u0105 wsp\\u00F3\\u0142czesnych mu tekst\\u00F3w literackich."@pl ,
		"Le Celtic Revival (Renaissance irlandaise en fran\\u00E7ais), \\u00E9galement connu sous le nom d\'Irish Literary Revival (Renaissance litt\\u00E9raire irlandaise) est un mouvement litt\\u00E9raire lanc\\u00E9 par Lady Gregory, Edward Martyn et William Butler Yeats en Irlande en 1896. Le Renouveau avait pour objet de revaloriser la litt\\u00E9rature irlandaise traditionnelle et d\'encourager la cr\\u00E9ation de nouvelles \\u0153uvres s\'inspirant de la culture du pays et se distinguant donc de celle de l\'Angleterre."@fr .

	rdfs:comment	"L\'art conceptuel est un mouvement de l\'art contemporain apparu dans les ann\\u00E9es 1960 mais dont les origines remontent aux ready made de Marcel Duchamp au d\\u00E9but du XXe si\\u00E8cle. L\'art est d\\u00E9fini non par les propri\\u00E9t\\u00E9s esth\\u00E9tiques des objets ou des \\u0153uvres, mais seulement par le concept ou l\'id\\u00E9e de l\'art."@fr ,
		"A arte conceptual ou arte conceitual foi iniciada nos anos 60 do s\\u00E9culo XX (1965); prevaleceu pela d\\u00E9cada de 70 o que implicou uma remodela\\u00E7\\u00E3o dos processos criativos e expressivos. Nesta arte valoriza-se mais a ideia da obra do que o produto acabado, sendo que \\u00E0s vezes este (produto) nem mesmo precisa de existir. \\u00C9 bastante expressada atrav\\u00E9s de fotografias, v\\u00EDdeos, mapas, textos escritos e performances."@pt ,

		"Conceptual art, sometimes simply called Conceptualism, is art in which the concept(s) or idea(s) involved in the work take precedence over traditional aesthetic and material concerns. Many works of conceptual art, sometimes called installations, may be constructed by anyone simply by following a set of written instructions."@en ,
		"Conceptuele kunst (conceptual art) is een kunstvorm waarbij het idee ofwel het concept belangrijker is dan esthetische of materiaal-technische afwegingen."@nl .
dbr:Conceptual_photography	rdfs:label	"Conceptual photography"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Conceptual photography  is a type of photography that illustrates an idea. There have been illustrative photographs made since the medium\'s invention, for example in the earliest staged photographs, such as Hippolyte Bayard\'s Self Portrait as a Drowned Man (1840). However, the term Conceptual Photography derives from Conceptual Art a movement of the late 1960s. Today the term is used to describe either a methodology or a genre."@en .

		"En filosof\\u00EDa, el conceptualismo es una doctrina que se encuentra a medio camino entre el nominalismo y el realismo. El conceptualismo mantiene que aunque los universales (abstracciones o ideas abstractas) no tienen existencia en el mundo externo, existen sin embargo como ideas o conceptos en la mente y que all\\u00ED implican algo m\\u00E1s que palabras."@es ,
		"Konceptualizm - w \\u015Bredniowieczu stanowisko w sporze o uniwersalia, przeciwstawne realizmowi poj\\u0119ciowemu, jedna z umiarkowanych postaci nominalizmu. Konceptuali\\u015Bci utrzymywali, i\\u017C powszechniki nie posiadaj\\u0105 realnego bytu, lecz s\\u0105 jedynie tworami ludzkiej wyobra\\u017Ani. Przedmiotem poj\\u0119\\u0107 og\\u00F3lnych s\\u0105 zatem pewne stany psychiczne. G\\u0142\\u00F3wni przedstawiciele: w filozofii \\u015Bredniowiecznej: Jan z Salisbury w filozofii nowo\\u017Cytnej: Franciszek Su\\u00E1rez R. Descartes John Locke Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz."@pl ,
		"Conceptualism is a philosophical theory that explains universality of particulars as conceptualized frameworks situated within the thinking mind. Intermediate between nominalism and realism, the conceptualist view approaches the metaphysical concept of universals from a perspective that denies their presence in particulars outside the mind\'s perception of them."@en ,
		"\\u6982\\u5FF5\\u8AD6\\uFF08\\u82F1\\u8BED\\uFF1AConceptualism\\uFF09\\uFF0C\\u4E2D\\u53E4\\u7D93\\u9662\\u54F2\\u5B78\\u7684\\u4E00\\u500B\\u5B78\\u6D3E\\uFF0C\\u4ED6\\u5011\\u7684\\u7ACB\\u5834\\u4ECB\\u65BC\\u552F\\u540D\\u8AD6\\u8207\\u552F\\u5BE6\\u8AD6\\u4E4B\\u9593\\uFF0C\\u88AB\\u8A8D\\u70BA\\u662F\\u6298\\u8877\\u5F8C\\u7684\\u552F\\u540D\\u8AD6\\u8005\\u3002\\u8DDF\\u552F\\u540D\\u8AD6\\u8005\\u76F8\\u540C\\uFF0C\\u4ED6\\u5011\\u8A8D\\u70BA\\u5171\\u76F8\\u53EA\\u5B58\\u5728\\u65BC\\u5FC3\\u9748\\u4E4B\\u4E2D\\uFF0C\\u6C92\\u6709\\u5916\\u90E8\\u7684\\u5BE6\\u9AD4\\uFF1B\\u4F46\\u662F\\u4ED6\\u5011\\u8A8D\\u70BA\\u4E00\\u65E6\\u5171\\u76F8\\u88AB\\u5EFA\\u7ACB\\u4E4B\\u5F8C\\uFF0C\\u80FD\\u88AB\\u7406\\u6027\\u6240\\u8A8D\\u8B58\\uFF0C\\u5B83\\u5C31\\u662F\\u5B58\\u5728\\u7684\\uFF0C\\u4E0D\\u6703\\u56E0\\u70BA\\u7279\\u5B9A\\u4EBA\\u6B7B\\u53BB\\u800C\\u6D88\\u5931\\u3002\\u7B2C\\u4E00\\u500B\\u6982\\u5FF5\\u8AD6\\u54F2\\u5B78\\u5BB6\\uFF0C\\u88AB\\u8A8D\\u70BA\\u662F\\u5F7C\\u5F97\\u00B7\\u963F\\u4F2F\\u62C9\\u3002\\u5965\\u5361\\u59C6\\u7684\\u5A01\\u5EC9\\u662F\\u53E6\\u4E00\\u500B\\u91CD\\u8981\\u7684\\u6982\\u5FF5\\u8AD6\\u4EBA\\u7269\\u3002"@zh ,
		"O conceitualismo (portugu\\u00EAs brasileiro) ou conceptualismo (portugu\\u00EAs europeu) conceptualismo (AO 1945: conceptualismo ou concetualismo) junto com o realismo e o nominalismo prop\\u00F5e uma solu\\u00E7\\u00E3o alternativa ao problema da exist\\u00EAncia dos universais. Para o conceitualismo, os universais s\\u00E3o apenas conte\\u00FAdos de nossa mente, intelig\\u00EDveis ou conceitos, representa\\u00E7\\u00F5es do intelecto que as deriva das coisas (universalia post rem) e dessas guarda alguma semelhan\\u00E7a."@pt ,
		"Le conceptualisme est une th\\u00E9orie philosophique selon laquelle un concept (id\\u00E9e g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rale ou abstraite) est un objet mental, et uniquement cela. Un concept (id\\u00E9e de rose, de rouge) est distinct des choses auxquelles il peut s\'appliquer (une rose rouge concr\\u00E8te), ce qui oppose le conceptualisme aux th\\u00E9ories dites r\\u00E9alismes (r\\u00E9alisme des id\\u00E9es ou des universaux) telles que le platonisme."@fr ,
		"\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0630\\u0647\\u0628 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u0635\\u0648\\u0631\\u064A \\u0647\\u0648 \\u0646\\u0638\\u0631\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0641\\u0644\\u0633\\u0641\\u064A\\u0629 \\u062A\\u0641\\u0633\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0637\\u0627\\u0628\\u0639 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0643\\u0644\\u064A \\u0644\\u0644\\u0643\\u064A\\u0627\\u0646\\u0627\\u062A \\u0628\\u0627\\u0639\\u062A\\u0628\\u0627\\u0631\\u0647\\u0627 \\u0623\\u064F\\u0637\\u0631\\u064B\\u0627 \\u062A\\u0635\\u0648\\u0631\\u064A\\u0629 \\u062A\\u0642\\u0639 \\u062F\\u0627\\u062E\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0642\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0641\\u0643\\u0631\\u064A. \\u0648\\u0646\\u0638\\u0631\\u064B\\u0627 \\u0644\\u0648\\u0642\\u0648\\u0639\\u0647\\u0627 \\u0648\\u0633\\u0637 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u0633\\u0645\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0648\\u0627\\u0642\\u0639\\u064A\\u0629\\u060C \\u062A\\u0646\\u062A\\u0647\\u062C \\u0627\\u0644\\u0631\\u0624\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u0635\\u0648\\u0631\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0641\\u0647\\u0648\\u0645 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u064A\\u062A\\u0627\\u0641\\u064A\\u0632\\u064A\\u0642\\u064A \\u0644\\u0644\\u0645\\u0633\\u0644\\u0645\\u0627\\u062A \\u0645\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0646\\u0638\\u0648\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0630\\u064A \\u064A\\u0646\\u0641\\u064A \\u0648\\u062C\\u0648\\u062F\\u0647\\u0627 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0643\\u064A\\u0627\\u0646\\u0627\\u062A \\u062E\\u0627\\u0631\\u062C \\u062A\\u0635\\u0648\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0642\\u0644 \\u0644\\u0647\\u0627."@ar ,
		"Il concettualismo \\u00E8 una dottrina filosofica che ha origine nella teorizzazione del filosofo medievale Pietro Abelardo nell\'ambito della disputa sugli universali e che si trova a met\\u00E0 tra nominalismo e realismo: sostiene il pensatore e teologo francese che gli universali esistono soltanto all\'interno della mente e non hanno realt\\u00E0 esterna o sostanziale.Per i concettualisti, in contrapposizione ai realisti, il concetto non rispecchia semplicemente l\'essenza, o nozione della forma, (universale in re, secondo la terminologia scolastica) della cosa, ma \\u00E8 una costruzione della mente umana. "@it .
dbr:Creative_nonfiction	rdfs:label	"Non-fiction romanc\\u00E9e"@fr ,
		"Creative nonfiction"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Creative nonfiction (also known as literary nonfiction or narrative nonfiction) is a genre of writing that uses literary styles and techniques to create factually accurate narratives. Creative nonfiction contrasts with other nonfiction, such as academic or technical writing or journalism, which is also rooted in accurate fact, but is not primarily written in service to its craft."@en ,
		"La non-fiction romanc\\u00E9e est un genre litt\\u00E9raire qui utilise les styles et les techniques de l\'\\u00E9criture romanesque pour expliquer, exporer ou raconter des faits r\\u00E9els. Ce nouveau genre litt\\u00E9raire contraste avec l\\u2019\\u00E9criture technique ou acad\\u00E9mique, ou le journalisme, qui se nourrissent aussi de faits r\\u00E9els mais qui, eux, n\\u2019ont pas de but cr\\u00E9atif. On compare souvent la non-fiction romanc\\u00E9e \\u00E0 la docufiction en cin\\u00E9ma."@fr .

		"Cultura (do latim cultura) \\u00E9 um conceito de v\\u00E1rias acep\\u00E7\\u00F5es, sendo a mais corrente, especialmente no senso comum, a defini\\u00E7\\u00E3o gen\\u00E9rica formulada por Edward B. Tylor segundo a qual cultura \\u00E9 \\"todo aquele complexo que inclui o conhecimento, as cren\\u00E7as, a arte, a moral, a lei, os costumes e todos os outros h\\u00E1bitos e capacidades adquiridos pelo homem como membro da sociedade\\"."@pt ,
		"En philosophie, le mot culture d\\u00E9signe ce qui est diff\\u00E9rent de la nature, c\'est-\\u00E0-dire ce qui est de l\'ordre de l\'acquis et non de l\'inn\\u00E9. La culture a longtemps \\u00E9t\\u00E9 consid\\u00E9r\\u00E9e comme un trait caract\\u00E9ristique de l\'humanit\\u00E9, qui la distinguait des animaux. N\\u00E9anmoins, des travaux r\\u00E9cents en \\u00E9thologie et en primatologie ont montr\\u00E9 l\'existence de cultures animales.En sociologie, la culture est d\\u00E9finie de fa\\u00E7on plus \\u00E9troite comme \\"ce qui est commun \\u00E0 un groupe d\'individus\\" et comme \\"ce qui le soude\\"."@fr ,

		"Der Sturm (1910\\u20131932) war eine erst w\\u00F6chentliche, dann halbmonatliche, seit 1915 meist monatliche Zeitschrift des Expressionismus, die in Berlin von Herwarth Walden herausgegeben wurde. Im M\\u00E4rz 1912 er\\u00F6ffnete Walden die Sturm-Galerie in einer Abrissvilla in der Berliner Tiergartenstra\\u00DFe mit einer Wanderausstellung des Blauen Reiter. Sp\\u00E4ter war sie in der Potsdamer Stra\\u00DFe 134 A angesiedelt, wo sich auch die Redaktion der Zeitschrift Der Sturm befand."@de ,
		"Der Sturm \\u00E8 un\'importante rivista tedesca dell\'espressionismo con sede editoriale a Berlino.Fu fondata nel 1910 da Herwarth Walden e usc\\u00EC, con frequenza quindicinale fino al 1932.Intorno alla rivista nacque ben presto il cosiddetto Sturmkreis che comprendeva un teatro, una galleria e delle serate, le Sturm-Abende nel corso delle quali venivano recitare poesie espressioniste.La casa editrice pubblic\\u00F2 anche drammi (ad esempio di Hermann Essig e August Stramm), raccolte d\'arte (Oskar Kokoschka), monografie (Kandinsky-Album) e saggi d\'arte di Herwarth Walden.Furono pubblicate anche cartoline artistiche e opere di artisti espressionisti, cubisti e futuristi come Franz Marc, Vasilij Kandinskij, Oskar Kokoschka, August Macke, Gabriele M\\u00FCnter e altri ancora."@it ,
		"Der Sturm \\u2013 czasopismo po\\u015Bwi\\u0119cone sztuce ekspresjonizmu, ukazuj\\u0105ce si\\u0119 w Berlinie w latach 1910\\u20131932, pocz\\u0105tkowo jako tygodnik, p\\u00F3\\u017Aniej dwa razy w miesi\\u0105cu.Pierwszy numer ukaza\\u0142 si\\u0119 3 marca 1910 roku z podtytu\\u0142em \\u201ETygodnik po\\u015Bwi\\u0119cony kulturze i sztuce\\u201D. Wydawc\\u0105 by\\u0142 Herwarth Walden, kt\\u00F3ry ze swoj\\u0105 pierwsz\\u0105 \\u017Con\\u0105 Else Lasker-Sch\\u00FCler mieszka\\u0142 w Berlinie-Wilmersdorfie przy Katharinenstra\\u00DFe 5. Czasopismo popiera\\u0142o wszystkie kierunki \\u00F3wczesnej awangardy: Dadaizm, Futuryzm, Ekspresjonizm i Kubizm."@pl ,
		"Der Sturm (German: The Storm) was a German art and literary magazine covering Expressionism, Cubism, Dada and Surrealism, among other artistic movements. It was published between 1910 and 1932."@en ,
		"Der Sturm (L\'Orage en allemand) est un magazine sur l\'expressionnisme fond\\u00E9 \\u00E0 Berlin en 1910 par Herwarth Walden. Il parut en bi-mensuel jusqu\'en 1932."@fr ,
		"Der Sturm (A Tempestade), 1910/32, foi uma revista vinculada ao Expressionismo alem\\u00E3o e publicada em Berlim, sendo a mais influente deste movimento. Fundada pelo poeta e cr\\u00EDtico de arte Herwarth Walden, que popularizou o termo Expressionismo, criado para caracterizar toda a arte moderna que se opunha ao Impressionismo, mais tarde este abriu uma galeria de arte hom\\u00F4nima (1912), divulgando em seu primeiro ano o grupo Der Blaue Reiter de Munique e os Futuristas italianos."@pt ,
		"Der Sturm (1910\\u20131932) fue una revista expresionista editada en Berl\\u00EDn por Herwarth Walden, publicada en principio semanalmente y m\\u00E1s quincenalmente.Entre los colaboradores literarios de la revista se encuentran Peter Altenberg, Max Brod, Richard Dehmel, Anatole France, Oskar Kokoschka, Knut Hamsun, Arno Holz, Karl Kraus, Selma Lagerl\\u00F6f, Else Lasker-Sch\\u00FCler, Adolf Loos, Heinrich Mann, Paul Scheerbart, Ren\\u00E9 Schickele. Alrededor de la revista se form\\u00F3 el Sturmkreis."@es .

		"In archeologia con il termine earthworks si definiscono le manipolazioni della morfologia del paesaggio aventi una diretta origine antropica, spesso a carattere difensivo o funerario.  Conosciuti talvolta come lumps and bumps (lett. cumuli e cunette), possono essere testimonianza diretta di una struttura (ad es. fossati circolari, motte, etc.) o indicarne la presenza al di sotto la superficie, come nel caso dei tumuli ."@it ,
		"En arqueolog\\u00EDa, una obra de tierra, movimiento de tierras o trabajo de tierra es un t\\u00E9rmino general para describir los cambios artificiales en el nivel de la tierra, por ejemplo un terrapl\\u00E9n o un mont\\u00EDculo. A los movimientos de tierras (earthworks en ingl\\u00E9s), a menudo, se los conoce coloquialmente como \\"terrones y baches\\".Las obras de tierra pueden ser por s\\u00ED mismas yacimientos arqueol\\u00F3gicos conjunto de vestigios, o bien pueden presentar vestigios bajo la superficie."@es ,
		"In archaeology, earthworks are artificial changes in land level, typically made from piles of artificially placed or sculpted rocks and soil. Earthworks are often known as barrows in England, and mounds in North America. Earthworks can themselves be archaeological features or they can show features beneath the surface."@en ,
		"Erdwerk bezeichnet in der Arch\\u00E4ologie ein Bodendenkmal aus Gr\\u00E4ben, W\\u00E4llen und ggf. Palisaden, wobei letztere obert\\u00E4gig oft nicht mehr zu erkennen bzw. selten nachzuweisen sind. Erdwerke k\\u00F6nnen Einbauten aus Holz oder Stein enthalten (was aber nur durch eine Ausgrabung zu kl\\u00E4ren ist) und gehen nur teilweise auf Befestigungsanlagen zur\\u00FCck.Im neuzeitlichen Festungsbau bezeichnet Erdwerk eine aus Erde aufgesch\\u00FCttete Befestigung."@de ,
		"\\u571F\\u5841\\uFF08\\u3069\\u308B\\u3044\\u3001\\u82F1: earthwork fortification\\uFF09\\u3068\\u306F\\u3001\\u6575\\u3084\\u52D5\\u7269\\u306A\\u3069\\u306E\\u4FB5\\u5165\\u3092\\u9632\\u3050\\u305F\\u3081\\u306B\\u7BC9\\u304B\\u308C\\u305F\\u571F\\u88FD\\u306E\\u5824\\u9632\\u72B6\\u306E\\u58C1\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja .

	rdfs:comment	"Literatura ergodyczna (stgr. \\u03AD\\u03C1\\u03B3\\u03BF, \\u00E9rgo \\u2013 praca, stgr. \\u03BF\\u03B4\\u03CC\\u03C2, od\\u00F3s \\u2013 \\u015Bcie\\u017Cka) \\u2013 termin wprowadzony przez ludologa Espena Aarsetha w odniesieniu do tekst\\u00F3w literackich wymagaj\\u0105cych nietrywialnego wysi\\u0142ku ze strony czytelnika, aby ich zawarto\\u015B\\u0107 mog\\u0142a zosta\\u0107 odczytana. Poj\\u0119cie literatury ergodycznej w literaturoznawstwie zdoby\\u0142o rozg\\u0142os za spraw\\u0105 pracy Aarsetha pod tytu\\u0142em Cybertekst."@pl ,
		"Ergodic literature is a term coined by Espen J. Aarseth in his book Cybertext\\u2014Perspectives on Ergodic Literature, and is derived from the Greek words ergon, meaning \\"work\\", and hodos, meaning \\"path\\". Aarseth\'s book contains the most commonly cited definition:In ergodic literature, nontrivial effort is required to allow the reader to traverse the text."@en ,
		"Literatura erg\\u00F3dica es un t\\u00E9rmino acu\\u00F1ado por Espen J. Aarseth en su obra Cybertext - Perspectives on Ergodic Literature, y deriva las palabras griegas \\u1F14\\u03C1\\u03B3\\u03BF\\u03BD (trabajo o esfuerzo) y \\u1F41\\u03B4\\u03CC\\u03C2 (camino o recorrido). El libro de Aarseth contiene la definici\\u00F3n m\\u00E1s citada habitualmente:En la literatura erg\\u00F3dica, se requiere un \\u00ABesfuerzo relevante\\u00BB por parte del lector para atravesar el texto."@es .

		"Aardrijkskunde of geografie (Oudgrieks: \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03BF\\u03C2 (geos), aarde en \\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03B5\\u03B9\\u03BD (grafein), (be)schrijven) is een wetenschappelijke discipline die zich bezighoudt met het bestuderen van het aardoppervlak, het in kaart brengen van vormen van bijvoorbeeld cultuur, het plantenleven en de dierenwereld, gebruik van het milieu en verkeer en het beschrijven van het landschap overal op de wereld.De geografie en verwante vakgebieden worden soms gezamenlijk aangeduid als de ruimtelijke wetenschappen."@nl ,
		"La Geograf\\u00EDa (del griego  - geographia, compuesto de \\u00AB\\u03B7 \\u03B3\\u03B7\\u00BB (h\\u00EA g\\u00EA), \\u2018la Tierra\\u2019 y \\u00AB\\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03B5\\u03B9\\u03BD\\u00BB (graphein), \\u2018describir, dibujar\\u2019, es la ciencia que trata de la descripci\\u00F3n o de la representaci\\u00F3n gr\\u00E1fica de la Tierra. En sentido amplio es la ciencia que estudia la superficie terrestre, las sociedades que la habitan y los territorios, paisajes, lugares o regiones que la forman al relacionarse entre s\\u00ED.El primer autor en utilizar la palabra Geograf\\u00EDa fue Erat\\u00F3stenes (276-194 a."@es ,
		"La geografia (dal latino geographia, a sua volta dal greco antico \\u03B3\\u1FC6, Terra e \\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1, descrizione, scrittura) \\u00E8 la scienza che ha per oggetto lo studio, la descrizione e la rappresentazione della Terra nella configurazione della sua superficie e nella estensione e distribuzione dei fenomeni fisici, biologici, umani che la interessano e che, interagendo tra loro, ne modificano continuamente l\'aspetto.La geografia \\u00E8 molto pi\\u00F9 che la cartografia, cio\\u00E8 lo studio delle mappe, o la topografia, scienze per definizione statistiche. "@it ,
		"Geography (from Greek \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1, geographia, lit. \\"earth description\\") is a field study of the lands, the features, the  inhabitants, and the phenomena of Earth. A literal translation would be \\"to describe or picture or write about the earth\\". The first person to use the word \\"geography\\" was Eratosthenes (276\\u2013194 BC)."@en ,
		"La g\\u00E9ographie (du grec ancien \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1 \\u2013 geographia, compos\\u00E9 de \\u00AB \\u03B7 \\u03B3\\u03B7 \\u00BB (h\\u00EA g\\u00EA) la Terre et \\u00AB \\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03B5\\u03B9\\u03BD \\u00BB (graphein) d\\u00E9crire) est l\'\\u00E9tude d\'une plan\\u00E8te, ses terres, ses caract\\u00E9ristiques, ses habitants, et ses ph\\u00E9nom\\u00E8nes. 		"Die Geographie, Geografie (griechisch \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03B1\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1 geograph\\u00EDa, zusammengesetzt aus \\u03B3\\u1FC6 g\\u0113 \\u201AErde\\u2018 und \\u03B3\\u03C1\\u03AC\\u03C6\\u03B5\\u03B9\\u03BD gr\\u00E1phein \\u201A(be-)schreiben\\u2018) oder Erdkunde ist die sich mit der Erdoberfl\\u00E4che befassende Wissenschaft, sowohl in ihrer physischen Beschaffenheit wie auch als Raum und Ort des menschlichen Lebens und Handelns."@de ,
		"A Geografia \\u00E9 a ci\\u00EAncia que estuda o conjunto de fen\\u00F3menos naturais e humanos, os quais s\\u00E3o aspectos da superf\\u00EDcie da Terra, considerada na sua distribui\\u00E7\\u00E3o e rela\\u00E7\\u00F5es rec\\u00EDprocas. 		"La geometr\\u00EDa (del lat\\u00EDn geometr\\u012Da, y este del griego \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03BC\\u03B5\\u03C4\\u03C1\\u03AF\\u03B1  de \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9 gueo, \\u2018tierra\\u2019, y \\u03BC\\u03B5\\u03C4\\u03C1\\u03AF\\u03B1 metr\\u00EDa, \\u2018medida\\u2019) es una rama de la matem\\u00E1tica que se ocupa del estudio de las propiedades de las figuras  en el plano o el espacio, incluyendo: puntos, rectas, planos, politopos (que incluyen paralelas, perpendiculares, curvas, superficies, pol\\u00EDgonos, poliedros, etc.).Es la base te\\u00F3rica de la geometr\\u00EDa descriptiva o del dibujo t\\u00E9cnico."@es ,

		"A Geometria (em grego antigo: \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03BC\\u03B5\\u03C4\\u03C1\\u03AF\\u03B1; geo- \\"terra\\", -metria \\"medida\\") \\u00E9 um ramo da matem\\u00E1tica preocupado com quest\\u00F5es de forma, tamanho e posi\\u00E7\\u00E3o relativa de figuras e com as propriedades do espa\\u00E7o. Um matem\\u00E1tico que trabalha no campo da geometria \\u00E9 denominado de ge\\u00F4metra."@pt ,
		"Die Geometrie (altgriechisch \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03BC\\u03B5\\u03C4\\u03C1\\u03AF\\u03B1 geometria \\u201AErdma\\u00DF\\u2018, \\u201ALandmessung\\u2018) ist ein Teilgebiet der Mathematik.Einerseits versteht man unter Geometrie die zwei- und dreidimensionale euklidische Geometrie, die Elementargeometrie, die auch im Schulunterricht gelehrt wird und die sich mit Punkten, Geraden, Ebenen, Abst\\u00E4nden, Winkeln etc."@de ,
		"Geometry (from the Ancient Greek: \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03BC\\u03B5\\u03C4\\u03C1\\u03AF\\u03B1; geo- \\"earth\\", -metron \\"measurement\\") is a branch of mathematics concerned with questions of shape, size, relative position of figures, and the properties of space. A mathematician who works in the field of geometry is called a geometer."@en ,
		"Traditionnellement, la g\\u00E9om\\u00E9trie est la partie des math\\u00E9matiques qui \\u00E9tudie les figures du plan et de l\'espace (g\\u00E9om\\u00E9trie euclidienne).Depuis la fin du XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle, la g\\u00E9om\\u00E9trie \\u00E9tudie \\u00E9galement les figures appartenant \\u00E0 d\'autres types d\'espaces (g\\u00E9om\\u00E9trie projective, g\\u00E9om\\u00E9trie non euclidienne, par exemple)."@fr ,
		"De meetkunde of geometrie (van het Oudgrieks: \\u03B3\\u03B5\\u03C9\\u03BC\\u03B5\\u03C4\\u03C1\\u03AF\\u03B1, geo-\\"aarde\\",-Metria \\"meting\\") het \\"meten van de aarde\\" is het onderdeel van de wiskunde, dat zich bezighoudt met het bepalen van afmetingen, vormen, de relatieve positie van figuren en de eigenschappen van de ruimte. De specifiek Nederlandse term meetkunde werd rond 1600 door de Vlaamse wiskundige Simon Stevin ge\\u00EFntroduceerd."@nl .

		"Die Hyperrealit\\u00E4t ist das Abbild von etwas, das es in der Realit\\u00E4t nicht gibt, sondern sein eigenes Simulacrum ist oder das \\u00FCberh\\u00F6hte, idealisierte, den Vorstellungen eines K\\u00FCnstlers entsprechende Bild eines wirklich existierenden Objektes.Diese Denkweise geht u. a."@de ,
		"Hiperrealidad (no confundir con el movimiento art\\u00EDstico Hiperrealismo) es un concepto en semi\\u00F3tica y filosof\\u00EDa postmoderna que se usa para denominar la incapacidad de la conciencia de distinguir la realidad de la fantas\\u00EDa, especialmente en las culturas posmodernas tecnol\\u00F3gicamente avanzadas."@es ,
		"In semiotics and postmodernism, hyperreality is an inability of consciousness to distinguish reality from a simulation of reality, especially in technologically advanced postmodern societies. Hyperreality is seen as a condition in which what is real and what is fiction are seamlessly blended together so that there is no clear distinction between where one ends and the other begins."@en ,
		"Hiperrzeczywisto\\u015B\\u0107 \\u2013 rzeczywisto\\u015B\\u0107 zapo\\u015Bredniczona przez symulacje, bardziej rzeczywista od samej rzeczywisto\\u015Bci, jest efektem zast\\u0105pienia rzeczywisto\\u015Bci jedynie jej znakami. 	rdfs:comment	"Con i termini giapponesi sumi-e (\\u58A8\\u7D75) e suibokuga (\\u6C34\\u58A8\\u753B), oppure con la parola cinese shuimohua (\\u6C34\\u58A8\\u753B), si indica uno stile pittorico monocromatico dell\'Estremo Oriente che utilizza solo inchiostro nero, il sumi, in varie concentrazioni.Questa tecnica nacque in Cina durante la dinastia Tang (618-907), consolidandosi con la dinastia Song (960-1279)."@it ,
		"Ink wash painting, also known as literati painting is an East Asian type of brush painting that uses black ink\\u2014the same as used in East Asian calligraphy, in various concentrations.  For centuries, this most prestigious form of Chinese art was practiced by highly educated scholar gentlemen or literati. Names used in the cultures concerned include: in Chinese shu\\u01D0 m\\u00F2 hu\\u00E0 (\\u6C34\\u58A8\\u756B), in Japanese sumi-e (\\u58A8\\u7D75) or suibokuga (\\u6C34\\u58A8\\u753B), in Korean  sumukhwa (\\uC218\\uBB35\\uD654), and in Vietnamese tranh th\\u1EE7y m\\u1EB7c (\\u5E40\\u6C34\\u58A8)."@en ,
		"Suiboku-ga (jap. \\u6C34\\u58A8\\u753B, suiboku-ga) - styl malarstwa japo\\u0144skiego wywodz\\u0105cy si\\u0119 z Chin. Jest to malarstwo monochromatyczne. Do malowania u\\u017Cywano czarnego tuszu, bardzo rzadko si\\u0119gano po farby (drobne plamy stonowanymi kolorami). 		"Sumi-e (jap. \\u58A8\\u7D75, dt. Tuschebild) ist die Schwarz-Wei\\u00DF-Kunst der Tuschmalerei (Tusche: jap. Sumi). 		"Le lavis est une technique picturale consistant \\u00E0 n\'utiliser qu\'une seule couleur (\\u00E0 l\'aquarelle ou \\u00E0 l\'encre de Chine) qui sera dilu\\u00E9e pour obtenir diff\\u00E9rentes intensit\\u00E9s de couleur. 		"Sumi-\\u00EA (em japon\\u00EAs: \\u58A8\\u7D75),  Suiboku-ga (em japon\\u00EAs: \\u6C34\\u58A8\\u753B) ou Shuimohua (chin\\u00EAs tradicional:\\u6C34\\u58A8\\u756B)  \\u00E9 uma uma t\\u00E9cnica de pintura oriental que surgiu na China no s\\u00E9culo II da era crist\\u00E3. Da China o sumi-\\u00EA foi levado ao Jap\\u00E3o onde tornou-se mais difundido. A palavra tem raiz japonesa e significa pintura com tinta.Seu conceito n\\u00E3o tem liga\\u00E7\\u00E3o com a pintura praticada no ocidente."@pt ,
		"Sumi-e o Suiboku (\\u58A8\\u7D75; tambi\\u00E9n \\"\\u6C34\\u58A8\\u753B;\\", \'suibokuga\'?) es una t\\u00E9cnica de dibujo monocrom\\u00E1tico en tinta de la escuela de pintura japonesa. Se desarroll\\u00F3 en China durante la dinast\\u00EDa Tang (618 - 907) y se implant\\u00F3 como estilo durante la dinast\\u00EDa Song (960 - 1279). Fue introducida en el Jap\\u00F3n a mediados del siglo XIV por monjes budistas zen y creci\\u00F3 en popularidad hasta su apogeo durante el Per\\u00EDodo Muromachi (1338 - 1573)."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Judson Dance Theater was a collective of dancers, composers, and visual artists who performed at the Judson Memorial Church in Greenwich Village, Manhattan New York City between 1962 and 1964. It grew out of a composition class taught by Robert Dunn, a musician who had studied with John Cage."@en ,

		"The law of attraction is the name given to the maxim \\"like attracts like\\" which in New Thought philosophy is used to sum up the idea that by focusing on positive or negative thoughts a person brings positive or negative experiences into their life. This belief is based upon the idea that people and their thoughts are both made from \\"pure energy\\", and the belief that like energy attracts like energy."@en .

		"Neo-conceptual art describes art practices in the 1980s and particularly 1990s to date that derive from the conceptual art movement of the 1960s and 1970s.  These subsequent initiatives have included the Moscow Conceptualists, United States neo-conceptualists such as Sherrie Levine and the Young British Artists, notably Damien Hirst and Tracey Emin in the United Kingdom, where there is also a Stuckism counter-movement and criticism from the 1970s conceptual art group Art and Language."@en .

dbr:Post-conceptual	rdfs:label	"Post-conceptual"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Post-conceptual, Postconceptual, Post-conceptualism or Postconceptualism is an art theory that builds upon the legacy of conceptual art in contemporary art, where the concept(s) or idea(s) involved in the work takes some precedence over traditional aesthetic and material concerns. The term first came into art school parlance through the influence of John Baldessari at the California Institute of the Arts in the early 1970s."@en .

		"\\u0625\\u062D\\u064A\\u0627\\u0621 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0645\\u0627\\u0631\\u0629"@ar ;
	rdfs:comment	"Il revivalismo nell\'architettura \\u00E8 la tendenza all\'impiego di stili architettonici che si ispirano chiaramente a modelli di epoche precedenti. Tale atteggiamento \\u00E8 legata a una concezione storicistica dell\'architettura."@it ,
		"Revivalism in architecture is the use of visual styles that consciously echo the style of a previous architectural era.Modern-day revival styles can be summarized within New Classical Architecture, and sometimes under the umbrella term traditional architecture."@en ,

		"Neostijlen zijn bouwstijlen waarin wordt teruggegrepen op de oude architectuur van de gotiek, de renaissance en de barok.Het tijdperk van de neostijlen breekt na ca. 1815 aan. Naar believen worden elementen uit de oude architectuur toegepast, soms zelfs gecombineerd in een enkel gebouw (dit was vooral het geval bij het zogenaamde eclecticisme).In Amsterdam bijvoorbeeld ondergaat de stad na \\u00B11880 een grote economische opbloei, waardoor er weer veel wordt gebouwd en verbouwd."@nl .

	rdfs:comment	"The Royal Academy of Arts (RA) is an art institution based in Burlington House on Piccadilly in London. It has a unique position as an independent, privately funded institution led by eminent artists and architects; its purpose is to promote the creation, enjoyment and appreciation of the visual arts through exhibitions, education and debate."@en ,

		"La Royal Academy \\u00E8 una istituzione artistica e si trova presso Burlington House a Piccadilly, nella citt\\u00E0 di Londra. Celebri sono le sue esposizioni d\'arte fin dalla sua fondazione, un tradizione tuttora continuata. Possiede anche una collezione permanente legata sia a opere di ex-allievi, sia a lasciti vari. Tra questi ultimi spicca la presenza del Tondo Taddei di Michelangelo, esposto gratuitamente negli orari di apertura dell\'istituzione."@it ,

		"Zelfhulp of zelfhelp (Engels: self-help) is een vorm van zorg waarbij de betrokkene(n) een problematiek probeert/proberen op te lossen of hanteerbaar te maken, zonder tussenkomst van professionele hulpverleners. Vaak vindt dit in groepsverband plaats, in zogenaamde zelfhulpgroepen, waarin een door de deelnemers gedeelde problematiek centraal staat."@nl ,
		"O termo autoajuda pode ser referir a qualquer caso onde um indiv\\u00EDduo ou um grupo (como um grupo de apoio) procura se aprimorar econ\\u00F4mica, espiritual, intelectual ou emocionalmente."@pt ,
		"Selbsthilfegruppen sind selbstorganisierte Zusammenschl\\u00FCsse von Menschen, die ein gleiches Problem oder Anliegen haben und gemeinsam etwas dagegen bzw. daf\\u00FCr unternehmen m\\u00F6chten. Typische Probleme sind etwa der Umgang mit chronischen oder seltenen Krankheiten, mit Lebenskrisen oder belastenden sozialen Situationen. Die Zahl der Selbsthilfegruppen in Deutschland wird auf 70.000-100.000 gesch\\u00E4tzt."@de ,
		"Self-help \\u00E8 un\'espressione inglese che letteralmente significa auto-aiuto, e da vari decenni, soprattutto negli USA, fa riferimento a un emergente ma diffuso movimento culturale e di mercato basato su libri, video, conferenze (anche a pagamento) indirizzate a chi desidera risolvere i propri problemi, concretizzare i propri desideri, e \\"realizzare s\\u00E9 stessi\\", sia in circostanze specifiche (ad esempio salute, benessere emotivo, lavoro, famiglia, amore), sia nella vita in generale.Il movimento del Self-help parte dal presupposto che per aiutare se stessi efficacemente \\u00E8 valida e utile l\'esperienza di studiare e mettere in pratica tecniche, idee e metodi provati con risultati concreti da altri che hanno gi\\u00E0 ottenuto l\'efficacia desiderata.Da qui il diffuso mercato attuale, con sezioni dedicate al Self-help praticamente in ogni libreria statunitense e britannica."@it .

	rdfs:comment	"De Sturm und Drang is een stroming in de Duitse literatuur tijdens de Verlichting (stroming). De Sturm und Drang, ook wel de periode van het Genie genoemd, wordt zo ongeveer tussen 1767 en 1785 voornamelijk door jongere auteurs uitgedragen.De term Sturm und Drang wordt pas na 1820 gebruikt, naar het toneelstuk \\"Sturm und Drang\\" van de Duitse dichter Friedrich Maximilian Klinger."@nl ,
		"Sturm und Drang bezeichnet eine Str\\u00F6mung der deutschen Literatur in der Epoche der Aufkl\\u00E4rung, die etwa von 1765 bis 1785 haupts\\u00E4chlich von jungen, etwa 20- bis 30-j\\u00E4hrigen Autoren getragen wurde. Wegen der \\u201EVerherrlichung des \\u201AOriginalgenies\\u2018 als Urbild des h\\u00F6heren Menschen und K\\u00FCnstlers\\u201C (Gero von Wilpert) wird diese Str\\u00F6mung auch als Geniezeit oder Genieperiode bezeichnet.Die Bezeichnung Sturm und Drang kam in den 1820er Jahren auf."@de ,
		"Sturm und Drang (German pronunciation: [\\u02C8\\u0283t\\u028A\\u0250\\u032Fm \\u028Ant \\u02C8d\\u0281a\\u014B], literally \\"Storm and Drive\\", \\"Storm and Urge\\", though conventionally translated as \\"Storm and Stress\\") is a proto-Romantic movement in German literature and music taking place from the late 1760s to the early 1780s, in which individual subjectivity and, in particular, extremes of emotion were given free expression in reaction to the perceived constraints of rationalism imposed by the Enlightenment and associated aesthetic movements."@en ,
		"Sturm und Drang (tempestade e \\u00EDmpeto) foi um movimento liter\\u00E1rio rom\\u00E2ntico alem\\u00E3o, que ocorreu no per\\u00EDodo entre 1760 a 1780.O movimento acontecia por uma rea\\u00E7\\u00E3o ao racionalismo que o Iluminismo do s\\u00E9culo XVIII postulara, bem como ao classicismo franc\\u00EAs que, como forma est\\u00E9tica, tinha grande influ\\u00EAncia na cultura europ\\u00E9ia, principalmente na Alemanha daquele tempo."@pt ,
		"El Sturm und Drang (en espa\\u00F1ol \'tormenta e \\u00EDmpetu\') fue un movimiento literario, que tambi\\u00E9n tuvo sus manifestaciones en la m\\u00FAsica y las artes visuales, desarrollado en Alemania durante la segunda mitad del siglo XVIII.En \\u00E9l se les concedi\\u00F3 a los artistas la libertad de expresi\\u00F3n a la subjetividad individual y, en particular, a los extremos de la emoci\\u00F3n en contraposici\\u00F3n a las limitaciones impuestas por el racionalismo de la Ilustraci\\u00F3n y los movimientos asociados a la est\\u00E9tica."@es ,
		"Sturm und Drang (\\u00AB Temp\\u00EAte et passion \\u00BB en fran\\u00E7ais) est un mouvement \\u00E0 la fois politique et litt\\u00E9raire allemand de la seconde moiti\\u00E9 du XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle. Il correspond \\u00E0 une phase de radicalisation dans la longue p\\u00E9riode des Lumi\\u00E8res (Aufkl\\u00E4rung). Le nom de ce mouvement vient d\'une pi\\u00E8ce de th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre de Friedrich Maximilian Klinger dont le titre, peut-\\u00EAtre provocateur, fut souffl\\u00E9 en 1776 par le Suisse Christoph Kaufmann, un disciple de Lavater."@fr ,
		"Sturm und Drang (tak\\u017Ce Okres burzy i naporu) to nazwa okresu w literaturze niemieckiej przypadaj\\u0105cego umownie na lata 1767-1785.Nazwa wywodzi si\\u0119 od tytu\\u0142u dramatu niemieckiego pisarza Friedricha Maximiliana Klingera o tej samej nazwie."@pl ,

		"The Ten American Painters was formed in 1898 to exhibit their artwork as a unified group. Among the many members of the society was John Henry Twachtman, who was dissatisfied with the conservative nature of the artists he was surrounded by- and in turn decided to accept the title of impressionism. J. H. Twachtman, J."@en ,

		"Die Ten American Painters (auch kurz The Ten) waren Maler, die aus Protest \\u00FCber den herrschenden Kunstbetrieb Ende 1897, Anfang 1898 geschlossen aus der Society of American Artists austraten.Alle zehn K\\u00FCnstler waren vom franz\\u00F6sischen Impressionismus beeinflusst und jeder entwickelte diesen Stil individuell weiter."@de ,
		"De Ten American Painters, ook bekend als The Ten waren tien Amerikaanse kunstschilders, die de Society of American Artists eind 1897 verlieten, uit protest tegen de commercialisering van de tentoonstellingen van deze groep en hun circusachtige sfeer."@nl ,
		"Ten American Painters (The Ten, The American Ten) \\u2013 grupa artystyczna malarzy ameryka\\u0144skich, kt\\u00F3rzy od\\u0142\\u0105czyli si\\u0119 Society of American Artists i wystawiali razem. Przyczyn\\u0105 roz\\u0142amu by\\u0142a komercjalizacja sztuki i konserwatyzm Society."@pl ,
		"Ten American Painters (The Ten), cio\\u00E8 \\"I Dieci pittori americani\\" (o \\"I dieci\\") \\u00E8 stata un\'associazione di 10 pittori americani impressionisti della seconda met\\u00E0 dell\'Ottocento che, alla fine del 1897, diedero le dimissioni dalla \\"Societ\\u00E0 degli artisti americani\\" per protestare contro il commercialismo che dominava le loro mostre e l\'ambiente da \\"circo equestre\\" che le caratterizzava.La Societ\\u00E0 si era distaccata vent\'anni prima dall\'Accademia Nazionale di Estetica sotto le pressioni di artisti come Mary Cassat, James Whistler, Thomas Eakins e Winslow Homer.I Dieci furono: Childe Hassam, Julian Alden Weir, John Henry Twachtman, Robert Lewis Reid, Willard Leroy Metcalf, Frank Weston Benson, Edmund Charles Tarbell, Thomas Wilmer Dewing, Joseph DeCamp, Edward Emerson Simmons.Abbott Handerson Thayer e Winslow Homer chiesero in seguito di far parte del gruppo, ma furono rifiutati. "@it .

	rdfs:comment	"Villeroy & Boch AG is een Europees bedrijf, met het hoofdkantoor te Mettlach in het Saarland (Duitsland). Het bedrijf maakt zowel sanitair als muurtegels en huishoudartikelen. De afdeling interieurdecoratie & huishoudartikelen omvat porseleinserviezen (borden, koffie- en theeserviezen en decoratie in porselein. In de tweede helft van de 20e eeuw kwamen hier ook bestek, en voorwerpen in kristal bij (kristalserviezen, karaffen, geschenkartikelen)."@nl ,
		"Villeroy & Boch (French pronunciation: \\u200B[vil\\u0281wa.e\\u02C8b\\u0254k], German: [\\u02CCv\\u026Al\\u0259r\\u0254\\u026A.\\u0294\\u028Ant\\u02C8b\\u0254x]) is a large manufacturer of ceramics with the company headquarters located in Mettlach, Germany."@en ,

		"Die Villeroy & Boch AG (dt. [\\u02CCv\\u026Al\\u0259r\\u0254\\u026A.\\u0294\\u028Ant\\u02C8b\\u0254x], frz. [vil\\u0281wa.e\\u02C8b\\u0254k]), kurz V&B (auch \'VB\'), ist ein deutscher Hersteller von Keramikwaren, dessen Ursprung im Jahr 1748 liegt. Das Unternehmen ist nach seinen beiden Gr\\u00FCndern Fran\\u00E7ois Boch und Nicolas Villeroy benannt und befindet sich nach \\u00FCber 265 Jahren immer noch gr\\u00F6\\u00DFtenteils in Familienbesitz. Die Hauptniederlassung von Villeroy & Boch ist in Mettlach im Saarland, daneben gibt es 14 Produktionsst\\u00E4tten in Europa, Asien und Amerika."@de ,
		"Villeroy & Boch es uno de los principales fabricantes del mundo de cer\\u00E1mica, tanto industrial como dom\\u00E9stica. La compa\\u00F1\\u00EDa tiene su sede en Mettlach, Alemania."@es .

		"\\u0411\\u0435\\u043B\\u044B\\u0435 \\u043A\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438"@ru ;
	rdfs:comment	"White Rabbits was the name given to a group of women sculptors who worked with Lorado Taft at the World\'s Columbian Exposition in 1893. As the date of the fair\'s opening grew closer Taft realized that he would not be able to complete the decorations and discovering that all the male sculptors to be had were already employed elsewhere. So he asked Burnham if he could use women assistants, an occurrence that was virtually unheard of at that time."@en ,
		"\\u00AB\\u0411\\u0435\\u043B\\u044B\\u0435 \\u043A\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438\\u00BB (\\u0430\\u043D\\u0433\\u043B. <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zero_(art)>	rdfs:label	"Zero (art)"@en ,
		"ZERO"@de ,
		"Groupe ZERO (art)"@fr ,
		"Zero (kunst)"@nl ;
	rdfs:comment	"Zero is a group of artists founded by Heinz Mack and Otto Piene willing to become an international art movement, sometimes associated with the Nouveau r\\u00E9alisme paradigm."@en ,
		"Zero is een beweging in de moderne kunst in de periode van 1958 tot 1966.In 1958 werd door de Duitse kunstenaars Heinz Mack en Otto Piene in D\\u00FCsseldorf de groep ZERO opgericht. Het was een Europese variant van Colorfield Painting. Zero-kunstenaars werkten echter meestal monochroom, vaak met wit. Ze streefden naar een nieuwe harmonie in de verhouding tussen mens en natuur, en vermeden in hun kunst individuele sporen."@nl ,
		"ZERO war eine D\\u00FCsseldorfer K\\u00FCnstlergruppe, die am 24. April 1958 von Heinz Mack und Otto Piene offiziell gegr\\u00FCndet wurde. Im Jahr 1961 kam G\\u00FCnther Uecker hinzu. Mack und Piene sahen die Nachkriegskunst \\u201Emit einem \\u00DCberma\\u00DF an Ballast befrachtet\\u201C. Die K\\u00FCnstler suchten einen neuen Anfang, eine \\u201EStunde Null\\u201C, die von der Vergangenheit unbelastet sein sollte."@de ,
		"ZERO \\u00E9tait moins un groupe organis\\u00E9 qu\'un rassemblement occasionnel d\'artistes autour de conceptions et de manifestations dont Heinz Mack pouvait \\u00EAtre consid\\u00E9r\\u00E9 comme le th\\u00E9oricien et l\'animateur.ZERO \\u00E9tait une sorte de regroupement internationalement ouvert aux artistes cherchant un certain renouveau artistique et se lan\\u00E7ant dans l\\u2019entreprise aventureuse de donner des formes \\u00E0 l\\u2019universalit\\u00E9."@fr .

	rdfs:comment	"Les Po\\u00E8tes obscurs ou \\u00AB Po\\u00E8tes brumeux \\u00BB (en chinois  \\u6726 \\u80E7 \\u8BD7 \\u4EBA, M\\u00E9ngl\\u00F3ng  Sh\\u012Br\\u00E9n) sont un groupe de po\\u00E8tes chinois du XXe si\\u00E8cle dont la production s\'inscrit en r\\u00E9action contre les restrictions de la R\\u00E9volution culturelle. 		"Mgli\\u015Bci Poeci (chi\\u0144.: \\u6726\\u80E7\\u8BD7\\u4EBA; pinyin: M\\u00E9ngl\\u00F3ng Sh\\u012Br\\u00E9n) to chi\\u0144ska grupa poetycka, kt\\u00F3ra zaistnia\\u0142a w czasie odwil\\u017Cy po restrykcjach jakie nast\\u0105pi\\u0142y w czasie rewolucji kulturalnej. 		"The Misty Poets (Chinese: \\u6726\\u80E7\\u8BD7\\u4EBA; pinyin: M\\u00E9ngl\\u00F3ng Sh\\u012Br\\u00E9n) are a group of 20th century Chinese poets who reacted against the restrictions on art during the Cultural Revolution. 		"La literatura persa (persa :\\u0627\\u062F\\u0628\\u06CC\\u0627\\u062A \\u067E\\u0627\\u0631\\u0633\\u06CC) abarca un per\\u00EDodo cultural de 2 500 a\\u00F1os, aunque la mayor\\u00EDa de los documentos pre-isl\\u00E1micos se han perdido. Sus or\\u00EDgenes provienen de las lejanas regiones m\\u00E1s all\\u00E1 de las fronteras del actual Ir\\u00E1n, porque la lengua persa floreci\\u00F3 y sobrevive en vastas franjas de Asia Central. As\\u00ED, Rumi, uno de los poetas persas e isl\\u00E1micos- m\\u00E1s respetados, escribi\\u00F3 en persa aunque vivi\\u00F3 en las hilamas Konya, actual Turqu\\u00EDa, luego capital de los sely\\u00FAcidas."@es ,
		"Die Geschichte der persischen Literatur l\\u00E4sst sich bis in das Altertum zur\\u00FCckverfolgen. 		"La letteratura persiana, o meglio neo-persiana, nasce a partire dall\'incontro/confronto con la cultura linguistica e letteraria degli Arabi conquistatori, che abbatterono l\'Impero sasanide a met\\u00E0 del secolo VII. Questo evento traumatico port\\u00F2 a grandi trasformazioni sia nella lingua (introduzione dell\'alfabeto arabo) che nella letteratura (introduzione di generi e metri poetici arabi)."@it ,
		"A literatura persa (em persa: \\u0627\\u062F\\u0628\\u06CC\\u0627\\u062A \\u067E\\u0627\\u0631\\u0633\\u06CC) abrange dois mil\\u00E9nios e meio de cria\\u00E7\\u00E3o liter\\u00E1ria, apesar de muito do material pr\\u00E9-isl\\u00E2mico se ter perdido.As suas fontes s\\u00E3o a regi\\u00E3o em que se situa o actual Ir\\u00E3o bem como outras \\u00E1reas da \\u00C1sia Central onde a l\\u00EDngua persa \\u00E9 ou foi usada. 		"Persian literature (Persian: \\u0627\\u062F\\u0628\\u06CC\\u0627\\u062A \\u0641\\u0627\\u0631\\u0633\\u06CC\\u200E\\u200E) is one of the world\'s oldest literatures. It spans two-and-a-half millennia, though much of the pre-Islamic material has been lost. Its sources have been within Greater Iran including present-day Iran and the Caucasus, as well as regions of Central Asia where the Persian language has historically been the national language."@en ,

		"La Secesi\\u00F3n vienesa (tambi\\u00E9n llamada Secessionsstil, o Sezessionsstil en Austria) form\\u00F3 parte del muy variado movimiento actualmente denominado modernismo. Fue fundada en 1897 por un grupo de 19 artistas vieneses que hab\\u00EDa abandonado la Asociaci\\u00F3n. Como proyecto de renovaci\\u00F3n art\\u00EDstica, trataba de reinterpretar los estilos del pasado ante los embates de la producci\\u00F3n industrial que estaba desnudando estructural y est\\u00E9ticamente la realidad del arte y la sociedad de la \\u00E9poca."@es ,
		"Secesja Wiede\\u0144ska (niem. Wiener Secession) \\u2013 stowarzyszenie artyst\\u00F3w plastyk\\u00F3w dzia\\u0142aj\\u0105ce w Wiedniu na prze\\u0142omie XIX i XX w."@pl ,
		"De Wiener Secession was een vereniging van beeldende kunstenaars (Vereinigung bildener K\\u00FCnstler Oesterreichs (Secession)) in het Wenen van het fin de si\\u00E8cle. Het is tevens de benaming van de plaatselijke variant van de jugendstil. De vereniging werd op 3 april 1897 opgericht door Gustav Klimt, Koloman Moser, Josef Hoffmann, Joseph Maria Olbrich, Otto Wagner, Max Kurzweil, Otto Friedrich en andere kunstenaars."@nl ,

		"Die Wiener Secession ist eine Vereinigung bildender K\\u00FCnstler in Wien aus der Zeit des Fin de si\\u00E8cle. Davon abgeleitet wird auch die Wiener Variante des Jugendstils als Secessionsstil oder Wiener Jugendstil bezeichnet."@de ,
		"La S\\u00E9cession viennoise (Sezessionsstil ou Wiener Secession en allemand) est un courant de l\'Art nouveau qui s\'est \\u00E9panoui en Autriche, plus particuli\\u00E8rement \\u00E0 Vienne, de 1892 \\u00E0 1906.Ce courant de l\'Art nouveau est moins v\\u00E9g\\u00E9tal et plus \\u00AB g\\u00E9om\\u00E9trique \\u00BB que l\'Art nouveau en France ou en Belgique."@fr ,
		"The Vienna Secession (German: Wiener Secession; also known as the Union of Austrian Artists, or Vereinigung Bildender K\\u00FCnstler \\u00D6sterreichs) was formed in 1897 by a group of Austrian artists who had resigned from the Association of Austrian Artists, housed in the Vienna K\\u00FCnstlerhaus. This movement included painters, sculptors, and architects. The first president of the Secession was Gustav Klimt, and Rudolf von Alt was made honorary president. Its official magazine was called Ver Sacrum."@en ,
		"A Secess\\u00E3o de Viena ou Secess\\u00E3o Vienense (1897-1920) foi o movimento de um grupo de jovens artistas no final do s\\u00E9culo XIX, constitu\\u00EDdo no \\u00E2mbito da K\\u00FCnstlerhaus - tradicional sociedade dos artistas austr\\u00EDacos. Liderado por Gustav Klimt, um dos primeiros a sair da K\\u00FCnstlerhaus, o grupo desejava romper com o que representava a Cooperativa dos Artistas das Artes Decorativas da \\u00C1ustria, fundada em 1861, e protestava contra as normas tradicionais, art\\u00EDsticas e \\u00E9tnicas da \\u00E9poca ."@pt .

dbr:Chicano_Moratorium	rdfs:label	"Chicano Moratorium"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Chicano Moratorium, formally known as the National Chicano Moratorium Committee, was a movement of Chicano anti-war activists that built a broad-based coalition of Mexican-American groups to organize opposition to the Vietnam War. Led by activists from local colleges and members of the \\"Brown Berets\\", a group with roots in the high school student movement that staged walkouts in 1968, the coalition peaked with an August 29, 1970 march in East Los Angeles that drew 30,000 demonstrators."@en .

dbr:French_moralists	rdfs:label	"Moraliste"@fr ,
		"French moralists"@en ,
		"\\u30E2\\u30E9\\u30EA\\u30B9\\u30C8"@ja ,
		"Franz\\u00F6sische Moralisten"@de ,
		"Moralistas franceses"@es ,
		"Moralista"@it ,
		"Moralistas franceses"@pt ;
	rdfs:comment	"The French Moralists (French, les moralistes) were those writers continuing a tradition in French literature, originating in Michel de Montaigne\'s Essays, concerned with the description of the moral character of humanity and with providing prescriptive rules, embodied as maxims, to guide living well.Many famous French stylists were moralists and the French moralists are perhaps the largest coherent group of writers of aphorisms in the Western literary tradition."@en ,
		"Os moralistas franceses s\\u00E3o um grupo heterog\\u00EAneo de pensadores franceses dos s\\u00E9culos XVII e XVIII. Trata-se de uma corrente que surge com Montaigne (1533-1592) e que culmina com o Iluminismo.Moralistas n\\u00E3o no sentido de defensores de uma moral conservadora, mas sim criticos dos costumes e da  (moral), estes pensadores foram atentos observadores da mentalidade e do esp\\u00EDrito de sua \\u00E9poca."@pt ,
		"\\u30E2\\u30E9\\u30EA\\u30B9\\u30C8\\uFF08\\u4ECF: moraliste\\uFF09\\u3068\\u306F\\u3001\\u73FE\\u5B9F\\u306E\\u4EBA\\u9593\\u3092\\u6D1E\\u5BDF\\u3057\\u3001\\u4EBA\\u9593\\u306E\\u751F\\u304D\\u65B9\\u3092\\u63A2\\u6C42\\u3057\\u3066\\u3001\\u305D\\u308C\\u3092\\u65AD\\u7AE0\\u5F62\\u5F0F\\u3084\\u7BB4\\u8A00\\u306E\\u3088\\u3046\\u306A\\u72EC\\u7279\\u306E\\u975E\\u9023\\u7D9A\\u7684\\u306A\\u6587\\u7AE0\\u3067\\u7DB4\\u308A\\u7D9A\\u3051\\u305F\\u4EBA\\u3005\\u306E\\u3053\\u3068\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u7279\\u306B16\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u304B\\u308918\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u306B\\u304A\\u3044\\u3066\\u6D3B\\u8E8D\\u3057\\u305F\\u30E2\\u30F3\\u30C6\\u30FC\\u30CB\\u30E5\\u3001\\u30D6\\u30EC\\u30FC\\u30BA\\u30FB\\u30D1\\u30B9\\u30AB\\u30EB\\u3001\\u30E9\\u30FB\\u30ED\\u30B7\\u30E5\\u30D5\\u30B3\\u30FC\\u3001\\u30E9\\u30FB\\u30D6\\u30EA\\u30E5\\u30A4\\u30A8\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u306A\\u3069\\u30D5\\u30E9\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u8A9E\\u570F\\u306E\\u601D\\u60F3\\u5BB6\\u3092\\u6307\\u3059\\u4E8B\\u304C\\u591A\\u3044\\u3002\\u3053\\u3046\\u3044\\u3063\\u305F\\u4EBA\\u9593\\u6027\\u63A2\\u7A76\\u306E\\u59FF\\u52E2\\u306F\\u3001\\u30D5\\u30E9\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u6587\\u5B66\\u306B\\u8108\\u6253\\u3064\\u3072\\u3068\\u3064\\u306E\\u4F1D\\u7D71\\u3068\\u3082\\u306A\\u3063\\u3066\\u3044\\u308B\\u3068\\u3044\\u3048\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Un moralista \\u00E8 uno scrittore che propone, in maniera discontinua, riflessioni sui costumi, le usanze e i modi di essere degli uomini, i loro caratteri e modi di vivere."@it ,
		"Bajo la denominaci\\u00F3n de moralistas franceses se engloba un grupo heterog\\u00E9neo de pensadores franceses de los siglos XVII y XVIII. Se trata de una corriente que surge con Montaigne (1533 - 1592) y que culmina junto con la Ilustraci\\u00F3n.Moralistas no en el sentido de defensores de una moral conservadora, sino, antes bien, de la cr\\u00EDtica de las costumbres[cita requerida] (mores), estos fueron agudos observadores de la mentalidad y el esp\\u00EDritu de su \\u00E9poca."@es ,
		"Un moraliste est un \\u00E9crivain qui propose, sous une forme discontinue, des r\\u00E9flexions sur les m\\u0153urs : les usages et les coutumes humaines, les caract\\u00E8res et les fa\\u00E7ons de vivre \\u2014 en somme, les actions et les comportements des hommes."@fr ,
		"Unter die franz\\u00F6sischen Moralisten rechnet man in franz\\u00F6sischer Sprache publizierende philosophische Schriftsteller des sp\\u00E4ten 16., 17. und 18. Jahrhunderts, deren Texte der europ\\u00E4ischen Moralistik zuzurechnen sind. Formal und inhaltlich ist diese Str\\u00F6mung bzw. Textgattung u.a. durch essayistischen Stil und die Tendenz charakterisierbar, das menschliche Verhalten analysieren zu wollen. Der Wortbestandteil \\u201EMoral\\u201C bezieht sich entsprechend nicht auf Gesichtspunkte normativer Ethik."@de .

	rdfs:comment	"Abstrakcja (\\u0142ac. abstractio \\u2013 oderwanie) \\u2013 w sztukach plastycznych: taka realizacja dzie\\u0142a, w kt\\u00F3rej jest ono pozbawione wszelkich cech ilustracyjno\\u015Bci, a artysta nie stara si\\u0119 na\\u015Bladowa\\u0107 natury.Autorzy stosuj\\u0105 r\\u00F3\\u017Cne \\u015Brodki wyrazu, dzi\\u0119ki kt\\u00F3rym \\"co\\u015B przedstawiaj\\u0105\\". 		"Typically, abstraction is used in the arts as a synonym for abstract art in general."@en ,
		"L\'abstraction en art s\'oppose aux repr\\u00E9sentations figuratives et narratives, elle r\\u00E9sulte de formes expressives et non de formes repr\\u00E9sentatives. Au regard de l\'histoire de l\'art, de tr\\u00E8s anciennes cultures ont touch\\u00E9 \\u00E0 l\'abstraction, que ce soit en Inde ou chez les peuples am\\u00E9rindiens.Le terme \\u00AB abstraction \\u00BB peut aussi renvoyer aux diff\\u00E9rents arts abstraits qui caract\\u00E9risent l\'art moderne \\u00E0 partir du d\\u00E9but du XXe si\\u00E8cle."@fr ,
		"Il termine astrazione indica il procedimento mentale attraverso il quale si sostituisce un insieme di oggetti con un concetto, pi\\u00F9 generale, che descrive gli oggetti in base a propriet\\u00E0 a loro comuni. Per esempio, a partire dall\'insieme di tutte le automobili esistenti, si pu\\u00F2 ricavare il concetto generico di automobile in base alle caratteristiche condivise da tutte le auto (hanno quattro ruote, un volante, ecc.). La parola deriva dal latino abstrahere (scostare)."@it .

		"Folk art encompasses art produced from an indigenous culture or by peasants or other laboring tradespeople. In contrast to fine art, folk art is primarily utilitarian and decorative rather than purely aesthetic."@en ,
		"El arte folcl\\u00F3rico es aquel creado de un modo tradicional por campesinos, marineros, artesanos o comerciantes que no cuentan con una preparaci\\u00F3n formal."@es ,
		"Volkskunst is kunst die gemaakt is door anonieme personen, zonder een artistieke bedoeling.Naast de grote kunststromingen zijn er in alle landen en in alle tijden ook steeds gewone mensen bezig geweest met kunst. Deze kunst heeft niet het commerci\\u00EBle of artistieke niveau van de grote meesters, maar de intentie is eerlijk en plichtbewust. Volkskunst is doorgaans soberder uitgewerkt, maar toch zeer in trek bij verzamelaars."@nl ,

		"Le Gothique Isab\\u00E9lin (en espagnol, gotico Isabelino) \\u00E9tait le style architectural dominant de la Couronne de Castille sous le r\\u00E8gne de la reine Isabelle premi\\u00E8re, il repr\\u00E9sente la fin de la transition gothique \\u00E0 l\'architecture Renaissance pr\\u00E9coce, avec des caract\\u00E9ristiques originales et des influences d\\u00E9coratives de l\'art hispano-mauresque, hispano-flamand et, dans une moindre mesure, de l\'architecture italienne.La consid\\u00E9ration du style isab\\u00E9lin comme forme du gothique ou de la Renaissance, comme un style g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rique, ou comme une phase \\u00E0 l\'int\\u00E9rieur du style plateresque, est une question d\\u00E9battue par l\'historiographie de l\'art et qui ne fait pas consensus."@fr ,
		"Isabelline Gothic (in Spanish, G\\u00F3tico Isabelino), was the dominant architectural style of the Crown of Castile during the reign of Queen Isabella I; it represents the transition between late Gothic and early Renaissance architecture, with original features and decorative influences of Mud\\u00E9jar, Flemish, and to a lesser extent, Italian architecture."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Kannada literature is the corpus of written forms of the Kannada language, a member of the Dravidian family spoken mainly in the Indian state of Karnataka and written in the Kannada script.Attestations in literature span something like one and a half millennia,with some specific literary works surviving in rich manuscript traditions, extending from the 9th century to the present.The Kannada language is usually divided into three linguistic phases: Old (450\\u20131200 CE), Middle (1200\\u20131700 CE) and Modern (1700\\u2013present);and its literary characteristics are categorised  as Jain, Veerashaiva and Vaishnava\\u2014recognising the prominence of these three faiths in giving form to, and fostering, classical expression of the language, until the advent of the modern era.Although much of the literature prior to the 18th century was religious, some secular works were also committed to writing.Starting with the Kavirajamarga (c. "@en ,
		"La literatura kannada (o canar\\u00E9s) es el corpus escrito en idioma canar\\u00E9s, hablado principalmente en el estado indio de Karnataka y escrito en alfabeto canar\\u00E9s.Existen testimonios escritos por un per\\u00EDodo aproximado de 1.500 a\\u00F1os con algunas obras que han sobrevivido gracias a valiosas tradiciones de copia manuscrita, desde el siglo IX hasta el presente.El idioma canar\\u00E9s usualmente se divide en tres fases ling\\u00FC\\u00EDsticas: Antigua (450\\u20131200), Media (1200\\u20131700) y Moderna (1700\\u2013presente); y sus caracter\\u00EDsticas literarias est\\u00E1n divididas en Jainismo, Lingayatismo y Visnuismo, reconociendo la preeminencia de estas tres religiones en darle forma a las expresiones cl\\u00E1sicas del lenguaje hasta el advenimiento de la era moderna.Aunque mucha de la literatura previa al siglo 18 era religiosa, se escribieron algunas obras seculares.Comenzando con el Kavirajamarga (c. "@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"\\u526A\\u5F71\\uFF08\\u6CD5\\u8BED\\uFF1Asilhouette\\uFF09\\u662F\\u4E00\\u7A2E\\u5C07\\u4EBA\\u4E8B\\u7269\\u4EE5\\u55AE\\u8272\\u63CF\\u7E6A\\uFF08\\u4EE5\\u9ED1\\u8272\\u70BA\\u4E3B\\uFF09\\uFF0C\\u51F8\\u986F\\u8F2A\\u5ED3\\u7684\\u85DD\\u8853\\u5716\\u50CF\\uFF0C\\u6216\\u6307\\u526A\\u5F71\\u85DD\\u8853\\u672C\\u8EAB\\uFF0C\\u53EF\\u5C6C\\u4E00\\u7A2E\\u8996\\u89BA\\u85DD\\u8853\\uFF0C\\u526A\\u5F71\\u88AB\\u904B\\u7528\\u5728\\u5404\\u7A2E\\u65B9\\u9762\\u3002"@zh ,
		"Une silhouette est une peinture, une photographie, r\\u00E9alis\\u00E9e par un trait trac\\u00E9 autour de l\'ombre projet\\u00E9e du visage ou du corps du sujet."@fr ,
		"A silhouette is the image of a person, animal, object or scene represented as a solid shape of a single colour, usually black, its edges matching the outline of the subject.  The interior of a silhouette is featureless, and the whole is typically presented on a light background, usually white, or none at all.  The silhouette differs from an outline, which depicts the edge of an object in a linear form, while a silhouette appears as a solid shape."@en ,

\\u0432\\u0435\\u043A\\u0430 \\u0433\\u0440\\u0430\\u0444\\u043E\\u043C \\u0424. \\u041F. \\u0422\\u043E\\u043B\\u0441\\u0442\\u044B\\u043C."@ru ,
		"Een silhouet is een visueel beeld van een ondoorzichtig object (persoon, voorwerp, gebouw, vogel, enz.), dat een goed contrast heeft met de achtergrond, en daardoor een duidelijke vorm, maar egaal van kleur is (in het algemeen zwart of grijs), doordat er weinig licht opvalt dat gereflecteerd zou kunnen worden, in verhouding tot de helderheid van het achtergrondlicht. De kleur kan grijs zijn door strooilicht/nevel tussen het object en de waarnemer."@nl ,
		"Una silueta es una vista de cierto objeto o escena que consiste en el esquema y un interior sin rasgos distintivos, con la silueta generalmente siendo negra."@es ,
		"Silhouette oder Schattenriss sind Begriffe aus der Malerei, Optik, Fotografie. Man bezeichnet damit den Umriss bzw. die Kontur einer Fl\\u00E4che oder die von dieser Kontur umschlossene Fl\\u00E4che, die sich dunkel von einem hellen Hintergrund (oder umgekehrt) abhebt. Das kann auch eine nat\\u00FCrliche Kontur (zum Beispiel der Schatten eines K\\u00F6rpers oder die durch die Bebauung erzeugte Kontur einer Stadt (Skyline)) oder eine k\\u00FCnstliche (zum Beispiel eine Schattenzeichnung oder ein Scherenschnitt) sein."@de ,
		"Silhueta \\u00E9 uma sombra de algo, de tamanho miniaturizado."@pt .

		"Visionnaire"@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"Defined broadly, a visionary is one who can envision the future.  For some groups this can involve the supernatural.The visionary state is achieved via meditation, drugs, lucid dreams, daydreams, or art. One example is Hildegard of Bingen, a 12th-century artist and Catholic saint. Other visionaries in religion are St Bernadette and Joseph Smith, said to have had visions of and communed with the Blessed Virgin and the Angel Moroni, respectively."@en .

		"La Pl\\u00E9iade (French pronunciation: \\u200B[la plejad]) is the name given to a group of 16th-century French Renaissance poets whose principal members were Pierre de Ronsard, Joachim du Bellay and Jean-Antoine de Ba\\u00EFf.  The name was a reference to another literary group, the original Alexandrian Pleiad of seven Alexandrian poets and tragedians (3rd century B.C.), corresponding to the seven stars of the Pleiades star cluster."@en ,
		"Plejada (fr. la Pl\\u00E9iade) - grupa poet\\u00F3w zebranych wok\\u00F3\\u0142 Pierre\'a de Ronsarda i Joachima du Bellaya, dzia\\u0142aj\\u0105ca we Francji w XVI wieku. 	rdfs:comment	"Realismo social es una expresi\\u00F3n utilizada a una corriente con el proposito de  expandir y hacer enfasis a problemas sociales, designando muy diferentes conceptos en la historia del arte y de la literatura, mediante la asociaci\\u00F3n de los t\\u00E9rminos \\"realismo\\" y \\"social\\", especialmente la denominada \\"cuesti\\u00F3n social\\" (la situaci\\u00F3n de los m\\u00E1s desfavorecidos);"@es ,
		"Der Begriff Neue Sachlichkeit bezeichnet eine Richtung der Literatur der Weimarer Republik. Er bezieht sich auf Werke, in denen die zwischen den Weltkriegen hervortretende Tendenz zu illusionslos-n\\u00FCchterner Darstellung von Gesellschaft, Erotik, Technik und Weltwirtschaftskrise als Reaktion auf den literarischen Expressionismus erkennbar ist."@de ,
		"Social realism, an international art movement, refers to the work of painters, printmakers, photographers and filmmakers who draw attention to the everyday conditions of the working class and the poor; social realists are critical of the social structures which maintain these conditions."@en ,
		"Onder het realisme, een kunst- en cultuurstroming reagerend op de symboliserende allegorische verstarring van het classicisme, sinds het midden van de 19e eeuw, erkent men het sociaal realisme, zowel in de schilderkunst als in de beeldhouwkunst.Bij het realistisch uitbeelden van de natuur en het leven van mens, dier en plant erin, cre\\u00EBert men het accentueren  van een aanklacht tegen sociaal schrijnende omstandigheden, waaraan het onderwerp het hoofd dient te bieden."@nl ,
		"Social realism \\u2013 termin okre\\u015Blaj\\u0105cy nurt w sztuce lat 20. i 30. 		"La movida madrile\\u00F1a"@pl ;
	rdfs:comment	"A Movida Madrile\\u00F1a foi um movimento contra-cultural surgido durante os primeiros anos da transi\\u00E7\\u00E3o da Espanha p\\u00F3s-franquista, que se estendeu rapidamente e com car\\u00E1cter nacional por toda a Espanha, na Movida Espanhola e se prolongou at\\u00E9 ao final dos anos oitenta, tendo tido o seu auge em 1981 com \\"O Concerto de Primavera\\" (\\"El Concierto de Primavera\\")."@pt ,
		"La Movida Madrile\\u00F1a (De Madrileense beweging) was een Spaanse socioculturele beweging die bestond in Madrid tijdens de eerste tien jaren na de dood van Francisco Franco in 1975. De beweging vertegenwoordigde de sociale vrijheid die ontstond na het einde van de dictatuur. Deze hedonistische en culturele beweging vond voornamelijk plaats in Madrid, maar ook in andere steden zoals Vigo."@nl ,

		"La Movida madrile\\u00F1a fue un movimiento contracultural surgido durante los primeros a\\u00F1os de la Transici\\u00F3n de la Espa\\u00F1a posfranquista, que se generalizar\\u00EDa m\\u00E1s tarde a otras provincias y se prolong\\u00F3 hasta mediados de los a\\u00F1os ochenta. Tradicionalmente se considera que el movimiento se materializ\\u00F3 con el renombrado Concierto homenaje a Canito en 1980, en memoria de Canito y promovido en la Escuela de Caminos de Madrid por los que posteriormente se convirtieron en Los Secretos."@es ,
		"La Movida Madrile\\u00F1a (English: The Madrilenian scene) was a countercultural movement that took place mainly in Madrid during the Spanish transition after Francisco Franco\'s death in 1975. It represented the resurrection of the economy in Spain and the emergence of a new Spanish identity.This hedonistic cultural wave was born in Madrid, but then followed in other Spanish cities, such as Barcelona, Bilbao and Vigo."@en ,
		"La Movida madrile\\u00F1a fu un movimento sociale ed artistico che part\\u00EC da Madrid, in puerta del Sol, alla fine della dittatura di Francisco Franco, durante i primi anni della Transizione spagnola e che dur\\u00F2 per tutti gli anni ottanta e oltre, toccando molte altre citt\\u00E0 della Spagna. La Movida faceva riferimento ad ideologie libertarie di sinistra ed ebbe il suo primo centro nella rivista La Luna."@it ,
		"La movida madrile\\u00F1a (pl. \\u201Eruch/scena/hulanka madrycka\\u201D) \\u2013 hiszpa\\u0144ski ruch odnowy kultury i obyczajowo\\u015Bci, kt\\u00F3ry rozpocz\\u0105\\u0142 si\\u0119 w Madrycie pod koniec lat 70. XX wieku, po \\u015Bmierci genera\\u0142a Franco i upadku jego dyktatury. Nazwa movida stanowi prze\\u015Bmiewcze nawi\\u0105zanie do Movimiento Nacional \\u2013 partii genera\\u0142a Franco."@pl ,
		"La Movida (ou Movida madrile\\u00F1a) est le nom donn\\u00E9 au mouvement culturel cr\\u00E9atif qui a touch\\u00E9 l\'ensemble de l\'Espagne pendant la fin de la p\\u00E9riode de la transition d\\u00E9mocratique espagnole, au d\\u00E9but des ann\\u00E9es 1980, apr\\u00E8s la mort du g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ral Franco.Le terme \\u00AB movida \\u00BB vient de l\'espagnol \\u00AB hacer una movida \\u00BB qui signifiait alors quitter le centre de Madrid pour s\'approvisionner en haschisch ou en drogues en tous genres et revenir le consommer dans la capitale.Port\\u00E9e par le d\\u00E9sir de renouveau de la jeunesse espagnole et l\'\\u00E9mergence de nouveaux acteurs sur le plan artistique et culturel, elle a contribu\\u00E9 \\u00E0 la modernisation et \\u00E0 l\'int\\u00E9gration de la soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 espagnole dans l\'Europe d\\u00E9mocratique."@fr .
dbr:New_Apocalyptics	rdfs:label	"New Apocalyptics"@en ,
		"Apocalittici"@it ;
	rdfs:comment	"Gli apocalittici o \\"movimento della nuova apocalisse\\" (in inglese New Apocalyptics), fu un movimento letterario inglese sorto alla fine degli anni Trenta, che prendevano il lore nome dall\'antologia \\"The New Apocalypse\\" (1939), scritta da J. F. Hendry (1912\\u20131986) ed Henry Treece. Ad essa seguirono le successive antologie \\"The White Horseman (1941)\\" e \\"Crown and Sickle (1944)\\".Il movimento tendeva al rifiuto della poesia politicamente impegnata e al ritorno al mito."@it ,
		"The New Apocalyptics were a poetry grouping in the UK in the 1940s, taking their name from the anthology The New Apocalypse (1939), which was edited by J. F. Hendry (1912\\u20131986) and Henry Treece. There followed the further anthologies The White Horseman (1941) and Crown and Sickle (1944).Their reaction against the political realism of much Thirties poetry drew for support upon D. H. Lawrence (Apocalypse, 1931), surrealism, myth, and expressionism."@en .

		"Peredvizjniki (Russisch: \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438, Peredvizjniki) was een groep van Russische kunstschilders uit de laat 19e - begin 20e eeuw. Later was de offici\\u00EBle benaming van Peredvizjniki: \\u201CMaatschappij voor reizende kunstexposities\\u201D. 		"I Peredvi\\u017Eniki (in russo: \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438? ovvero gli Itineranti o Ambulanti), fu un gruppo di artisti realisti russi che protestarono contro le restrizioni accademiche e che form\\u00F2 una cooperativa che evolvette nella societ\\u00E0 per mostre itineranti nel 1870, chiamata anche \\"Compagnia delle esportazioni di arte itinerante\\"."@it ,
		"Peredvizhniki (Russian: \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0301\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438; IPA: [p\\u02B2\\u026Ar\\u02B2\\u026A\\u02C8dv\\u02B2i\\u0290n\\u02B2\\u026Ak\\u02B2\\u026A]), often called The Wanderers or The Itinerants in English, were a group of Russian realist artists who in protest at academic restrictions formed an artists\' cooperative; it evolved into the Society for Travelling Art Exhibitions in 1870."@en ,
