		"Les Ambulants ou Itin\\u00E9rants (en russe : \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438, Peredvijniki) est le terme donn\\u00E9 au mouvement r\\u00E9aliste apparu en Russie en 1863 et qui exista jusqu\'aux ann\\u00E9es 1890, en r\\u00E9action contre l\'enseignement, les sujets et les m\\u00E9thodes de l\'Acad\\u00E9mie imp\\u00E9riale des beaux-arts de Saint-P\\u00E9tersbourg. C\'est sous la forme de l\'Artel des artistes fond\\u00E9 par Ivan Kramsko\\u00EF que d\\u00E9buta ce mouvement en 1863."@fr ,
		"Peredv\\u00EDzhniki (en ruso: \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0301\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438), com\\u00FAnmente conocidos como \\"Los Ambulantes\\", o adem\\u00E1s como \\"Los Vagabundos\\" o \\"Los Itinerantes\\". Nombre de una sociedad cooperativa de pintores rusos de la d\\u00E9cada de 1870 que desarroll\\u00F3 en sus obras el realismo cr\\u00EDtico iniciado en la d\\u00E9cada anterior por otros artistas."@es ,
		"A Sociedade de Exposi\\u00E7\\u00F5es Itinerantes de Obras de Artistas Russos, mais conhecida como os Itinerantes (em russo: Peredvizhniki), foi um grupo de pintores russos que fundaram um movimento dissidente da Academia Imperial de S\\u00E3o Petersburgo em 1870. Embora sua proposta tivesse um fundo rom\\u00E2ntico, foram a maior for\\u00E7a para a divulga\\u00E7\\u00E3o do Realismo na arte russa, agregando em seu auge os melhores talentos de sua \\u00E9poca e praticando uma pintura nacionalista de cr\\u00EDtica social."@pt ,
		"Die Peredwischniki (russisch \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0301\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438; deutsch: Wanderer) waren eine Gruppe von russischen K\\u00FCnstlern, vorrangig Malern, die Vertreter des Realismus in der Malerei waren."@de ,
		"Pieriedwi\\u017Cnicy, ros. \\u041F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438, Towarzystwo Objazdowych Wystaw Artystycznych (\\u0422\\u043E\\u0432\\u0430\\u0440\\u0438\\u0449\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u043E \\u043F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u0432\\u044B\\u0441\\u0442\\u0430\\u0432\\u043E\\u043A) \\u2013 rosyjska grupa artystyczna, powsta\\u0142a w 1870 w Petersburgu. 		"Por s\\u00E9culo de ouro entende-se a \\u00E9poca cl\\u00E1ssica e apogeu da cultura espanhola, essencialmente desde o Renascimento do s\\u00E9culo XVI at\\u00E9 o Barroco do s\\u00E9culo XVII."@pt ,
		"Als Siglo de Oro (w\\u00F6rtlich goldenes Jahrhundert) bezeichnet man das Goldene Zeitalter Spaniens, das in der spanischen Geschichte eine Epoche besonderer Prosperit\\u00E4t und politischer Macht in Europa repr\\u00E4sentiert und zu einer hohen Bl\\u00FCte der Kunst und Kultur f\\u00FChrte. Das Siglo de Oro stellte in Spanien den \\u00DCbergang von der Renaissance zum Barock dar und dauerte etwa von 1550 bis 1680."@de ,
		"The Spanish Golden Age (Spanish: Siglo de Oro, Golden Century) is a period of flourishing in arts and literature in Spain, coinciding with the political rise and decline of the Spanish Habsburg dynasty. El Siglo de Oro does not imply precise dates and is usually considered to have lasted longer than an actual century."@en ,
		"El Siglo de Oro espa\\u00F1ol fue un per\\u00EDodo de florecimiento del arte y la literatura en Espa\\u00F1a, que coincidi\\u00F3 con el auge pol\\u00EDtico y posterior declive de la dinast\\u00EDa de los Austrias o Habsburgo espa\\u00F1oles. El Siglo de Oro no supone fechas precisas y generalmente se considera que dur\\u00F3 m\\u00E1s de un siglo. Su inicio no fue antes de 1492, con el fin de la Reconquista, los viajes de Crist\\u00F3bal Col\\u00F3n al Nuevo Mundo, y la publicaci\\u00F3n de la Gram\\u00E1tica de la lengua castellana de Antonio de Nebrija."@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"Digitale Poesie ist eine Form des k\\u00FCnstlerischen Umgangs mit Sprache, die in Medien wie Computer und Internet realisiert und seit den 1990er Jahren als eigenst\\u00E4ndige Kunstform wahrgenommen wird.Der Begriff der digitalen Poesie vereint mehrere unabh\\u00E4ngig voneinander entstandene Zweige der computerbasierten Sprachkunst in sich."@de ,
		"La po\\u00E9sie num\\u00E9rique est un genre de po\\u00E9sie assist\\u00E9e par l\'informatique. L\'ordinateur peut aussi bien \\u00EAtre utilis\\u00E9 pour produire ou g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rer une po\\u00E9sie que comme support de pr\\u00E9sentation.La po\\u00E9sie num\\u00E9rique englobe la po\\u00E9sie g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rative (dont Jean-Pierre Balpe est un des repr\\u00E9sentants), la po\\u00E9sie multim\\u00E9dia ou cin\\u00E9tique et la vid\\u00E9o po\\u00E9sie."@fr ,
		"La poesia elettronica \\u00E8 una sperimentazione artistica che integra testo poetico e arte dei nuovi media (videoarte, digital art, net.art, installazioni, ecc.). Si possono distinguere in essa due grandi aree, spesso intrecciate nella ricerca: la videopoesia (video poetry), definitasi come genere negli anni 80, e la computer poetry, che integra l\'uso di tecnologie digitali e si afferma con il diffondersi di queste, tra la fine degli anni 80 e gli anni 90."@it ,
		"La ciberpoes\\u00EDa (tambi\\u00E9n llamada \\"poes\\u00EDa electr\\u00F3nica\\" o \\"poes\\u00EDa digital\\") es la rama de la ciberliteratura en la que predomina la funci\\u00F3n est\\u00E9tica del lenguaje. T\\u00E9cnicamente se caracteriza por el empleo de diversos recursos tecnol\\u00F3gicos, desde el simple hipertexto, la animaci\\u00F3n bi- o tridimensional, hasta las m\\u00E1s avanzadas interfaces de realidad virtual."@es ,
		"Digital poetry is a form of electronic literature, displaying a wide range of  approaches to poetry, with a prominent and crucial use of computers."@en ,

Una delle ragioni per questo arrivo ritardato fu il lungo periodo di guerre (la Guerra dei cent\'anni, 1338-1453, e la Guerra delle due rose, 1454-1485), che distrasse gli interessi umani e caus\\u00F2 una fase di stasi nell\'arte creativa."@it ,

		"The English Renaissance was a cultural and artistic movement in England dating from the late 15th to the early 17th century. It is associated with the pan-European Renaissance that is usually regarded as beginning in Italy in the late 14th century. Like most of northern Europe, England saw little of these developments until more than a century later."@en ,
		"Engelse renaissance is een term die gebruikt wordt om een vanuit Itali\\u00EB ge\\u00EFnspireerde culturele en kunstzinnige beweging te beschrijven die plaatsvond in het Engeland van begin 16e eeuw tot ongeveer de helft van de 17e eeuw, en behalve het Engels renaissancetheater ook de literatuur, muziek, architectuur en beeldende kunst van deze periode omvat."@nl .

		"\\u0627\\u0633\\u062A\\u0642\\u0644\\u0627\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0628\\u0644\\u062F\\u064A\\u0627\\u062A \\u0627\\u0644\\u0630\\u0627\\u062A\\u064A \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u062D\\u0631\\u0631\\u064A"@ar ;
	rdfs:comment	"Wolno\\u015Bciowy municypalizm \\u2013 termin u\\u017Cyty po raz pierwszy przez wolno\\u015Bciowego socjalist\\u0119 Murraya Bookchina, stosowany dla okre\\u015Blenia wariantu anarchistycznego ustroju spo\\u0142ecznego, w kt\\u00F3rym pa\\u0144stwo zast\\u0105pione jest przez woln\\u0105 konfederacj\\u0119 miast, rz\\u0105dzonych przez instytucje demokracji uczestnicz\\u0105cej."@pl ,
		"Le municipalisme libertaire, est une application locale de l\'\\u00E9cologie sociale \\u00E9labor\\u00E9e par le th\\u00E9oricien communiste libertaire et \\u00E9cologiste politique Murray Bookchin.Ce terme est utilis\\u00E9 pour d\\u00E9crire un syst\\u00E8me politique dans lequel des institutions libertaires, compos\\u00E9es d\'assembl\\u00E9es de citoyens, dans un esprit de d\\u00E9mocratie directe, remplaceraient l\'\\u00C9tat-nation par une conf\\u00E9d\\u00E9ration de municipalit\\u00E9s (communes) libres.On parle parfois aussi de communalisme libertaire, la notion est proche."@fr ,
		"Libertarian municipalism is a political program developed by libertarian socialist theorist Murray Bookchin, to create democratic citizens\' assemblies in towns and urban neighborhoods. The assemblies in these free municipalities join together to replace the state with a directly democratic confederation.Bookchin became an advocate of face-to-face or assembly democracy in the 1950s, inspired by writings on the ancient Athenian polis by H. D. F. Kitto and Alfred Eckhard Zimmern."@en ,
		"O Municipalismo ou Municipalismo Libert\\u00E1rio, consiste em uma ideologia pol\\u00EDtica que objetiva oferecer maior autonomia aos munic\\u00EDpios, atendendo especialmente \\u00E0 organiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o e prerrogativas das cidades, por meio de uma descentraliza\\u00E7\\u00E3o da administra\\u00E7\\u00E3o p\\u00FAblica.Os defensores dessa linha de pensamento costumam salientar a import\\u00E2ncia da cidade, uma vez que \\u00E9 nesse espa\\u00E7o onde se vive e se trabalha."@pt ,
		"Il municipalismo libertario \\u00E8 un programma politico sviluppato dal socialista libertario Murray Bookchin, basato sulla pratica della democrazia diretta per mezzo dell\'istituzione di assemblee popolari in villaggi, paesi, quartieri e citt\\u00E0, federate in una confederazione di municipalit\\u00E0 libertarie in alternativa alla gestione in forma di Stato.Secondo Bookchin il municipalismo libertario \\u00E8 strettamente correlato all\'obiettivo della municipalizzazione dell\'economia, non della sua nazionalizzazione o privatizzazione, intendendo con questo l\'acquisizione dei mezzi di sussistenza da parte della comunit\\u00E0 e il controllo della vita economica da parte dell\'assemblea cittadina. "@it ,
		"El municipalismo libertario es una idea de organizaci\\u00F3n pol\\u00EDtica basada en instituciones asamblearias de \\u00EDndole vecinal que, practicando la democracia directa, se federar\\u00EDan en una confederaci\\u00F3n de municipios o comunas libres, siendo una alternativa al Estado centralizado. Formulada a partir de la tradici\\u00F3n localista y municipalista del anarquismo, fue esbozada contempor\\u00E1neamente por Murray Bookchin."@es ,

		"The genre of military art is characterized by its subject matter rather than by any specific style or material used.  The battle scene is one of the oldest types of art in developed civilizations, as rulers have always been keen to celebrate their victories and intimidate potential opponents. The depiction of other aspects of warfare, especially the suffering of casualties and civilians, has taken much longer to develop."@en ,

Der Neoexpressionismus entstand Anfang der 1960er Jahre in Abkehr zum vorherrschenden Informel. Ma\\u00DFgeblich an der Entstehung beteiligt waren in Deutschland Meistersch\\u00FCler der Kunstschulen in Ost- und West-Berlin wie Georg Baselitz und Eugen Sch\\u00F6nebeck."@de ,

		"Het neo-expressionisme is een hedendaagse kunststroming binnen de 20e-eeuwse schilderkunst in de late jaren van 1970 tot midden van de jaren 1980 die zich afzet tegen het minimalisme en conceptualisme van de jaren zestig en zeventig en breekt met het modernistische vooruitgangsdenken in de kunst. . Minder gebruikelijk wordt de benaming gebruikt voor beeldhouwkunst (bijvoorbeeld Anish Kapoor) en architectuur (bijvoorbeeld Frank Gehry, Dane John Utzen)."@nl ,
		"Neoekspresjonizm, r\\u00F3wnie\\u017C Nowoekspresjonizm, Nowa Ekspresja \\u2013 trend w sztuce wsp\\u00F3\\u0142czesnej, kt\\u00F3rego pocz\\u0105tki mo\\u017Cna odnale\\u017A\\u0107 w p\\u00F3\\u017Anych latach 60., prze\\u017Cywaj\\u0105cy sw\\u00F3j rozkwit w latach 80. XX wieku. Powsta\\u0142 w kontra\\u015Bcie do modnego w\\u00F3wczas minimalizmu, konceptualizmu i abstrakcji geometrycznej. Cech\\u0105 charakterystyczn\\u0105 Neoekspresjonist\\u00F3w jest wyra\\u017Canie uczu\\u0107, pos\\u0142ugiwanie si\\u0119 emocjami, ekspresj\\u0105 i intuicj\\u0105."@pl ,
		"Le n\\u00E9o-expressionnisme est un ph\\u00E9nom\\u00E8ne pictural qui a \\u00E9merg\\u00E9 vers la fin des ann\\u00E9es 1970 et qui est surtout caract\\u00E9ristique de la sc\\u00E8ne artistique occidentale des ann\\u00E9es 1980. Il s\'est d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 en Europe  et aux \\u00C9tats-Unis en r\\u00E9action contre l\'art conceptuel et minimaliste."@fr ,
		"El neoexpresionismo es un movimiento pict\\u00F3rico surgido a finales de los a\\u00F1os setenta y principios de los a\\u00F1os ochenta en Alemania, desde donde se extendi\\u00F3 por el resto de Europa y Estados Unidos. Fuertemente vinculado a la transvanguardia italiana y la figuraci\\u00F3n libre francesa, este estilo surgi\\u00F3 como una reacci\\u00F3n contra el minimalismo y el arte conceptual que predominaron durante los a\\u00F1os setenta."@es ,
		"Neo-expressionism is a style of late-modernist or early-postmodern painting and sculpture that emerged in the late 1970s. Neo-expressionists were sometimes called Neue Wilden (\'The new wild ones\'; \'New Fauves\' would better meet the meaning of the term). It is characterized by intense subjectivity and rough handling of materials.Neo-expressionism developed as a reaction against conceptual art and minimal art of the 1970s."@en ,
		"Il neoespressionismo \\u00E8 stato un movimento artistico, perlopi\\u00F9 focalizzato sulla pittura, che nasce negli anni settanta del Novecento, si caratterizza per un deciso recupero della figura spesso rappresentata sotto la lente deformata dell\'inquietudine."@it ,

	rdfs:comment	"The Northern Renaissance was the Renaissance that occurred in Europe north of the Alps. Before 1497, Italian Renaissance humanism had little influence outside Italy. From the early 16th century, its ideas spread around Europe."@en ,
		"La Renaissance nordique ou Renaissance du Nord est la Renaissance ayant eu lieue dans les pays du Nord de l\'Europe, notamment par opposition \\u00E0 la Renaissance italienne qui ne se limite qu\'\\u00E0 l\'Italie.Portail de la Renaissance Portail de la Renaissance"@fr ,
		"O Renascimento n\\u00F3rdico \\u00E9 o termo usado para descrever o Renascimento na Europa setentrional, ou, mais amplamente na Europa, com exce\\u00E7\\u00E3o da It\\u00E1lia. Antes de 1450, o humanismo renascentista italiano teve pouca influ\\u00EAncia fora da It\\u00E1lia. A partir do final do s\\u00E9culo XV, as ideias difundiram-se por toda a Europa."@pt ,
		"Noordelijke renaissance of renaissance van het noorden is de aanduiding voor een meestal onduidelijk afgebakende kunsthistorische periode in de Nederlanden en andere landen in Noord-Europa. De term is eigenlijk een vertaling van het in de Angelsaksische kunsthistorisch literatuur aangewende \\"Northern Renaissance\\" en kan nogal uiteenlopende ladingen dekken: Een kunsthistorische stroming in het noorden van Europa die zich in de periode tussen ca. 15e tot ca."@nl ,
		"Renacimiento n\\u00F3rdico es un t\\u00E9rmino de la historiograf\\u00EDa del arte utilizado para clasificar y describir el Renacimiento europeo al norte de los Alpes, es decir, fuera de Italia y con exclusi\\u00F3n del renacimiento espa\\u00F1ol.En el siglo XV el Renacimiento italiano (Quattrocento) no hab\\u00EDa tenido casi influencia fuera de Italia."@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"The Nuyorican Movement is a cultural and intellectual movement involving poets, writers, musicians and artists who are Puerto Rican or of Puerto Rican descent, who live in or near New York City, and either call themselves or are known as Nuyoricans."@en .

dbr:Protest_art	rdfs:label	"Protesto art\\u00EDstico"@pt ,
		"Protest art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Protest art is a broad term that refers to creative works that concern or are produced by activists and social movements.  There are also contemporary and historical works and currents of thought that can be characterized in this way.Social movements produce such works as the signs, banners, posters, and other printed materials used to convey a particular cause or message.  Often, such art is used as part of demonstrations or acts of civil disobedience."@en ,
		"Protesto art\\u00EDstico refere se a cartazes, faixas, e outras formas de express\\u00F5es criativas usadas pelos ativistas para passar informa\\u00E7\\u00F5es sobre uma causa em particular ou mensagem.  A arte \\u00E9 freq\\u00FCentemente usada como parte destas demonstra\\u00E7\\u00F5es ou em atos de desobedi\\u00EAncia civil.  Um dos \\u00EDcones dos protestos art\\u00EDsticos e a pomba, o s\\u00EDmbolo da paz, e mensagens de insultos.Os protestos art\\u00EDsticos dependem do entendimento das pessoas dos s\\u00EDmbolos usados na arte."@pt .

		"\\u0423\\u043B\\u0438\\u0447\\u043D\\u0430\\u044F \\u0444\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0433\\u0440\\u0430\\u0444\\u0438\\u044F, \\u0441\\u0442\\u0440\\u0438\\u0442-\\u0444\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0433\\u0440\\u0430\\u0444\\u0438\\u044F (\\u0430\\u043D\\u0433\\u043B. street photography) \\u2014 \\u0436\\u0430\\u043D\\u0440 \\u0444\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0433\\u0440\\u0430\\u0444\\u0438\\u0438, \\u0441\\u0434\\u0435\\u043B\\u0430\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0432 \\u043E\\u0431\\u0449\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u043C \\u043C\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0435: \\u043D\\u0430 \\u0443\\u043B\\u0438\\u0446\\u0435, \\u0432 \\u043F\\u0430\\u0440\\u043A\\u0435, \\u043D\\u0430 \\u043F\\u043B\\u044F\\u0436\\u0435 \\u0438 \\u0442. \\u043F. \\u0423\\u043B\\u0438\\u0447\\u043D\\u0430\\u044F \\u0444\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0433\\u0440\\u0430\\u0444\\u0438\\u044F \\u0431\\u044B\\u0432\\u0430\\u0435\\u0442 \\u0434\\u043E\\u043A\\u0443\\u043C\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0430\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439, \\u043D\\u043E \\u043D\\u0435 \\u043E\\u0433\\u0440\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0447\\u0438\\u0432\\u0430\\u0435\\u0442\\u0441\\u044F \\u0438\\u0441\\u043A\\u043B\\u044E\\u0447\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u043E \\u0434\\u043E\\u043A\\u0443\\u043C\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0430\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u044B\\u043C \\u0436\\u0430\\u043D\\u0440\\u043E\\u043C."@ru ,
		"Stra\\u00DFenfotografie ist eine Genrebezeichnung der Fotografie, die zahlreiche Fotografen und Stile umfasst. Allgemein ist damit eine Fotografie gemeint, die im \\u00F6ffentlichen Raum entsteht, auf Stra\\u00DFen, in Gesch\\u00E4fte oder Caf\\u00E9s hineinblickend, Passantengruppen oder Einzelne herausgreifend, oftmals als Momentaufnahme, aber ebenso essayhafte Abfolge und Milieustudie."@de ,
		"Straatfotografie (Engels: street photography) is een fotografiegenre waarbij mensen op publieke plaatsen zoals straten, parken en metrostations gefotografeerd worden zonder dat ze zich daar bewust van zijn. Het is een kunstzinnige vorm van candid camera-fotografie die natuurlijke in plaats van geposeerde foto\\u2019s oplevert."@nl ,
		"La photographie de rue ou photo de rue (\\u00AB Street Photography \\u00BB en anglais) est une branche en photographie dont le sujet principal est une pr\\u00E9sence humaine, directe ou indirecte, dans des situations spontan\\u00E9es et dans des lieux publics comme la rue, les parcs, les plages, les grands magasins ou les manifestations."@fr ,

		"Tachismus (von franz\\u00F6sisch la tache = Farbfleck) ist eine Richtung des Informel in der abstrakten Malerei, die in den 1940er Jahren in Paris entstand und bis etwa 1960 aktiv war. Der Begriff wurde vom franz\\u00F6sischen Kunstkritiker Pierre Gu\\u00E9guen gepr\\u00E4gt, der die Werke abf\\u00E4llig tachisme (deutsch Fleckwerk) bezeichnete.Im Tachismus versucht der K\\u00FCnstler, spontane Empfindungen und das Unbewusste unter Vermeidung jeder rationalen Kontrolle durch Auftrag von Farbflecken auf eine Leinwand darzustellen."@de ,

		"Il tachisme \\u00E8 uno stile pittorico di arte astratta iniziato in Francia negli anni quaranta e  gli anni cinquanta. \\u00C8 considerato spesso l\'equivalente europeo dell\'espressionismo astratto. \\u00C8 un movimento chiamato anche arte informale.Il compositore di colonne sonore Michel Magne ha registrato nel 1959, per Barclay/Bel Air, un album di musica strumentale dal titolo \\"Musique Tachiste\\"."@it ,
		"El Tachismo (en idioma espa\\u00F1ol, Tachisme, derivado de la palabra francesa tache - mancha) fue un estilo de pintura abstracta franc\\u00E9s desarrollado durante los a\\u00F1os 1940 y 1950. A menudo se le considera el equivalente europeo al expresionismo abstracto. Pertenece al movimiento m\\u00E1s amplio del Informalismo (Art informel). Tambi\\u00E9n se conoce el Tachisme (similar a la action painting) como abstraction lyrique (relacionado con la abstracci\\u00F3n l\\u00EDrica estadounidense)."@es ,
		"Tachisme (alternative spelling: Tachism, derived from the French word tache, stain) is a French style of abstract painting popular in the 1940s and 1950s. The term is said to have been first used with regards to the movement in 1951. It is often considered to be the European equivalent to abstract expressionism, although there are stylistic differences (American abstract expressionism tended to be more \\"aggressively raw\\" than tachisme)."@en ,
		"Tachisme, afgeleid van het Franse woord tache voor vlek, is een stijlvariant binnen de abstracte schilderkunst die populair werd in de jaren \'40 en \'50. De naam van deze schilderstijl komt uit Frankrijk. Tachisme wordt vaak beschouwd als het Europese equivalent van het Amerikaanse abstract expressionisme."@nl ,
		"Le tachisme est un style de peinture abstraite r\\u00E9pandu en France dans les ann\\u00E9es 1940 et 1950. Ce mouvement est souvent consid\\u00E9r\\u00E9 comme l\'\\u00E9quivalent europ\\u00E9en de la tendance de l\'expressionnisme abstrait am\\u00E9ricain repr\\u00E9sent\\u00E9e par l\'action painting. Il d\\u00E9signe l\'un des aspects de l\'art informel, au sein de l\'une de ses composantes d\\u00E9nomm\\u00E9e abstraction lyrique."@fr ,
		"O Tachismo \\u00E9 um estilo de pintura abstrata que se desenvolveu na Fran\\u00E7a entre os anos 40 e 50 como um equivalente do Expressionismo abstrato norte-americano. O termo deriva do franc\\u00EAs tache, que significa mancha."@pt ,

		"\\u0417\\u0430\\u0443\\u043C\\u044C"@ru ,

		"Zaum"@pt ;
	rdfs:comment	"Zaum\' in russo: \\u0417\\u0430\\u0443\\u043C\\u044C? \\u00E8 una parola usata per descrivere gli esperimenti linguistici di fonosimbolismo e di creazione del linguaggio condotti da un gruppo di poeti futuristi russi come Velimir Khlebnikov e Aleksej Kru\\u010D\\u00EBnykh.Coniata da Kru\\u010D\\u00EBnykh nel 1913, la parola zaum\' \\u00E8 formata dal prefisso za (oltre) in russo: \\u0437\\u0430? e dal sostantivo um\' in russo: \\u0443\\u043C\\u044C? (la mente, il nous), ed \\u00E8 stata tradotta con \\"transmentale\\")."@it ,
		"Zaum (Russian: \\u0437\\u00E1\\u0443\\u043C\\u044C) are the linguistic experiments in sound symbolism and language creation of Russian-empire Futurist poets such as Velimir Khlebnikov and Aleksei Kruchenykh.Coined by Kruchenykh in 1913, the word zaum is made up of the Russian prefix \\u0437\\u0430 \\"beyond, behind\\" and noun \\u0443\\u043C \\"the mind, nous\\" and has been translated as \\"transreason\\", \\"transration\\" or \\"beyonsense\\" (Paul Schmidt)."@en ,
		"Le zaoum (en russe : \\u0437\\u0430\\u0443\\u043C\\u044C ou \\u0437\\u0430\\u0443\\u043C\\u043D\\u044B\\u0439 \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A) est un type de po\\u00E9sie des futuristes russes (notamment Velimir Khlebnikov et Alexe\\u00EF Kroutchenykh) qui vise principalement l\\u2019organisation des sons pour eux-m\\u00EAmes : tout le po\\u00E8me est tourn\\u00E9 vers le c\\u00F4t\\u00E9 phonique du discours.Invent\\u00E9 par Kroutchenykh en 1913, le mot \\u00AB zaoum \\u00BB est compos\\u00E9 du pr\\u00E9fixe russe za- (au-del\\u00E0) et du nom oum (l\'esprit) et peut se comprendre comme \\u00AB trans-mental \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"\\u0417\\u0430\\u0301\\u0443\\u043C\\u044C, \\u0437\\u0430\\u0443\\u0301\\u043C\\u043D\\u044B\\u0439 \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A \\u2014 \\u043B\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u043D\\u044B\\u0439 \\u043F\\u0440\\u0438\\u0451\\u043C, \\u0437\\u0430\\u043A\\u043B\\u044E\\u0447\\u0430\\u044E\\u0449\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u044F \\u0432 \\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u043D\\u043E\\u043C \\u0438\\u043B\\u0438 \\u0447\\u0430\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u0447\\u043D\\u043E\\u043C \\u043E\\u0442\\u043A\\u0430\\u0437\\u0435 \\u043E\\u0442 \\u0432\\u0441\\u0435\\u0445 \\u0438\\u043B\\u0438 \\u043D\\u0435\\u043A\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u044B\\u0445 \\u044D\\u043B\\u0435\\u043C\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u043E\\u0432 \\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u0430 \\u0438 \\u0437\\u0430\\u043C\\u0435\\u0449\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0438 \\u0438\\u0445 \\u0434\\u0440\\u0443\\u0433\\u0438\\u043C\\u0438 \\u044D\\u043B\\u0435\\u043C\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0430\\u043C\\u0438 \\u0438\\u043B\\u0438 \\u043F\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u0440\\u043E\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u044F\\u043C\\u0438, \\u043F\\u043E \\u0430\\u043D\\u0430\\u043B\\u043E\\u0433\\u0438\\u0438 \\u043E\\u0441\\u043C\\u044B\\u0441\\u043B\\u044F\\u0435\\u043C\\u044B\\u043C\\u0438 \\u043A\\u0430\\u043A \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u043E\\u0432\\u044B\\u0435."@ru ,
		"Zaum (em russo: \\u0437\\u0430\\u0443\\u043C\\u044C u \\u0437\\u0430\\u0443\\u043C\\u043D\\u044B\\u0439 \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A), ou Linguagem transmental \\u00E9 um conceito utilizado para designar os experimentos lingu\\u00EDsticos do simbolismo fon\\u00E9tico na cria\\u00E7\\u00E3o de l\\u00EDnguas art\\u00EDsticas, realizados por alguns poetas futuristas russos, entre os quais Velimir Khl\\u00E9bnikov e Aleksei Krutchionikh. A palavra \\"zaum\\" est\\u00E1 composta pelo prefixo \\u0437\\u0430 (al\\u00E9m, por tr\\u00E1s) e a palavra \\u0443\\u043C (mente, conhecimento)."@pt .

dbr:New_Sculpture	rdfs:label	"New Sculpture"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The New Sculpture refers to a movement in late 19th-century British sculpture. The term \\"New Sculpture\\" was coined by the first historian of the movement, the critic Edmund Gosse, who wrote a four-part series for The Art Journal in 1894.  After a protracted period of a stylized neoclassicism, sculpture in the last quarter of the century began to explore a greater degree of naturalism and wider range of subject matter."@en .
dbr:New_Sincerity	rdfs:label	"New Sincerity"@it ,
		"New Sincerity"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"New Sincerity (in inglese lett. \\"nuova sincerit\\u00E0\\") \\u00E8 un termine che \\u00E8 stato adoperato in musica, estetica, critica cinematografica, poesia, critica letteraria e filosofia, in genere per descrivere forme d\'arte o concetti che vanno contro le mode prevalenti dell\'ironia o del cinismo postmodernisti. Il suo uso risale alla met\\u00E0 degli anni ottanta."@it ,
		"New Sincerity is a term that has been used in music, aesthetics, film criticism, poetry, literary criticism and philosophy, generally to describe art or concepts that run against prevailing modes of postmodernist irony or cynicism. Its usage dates back to the mid-1980s."@en .

		"Der Begriff der Medienkunst bezeichnet k\\u00FCnstlerisches Arbeiten, das sich der Medien bedient, die haupts\\u00E4chlich im 20./21. Jahrhundert entstanden sind, wie beispielsweise Film, Videos, Holographien, Internet, Computer, Mobiltelefonie, Spiele etc. Im Englischen wird der Begriff media art dagegen teilweise synonym zu new media art verwendet. Neue Medien sind hierbei jeweils Tr\\u00E4ger, Vermittler oder Arbeitsmaterial in der Kunst."@de ,
		"Onder mediakunst verstaat men in het algemeen de diverse producten voortvloeiend uit kunstpraktijken die zich bedienen van de netwerktechnologie\\u00EBn van de late 20e en de vroege 21e eeuw."@nl ,
		"New media art is a genre that encompasses artworks created with new media technologies, including digital art, computer graphics, computer animation, virtual art, Internet art, interactive art, video games, computer robotics, 3D printing, and art as biotechnology. The term differentiates itself by its resulting cultural objects and social events, which can be seen in opposition to those deriving from old visual arts (i.e. traditional painting, sculpture, etc.)."@en ,
		"El arte de  los nuevos medios (en ingl\\u00E9s new media art) es una forma de arte, que hace referencia a las obras creadas o que incorpora el uso de las nuevas tecnolog\\u00EDas. A menudo se utilizan indistintamente como sin\\u00F3nimos del arte de los nuevos medios categorizaciones precedentes como arte digital, arte electr\\u00F3nico, arte multimedia y arte interactivo."@es .

		"Po\\u00E8te maudit (dt. verfemter Dichter) bezeichnet eine seit der zweiten H\\u00E4lfte des 19. Jahrhunderts typisierte Lebenshaltung in Literaten- und K\\u00FCnstlerkreisen. 		"La nozione romantica di maledizione del poeta appare gi\\u00E0 nel 1832 nell\\u2019opera di Alfred de Vigny Stello, che espose il problema dei rapporti tra poeti e societ\\u00E0, anticipante la pi\\u00E8ce Chatterton: Figura tragica spinta agli estremi, sprofondata non di rado nella demenza, l\\u2019immagine del po\\u00E8te maudit costituisce, in qualche modo, il vertice insuperabile del pensiero romantico."@it ,
		"Een po\\u00E8te maudit (gedoemde dichter) is de benaming voor een miskende of maatschappelijk onaangepaste dichter. 		"A po\\u00E8te maudit (French pronunciation: \\u200B[p\\u0254\\u025Bt modi], accursed poet) is a poet living a life outside or against society. 	rdfs:comment	"El Rangaku (\\u862D\\u5B66, \\"aprendizaje holand\\u00E9s\\"?) fue el m\\u00E9todo por el cual Jap\\u00F3n se mantuvo al corriente de la tecnolog\\u00EDa y medicina occidentales, durante el periodo de su historia en el que estuvo cerrado a los extranjeros, 1641\\u20131853, debido a la pol\\u00EDtica de aislamiento nacional del shogun Tokugawa (sakoku).Los comerciantes holandeses de Dejima en Nagasaki fueron los \\u00FAnicos extranjeros tolerados durante este periodo, y sus movimientos eran cuidadosamente observados y estrictamente controlados."@es ,
		"Rangaku (Japans: \\u862D\\u5B66) is de Japanse \'Nederlandkunde\', de studie van Nederland en het Nederlands zoals deze lange tijd in Japan bedreven is gedurende de tijd dat de Hollandse handelspost op Desjima de enige verbinding met de buitenwereld en met name het westen was.De Japanse Nederlandkunde stelde het land in staat kennis te nemen van de ontwikkelingen in de westerse technologie en heelkunde in de periode 1641\\u20131853, die bekendstaat als de sakoku ofwel isolatement van het Tokugawa-shogunaat.Rangaku is er in belangrijke mate voor verantwoordelijk dat Japan voldoende op de hoogte bleef van de technologische revolutie die zich in deze tijd in Europa voltrok, zodat het land na de opening van 1854 in staat was snel te moderniseren."@nl ,
		"Als Rangaku (jap. \\u862D\\u5B66, dt. \\u201EHollandkunde, Hollandstudien\\u201C) bezeichnet man die Erkundung des Westens durch das Medium der niederl\\u00E4ndischen Sprache w\\u00E4hrend der Zeit der Abschlie\\u00DFung Japans von 1641 bis 1854."@de ,

		"Il rangaku (\\u862D\\u5B66?)(letteralmente \\"Studio olandese\\") era un metodo di apprendimento scientifico in uso durante il periodo antecedente allo sbarco del commodoro Mattew Perry (Convenzione di Kanagawa), quando il Giappone era ancora isolato dal resto del mondo per via della politica di isolamento (sakoku) dello Shogunato Tokugawa tra il 1641-1853.Attraverso il rangaku molti medici e menti scientifiche del Giappone poterono apprendere e rimanere aggiornati sulle vicende mediche, scientifiche e tecnologiche che avvenivano in Europa.Non a caso venne definito \\"studio olandese\\" poich\\u00E9 allora gli unici occidentali che avevano il permesso di entrare in Giappone erano appunto commercianti olandesi."@it ,
		"Le Rangaku (Ky\\u016Bjitai: \\u862D\\u5B78/Shinjitai: \\u862D\\u5B66, signifiant litt\\u00E9ralement \\u00AB \\u00C9tudes hollandaises \\u00BB et par extension \\u00AB \\u00C9tudes occidentales \\u00BB) est un recueil d\'analyses d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9es par le Japon lors de ses contacts avec les Hollandais de l\'\\u00EEle de Dejima, qui lui permit de d\\u00E9couvrir les technologies et la m\\u00E9decine du monde occidental \\u00E0 une \\u00E9poque o\\u00F9 le pays \\u00E9tait repli\\u00E9 sur lui-m\\u00EAme, ferm\\u00E9 aux \\u00E9trangers, de 1641 \\u00E0 1853, en raison de la politique isolationniste du shogunat Tokugawa (voir sakoku)."@fr ,
		"\\u0420\\u0430\\u043D\\u0433\\u0430\\u043A\\u0443 (\\u044F\\u043F. \\u862D\\u5B66, \\u0431\\u0443\\u043A\\u0432. \\u00AB\\u0433\\u043E\\u043B\\u043B\\u0430\\u043D\\u0434\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0435 		"Rangaku (Ky\\u016Bjitai: \\u862D\\u5B78/Shinjitai: \\u862D\\u5B66, literally \\"Dutch Learning\\", and by extension \\"Western Learning\\") is a body of knowledge developed by Japan through its contacts with the Dutch enclave of Dejima, which allowed Japan to keep abreast of Western technology and medicine in the period when the country was closed to foreigners, 1641\\u20131853, because of the Tokugawa shogunate\\u2019s policy of national isolation (sakoku).Through Rangaku, some people in Japan learned many aspects of the scientific and technological revolution occurring in Europe at that time, helping the country build up the beginnings of a theoretical and technological scientific base, which helps to explain Japan\\u2019s success in its radical and speedy modernization following the opening of the country to foreign trade in 1854."@en ,
		"Rangaku (\\u862D\\u5B66, lit."@pt .

dbr:African_nationalism	rdfs:label	"Nazionalismo africano"@it ,
		"African nationalism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Nazionalismo africano \\u00E8 il nome con il quale viene indicato quel movimento politico e di pensiero che vorrebbe il continente africano unito sotto una unica bandiera, nel nome di una forte identit\\u00E0 nera comune per la salvaguardia dei costumi e delle usanze delle trib\\u00F9 indigene.Le origini del movimento sono da rintracciare tra le file dei pensatori del nazionalismo europeo, fortemente fagocitate dall\'influenza data dal cristianesimo e dalla filosofia internazionalista promossa da Mahatma Gandhi, e in parte, anche dal leninismo quale ideologia politica per l\'internazionalizzazione dei rapporti.Con la perdita di molti dei territori coloniali extraeuropei delle superpotenze al termine della seconda guerra mondiale, diversi portavoce di neonate nazioni africane portarono avanti una corrente di pensiero nata intorno la grande guerra tra le varie comunit\\u00E0 di afroamericani oramai insediatesi negli Stati Uniti d\'America. "@it ,
		"African nationalism is a political movement for Pan-Africanism and for national self-determination. Political interest began in the 1870s and political organizations started to form in the 1890s. In the years after World War II, African nationalism gained strength, resulting in independence for Libya in 1951 and Ghana in 1957. All but six African countries were independent nation-states by 1966.Edward Wilmot Blyden has been described as the founder of African nationalism."@en .

		"Anti-Zionism is opposition to Zionism, broadly defined in the modern era as the opposition to the  ethnonationalist and political movement of Jews and Jewish culture that supports the establishment of a Jewish state as a Jewish homeland in the territory defined as the historic Land of Israel (also referred to as Palestine, Canaan or the Holy Land) or to the modern State of Israel as defined as A Jewish and Democratic State.The term is used to describe various religious, moral and political points of view, but their diversity of motivation and expression is sufficiently different that \\"anti-Zionism\\" cannot be seen as having a single ideology or source. "@en ,
		"\\u0645\\u0639\\u0627\\u062F\\u0627\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0635\\u0647\\u064A\\u0648\\u0646\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0645\\u0635\\u0637\\u0644\\u062D \\u064A\\u0645\\u062B\\u0644 		"Antysyjonizm - postawa sprzeciwu wobec ideologii i praktyki syjonizmu niekiedy prowadz\\u0105ca do sprzeciwu wobec samego faktu istnienia pa\\u0144stwa Izrael.Ten punkt widzenia charakteryzuje r\\u00F3\\u017Cne grupy o zr\\u00F3\\u017Cnicowanych motywach, m.in. \\u015Brodowiska komunistyczne, anarchistyczne, pewne \\u015Brodowiska \\u017Cydowskie i przewa\\u017Caj\\u0105c\\u0105 cz\\u0119\\u015B\\u0107 organizacji palesty\\u0144skich, a tak\\u017Ce \\u015Brodowiska antysemickie, np. nacjonalist\\u00F3w (arabskich i nie tylko), fundamentalist\\u00F3w islamskich."@pl ,
		"Antizionismus ist eine gegen den Zionismus gerichtete politische Ideologie. Seit der Gr\\u00FCndung des Staates Israel 1948 wendet sie sich gegen diesen als j\\u00FCdischen Staat. Antizionismus wird sowohl s\\u00E4kular wie religi\\u00F6s begr\\u00FCndet und findet sich auf dem gesamten Kontinuum des politischen Spektrums, mitunter bestehen enge Zusammenh\\u00E4nge zur Judenfeindlichkeit."@de ,
		"Antizionisme is politiek verzet tegen het zionisme, een internationale politieke beweging die een Joods thuisland of Joodse staat, in het Heilige of Beloofde Land, voor het Joodse volk in Eretz Isra\\u00EBl voor ogen heeft. Antizionisme kan vele vormen aannemen, vari\\u00EBrend van politieke of religieuze oppositie tegen het idee van een Joodse staat, tot het ontkennen van Isra\\u00EBls recht om te bestaan en de legitimiteit van het concept zelf, tot verschillende vormen van geweld."@nl ,
		"Antissionismo \\u00E9 a oposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o pol\\u00EDtica, moral ou religiosa \\u00E0s v\\u00E1rias correntes ideol\\u00F3gicas inclu\\u00EDdas no sionismo, inclusive ao estado judeu, criado com base nesse conceito.Eventualmente, o termo tamb\\u00E9m \\u00E9 muitas vezes aplicado \\u00E0 oposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o  pol\\u00EDtica ao governo de Israel, sobretudo se motivada por den\\u00FAncias de viola\\u00E7\\u00F5es sistem\\u00E1ticas de direitos humanos dos palestinos, incluindo crimes de guerra[carece de fontes?], mas tamb\\u00E9m \\u00E0 nega\\u00E7\\u00E3o ao direito de exist\\u00EAncia do Estado de Israel.Da mesma forma, frequentemente se estabelece uma identidade entre antissionismo e antissemitismo, de modo que, afinal, uma boa parte dos opositores do governo de Israel, inclusive muitos judeus, \\u00E9 tachada de antissemita. "@pt ,
		"L\'antisionismo \\u00E8 l\'atteggiamento di coloro che si oppongono al sionismo, cio\\u00E8 al movimento politico fondato nel 1897 volto alla costituzione di uno Stato nazionale ebraico in parte di quello che fu il Mandato britannico della Palestina e, prima ancora, la Palestina ottomana. Il sionismo raggiunse il proprio obiettivo con la fondazione dello stato d\'Israele nel 1948, ma il movimento sionista continu\\u00F2 ad operare con entusiasmo per rinsaldare e proteggere il nuovo Stato."@it ,
		"L\'antisionisme (ou anti-sionisme) d\\u00E9signe historiquement l\'opposition au projet sioniste d\'\\u00E9tablissement d\'un foyer national juif en Palestine.Il appara\\u00EEt d\'une part parmi les dirigeants traditionalistes juifs pour des raisons religieuses ou par crainte des Juifs assimiliationistes et d\'autre part parmi les dirigeants arabes de Palestine et certains officiers britanniques quand la Grande-Bretagne obtient de la soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 des Nations un mandat pour administrer le pays."@fr ,
		"El antisionismo es la oposici\\u00F3n al sionismo, un nacionalismo de Jud\\u00EDos que apoya un Estado naci\\u00F3n jud\\u00EDo  en el territorio definido como la Tierra de Israel."@es .

		"The anti-globalization movement, or counter-globalisation movement, is a social movement critical of the globalization of corporate capitalism. The movement is also commonly referred to as the global justice movement, alter-globalization movement, anti-globalist movement, anti-corporate globalization movement, or movement against neoliberal globalization.Participants base their criticisms on a number of related ideas."@en ,
		"Antiglobalisme of antimondialisme is een beweging die zich verzet tegen het globalisme in zijn geheel. Antiglobalisten verzetten zich radicaal tegen iedere vorm van globalisering, men ziet het als een bedreiging voor de lokale cultuur en economie."@nl ,
		"Antimondialisme est le terme g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rique utilis\\u00E9 au cours des ann\\u00E9es 1990 pour d\\u00E9crire le mouvement d\'opposition au mondialisme. Il n\'est pas \\u00E0 confondre avec l\'antimondialisation qui est l\'opposition \\u00E0 un processus d\\u2019\\u00E9changes mat\\u00E9riels et immat\\u00E9riels dus au progr\\u00E8s technique. L\'antimondialisme d\\u00E9signe l\'opposition \\u00E0 toute forme de mondialisme, \\u00E0 la diff\\u00E9rence des altermondialistes qui pr\\u00F4nent un autre mondialisme."@fr ,

		"Movimento no-global o movimento anti-globalizzazione sono locuzioni nate nella stampa italiana per indicare un insieme internazionale di gruppi, organizzazioni non governative, associazioni e singoli individui relativamente eterogenei dal punto di vista politico e accomunati dalla critica all\'attuale sistema economico neoliberista, la cui prima comparsa si ritiene comunemente avvenuta intorno al 1999 in occasione della Conferenza Ministeriale della WTO (l\'Organizzazione Mondiale del Commercio) a Seattle negli Stati Uniti. El pensamiento antiimperialista est\\u00E1 estrechamente vinculado al cuestionamiento de los mecanismos de dependencia neocolonial caracterizados por mecanismos de sujeci\\u00F3n econ\\u00F3micos y financieros, as\\u00ED como a los llamados procesos de liberaci\\u00F3n nacional."@es ,
		"Anti-imperialism in political science and international relations is a term used in a variety of contexts, usually by nationalist movements, who want to secede from a larger polity (usually in the form of an empire, but also in a multi-ethnic sovereign state) or as a specific theory opposed to capitalism in Marxist\\u2013Leninist discourse, derived from Vladimir Lenin\'s work Imperialism, the Highest Stage of Capitalism."@en ,

		"L\'anti-imp\\u00E9rialisme est une id\\u00E9ologie qui au sens strict comprend toute id\\u00E9e ou mouvement oppos\\u00E9s \\u00E0 une quelconque forme d\'imp\\u00E9rialisme. Plus g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement, l\'anti-imp\\u00E9rialisme suppose une opposition aux guerres de conqu\\u00EAte, concernant plus particuli\\u00E8rement des territoires non-limitrophes ou des peuples \\u00E0 la culture et au langage diff\\u00E9rents."@fr .

	rdfs:comment	"Con il termine fauves (in francese \\"belve, selvaggi\\") si indica un gruppo di pittori, perlopi\\u00F9 francesi, che all\\u2019inizio del Novecento diedero vita ad un\\u2019esperienza di breve durata temporale, ma di grande importanza nell\\u2019evoluzione dell\\u2019arte."@it ,
		"O fauvismo (do franc\\u00EAs fauvisme, oriundo de les fauves, \\"as feras\\", como foram chamados os pintores n\\u00E3o seguidores do c\\u00E2none impressionista, vigente \\u00E0 \\u00E9poca) \\u00E9 uma corrente art\\u00EDstica do in\\u00EDcio do s\\u00E9culo XX, que se desenvolveu sobretudo entre 1905 e 1907. O Dicion\\u00E1rio Houaiss indica fovismo como um termo hom\\u00F4nimo.O estilo come\\u00E7ou em 1901 mas s\\u00F3 foi denominado e reconhecido como um movimento art\\u00EDstico em 1905."@pt ,
		"Le fauvisme est un courant de peinture du d\\u00E9but du XXe si\\u00E8cle. Tir\\u00E9 d\'une expression du journaliste Louis Vauxcelles, il d\\u00E9bute historiquement \\u00E0 l\'automne 1905, lors du Salon d\'automne qui cr\\u00E9a scandale, pour s\'achever moins de cinq ans plus tard, au d\\u00E9but des ann\\u00E9es 1910. En fait, d\\u00E8s 1908, il est d\\u00E9j\\u00E0 \\u00E0 son cr\\u00E9puscule. Son influence marque n\\u00E9anmoins tout l\'art du XXe si\\u00E8cle, notamment par la lib\\u00E9ration de la couleur."@fr ,

		"Fauvism is the style of les Fauves (French for \\"the wild beasts\\"), a loose group of early twentieth-century Modern artists whose works emphasized painterly qualities and strong color over the representational or realistic values retained by Impressionism. While Fauvism as a style began around 1900 and continued beyond 1910, the movement as such lasted only a few years, 1904\\u20131908, and had three exhibitions. The leaders of the movement were Henri Matisse and Andr\\u00E9 Derain."@en ,
		"\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062F\\u0631\\u0633\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0648\\u062D\\u0634\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0623\\u0648 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062D\\u0648\\u0634\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0623\\u0648 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0641\\u0648\\u0641\\u064A\\u0629 fauvism \\u0643\\u0644\\u0645\\u0629 \\u0641\\u0631\\u0646\\u0633\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0628\\u0645\\u0639\\u0646\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0648\\u062D\\u0634 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u062A\\u0641\\u0631\\u0633. \\u0648\\u0647\\u064A \\u062D\\u0631\\u0643\\u0629 \\u062A\\u0645\\u064A\\u0632\\u062A \\u0628\\u0627\\u0633\\u062A\\u062E\\u062F\\u0627\\u0645 \\u0623\\u0644\\u0648\\u0627\\u0646 \\u063A\\u0631\\u064A\\u0628\\u0629 \\u0635\\u0627\\u0631\\u062E\\u0629 \\u0648\\u062A\\u062D\\u0631\\u064A\\u0641 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0634\\u0643\\u0627\\u0644 \\u0628\\u062A\\u063A\\u064A\\u064A\\u0631 \\u062D\\u062C\\u0648\\u0645\\u0647\\u0627 \\u0648\\u0646\\u0633\\u0628\\u0647\\u0627 \\u0648\\u0623\\u0644\\u0648\\u0627\\u0646\\u0647\\u0627 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u0642\\u0644\\u064A\\u062F\\u064A\\u0629. \\u0648\\u0642\\u062F \\u0623\\u0637\\u0644\\u0642 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0646\\u0627\\u0642\\u062F \\u0644\\u0648\\u064A\\u0633 \\u0641\\u0648\\u0643\\u0633\\u064A\\u0644 \\u0647\\u0630\\u0627 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0627\\u0633\\u0645 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0635\\u062D\\u0627\\u0628 \\u0647\\u0630\\u0647 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062D\\u0631\\u0643\\u0629 \\u0644\\u0644\\u0625\\u0634\\u0627\\u0631\\u0629 \\u0625\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u0646\\u0627\\u0642\\u0636 \\u0628\\u064A\\u0646 \\u0636\\u0631\\u0627\\u0648\\u0629 \\u0623\\u0644\\u0648\\u0627\\u0646\\u0647\\u0645 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0633\\u0627\\u0644\\u064A\\u0628 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0634\\u0627\\u0626\\u0639\\u0629. \\u0648\\u0642\\u062F \\u0638\\u0647\\u0631\\u062A \\u0641\\u064A \\u0641\\u0631\\u0646\\u0633\\u0627 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0645\\u0633\\u062A\\u0647\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0631\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0634\\u0631\\u064A\\u0646."@ar ,
		"Fauvisme is een stroming in de schilderkunst die begin 20e eeuw ontstond.Het fauvisme kenmerkt zich door het gebruik van felle, nauwelijks gemengde kleuren. De stroming staat aan het begin van de moderne kunst en vond haar voortzetting in de schilderkunst van de 20e eeuw. Het hoogtepunt bereikte de stroming tussen 1898 en 1908."@nl ,
		"El fovismo, tambi\\u00E9n conocido como fauvismo, en franc\\u00E9s fauvisme, (1904-1908) fue un movimiento pict\\u00F3rico franc\\u00E9s caracterizado por un empleo provocativo del color. Su nombre procede del calificativo fauve, fiera en espa\\u00F1ol, dado por el cr\\u00EDtico de arte Louis Vauxcelles al conjunto de obras presentadas en el Sal\\u00F3n de Oto\\u00F1o de Par\\u00EDs de 1905. El precursor de este movimiento fue Henri Matisse y su mayor influencia en la pintura posterior se ha relacionado con la utilizaci\\u00F3n libre del color."@es ,
		"Fauvismus wird in der Kunstgeschichte einer Stilrichtung der Malerei zugeordnet. Sie entstand aus einer Bewegung innerhalb der franz\\u00F6sischen Avantgarde zu Anfang des 20. Jahrhunderts. Der Fauvismus, getragen von sehr unterschiedlichen K\\u00FCnstlern, bildet die erste Bewegung der klassischen Moderne.Die Hauptvertreter der zun\\u00E4chst geschm\\u00E4hten Bewegung waren Henri Matisse, Andr\\u00E9 Derain und Maurice de Vlaminck."@de .

		"A Era de Ouro da Fic\\u00E7\\u00E3o Cient\\u00EDfica (Golden Age of Science Fiction em ingl\\u00EAs), freq\\u00FCentemente reconhecida como um per\\u00EDodo que vai de fins dos anos 1930 ou in\\u00EDcio dos anos 1940, foi uma \\u00E9poca durante a qual o g\\u00EAnero fic\\u00E7\\u00E3o cient\\u00EDfica ganhou a ampla aten\\u00E7\\u00E3o p\\u00FAblica e onde muitas hist\\u00F3rias cl\\u00E1ssicas foram publicadas. Na hist\\u00F3ria da fic\\u00E7\\u00E3o cient\\u00EDfica, a Era de Ouro sucede a \\"era pulp\\" dos anos 1920 e 1930 e precede a \\"fic\\u00E7\\u00E3o new wave\\" dos anos 1960 e 1970."@pt ,
		"La primera Edad de oro de la ciencia ficci\\u00F3n \\u2014reconocida a menudo como la etapa comprendida entre 1939 y 1966\\u2014 fue un per\\u00EDodo donde el g\\u00E9nero de la ciencia ficci\\u00F3n comienza a atraer la atenci\\u00F3n del p\\u00FAblico, y donde muchas historias cl\\u00E1sicas de este g\\u00E9nero fueron publicadas.  En la historia de la ciencia ficci\\u00F3n, la Edad de Oro fue precedida por la era pulp de los a\\u00F1os 1920 y 1930, y precede a la nueva ola de los a\\u00F1os 1960 y 1970."@es ,

		"Literary modernism, or modernist literature, has its origins in the late 19th and early 20th centuries, mainly in Europe and North America. Some philosophers, like Georg Lukacs, theorized that literary modernism had its origins in the philosophy of Walter Benjamin. Modernism is characterized by a self-conscious break with traditional styles of poetry and verse. Modernists experimented with literary form and expression, adhering to Ezra Pound\'s maxim to \\"Make it new\\"."@en .

		"Sufra\\u017Cystka (\\u0142ac. suffragium \\u2013 g\\u0142os wyborczy) \\u2013 aktywistka dzia\\u0142aj\\u0105ca w Wielkiej Brytanii i Stanach Zjednoczonych walcz\\u0105ca o prawa wyborcze dla kobiet w ko\\u0144cu XIX i na pocz\\u0105tku XX wieku, zw\\u0142aszcza przed rozpocz\\u0119ciem I wojny \\u015Bwiatowej. 		"Suffragettes were members of women\'s organisation (right to vote) movements in the late 19th and early 20th century, particularly militants in Great Britain such as members of the Women\'s Social and Political Union (WSPU).  Suffragist is a more general term for members of suffrage movement.The term \\"suffragette\\" is particularly associated with activists in the British WSPU, led by Emmeline and Christabel Pankhurst, who were influenced by Russian methods of protest such as hunger strikes."@en ,
		"El t\\u00E9rmino sufragetes (en franc\\u00E9s: suffragettes) designa a los militantes de la Uni\\u00F3n Social y Pol\\u00EDtica de las Mujeres, una organizaci\\u00F3n fundada en 1903 por Emmeline Pankhurst para reinvindicar el derecho a voto de las mujeres en el Reino Unido partidaria de la acci\\u00F3n directa -reuniones p\\u00FAblicas y marchas de protesta ante la C\\u00E1mara de los Comunes- que nace en contraposici\\u00F3n al sector sufragista brit\\u00E1nico moderado, agrupado en la  Uni\\u00F3n Nacional de Sociedades de Sufragio Femenino (NUWSS), creada en 1987 y liderada por Millicent Fawcett (1847-1929), dedicada a la convocatoria de campa\\u00F1as y m\\u00EDtines en la m\\u00E1s estricta legalidad. "@es ,
		"Con il termine suffragette si indicavano le appartenenti a un movimento di emancipazione femminile nato per ottenere il diritto di voto per le donne (dalla parola \\"suffragio\\" nel suo significato di \\"voto\\").In seguito la parola \\"suffragetta\\" ha finito per indicare, in senso lato, la donna che lotta o si adopera per ottenere il riconoscimento della piena dignit\\u00E0 delle donne, coincidendo in parte quindi con il termine femminista."@it .

		"El tonalismo fue un estilo art\\u00EDstico que surgi\\u00F3 durante los a\\u00F1os 1880 cuando artistas estadounidenses empezaron pintar paisajes con un tono de atm\\u00F3sfera o neblina. Entre 1880 y 1915, tonos oscuros y neutrales como gris, marr\\u00F3n o azul a menudo dominaron composiciones por artistas asociados con el estilo. Durante los fines de los a\\u00F1os 1890, los cr\\u00EDticos de arte americanos comenzaron utilizar el t\\u00E9rmino \\"tonal\\" para describir estas obras."@es ,
		"Tonalism was an artistic style that emerged in the 1880s when American artists began to paint landscape forms with an overall tone of colored atmosphere or mist. Between 1880 and 1915, dark, neutral hues such as gray, brown or blue, often dominated compositions by artists associated with the style. During the late 1890s, American art critics began to use the term \\"tonal\\" to describe these works."@en ,
		"Le tonalisme (1880-1915) est un style artistique de peinture de paysage qui a \\u00E9merg\\u00E9 dans les ann\\u00E9es 1880, pour d\\u00E9crire des toiles \\u00AB tonales \\u00BB de peintres am\\u00E9ricains, c\'est-\\u00E0-dire dont l\\u2019atmosph\\u00E8re semble colori\\u00E9 ou sous la brume.Entre 1880 et 1918, des tons sombres et neutres comme le gris le brun ou le bleu ont souvent domin\\u00E9 les compositions des artistes qui \\u00E9taient associ\\u00E9 \\u00E0 ce style.Durant la fin des ann\\u00E9es 1890, les critiques am\\u00E9ricains ont commenc\\u00E9 d\\u2019utiliser le terme \\u00AB tonale \\u00BB pour d\\u00E9crire ces \\u0153uvres. "@fr ,
		"O Tonalismo foi um estilo art\\u00EDstico que surgiu na d\\u00E9cada de 1880 nos EUA. \\u00C9 caracterizado por pinturas atmosf\\u00E9ricas, com um tom predominante, quase monocrom\\u00E1ticas, que visavam representar algum estado de esp\\u00EDrito, emo\\u00E7\\u00E3o ou sentimento melanc\\u00F3lico, mais do que reproduzir exatamente o tema retratado. Os maiores representantes desse movimento foram George Iness e James McNeill Whistler. \\u00C9 derivado da escola de Barbizon."@pt ,
		"Tonalizm \\u2013 ruch artystyczny panuj\\u0105cy w malarstwie ameryka\\u0144skim od lat 80. XIX wieku do lat 20. 		"Tonalismus (1880 bis 1915) ist eine Stilrichtung in der Malerei, die entstand, als amerikanische K\\u00FCnstler begannen, Landschaften in einem \\u00FCbergreifenden Ton farbiger Atmosph\\u00E4re oder Dunst zu malen.Dunkle, neutrale Farbschattierungen, wie grau, braun oder blau dominieren gew\\u00F6hnlich solche Kompositionen. W\\u00E4hrend der sp\\u00E4ten 1890er Jahre begannen amerikanische Kunstkritiker den Ausdruck \\"tonal\\" f\\u00FCr diese Werke zu benutzen."@de .

	rdfs:comment	"A parody (/\\u02C8p\\u00E6r\\u0259di/; also called spoof, send-up or lampoon), in use, is a work created to imitate, make fun of, or comment on an original work, its subject, author, style, or some other target, by means of satiric or ironic imitation."@en ,
		"A par\\u00F3dia \\u00E9 uma releitura c\\u00F4mica de alguma composi\\u00E7\\u00E3o liter\\u00E1ria , que frequentemente utiliza ironia e deboche. Ela geralmente \\u00E9 parecida com a obra original, e quase sempre tem sentidos diferentes.A par\\u00F3dia surge a partir de uma nova interpreta\\u00E7\\u00E3o, da recria\\u00E7\\u00E3o de uma obra j\\u00E1 existente e, em geral, consagrada."@pt ,
		"La parodie est une forme d\'humour qui utilise le cadre, les personnages, le style et le fonctionnement d\'une \\u0153uvre ou une institution pour s\'en moquer.Elle se base entre autres sur l\'inversion et l\'exag\\u00E9ration des caract\\u00E9ristiques appartenant au sujet parodi\\u00E9.Selon Dominique Maingueneau, la parodie constitue une \\u00AB strat\\u00E9gie de r\\u00E9investissement d\'un texte ou d\'un genre de discours dans d\'autres \\u00BB : il s\'agit d\'une strat\\u00E9gie de \\u00AB subversion \\u00BB, visant \\u00E0 disqualifier l\'auteur du texte ou du genre source, tandis que la strat\\u00E9gie oppos\\u00E9e (la \\u00AB captation \\u00BB, imitation positive) permet de \\u00AB transf\\u00E9rer sur le discours r\\u00E9investisseur l\'autorit\\u00E9 attach\\u00E9e au texte ou au genre source \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"La parodia - dalla lingua greca \\u03C0\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u1FF3\\u03B4\\u03AF\\u03B1 par\\u00E0 (\\u03C0\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B1, simile) e od\\u00E8 (\\u1FA0\\u03B4\\u03AE, canto) - \\u00E8 l\'imitazione di uno stile letterario, musicale o artistico destinata a essere riconosciuta come tale o anche l\'imitazione caricaturale di un quantomeno noto personaggio esistente o fittizio.In un\'accezione pi\\u00F9 comune tale rielaborazione avviene in chiave comica o pi\\u00F9 spesso farsesca.Si pu\\u00F2 distinguere la parodia di opere specifiche, di autori e di generi letterari.Uno degli esempi pi\\u00F9 antichi \\u00E8 la Batracomiomachia (La battaglia dei topi e delle rane), parodia del poema epico.Negli ambienti goliardici, dal medioevo ai giorni nostri, \\u00E8 comune la parodia \\"dotta\\", si pensi ai poemetti burleschi novecenteschi Ifigonia (che rimanda all\'Ifigenia di Euripide) e Il processo di Sculacciabuchi (imitazione scurrile di un procedimento penale). "@it ,
		"\\u30D1\\u30ED\\u30C7\\u30A3\\uFF08\\u82F1\\u8A9E: parody\\u3001\\u30AE\\u30EA\\u30B7\\u30A2\\u8A9E: \\u03C0\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03C9\\u03B4\\u03B9\\u03B1\\uFF09\\u306F\\u3001\\u73FE\\u4EE3\\u306E\\u6163\\u7528\\u306B\\u304A\\u3044\\u3066\\u306F\\u4ED6\\u306E\\u82B8\\u8853\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\u3092\\u63F6\\u63C4\\u3084\\u98A8\\u523A\\u3001\\u6279\\u5224\\u3059\\u308B\\u76EE\\u7684\\u3092\\u6301\\u3063\\u3066\\u6A21\\u5023\\u3057\\u305F\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\u3001\\u3042\\u308B\\u3044\\u306F\\u305D\\u306E\\u624B\\u6CD5\\u306E\\u3053\\u3068\\u3092\\u6307\\u3059\\u3002"@ja ,

		"La parodia (del griego, \\u03C0\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03CE\\u03B4\\u00EF\\u03B1, \\u03C0\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B1, en contra de o al lado de, y \\u03CE\\u03B4\\u03AE, oda) es una obra sat\\u00EDrica que caracteriza o interpreta humor\\u00EDsticamente otra obra de arte, un autor o un tema, mediante la emulaci\\u00F3n o alusi\\u00F3n ir\\u00F3nica. 	rdfs:comment	"Primitivismo, sob um ponto de vista antropol\\u00F3gico, grosso modo, poderia ser definido como  a cren\\u00E7a na superioridade do estilo de vida simples das sociedades pr\\u00E9-industriais, ou o pr\\u00F3prio estilo de vida destas culturas, normalmente as africanas, pr\\u00E9-colombianas ou da Oceania. 		"Primitivisme is een stroming in de beeldende kunst waarbij kunstenaars (de primitivisten) er naar streven om terug te keren naar de tijd van voor de moderne beschaving, naar het primitieve, toen alles nog \'onbedorven eenvoudig en oorspronkelijk\' was. Het spontane en het na\\u00EFeve staan centraal. Vaak wordt dit gekenmerkt door gebrek aan perspectief en abstraheren van het onderwerp."@nl ,
		"Primitivism is a Western art movement that borrows visual forms from non-Western or prehistoric peoples, such as Paul Gauguin\'s inclusion of Tahitian motifs in paintings and ceramics. Borrowings from primitive art has been important to the development of modern art.The term \\"primitivism\\" is often applied to other professional painters working in the style of na\\u00EFve or folk art like Henri Rousseau, Mikhail Larionov, Paul Klee and others."@en ,
		"Der Begriff Primitivismus wurde erstmals in Frankreich im 19. Jahrhundert als kunsthistorischer Begriff gebraucht und bedeutete eine Imitation des Primitiven, wobei man unter den \\u201EPrimitiven\\u201C zun\\u00E4chst die Italiener und Flamen des 14. und 15."@de ,
		"Le Primitivisme ou N\\u00E9o-primitivisme est un mouvement pictural apparu en Russie et pr\\u00F4n\\u00E9 par certains peintres du Valet de Carreau et surtout de Queue d\'\\u00C2ne \\u00E0 partir de 1911, qui privil\\u00E9gie les formes na\\u00EFves et primitives de l\'Art : l\'imagerie populaire (loubok), les ic\\u00F4nes, les enseignes des marchands, les plateaux peints, les objets et les couleurs de la culture paysanne."@fr ,
		"El primitivismo es un movimiento art\\u00EDstico surgido en Rusia y defendido por algunos pintores de la Sota de Diamantes, que privilegia las formas ingenuas y primitivas del arte: la imaginer\\u00EDa popular, los iconos, las ense\\u00F1as de los comerciantes, los platos pintados, los objetos y los colores de la cultura campesina. Es tambi\\u00E9n, en parte, una reacci\\u00F3n contra la influencia a nivel nacional de la pintura francesa, considerada entonces preponderante."@es .

		"El antifascismo es la oposici\\u00F3n a ideolog\\u00EDas, organizaciones, gobiernos y personas de ultraderecha o extrema derecha, es decir, contra el fascismo en cualquiera de sus vertientes: nazismo, franquismo, o fascismo propiamente dicho.Se asocia hist\\u00F3ricamente con la resistencia pol\\u00EDtica en los pa\\u00EDses o estados con gobiernos fascistas o nazis, aunque tambi\\u00E9n se autodenominan \\"antifascistas\\" a ciertos grupos europeos y estadounidenses que desde la d\\u00E9cada de 1970 se han enfrentado, mediante la propaganda o la movilizaci\\u00F3n en la calle, a los partidos y bandas de extrema derecha. "@es ,
		"L\'antifascisme est l\'opposition organis\\u00E9e au fascisme et, plus largement, \\u00E0 l\'extr\\u00EAme droite. Il prend forme dans les ann\\u00E9es 1920 et se d\\u00E9veloppe cons\\u00E9quemment \\u00E0 la mont\\u00E9e du fascisme en Europe. Il a connu un tr\\u00E8s fort d\\u00E9veloppement au cours des ann\\u00E9es 1930, \\u00E9tant \\u00E0 l\'origine de la formation des Fronts populaires, puis pendant la Seconde Guerre mondiale au sein des r\\u00E9sistances contre les dictatures fasciste et nazie ainsi que les r\\u00E9gimes de collaboration."@fr ,
		"Antyfaszyzm \\u2013 ruch g\\u0142osz\\u0105cy sprzeciw wobec ideologii i praktyki faszyzmu. Powsta\\u0142 z inspiracji \\u015Brodowisk lewicowych w latach 20. W latach 30. powsta\\u0142 w Niemczech lewicowy ruch Antifa, z kolei w Hiszpanii idee sprzeciwu wobec faszyzmu reprezentowali ochotnicy z Brygad Mi\\u0119dzynarodowych."@pl ,

		"Het antifascisme is een veelvormige beweging die ageert tegen alle vormen van extreemrechts (met name nazisme, fascisme en neofascisme). Antifascisten komen vaak uit een extreemlinks milieu en organiseren regelmatig tegendemonstraties bij extreemrechtse demonstraties en bijeenkomsten.Antifascistische organisaties doen vaak onderzoek naar extreemrechtse organisaties en publiceren hierover.Tegenstanders van het antifascisme staan bekend onder de noemer antiantifa."@nl ,
		"Il termine antifascismo, dal punto di vista storico e sociologico, designa un movimento eterogeneo che, a partire dal termine della prima guerra mondiale ad oggi, sia avverso, osteggi e/o combatta il fascismo e le sue manifestazioni e declinazioni, sia a livello di governo sia come movimenti politici.Sono usati \\u2013 in riferimento ad altri regimi para-fascisti, come il nazismo e il franchismo \\u2013 anche i termini antinazismo (nato in Germania per designare la resistenza tedesca e poi usato a livello globale per tutte le opposizioni all\'ideologia di Hitler) e, in Spagna, antifranchismo (usato soprattutto per l\'opposizione storica al regime filofascista di Francisco Franco)."@it ,
		"Anti-fascism is opposition to fascist ideologies, groups and individuals. The anti-fascist movement began in a few European countries in the 1920s, and eventually spread to other countries around the world."@en ,

		"An anti-war movement (also antiwar) is a social movement, usually in opposition to a particular nation\'s decision to start or carry on an armed conflict, unconditional of a maybe-existing just cause. The term can also refer to pacifism, which is the opposition to all use of military force during conflicts. Many activists distinguish between anti-war movements and peace movements."@en .

		"Romantismo sombrio (em ingl\\u00EAs: Dark Romanticism) \\u00E9 um subg\\u00EAnero liter\\u00E1rio que surgiu no final do s\\u00E9culo XVIII. Suas caracter\\u00EDsticas s\\u00E3o irracionais e melanc\\u00F3licas, com a \\u00EAnfase no fasc\\u00EDnio sobre a forma\\u00E7\\u00E3o da loucura humana e do mal. As obras dos autores e artistas envolvidos geralmente s\\u00E3o sombrias, cheias de resigna\\u00E7\\u00E3o e protagonistas autodestrutivos. J\\u00E1 nos Estados Unidos surgiu a partir do movimento filos\\u00F3fico chamado transcendentalismo."@pt ,
		"Die Schwarze Romantik (auch Schauerromantik, Negative Romantik oder Dunkle Romantik) ist eine Unterstr\\u00F6mung, die innerhalb der Romantik am Ende des 18. Jahrhunderts aufkam."@de ,
		"Dark romanticism (often conflated with Gothicism or called American romanticism) is a literary subgenre centered on the writers Edgar Allan Poe, Nathaniel Hawthorne, and Herman Melville.As opposed to the perfectionist beliefs of Transcendentalism, the Dark Romantics emphasized human fallibility and proneness to sin and self-destruction, as well as the difficulties inherent in attempts at social reform."@en ,
		"El romanticismo oscuro (\\"Dark Romanticism\\", en ingl\\u00E9s) es un subg\\u00E9nero literario estadounidense surgido en el siglo XIX a partir del movimiento filos\\u00F3fico denominado trascendentalismo. Las obras de este subg\\u00E9nero, pues, se vieron muy influidas por el trascendentalismo, aunque no comulgaban con sus ideas. El romanticismo oscuro, a grandes rasgos, se manifiesta mucho menos optimista que aqu\\u00E9l acerca de la condici\\u00F3n humana, la naturaleza y la divinidad."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Literature, in its broadest sense, is any written work; etymologically the term derives from Latin litaritura/litteratura \\"writing formed with letters\\", although some definitions include spoken or sung texts. More restrictively, it is writing that possesses literary merit, and language that foregrounds literariness, as opposed to ordinary language."@en ,

		"Literatur  ist seit dem 19. Jahrhundert der Bereich aller m\\u00FCndlich (etwa durch Vers\\u00ADformen und Rhythmus) oder schriftlich fixierten sprachlichen Zeugnisse. Man spricht in diesem \\u201Eweiten\\u201C Begriffsverst\\u00E4ndnis etwa von \\u201EFachliteratur\\u201C oder \\u201ENotenliteratur\\u201C (Partituren) im Blick auf die hier gegebene schriftliche Fixierung. Die \\u00F6ffentliche Literaturdiskussion ist demgegen\\u00FCber seit dem 19."@de ,
		"La letteratura di una certa lingua \\u00E8 l\'insieme delle opere scritte e pervenute fino al presente. Tale definizione non \\u00E8 affatto scontata e va precisata sotto diversi aspetti. Da un lato, le definizioni che sono state date del termine, sensibili a diverse ideologie, visioni del mondo, sensibilit\\u00E0 politiche o filosofiche, sono diverse tra loro e spesso assolutamente inconciliabili."@it ,
		"La literatura, en su sentido m\\u00E1s amplio, es cualquier trabajo escrito; aunque algunas definiciones incluyen textos hablados o cantados. En un sentido m\\u00E1s restringido y tradicional, es la escritura que posee m\\u00E9rito literario y que privilegia la literariedad, en oposici\\u00F3n al lenguaje ordinario."@es ,
		"Le mot litt\\u00E9rature, issu du latin litteratura, qui signifie \\u00AB BELLES LETTRES \\u00BB. Le mot litteratura appara\\u00EEt au d\\u00E9but du XIIe si\\u00E8cle avec un sens technique de \\u00AB chose \\u00E9crite \\u00BB puis \\u00E9volue \\u00E0 la fin du Moyen \\u00C2ge vers le sens de \\u00AB savoir tir\\u00E9 des livres \\u00BB, avant d\'atteindre aux XVIIe\\u2009\\u2011\\u2009XVIIIe si\\u00E8cles son sens principal actuel : ensemble des \\u0153uvres \\u00E9crites ou orales comportant une dimension esth\\u00E9tique (ex."@fr ,

		"A Literatura \\u00E9 a arte de compor e expor escritos art\\u00EDsticos, em prosa ou em verso, de acordo com princ\\u00EDpios te\\u00F3ricos e pr\\u00E1ticos; o exerc\\u00EDcio dessa arte ou da eloqu\\u00EAncia e poesia.A palavra Literatura vem do latim \\"litteris\\" que significa \\"Letras\\", e possivelmente uma tradu\\u00E7\\u00E3o do grego \\"grammatikee\\". Em latim, literatura significa uma instru\\u00E7\\u00E3o ou um conjunto de saberes ou habilidades de escrever e ler bem, e se relaciona com as artes da gram\\u00E1tica, da ret\\u00F3rica e da po\\u00E9tica."@pt ,
		"Met literatuur wordt in het algemeen bedoeld: het geheel van teksten waarvan geoordeeld wordt dat ze universele waarde hebben. Traditioneel gaat het om proza- en dichtwerken die erin slagen zich in vorm, inhoud en intentie te onderscheiden van andere esthetische geschriften."@nl .

	rdfs:comment	"Die Parnassiens waren eine franz\\u00F6sische Dichtergruppe in der zweiten H\\u00E4lfte des 19. Jahrhunderts, die am Prinzip des L\\u2019art pour l\\u2019art orientiert war. Den Namen erhielten sie von der 1866 bei Alphonse Lemerre erschienenen Anthologie Le Parnasse contemporain (der 1871 und 1876 ein zweiter und dritter Band folgten). Der Name bezieht sich auf den Parnassos, den \\u201EBerg der Musen\\u201C in der griechischen Mythologie.Die bedeutendsten Vertreter waren Charles Leconte de Lisle und Th\\u00E9ophile Gautier."@de ,
		"Parnasizm, parnasi\\u015Bci \\u2013 pocz\\u0105tkowo nazwa grupy poetyckiej spod znaku Charles\'a Leconte\'a de Lisle\'a, p\\u00F3\\u017Aniej pr\\u0105d literacki oficjalnie zapocz\\u0105tkowany we Francji w drugiej po\\u0142owie XIX wieku, kt\\u00F3rego korzenie si\\u0119gaj\\u0105 lat 40. XIX wieku. Parnasizm by\\u0142 g\\u0142\\u00F3wnym nurtem epoki przej\\u015Bciowej mi\\u0119dzy romantyzmem a symbolizmem, oddzia\\u0142uj\\u0105c r\\u00F3wnie\\u017C na modernizm oraz pokolenie M\\u0142odej Polski."@pl ,
		"El parnasianismo fue un movimiento literario franc\\u00E9s de la segunda mitad del siglo XIX (D.C . 1870) creado como reacci\\u00F3n contra el romanticismo de V\\u00EDctor Hugo, el subjetivismo y el socialismo art\\u00EDstico.  Los fundadores de este movimiento fueron Th\\u00E9ophile Gautier (1811-1872) y Leconte de Lisle (1818-1894)."@es ,
		"De Parnasse of de Parnassiens is een Franse beweging van dichters in de tweede helft van de 19e eeuw, vernoemd naar de oud-Griekse godenberg Parnassus, maar met een knipoog naar de Montparnasse, waar veel van hun leden zich troffen.De dichters van de Parnasse zetten zich vooral in de vorm af tegen de Romantiek en propageerden het principe van \'l\'Art pour l\'Art\' (kunst omwille van de kunst): alleen dat wat zonder enig nut is kan mooi zijn."@nl ,
		"Parnassianism (or Parnassism) was a French literary style which began during the positivist period of the 19th century.  The style was influenced by the author Th\\u00E9ophile Gautier as well as by the philosophical ideas of Arthur Schopenhauer."@en ,
		"Le terme parnasse, dans son usage commun, d\\u00E9signe la po\\u00E9sie en g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ral et les po\\u00E8tes.    Le mouvement po\\u00E9tique appel\\u00E9 Parnasse est apparu en France dans la seconde moiti\\u00E9 du XIXe si\\u00E8cle : il tire son nom du recueil po\\u00E9tique le Parnasse contemporain publi\\u00E9 entre 1866 et 1876 par l\'\\u00E9diteur Alphonse Lemerre. Il appara\\u00EEt en r\\u00E9action au lyrisme et aux sentiments du romantisme."@fr ,

		"O parnasianismo \\u00E9 uma escola liter\\u00E1ria ou um movimento liter\\u00E1rio essencialmente po\\u00E9tico, contempor\\u00E2neo do Realismo-Naturalismo. Um estilo de \\u00E9poca que se desenvolveu na poesia a partir de 1850, na Fran\\u00E7a, com o objetivo de retomar a cultura cl\\u00E1ssica."@pt ,
		"Il Parnassianesimo \\u00E8 un movimento poetico apparso in Francia nella seconda met\\u00E0 dell\'XIX secolo. Il suo scopo era riportare la poesia al Parnaso, il monte sacro al dio Apollo, dal quale Lamartine l\'aveva fatta cadere gi\\u00F9. Il nome apparve per la prima volta in una antologia pubblicata dall\'editore Alphonse Lemerre nel 1866, intitolata Il Parnaso contemporaneo (le Parnasse contemporain)."@it .

		"Postcolonialism or postcolonial studies is an academic discipline featuring methods of intellectual discourse that analyze, explain, and respond to the cultural legacies of colonialism and imperialism, to the human consequences of controlling a country and establishing settlers for the economic exploitation of the native people and their land."@en ,
		"Le post-colonialisme ou postcolonialisme est un courant de pens\\u00E9e dont les principaux fondements se situent dans les \\u0153uvres de Frantz Fanon (Peau noire, masques blancs, 1952 et Les Damn\\u00E9s de la terre, 1961) et dans l\'ouvrage d\'Edward Sa\\u00EFd, L\'Orientalisme, paru en 1978. En tant que th\\u00E9orie litt\\u00E9raire, il fournit des outils critiques permettant d\'analyser les \\u00E9crits produits par les auteurs issus des pays qui ont une histoire de colonisation."@fr ,
		"P\\u00F3s-colonialismo (ou p\\u00F3scolonialismo) \\u00E9 um conjunto de teorias que analisa os efeitos pol\\u00EDticos, filos\\u00F3ficos, art\\u00EDsticos e liter\\u00E1rios deixados pelo colonialismo nos pa\\u00EDses colonizados.Como teoria liter\\u00E1ria (ou abordagem cr\\u00EDtica), lida com a literatura produzida em pa\\u00EDses que outrora foram col\\u00F4nias de outros pa\\u00EDses, especialmente das pot\\u00EAncias coloniais europeias Gr\\u00E3-Bretanha, Fran\\u00E7a e Espanha; em alguns contextos, inclui pa\\u00EDses ainda em situa\\u00E7\\u00E3o colonial."@pt ,

		"Postkolonialismus ist eine geistige Str\\u00F6mung seit Mitte des 20. Jahrhunderts aus der Zeit nach dem Kolonialismus, die sich auf diesen bezieht. Sie wird dem Poststrukturalismus zugerechnet. Vorausgegangen ist die Unabh\\u00E4ngigkeit der Kolonie von ihrem Kolonisator."@de ,
		"Post-kolonializm (tak\\u017Ce studia post-kolonialne, teoria post-kolonialna, postkolonializm) to dyscyplina naukowa opieraj\\u0105ca si\\u0119 na intelektualnym dyskursie, kt\\u00F3ry s\\u0142u\\u017Cy do analizowania i wyja\\u015Bniania zar\\u00F3wno kulturowych pozosta\\u0142o\\u015Bci kolonializmu i imperializmu, jak i badania konsekwencji kontrolowania kraju i zasiedlania go w celu ekonomicznej eksploatacji ludno\\u015Bci tubylczej i jej ziemi."@pl ,
		"Het postkolonialisme is een stroming binnen de geesteswetenschappen, literatuur en politicologie die ageert tegen het westerse kolonialisme en de overblijfselen daarvan na de dekolonisatie. Een belangrijk middel hierin is de deconstructie van koloniale discoursen en met name de identificatie en kritiek op koloniale begrippenparen als westers/oosters (zie ori\\u00EBntalisme) en de vervanging daarvan door een systeem van verschil en pluraliteit."@nl ,

		"El poscolonialismo, tambi\\u00E9n conocido como teor\\u00EDa poscolonial, trata de un conjunto de teor\\u00EDas que lidian con el legado de la colonizaci\\u00F3n brit\\u00E1nica y francesa durante el siglo XIX o espa\\u00F1ola y portuguesa desde el siglo XVI hasta el XIX. Como teor\\u00EDa literaria, o postura cr\\u00EDtica, trata la literatura producida en pa\\u00EDses que fueron o son a\\u00FAn colonias de otros pa\\u00EDses. Tambi\\u00E9n analiza los efectos del conocimiento producido en los pa\\u00EDses colonizadores sobre los pa\\u00EDses colonizados, o sus habitantes."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Een psychologische roman, ook wel psychologisch realisme genoemd, is een literair genre waarin meer dan normaal de nadruk wordt gelegd op het innerlijk van de karakters, motieven, omstandigheden en innerlijke handelingen en gedachten die ontstaan.De roman vertelt niet alleen de verschillende gebeurtenissen, maar gaat dieper in op het waarom en waarvoor deze gebeurtenissen tot stand komen."@nl ,

		"La novela psicol\\u00F3gica o novela de an\\u00E1lisis psicol\\u00F3gico, tambi\\u00E9n conocida como realismo psicol\\u00F3gico, es una obra de ficci\\u00F3n en prosa que enfatiza la caracterizaci\\u00F3n interior de sus personajes, sus motivos, circunstancias y acci\\u00F3n interna que nace y se desarrolla a partir de la acci\\u00F3n externa. La novela psicol\\u00F3gica \\"pospone la narraci\\u00F3n a la descripci\\u00F3n de los estados de \\u00E1nimo, pasiones y conflictos psicol\\u00F3gicos\\" de los personajes."@es ,
		"Il romanzo psicologico \\u00E8 un tipo di romanzo nato tra l\'Ottocento e il Novecento, nel clima di crisi e di tensione che caratterizz\\u00F2 gli anni tra le guerre, si possono riscontrare due tendenze principali in letteratura: da una parte, una chiusura nella propria interiorit\\u00E0, dall\\u2019altra una forte esigenza di realismo.Davanti ai drammi della guerra, alla violenza, ai soprusi molti autori scelsero la letteratura come mezzo di autoanalisi e riflessione profonda su di s\\u00E9."@it ,
		"O romance psicol\\u00F3gico \\u00E9 um g\\u00EAnero liter\\u00E1rio que se volta menos aos condicionantes exteriores do meio ambiente social e cultural e, mais, aos motivos \\u00EDntimos das escolhas e a\\u00E7\\u00F5es humanas, no fluxo de afetos e mem\\u00F3rias do inconsciente para o consciente, determinando comportamentos.O tema \\u00E9 antigo e foi inaugurado por Choderlos de Laclos, autor de \\"Liga\\u00E7\\u00F5es Perigosas\\" (1782)."@pt ,
		"A psychological novel, also called psychological realism, is a work of prose fiction which places more than the usual amount of emphasis on interior characterization, and on the motives, circumstances, and internal action which springs from, and develops, external action. The psychological novel is not content to state what happens but goes on to explain the motivation of this action."@en .
dbr:Punk_ideologies	rdfs:label	"Id\\u00E9ologie punk"@fr ,
		"Ideologia punk"@pt ,
		"Punk ideologies"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"L\'id\\u00E9ologie punk est la pens\\u00E9e (textes de chansons, presse alternative, fanzines), le graphisme, l\'esth\\u00E9tique et la musique (Sex Pistols, The Clash, Jamie Reid...) du mouvement punk et ses variantes dans le temps. Son action li\\u00E9e au do it yourself (en fran\\u00E7ais : faites le vous-m\\u00EAme) est ouvertement politique, li\\u00E9e \\u00E0 la contestation de l\'ordre \\u00E9tabli, \\u00E0 la notion de libert\\u00E9 individuelle, \\u00E0 l\'anarchisme (Crass, Jello Biafra, B\\u00E9rurier Noir, etc.)."@fr ,
		"Desde o seu in\\u00EDcio, a cultura punk teve ideias apartid\\u00E1rias e a liberdade para acreditar ou n\\u00E3o em um deus ou religi\\u00E3o qualquer."@pt ,
		"Punk ideologies are a group of varied social and political beliefs associated with the punk subculture. In its original incarnation, the punk subculture was primarily concerned with concepts such as anti-establishment, equality, freedom, anti-authoritarianism, individualism, direct action, free thought and non-conformity. Punk ideologies are usually expressed through punk rock music, punk literature, spoken word recordings, punk fashion, or punk visual art."@en .

dbr:Social_commentary	rdfs:label	"Critica sociale (sociologia)"@it ,
		"Social commentary"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Una critica sociale \\u00E8 l\'atto del ribellarsi a un individuo o a un gruppo sociale da un punto di vista retorico. Spesso \\u00E8 in connessione all\'idea di dover favorire o promuovere un cambiamento nel fare informazione alla popolazione generale su un determinato problema e richiamarsi al senso di giustizia comune. Due esempi di forte e dura critica sociale possono essere gli scritti di Jonathan Swift e Martin Lutero."@it ,
		"Social commentary is the act of using rhetorical means to provide commentary on issues in a society. This is often done with the idea of implementing or promoting change by informing the general populace about a given problem and appealing to people\'s sense of justice."@en .
