		"L\'art copte d\\u00E9signe l\'ensemble des productions artistiques des populations chr\\u00E9tiennes d\'\\u00C9gypte pendant la p\\u00E9riode comprenant la fin de l\'occupation romaine, la p\\u00E9riode byzantine et une partie de la p\\u00E9riode islamique. On consid\\u00E8re donc en g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ral qu\'il repr\\u00E9sente la p\\u00E9riode comprise entre le IIIe si\\u00E8cle et le XIIe si\\u00E8cle.C\'est un art h\\u00E9ritier de nombreuses influences, \\u00E0 savoir pharaoniques,  gr\\u00E9co-romaines et orientales."@fr ,
		"Per arte copta si intende sia l\'arte egiziana agli inizi dell\'era cristiana, sia l\'arte dei cristiani copti che ebbe i suoi periodi pi\\u00F9 fulgidi nel V-VI secolo e nel XII-XIII secoloL\'atto di nascita dell\'arte copta fu costituito dall\'apertura dei primi conventi cristiani avvenuta per merito degli anacoreti san Macario e san Pacomio."@it ,
		"A arte copta \\u00E9 a arte dos povos cristianizados no Egipto, que se desenvolveu entre os s\\u00E9culos IV e VII. Este estilo baseia-se na arte greco-romana tendo sido tamb\\u00E9m influenciado pela arte s\\u00EDria e do Pr\\u00F3ximo Oriente. Desenvolvem-se principalmente pe\\u00E7as decorativas parietais (t\\u00EAxteis), iluminuras e pe\\u00E7as em marfim."@pt ,
		"El arte copto es un t\\u00E9rmino para referirse al arte egipcio producido en la era paleocristiana o al arte producido propiamente por los coptos.Es conocido especialmente por sus frescos, textiles, miniaturas y trabajos en metal, muchos de los cuales se conservan en monasterios e iglesias. La artesan\\u00EDa es a menudo funcional, ya que eran pocas las diferencias entre artista y artesano, e incluye t\\u00FAnicas, l\\u00E1pidas y retratos de santos."@es ,
		"Die Koptische Kunst ist die Kunst der christlichen Nachkommen (Kopten) \\u00C4gyptens. Sie ging aus der r\\u00F6mischen Zeit \\u00C4gyptens hervor und blieb im Laufe ihrer Entwicklung im Wesentlichen Volkskunst. Das christliche Kunstschaffen in \\u00C4gypten kann in zwei Phasen unterteilt werden. Vor der Eroberung \\u00C4gyptens durch die Araber im Jahr 641 war die dortige Kunst praktisch eine lokale Variante byzantinischer Kunst, die auch Elemente des alt\\u00E4gyptischen Kunstschaffens aufwies."@de ,
		"Coptic art is a term used either for the art of Egypt produced in the early Christian era or for the art produced by the Coptic Christians themselves.  Coptic art is most well known for its wall-paintings, textiles, illuminated manuscripts, and metalwork, much of which survives in monasteries and churches."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Le costumbrismo (de l\'espagnol \\u00AB costumbre \\u00BB, \\u00AB coutume \\u00BB, \\u00AB m\\u0153urs \\u00BB, \\u00AB tradition \\u00BB) est un courant artistique pr\\u00E9tendant faire de l\'\\u0153uvre d\'art un reflet fid\\u00E8le des coutumes et usages sociaux. Le costumbrismo s\'\\u00E9tend \\u00E0 l\'ensemble des arts ; ainsi, il est possible de parler de tableaux ou de romans costumbristas."@fr ,
		"Costumbrismo \\u00E9 a interpreta\\u00E7\\u00E3o liter\\u00E1ria ou pict\\u00F3rica da vida cotidiana, maneirismos e costumes locais, principalmente no cen\\u00E1rio hisp\\u00E2nico e, particularmente , no s\\u00E9culo XIX. O costumbrismo est\\u00E1 relacionado tanto com o realismo art\\u00EDstico e quanto ao romantismo, partilhando o interesse rom\\u00E2ntico pela express\\u00E3o contra a simples representa\\u00E7\\u00E3o e o foco rom\\u00E2ntico e realista na representa\\u00E7\\u00E3o exata de determinados tempos e lugares, ao inv\\u00E9s da humanidade em abstrato."@pt ,
		"Costumbrismo (sometimes anglicized as Costumbrism)  is the literary or pictorial interpretation of local everyday life, mannerisms, and customs, primarily in the Hispanic scene, and particularly in the 19th century. Costumbrismo is related both to artistic realism and to Romanticism, sharing the Romantic interest in expression as against simple representation and the romantic and realist focus on precise representation of particular times and places, rather than of humanity in the abstract."@en ,
		"Il termine costumbrismo (dallo spagnolo costumbre, ossia \\"costume\\") indica un genere di letteratura narrativa sviluppatosi in Spagna nella prima met\\u00E0 del XIX secolo. Esso si contraddistingue per l\'interesse nel creare un\'opera d\'arte prendendo spunto dai costumi e dagli usi popolari."@it ,
		"Der Costumbrismo (dt. Kostumbrismus, von span.: costumbre Brauchtum, Landessitte) ist eine literarische Str\\u00F6mung von etwa 1830 bis zur Mitte des 19. Jahrhunderts, die die Sitten und Gebr\\u00E4uche der spanischen Gesellschaft schildert. Die Vertreter dieser Str\\u00F6mung werden als Costumbristas bezeichnet."@de ,
		"Kostumbryzm (hiszp. costumbrismo, od costumbre - obyczaj) \\u2013 kierunek w literaturze i sztuce hiszpa\\u0144skiej i hispanoameryka\\u0144skiej. Zapocz\\u0105tkowany w Hiszpanii w XVII w., rozwin\\u0105\\u0142 si\\u0119 w okresie romantyzmu."@pl ,

	rdfs:comment	"Die Amsterdamse Joffers waren eine Gruppe niederl\\u00E4ndischer K\\u00FCnstlerinnen um Prof. August Alleb\\u00E9 und Th\\u00E9r\\u00E8se Schwartze. Sie werden zu den niederl\\u00E4ndischen Impressionisten des 19. und des 20. Jahrhunderts gez\\u00E4hlt."@de ,
		"De Amsterdamse Joffers is de aanduiding voor een groep kunstenaressen die aan het eind van de 19e eeuw studeerden aan de Rijksakademie van beeldende kunsten in Amsterdam. De schilderessen raakten bevriend en exposeerden samen."@nl ,
		"The Amsterdamse Joffers was a group of women artists in Amsterdam who met weekly in the last quarter of the 19th century to paint and show their works together. They were known for their style that followed the example of the Amsterdam Impressionists, and were all members of the Amsterdam artist societies Arti et Amicitiae and Sint Lucas, and most followed lessons by the Amsterdam professor August Alleb\\u00E9.Ausgangssprache: Niederl\\u00E4ndisch"@en .

dbr:Holloware	rdfs:label	"Holloware"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Holloware (hollowware, or hollow-ware ) is tableware such as sugar bowls, creamers, coffee pots, teapots, soup tureens, hot food covers, water jugs, platters, butter pat plates, and other metal items that went with the dishware on a table. It does not include flatware. Holloware was constructed to last a long time. It differs from some other silverplated items in being made with thicker walls and more layers of silverplate.Dining car holloware is a type of railroad collectible (railroadiana)."@en .
dbr:La_Onda	rdfs:label	"La Onda"@nl ,
		"La Onda"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"La Onda (The Wave) was a multidisciplinary artistic movement created in Mexico by artists and intellectuals as part of the world-wide waves of the counterculture of the 1960s and the avant-garde."@en ,
		"La Onda (Nederlands: De Golf) is de benaming voor de Mexicaanse tegencultuur die is ontstaan in de jaren \'60.Na het neerslaan van de studentenprotesten van 1968 en het Bloedbad van Tlatelolco, begon zich een meer cultureel gerichte tegenbeweging te organiseren, gekenmerkt door onder andere de jipitecas, de Mexicaanse hippies. Rond 1970 ontstond een nieuwe stroming van Mexicaanse muziek, waarin Mexicaanse en buitenlandse muziek werd vermengd met politiek protest."@nl .

	rdfs:comment	"Die Lichtkunst ist heute neben der Malerei, Plastik oder der Fotografie eine eigenst\\u00E4ndige Kunstgattung, die in den \\u00FCbergeordneten Kategorien der Skulptur und Installation zu finden ist. Zeitgen\\u00F6ssische Lichtk\\u00FCnstler arbeiten vor allem mit k\\u00FCnstlichem Licht als Lichtquelle. Von Lichtkunst kann nur dann gesprochen werden, wenn der Einsatz von Lichtquellen \\u00E4sthetischen Zwecken dient."@de ,
		"Le light art (litt\\u00E9ralement \\u00AB art lumineux \\u00BB en anglais) est un art visuel dont le principal moyen d\'expression est la lumi\\u00E8re."@fr ,
		"Light art is an applied arts form in which light is the main medium of expression."@en ,
		"La Light Art \\u00E8 una forma di arte visiva in cui il mezzo di espressione e il fine dell\'opera \\u00E8 la luce.La Light Art vede i suoi esordi all\'incirca attorno alla met\\u00E0 del XX secolo. Si afferma come forma d\'arte mediante le opere di Dan Flavin e James Turrell."@it ,
		"Light-art is een beeldende kunstvorm waarbij de belichting van een object deel uitmaakt van het kunstobject, of door belichting een alledaags voorwerp of gebouw een kunstvoorwerp wordt.In sommige gevallen wordt gebruikgemaakt van sensoren, waarbij de kijker of passant gewenst of ongewenst invloed uitoefent op de belichting, en zo op het kunstwerk."@nl ,
		"El tratamiento de la luz en el arte es uno de los temas m\\u00E1s importantes de las t\\u00E9cnicas art\\u00EDsticas de cada una de las artes (especialmente las denominadas artes visuales); as\\u00ED como de la teor\\u00EDa del arte y de la est\\u00E9tica."@es .

		"Post-painterly abstraction is a term created by art critic Clement Greenberg as the title for an exhibit he curated for the Los Angeles County Museum of Art in 1964, which subsequently travelled to the Walker Art Center and the Art Gallery of Toronto.Greenberg had perceived that there was a new movement in painting that derived from the abstract expressionism of the 1940s and 1950s but \\"favored openness or clarity\\" as opposed to the dense painterly surfaces of that painting style."@en ,
		"La abstracci\\u00F3n pospict\\u00F3rica (en ingl\\u00E9s post-painterly abstraction) es un t\\u00E9rmino creado por el cr\\u00EDtico de arte Clement Greenberg como el t\\u00EDtulo de una exposici\\u00F3n de la que fue curador en el Museo de Arte del Condado de Los \\u00C1ngeles en 1964, que posteriormente se present\\u00F3 en el Centro de Arte Walker y la Galer\\u00EDa de Arte de Ontario en Toronto.Greenberg hab\\u00EDa percibido que hab\\u00EDa un nuevo movimiento en pintura que derivaba del expresionismo abstracto de los a\\u00F1os cuarenta y los cincuenta pero que \\u00ABfavorec\\u00EDa la apertura o claridad\\u00BB en oposici\\u00F3n a las superficies pict\\u00F3ricamente densas de aquel estilo pict\\u00F3rico. "@es ,

dbr:Abstract_Illusionism	rdfs:label	"Abstract Illusionism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Abstract illusionism, a name coined by art historian and critic Barbara Rose, is an artistic movement that came into prominence in the United States during the mid-1970s. Works consisted of both hard-edge and expressionistic abstract painting styles that employed the use of perspective, artificial light sources, and simulated cast shadows to achieve the illusion of three-dimensional space on a two-dimensional surface."@en .

		"Een animalier (meervoud: animaliers) is een kunstenaar die zich specialiseert in de realistische weergave van dieren. Het begrip stamt uit Frankrijk in de 19de eeuw en slaat meestal op een beeldhouwer of een schilder."@nl ,
		"An animalier is an artist, mainly from the 19th century, who specializes in, or is known for, skill in the realistic portrayal of animals. \\"Animal painter\\" is the more general term for earlier artists.  Although the work may be in any genre or format, the term is most often applied to sculptors and painters."@en ,

	rdfs:comment	"Estridentismo foi um movimento art\\u00EDstico inscrito no ciclo das vanguardas hist\\u00F3ricas, surgido em 1921, na Cidade do M\\u00E9xico, de car\\u00E1ter intedisciplinar, combinando aspectos dos movimentos cubista, futurista e dada\\u00EDsta.Fundado pelo poeta Manuel Maples Arce, visava enaltecer a emo\\u00E7\\u00E3o como fonte de cria\\u00E7\\u00E3o est\\u00E9tica, baseando sua express\\u00E3o em associa\\u00E7\\u00F5es livres."@pt ,
		"El Estridentismo fue  un movimiento art\\u00EDstico y de vanguardia \\u2009interdisciplinario que se inici\\u00F3 el 31 de diciembre de 1921 en la Ciudad de M\\u00E9xico, tras el lanzamiento del manifiesto Actual N\\u00BA1 por el poeta Manuel Maples Arce. A \\u00E9l se sumaron Arqueles Vela, Germ\\u00E1n List Arzubide, Salvador Gallardo, Germ\\u00E1n Cueto, Ferm\\u00EDn Revueltas, Ram\\u00F3n Alva de la Canal, Luis Quintanilla y Leopoldo M\\u00E9ndez, quienes constituir\\u00EDan el grupo estridentista, propiamente dicho."@es ,
		"Le stridentisme est un mouvement artistique mexicain d\'avant-garde interdisciplinaire compos\\u00E9 de po\\u00E8tes, d\'\\u00E9crivains, de musiciens et de peintres, fond\\u00E9 \\u00E0 Mexico par le po\\u00E8te Manuel Maples Arce le 31 d\\u00E9cembre 1921 \\u00E0 Jalapa, avec le lancement du manifeste  Actual n\\u00BA1 par le po\\u00E8te Manuel Maples Arce. Le stridentisme - estridentismo en espagnol - n\'a gu\\u00E8re dur\\u00E9 qu\'une douzaine d\'ann\\u00E9es."@fr ,
		"Estridentismus (englisch Stridentism) ist die deutsche Ableitung des spanischen Begriffs Estridentismo, der f\\u00FCr die avantgardistische und interdisziplin\\u00E4re K\\u00FCnstlerbewegung Mexikos w\\u00E4hrend der Mexikanischen Revolution steht, und der unmittelbar mit der Gr\\u00FCndung der K\\u00FCnstlergruppe \\u201ELos Estridentistas\\u201C am 31."@de ,
		"Stridentism (Spanish: Estridentismo) was an artistic and multidisciplinary avant-garde movement, founded in Mexico City by Manuel Maples Arce at the end of 1921 but formally developed in Xalapa where all the founders moved after the University of Veracruz granted its support for the movement."@en .

		"La T\\u00E9cnica de fondo blanco de vasos pintados floreci\\u00F3 en Atenas y Etruria entre finales del siglo VI  a. C. y finales del siglo V  a. C.Los restos m\\u00E1s antiguos de una cer\\u00E1mica pintada con esta t\\u00E9cnica, pertenecen a un k\\u00E1ntharos datado en torno al 570  a. C. y firmado por el alfarero-pintor Nearco, que se encontr\\u00F3 en la Acr\\u00F3polis de Atenas (Akropolis 611). El m\\u00E9todo consiste en un engobe blanco de una arcilla calc\\u00E1rea local aplicada a un vaso de terracota y posteriormente pintado."@es ,
		"L\'espressione tecnica a fondo bianco per convenzione si riferisce propriamente ad una tipologia di decorazione ceramografica nata ad Atene durante il secondo quarto del V secolo a.C. e utilizzata fino alla fine dello stesso secolo prevalentemente nella produzione di piccoli unguentari o lekythoi a scopo funerario."@it ,
		"Als Wei\\u00DFgrundige Vasenmalerei bezeichnet man eine Sonderform der griechischen Vasenmalerei, die sich in Attika zu einer eigenen Gattung der Vasenmalerei herausbildete.Bei der Wei\\u00DFgrundigen Vasenmalerei wird die Keramik mit einem hellen, wei\\u00DFlichem \\u00DCberzug aus kaolinithaltigem Tonschlicker \\u00FCberzogen. Dieser war sowohl in geometrischer wie auch in archaischer Zeit als Bilduntergrund in Verwendung. Wei\\u00DFgrundige Vasen wurden beispielsweise in Ionien, Lakonien und auf den Kykladen hergestellt."@de ,
		"White-ground technique is a style of ancient Greek vase painting in which figures appear on a white background. It developed in the region of Attica, dated to about 500 B.C."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"\\u041C\\u0430\\u043A\\u043E\\u043D\\u0434\\u043E (\\u0438\\u0441\\u043F. McOndo, \\u041C\\u0430\\u043A-\\u041E\\u043D\\u0434\\u043E) \\u2014 \\u0438\\u0441\\u043F\\u0430\\u043D\\u043E\\u0430\\u043C\\u0435\\u0440\\u0438\\u043A\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0435 \\u043B\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u043D\\u043E\\u0435 \\u0442\\u0435\\u0447\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435, \\u043F\\u043E\\u044F\\u0432\\u0438\\u0432\\u0448\\u0435\\u0435\\u0441\\u044F \\u0432 1990-\\u0435 \\u043A\\u0430\\u043A \\u043E\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u0442\\u043D\\u0430\\u044F \\u0440\\u0435\\u0430\\u043A\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F \\u043D\\u0430 \\u0432\\u043B\\u0438\\u044F\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u043B\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0448\\u043A\\u043E\\u043B\\u044B \\u043C\\u0430\\u0433\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0440\\u0435\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C\\u0430, \\u0432\\u043B\\u0430\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u043E\\u0432\\u0430\\u0432\\u0448\\u0435\\u0439 \\u043D\\u0430\\u0434 \\u043B\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u043E\\u0439 \\u041B\\u0430\\u0442\\u0438\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0410\\u043C\\u0435\\u0440\\u0438\\u043A\\u0438 \\u0441 1960-\\u0445. \\u041D\\u0430\\u0437\\u0432\\u0430\\u043D\\u043E \\u0432 \\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u044C \\u0432\\u044B\\u043C\\u044B\\u0448\\u043B\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0433\\u043E\\u0440\\u043E\\u0434\\u0430, \\u043E\\u0441\\u043D\\u043E\\u0432\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u043C\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0430 \\u0434\\u0435\\u0439\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0438\\u044F \\u0440\\u043E\\u043C\\u0430\\u043D\\u0430 \\u00AB\\u0421\\u0442\\u043E \\u043B\\u0435\\u0442 \\u043E\\u0434\\u0438\\u043D\\u043E\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0430\\u00BB \\u0413\\u0430\\u0431\\u0440\\u0438\\u044D\\u043B\\u044F \\u0413\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u0438\\u0430 \\u041C\\u0430\\u0440\\u043A\\u0435\\u0441\\u0430."@ru ,
		"McOndo es una corriente literaria de Hispanoam\\u00E9rica surgido en la d\\u00E9cada de los noventa como reacci\\u00F3n contra la escuela literaria del realismo m\\u00E1gico, que dominaba la recepci\\u00F3n europea de la literatura de Am\\u00E9rica Latina desde 1960.Se caracteriza por describir escenarios realistas, sin exagerar ni enfatizar un supuesto exotismo y colorido latinoamericano, prefiriendo ambientes urbanos con referencias a la cultura pop y a la vida cotidiana de la Am\\u00E9rica Latina de fines del siglo XX."@es ,
		"McOndo is a Latin American literary movement that breaks from the Magical Realism (Realismo m\\u00E1gico) mode of narration, and counters it with the strong, ideologic associations of the cultural and narrative languages of the mass communications media, and with the modernity of urban living; the experience of town versus country, of McOndo vs. Macondo."@en ,
		"McOndo est un mouvement litt\\u00E9raire latino-am\\u00E9ricain qui est n\\u00E9 en r\\u00E9action \\u00E0 la tradition litt\\u00E9raire du r\\u00E9alisme magique, longtemps pr\\u00E9dominante en Am\\u00E9rique latine."@fr ,
		"McOndo - termin stworzony przez chilijskiego pisarza Alberto Fugueta i okre\\u015Blaj\\u0105cy now\\u0105 proz\\u0119 iberoameryka\\u0144sk\\u0105.Nazwa nurtu jest gr\\u0105 s\\u0142own\\u0105, zbitk\\u0105 s\\u0142\\u00F3w: nazwy sieci bar\\u00F3w McDonald\\u2019s, luksusowych hoteli (Condo hotels) oraz fikcyjnej wioski Macondo stworzonej przez kolumbijskiego pisarza Gabriela M\\u00E1rqueza. McOndo po raz pierwszy zaistnia\\u0142o w 1996 jako tytu\\u0142 zbioru opowiada\\u0144 napisanych przez grup\\u0119 dwudziesto-trzydziestolatk\\u00F3w."@pl .
dbr:Southern_art	rdfs:label	"Southern art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Southern art is a broad term that applies to art of, about, and from the Southern United States. The Ogden Museum of Southern Art in New Orleans houses the largest single collection of Southern art. In 1992, the Morris Museum of Art opened in Augusta, Georgia, with a focus on Mid-Twentieth Century American Southern art."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"L\\u2019infrarealismo \\u00E8 un movimento poetico che nasce dalla mano del cileno Roberto Matta quando Andr\\u00E9 Breton lo espelle dal surrealismo. Questo movimento aveva come consegna \\"far saltare in aria il cervello alla cultura ufficiale\\". Fu fondato dopo l\\u2019abbandono del laboratorio di poesia di Juan Ba\\u00F1uelos alla UNAM.Intorno al 1974 l\\u2019infrarealismo riappare in Messico con un gruppo di poeti messicani e cileni. Tra gli scrittori pi\\u00F9 importanti troviamo infatti Mario Santiago e Roberto Bola\\u00F1o."@it ,
		"El infrarrealismo es un movimiento po\\u00E9tico fundado en M\\u00E9xico, D. F. en 1975 por un grupo de veinte poetas j\\u00F3venes, entre los que se encontraban Roberto Bola\\u00F1o, Mario Santiago Papasquiaro, Jos\\u00E9 Vicente Anaya, Rub\\u00E9n Medina y Jos\\u00E9 Rosas Ribeyro.Los infrarrealistas, tambi\\u00E9n conocidos simplemente como \\u00ABinfras\\u00BB, tomaron como consigna la frase de Matta \\u00ABvolarle la tapa de los sesos a la cultura oficial\\u00BB."@es ,
		"Infrarrealismo is a poetic movement founded in Mexico City in 1975 by a group of twenty young poets including Roberto Bola\\u00F1o, Mario Santiago Papasquiaro, Jos\\u00E9 Vicente Anaya, Rub\\u00E9n Medina and Jos\\u00E9 Rosas Ribeyro."@en ,
		"L\'infrar\\u00E9alisme est un mouvement po\\u00E9tique d\\u2019avant-garde fond\\u00E9 en 1975 par le po\\u00E8te mexicain Mario Santiago Papasquiaro et l\\u2019\\u00E9crivain chilien Roberto Bola\\u00F1o."@fr .

		"La literatura de Argelia consiste en la producci\\u00F3n literaria de los autores oriundos del territorio que corresponde a la Argelia contempor\\u00E1nea, as\\u00ED como de los autores europeos que viv\\u00EDan en Argelia durante la \\u00E9poca colonial francesa. 		"Algerian literature has been influenced by many cultures, including the ancient Romans, Arabs, French and Spanish, as well as the indigenous people. The dominant languages in Algerian literature are French and Arabic, but Berber is also represented.A few of the more notable Algerian writers are , Kateb Yacine, Rachid Mimouni, Mouloud Mammeri, Mouloud Feraoun, Assia Djebar and Mohammed Dib."@en ,
		"La litt\\u00E9rature alg\\u00E9rienne fait partie de la litt\\u00E9rature maghr\\u00E9bine. Elle utilise plusieurs langues : le fran\\u00E7ais, l\'arabe et le berb\\u00E8re."@fr .

		"Marine (peinture)"@fr ,

		"Marine art"@en ,
		"Arte marinha"@pt ;
	rdfs:comment	"Marina, pejza\\u017C marynistyczny \\u2013 przedstawienie malarskie, kt\\u00F3rego g\\u0142\\u00F3wnym tematem jest morze, widok portu, wybrze\\u017Ca, bitwy morskiej. Pejza\\u017C marynistyczny jako odr\\u0119bny gatunek malarski zaistnia\\u0142 w XVII wieku w tw\\u00F3rczo\\u015Bci mistrz\\u00F3w holenderskich (Salomon van Ruisdael)."@pl ,
		"Se conoce como marina, pintura marina o g\\u00E9nero de pintura de marinas, a cualquier forma de arte figurativo (pintura, dibujo, grabado y escultura) cuya inspiraci\\u00F3n principal es el mar."@es ,
		"Een marine, ook zeegezicht genoemd, is iedere vorm van figuratieve kunst (schilderijen, tekeningen, beeldhouwwerk ...) met de zee als onderwerp. Een marine haalt zijn inspiratie voornamelijk uit alles rond de zee en schepen. Het is een genre dat vooral tussen de 17e en 19e eeuw werd beoefend. In de praktijk omvat de marine ook scheepvaart op rivieren, havens en boten op het strand.Schepen op water zijn al heel vroeg een thema geweest op schilderijen. Op petrogliefen van 12.000 v.Chr."@nl ,
		"Die Marinemalerei ist ein Bereich der Malerei, der maritime Themen auf Gem\\u00E4lden zeigt. Bis ins 19. Jahrhundert wurde die See, beziehungsweise das Meer, nie allein dargestellt; Wasserfahrzeuge aller Art, Gr\\u00F6\\u00DFe und Vielzahl waren die Hauptthemen. Die Marinemalerei als Sujet wird sehr weit gefasst, kann damit auch Landschaften, Personen und Ereignisse zeigen und reicht so in mehrere Bildgattungen hinein. Die Entwicklung als eigenst\\u00E4ndiges Thema begann im 16. Jahrhundert und gelangte im 17."@de ,
		"Une marine est un genre de peinture dont le sujet est la mer, elle peut donc repr\\u00E9senter des sc\\u00E8nes de navire dans des situations diverses selon les \\u00E9poques : parfois en haute mer, parfois entrant ou sortant d\'un port. Le tableau peut repr\\u00E9senter des batailles, ou une lutte contre les \\u00E9l\\u00E9ments (oc\\u00E9an en furie, vents de temp\\u00EAte).Traditionnellement le ch\\u00E2ssis, pour une marine est horizontal et plus allong\\u00E9 que celui du paysage."@fr ,

		"Abraham Shlonsky (Karyokov, actual Ucrania, 6 de marzo de 1900 \\u2013 Tel Aviv, Israel, 18 de mayo de 1973), en hebreo: \\u05D0\\u05D1\\u05E8\\u05D4\\u05DD \\u05E9\\u05DC\\u05D5\\u05E0\\u05E1\\u05E7\\u05D9, en ruso: \\u0410\\u0432\\u0440\\u0430\\u043C \\u0428\\u043B\\u0451\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0439) fue un poeta y editor israel\\u00ED ganador del Premio Israel de literatura en 1967. Such works generally take place in an urban setting and within the confines of a fairly elaborate, and almost always hierarchical, social structure. The term was first used in print by science fiction critic Donald G."@en ,

dbr:New_Thought	rdfs:label	"Movimento Novo Pensamento"@pt ,
		"New Thought"@it ,
		"\\u30CB\\u30E5\\u30FC\\u30BD\\u30FC\\u30C8"@ja ,
		"New Thought"@en ,
		"Nuevo Pensamiento"@es ,
		"Nouvelle Pens\\u00E9e"@fr ,
		"\\u041D\\u043E\\u0432\\u043E\\u0435 \\u043C\\u044B\\u0448\\u043B\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435"@ru ,
		"Neugeist-Bewegung"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"La Nouvelle Pens\\u00E9e (New Thought), parfois \\u00E9galement appel\\u00E9e Penser Nouveau, est un courant de pens\\u00E9e philosophique et religieux qui s\'est d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 dans la seconde moiti\\u00E9 du XIXe si\\u00E8cle aux \\u00C9tats-Unis et existe encore de nos jours. Ce courant, \\u00E0 ne pas confondre avec le New Age, couvre un ensemble d\'organisations, de philosophes et de th\\u00E9ologiens partageant une s\\u00E9rie de croyances m\\u00E9taphysiques."@fr ,
		"The New Thought movement is a spiritual movement which developed in the United States in the 19th century, following the teachings of Phineas Quimby. The three major organizations within New Thought movement today are Religious Science, Unity Church and the Church of Divine Science, with an estimated number of some 1,500,000 adherents in the United States among them."@en ,
		"Neugeist (engl. New Thought f\\u00FCr \\u201ENeues Denken\\u201C) bezeichnet eine spirituelle Lebensphilosophie, deren Anh\\u00E4nger in der Neugeist-Bewegung verbunden sind und teils organisiert, teils unabh\\u00E4ngig voneinander deren Lehren praktizieren."@de ,
		"Il New Thought (espressione inglese per Pensiero nuovo) designa un insieme eterogeneo di organizzazioni, chiese, scrittori, filosofi e pensatori che condividono una base comune di idee circa la visione del divino e la guarigione. Il movimento ha avuto origine negli Stati Uniti nella seconda met\\u00E0 dell\'Ottocento e continua ancora oggi."@it ,
		"El Nuevo Pensamiento es una corriente filos\\u00F3fica que surgi\\u00F3 a mediados del siglo XIX en Estados Unidos. Conocido en sus inicios como Ciencia Mental a\\u00F1os m\\u00E1s tarde recibir\\u00EDa el nombre de Nuevo Pensamiento (New Thought, en ingl\\u00E9s) este movimiento creci\\u00F3 internacionaliz\\u00E1ndose y produciendo grandes escritores durante todo el siglo XX."@es ,

		"O Novo Pensamento ou Movimento Novo Pensamento \\u00E9 um movimento espiritual que eclodiu nos Estados Unidos no final do s\\u00E9culo XIX e que enfatiza cren\\u00E7as metaf\\u00EDsicas. Ele consiste de um grupo livremente formado por denomina\\u00E7\\u00F5es religiosas, organiza\\u00E7\\u00F5es seculares, autores, fil\\u00F3sofos, e indiv\\u00EDduos que compartilham um conjunto de cren\\u00E7as metaf\\u00EDsicas referentes aos efeitos do pensamento positivo, Lei da atra\\u00E7\\u00E3o, cura, for\\u00E7a vital, visualiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o criativa e poder pessoal."@pt .

	rdfs:comment	"Nihonga (\\u65E5\\u672C\\u753B, Nihonga?) o, literalmente, \\"Pinturas de estilo japon\\u00E9s\\" son pinturas que se han realizado de acuerdo con las convenciones art\\u00EDsticas tradicionales de Jap\\u00F3n, incluyendo t\\u00E9cnicas y materiales. Aunque est\\u00E1 basado en las tradiciones de m\\u00E1s de mil a\\u00F1os de antig\\u00FCedad, el t\\u00E9rmino fue acu\\u00F1ado en el periodo Meiji del Jap\\u00F3n Imperial, para distinguir obras de estilo occidental, cuadros, o Y\\u014Dga (\\u6D0B\\u753B, Y\\u014Dga?)."@es ,
		"Nihonga (\\u65E5\\u672C\\u753B, Nihonga) or literally \\"Japanese-style paintings\\" are paintings that have been made in accordance with traditional Japanese artistic conventions, techniques and materials. While based on traditions over a thousand years old, the term was coined in the Meiji period of the Imperial Japan, to distinguish such works from Western-style paintings, or Y\\u014Dga (\\u6D0B\\u753B, Y\\u014Dga)."@en ,
		"Le terme nihonga (\\u65E5\\u672C\\u753B, nihonga?), ou nihon-ga, signifie litt\\u00E9ralement peinture (ga) japonaise (nihon) ; on r\\u00E9unit sous ce nom depuis plus d\'un si\\u00E8cle des peintures faites selon les conventions, les techniques et les mat\\u00E9riaux de la peinture japonaise traditionnelle."@fr ,
		"Nihonga (jap. \\u65E5\\u672C\\u753B, dt. japanische Malerei) wurde 1890 von dem US-amerikanischen Orientalisten Ernest Fenollosa und dem japanischen Kunsthistoriker Okakura Kakuzo mit dem Ziel eingef\\u00FChrt, die traditionelle japanischer Malerei in der Zeit des Umbruchs in modernisierter Form zu erhalten."@de ,

	rdfs:comment	"The Ordre Nouveau (\'New Order) was a non-conformist political organization in the 1930s in France, created by Alexandre Marc and influenced by Robert Aron and Arnaud Dandieu\'s works. Some of its noted members included the future French leader Charles de Gaulle, Jean Coutrot, Charles Spinasse, and Henri Daniel-Rops."@en .

		"\\u0420\\u0435\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C (\\u0436\\u0438\\u0432\\u043E\\u043F\\u0438\\u0441\\u044C)"@ru ,

		"Realism (art movement)"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Realismo es la denominaci\\u00F3n de un estilo o movimiento pict\\u00F3rico que se dio en Francia a mediados del siglo XIX, cuyo principal representante es Gustave Courbet. El propio pintor fue quien acu\\u00F1\\u00F3 el t\\u00E9rmino al dar nombre al pabell\\u00F3n que hizo construir para una provocativa exposici\\u00F3n de 1855, alternativa al Sal\\u00F3n de Par\\u00EDs, bajo el t\\u00EDtulo \\"Realismo\\"."@es ,
		"Realism was an artistic movement that began in France in the 1850s, after the 1848 Revolution. Realists rejected Romanticism, which had dominated French literature and art since the late 18th century.  Realism revolted against the exotic subject matter and exaggerated emotionalism and drama of the Romantic movement. Instead it sought to portray real and typical contemporary people and situations with truth and accuracy, and not avoiding unpleasant or sordid aspects of life."@en ,
		"\\u0420\\u0435\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0301\\u0437\\u043C \\u2014 \\u044D\\u0441\\u0442\\u0435\\u0442\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043F\\u043E\\u0437\\u0438\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F, \\u0441\\u043E\\u0433\\u043B\\u0430\\u0441\\u043D\\u043E \\u043A\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0437\\u0430\\u0434\\u0430\\u0447\\u0430 \\u0438\\u0441\\u043A\\u0443\\u0441\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0430 \\u0441\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u043E\\u0438\\u0442 \\u0432 \\u043A\\u0430\\u043A \\u043C\\u043E\\u0436\\u043D\\u043E \\u0431\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0435 \\u0442\\u043E\\u0447\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0438 \\u043E\\u0431\\u044A\\u0435\\u043A\\u0442\\u0438\\u0432\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0444\\u0438\\u043A\\u0441\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u0438 \\u0434\\u0435\\u0439\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438. \\u0412 \\u0441\\u0444\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435 \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0434\\u0435\\u044F\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438 \\u0437\\u043D\\u0430\\u0447\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u0440\\u0435\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C\\u0430 \\u043E\\u0447\\u0435\\u043D\\u044C \\u0441\\u043B\\u043E\\u0436\\u043D\\u043E \\u0438 \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0442\\u0438\\u0432\\u043E\\u0440\\u0435\\u0447\\u0438\\u0432\\u043E."@ru ,
		"A pintura do Realismo come\\u00E7ou por manifestar-se no tratamento da paisagem, que se despiu da exalta\\u00E7\\u00E3o e personifica\\u00E7\\u00E3o rom\\u00E2nticas para se ater, simplesmente, na reprodu\\u00E7\\u00E3o desapaixonada e neutra, do que se oferece \\u00E0 vista do pintor. Passou, depois, aos temas do quotidiano, que tratou de forma simples e crua, sem nada acrescentar ou retirar \\u00E0 realidade."@pt ,
		"En peinture, le r\\u00E9alisme est un mouvement artistique du XIXe si\\u00E8cle apparu en France entre 1848 et la fin du si\\u00E8cle, consacr\\u00E9 \\u00E0 la soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 et plus g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement \\u00E0 une repr\\u00E9sentation fid\\u00E8le de la vie quotidienne. Son chef de file est le peintre Gustave Courbet (1819-1877) qui emploie le terme \\u00AB r\\u00E9alisme \\u00BB pour d\\u00E9signer cette peinture en 1855."@fr .

In Frankreich und England tritt die Tendenz der Empfindsamkeit bereits ab etwa 1700 auf. In der Literaturwissenschaft ist die Empfindsamkeit eine Epoche zwischen 1740 und 1790."@de ,
		"\\u0421\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0438\\u043C\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0301\\u0437\\u043C (\\u0444\\u0440. sentimentalisme, \\u043E\\u0442 \\u0444\\u0440. sentiment \\u2013 		"Sentimentalism  is the practice of being sentimental, or the tendency to base actions and reactions from emotions and feelings as opposed to reason. As a literary mode, sentimentalism has been a recurring aspect of world literature, and is important to the traditions of India, China, and Vietnam."@en ,
		"Het sentimentalisme was een literaire stroming in de preromantiek (18e eeuw), en behelsde een overdrijving van romantische gevoelens, die zich uitte in een sterke overgevoeligheid, en het zoeken naar zaken die medelijden en tranen konden opwekken. De psychologische roman is ontstaan tijdens deze periode. De term is ontleend aan het boek A Sentimental Journey Through France and Italy van de Engelse schrijver Laurence Sterne."@nl ,
		"Sentimentalismo profundo, expresi\\u00F3n de sentimientos, Sentimentalismo es una de las caracter\\u00EDsticas generales del romanticismo.Sentimentalismo (literalmente, apelaci\\u00F3n a los sentimientos), como un discurso pol\\u00EDtico y art\\u00EDstico, ha ocurrido con frecuencia en las tradiciones literarias de todas las regiones del mundo, y es un elemento central en las tradiciones de la literatura hind\\u00FA, literatura china, y literatura vietnamita (como en Ho Xuan Huong)."@es ,
		"Sentymentalizm \\u2013 kierunek umys\\u0142owy i literacki w Europie, kt\\u00F3ry trwa\\u0142 od lat 70. XVIII wieku do pocz\\u0105tku wieku XIX, by\\u0142 okresem pomi\\u0119dzy o\\u015Bwieceniem a romantyzmem. Jego tw\\u00F3rcami byli Jean Jacques Rousseau (we Francji) i Laurence Sterne (w Anglii). Nazwa nurtu pochodzi od dzie\\u0142a Laurence\'a Sterne\'a Podr\\u00F3\\u017C sentymentalna przez Francj\\u0119 i W\\u0142ochy.Sentymentali\\u015Bci w centrum zainteresowania stawiali cz\\u0142owieka i jego uczucia, skupiali si\\u0119 na indywidualizmie, wn\\u0119trzu."@pl ,
		"L\'\\u00E9poque litt\\u00E9raire de l\\u2019Empfindsamkeit (voir pi\\u00E9tisme) s\'\\u00E9tend de 1740 \\u00E0 1780. C\'est un courant en r\\u00E9action \\u00E0 l\'oppression rationnelle des sentiments exerc\\u00E9s par les Lumi\\u00E8res. Son origine est en grande partie religieuse. Les textes accompagnant les oratorios de Johann Sebastian Bach en sont des exemples repr\\u00E9sentatifs."@fr .
dbr:Suggestivism	rdfs:label	"Suggestivism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Suggestivism is a class of contemporary art that demonstrates a \\"suggestion\\". Exhibitions of Suggestivist artists have been shown since 2011 in New York, Los Angeles, and Italy. The term was first popularized by Sadakichi Hartmann and later used by curator and author Nathan Spoor."@en .
dbr:Superfiction	rdfs:label	"Superfiction"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"A Superfiction is a visual or conceptual artwork which uses fiction and appropriation to mirror organizations, business structures, and/or the lives of invented individuals (Hill). The term was coined by Glasgow-born artist Peter Hill in 1989. Often superfictions are subversive cultural events in which the artwork can be said to escape from the picture frame or in which a narrative can be said to escape from the pages of the novel into three-dimensional reality."@en .

Palisades verf\\u00FCgt \\u00FCber eine eigene Bibliothek und eine Post. Der Ortsteil besteht fast ausschlie\\u00DFlich aus Wohnbebauung,  mit Ausnahme eines kleinen Industriegebiets an der Grenze zu Tappan."@de ,
		"Palisades est un hameau de l\'\\u00C9tat de New York, aux \\u00C9tats-Unis. Ce lieu fait partie de la ville de Orangetown, au sud-est du comt\\u00E9 de Rockland. Le hameau est bord\\u00E9 par l\'Hudson River \\u00E0 l\'est."@fr ,
		"Palisades, formerly known as Sneden\'s Landing, is a hamlet in the Town of Orangetown in Rockland County, New York, United States, located north of Rockleigh and Alpine, New Jersey; east of Tappan; south of Sparkill; and west of the Hudson River.The hamlet has no mayor, nor any official legislative bodies. It does, however, have its own library, and post office with the zip code 10964 and served by the 359 exchange in Area Code 845."@en .

dbr:Crooner	rdfs:label	"Crooner"@it ,
		"Crooner"@es ,
		"\\u041A\\u0440\\u0443\\u043D\\u0435\\u0440"@ru ,
		"Crooner"@en ,
		"Crooner"@pt ,
		"Crooner"@pl ,
		"Crooner"@nl ,
		"Crooner"@fr ,
		"Crooning"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"La denominaci\\u00F3n crooner se aplica a ciertos cantantes masculinos que interpretan cierto tipo de canci\\u00F3n popular cl\\u00E1sica, un g\\u00E9nero que en Estados Unidos se conoce como traditional pop o pop standard. La palabra crooner es de origen estadounidense y en ingl\\u00E9s tiene connotaciones semejantes a trovador. Un crooner suele poseer una voz grave y normalmente se hace acompa\\u00F1ar por una orquesta o una big band."@es ,
		"Un crooner est un chanteur de vari\\u00E9t\\u00E9 am\\u00E9ricaine ou de jazz, souvent accompagn\\u00E9 d\'un orchestre ou d\'un big band. Le crooner du verbe anglais to croon qui signifie \\u00AB fredonner \\u00BB, chante surtout des ballades et reste g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement dans le registre du \\u00AB chanteur de charme \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"Crooner is an American epithet given to male singers of jazz standards, mostly from the Great American Songbook, either backed by a full orchestra, a big band or by a piano. Originally it was an ironic term denoting an emphatically sentimental, often emotional singing style made possible by the use of microphones. Some performers, such as Russ Colombo, did not accept the term: in an interview Frank Sinatra said that he did not consider himself or Bing Crosby \\"crooners\\"."@en ,
		"Crooner - rodzaj \\u015Bpiewaka, interpretuj\\u0105cego w swoisty spos\\u00F3b muzyk\\u0119 swing. Okres pomi\\u0119dzy latami 40. i latami 60. XX wieku uwa\\u017Ca si\\u0119 za er\\u0119 crooner\\u00F3w w muzyce jazzowej."@pl ,
		"Crooner \\u00E9 um ep\\u00EDteto dado a um cantor masculino de um certo estilo de can\\u00E7\\u00F5es populares, apelidado de pop tradicional. Um crooner \\u00E9 um cantor de baladas populares. O cantor \\u00E9 normalmente acompanhado por uma orquestra completa ou uma big band. Geralmente, crooners cantam e disseminam as m\\u00FAsicas populares estadunidenses.Crooner foi originalmente tido como um termo negativo, e muitas pessoas que detinham o t\\u00EDtulo, como Russ Columbo, n\\u00E3o se consideravam crooners."@pt ,
		"Il crooner \\u00E8 un cantante che interpreta canzoni melodiche in chiave confidenziale."@it ,
		"Een crooner is een zanger, meestal een man die een ontspannen en intieme houding heeft en zingt met een zachte, lage stem. Vaak zijn de teksten wat sentimenteel. De term is Engels, en wordt ook gebruikt in \\"her crooning soon put the child to sleep\\" wat vertaald kan worden met \\"door haar zachte zingen viel het kind snel in slaap\\".Deze manier van zingen werd mogelijk met de uitvinding van de microfoon. Voor die tijd moest een zanger namelijk ver reiken met zijn stem."@nl ,

		"Crooning beschreibt einen in den 1920er Jahren mit der Entwicklung des Mikrofons entstandenen Gesangsstil der popul\\u00E4ren Musik, dessen vorwiegend m\\u00E4nnliche Repr\\u00E4sentanten als Crooner bezeichnet werden. 		"COBRA (or CoBrA) was a European avant-garde movement active from 1948 to 1951. The name was coined in 1948 by Christian Dotremont from the initials of the members\' home cities: Copenhagen (Co), Brussels (Br), Amsterdam (A)."@en ,
		"CO.BR.A \\u00E8 stato un movimento artistico d\'avanguardia europeo attivo dal 1948 sino al 1951."@it ,
		"De Cobragroep (1948-1951) was van 1948 tot 1951 een avant-gardebeweging van kunstenaars uit Denemarken, Belgi\\u00EB en Nederland. De beweging werd op 8 november 1948 opgericht in het Caf\\u00E9 Notre-Dame in Parijs. De naam CoBrA is een acroniem van de hoofdsteden waar de oprichtende leden vandaan komen: Copenhague, Bruxelles en Amsterdam. Dit op z\\u2019n Frans, want Frans was de voertaal van de beweging."@nl ,
		"CoBrA (auch Cobra oder COBRA) war eine von 1948 bis 1951 bestehende internationale K\\u00FCnstlergruppe."@de ,
		"Cobra (graphie CoBrA) ou l\\u2019Internationale des artistes exp\\u00E9rimentaux (IAE) est un mouvement artistique cr\\u00E9\\u00E9 \\u00E0 Paris le 8 novembre 1948 au caf\\u00E9 de l\'h\\u00F4tel Notre-Dame par les po\\u00E8tes Christian Dotremont, Joseph Noiret et les peintres Karel Appel, Constant, Corneille, et Asger Jorn, en r\\u00E9action \\u00E0 la querelle entre l\'abstraction et la figuration. Ce mouvement publie la revue Cobra (1948-1951) avant de se dissoudre en 1951."@fr ,
		"O grupo COBRA foi um movimento art\\u00EDstico da vanguarda europeia, criada na Europa em 8 de novembro de 1948, influenciado pela arte popular n\\u00F3rdica, expressionismo e surrealismo, atuante entre 1948 e 1951, embora reconhecido internacionalmente, principalmente nos Estados Unidos e na Europa na d\\u00E9cada de 1960."@pt ,
		"Cobra \\u2013 mi\\u0119dzynarodowa awangardowa grupa artystyczna za\\u0142o\\u017Cona w Pary\\u017Cu w roku 1948 podczas Mi\\u0119dzynarodowej Konferencji na temat Dokumentacji Sztuki Awangardy. Dzia\\u0142a\\u0142a g\\u0142\\u00F3wnie w Brukseli do roku 1950. Nale\\u017Celi do niej malarze, pisarze i poeci z Danii, Belgii i Holandii. Nazwa zosta\\u0142a utworzona z pierwszych liter nazw stolic w\\u0142a\\u015Bnie tych pa\\u0144stw: COpenhaga, BRuksela i Amsterdam. Grupa wydawa\\u0142a czasopismo \\"Cobra\\". Powstanie grupy zainicjowa\\u0142 du\\u0144czyk Asger Jorn."@pl ,
		"El Grupo \\u00ABCobra\\u00BB o CoBrA es un movimiento art\\u00EDstico fundado en Par\\u00EDs en 1948 y disuelto en 1951, debido a las disensiones y rivalidades internas as\\u00ED como por la mala salud de sus miembros Asger Jorn y Christian Dotremont. El nombre es el acr\\u00F3nimo de \\u00ABCopenhague, Bruselas, \\u00C1msterdam\\u00BB, ciudades de origen de los fundadores del movimiento."@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"De Stijl is een Nederlandse kunstbeweging, vernoemd naar het in 1917 in Leiden opgerichte tijdschrift De Stijl. De belangrijkste leden van De Stijl waren Theo van Doesburg, Piet Mondriaan, Vilmos Husz\\u00E1r, Bart van der Leck, J.J.P. Oud, Jan Wils, Robert van \'t Hoff, Gerrit Rietveld en Georges Vantongerloo. De Stijl is vooral een project van kunstenaar en publicist Theo van Doesburg, de zelfbenoemde oprichter, redacteur en propagandist van De Stijl."@nl ,
		"\\u062F\\u064A \\u0633\\u062A\\u0627\\u064A\\u0644 (\\u0628\\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u064A\\u0629: De Stijl \\u061B \\u0628\\u0627\\u0644\\u0625\\u0646\\u062C\\u0644\\u064A\\u0632\\u064A\\u0629 : The Style) \\u0623\\u064A\\u0636\\u0627 \\u062A\\u0639\\u0631\\u0641 \\u0628 \\"Neoplasticism\\" \\u0645\\u062F\\u0631\\u0633\\u0629 \\u0641\\u0646\\u064A\\u0629 \\u062A\\u0623\\u0633\\u0633\\u062A \\u0641\\u064A \\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u0627 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0639\\u0627\\u0645 1917. \\u0645\\u0635\\u0637\\u0644\\u062D De Stijl \\u064A\\u0634\\u064A\\u0631 \\u0628\\u0634\\u0643\\u0644 \\u0636\\u064A\\u0642 \\u0625\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0639\\u0645\\u0627\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u064A \\u0638\\u0647\\u0631\\u062A \\u0645\\u0627 \\u0628\\u064A\\u0646 1917 - 1931 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u064A \\u0634\\u064F\\u064A\\u062F\\u062A \\u0641\\u064A \\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u0627. 		"De Stijl (Aussprache [d\\u0259 \\u02C8st\\u025B\\u026Al]) war eine niederl\\u00E4ndische Gruppe von Malern, Architekten und Designern, die 1917 in Leiden eine K\\u00FCnstlervereinigung und eine Zeitschrift gleichen Namens gr\\u00FCndete. Gr\\u00FCndungsmitglieder waren der Maler und Kunsttheoretiker Theo van Doesburg, die Maler Piet Mondrian und Georges Vantongerloo, die Architekten Robert van\'t Hoff, J. J. P. Oud und Jan Wils, die Maler Vilmos Husz\\u00E1r und Bart van der Leck, sowie der Dichter Antony Kok."@de ,
		"De Stijl (po niderlandzku styl) \\u2013 kierunek w sztuce rozwijaj\\u0105cy si\\u0119 w latach 20. XX wieku. Znany jest tak\\u017Ce pod nazw\\u0105 neoplastycyzm.Tw\\u00F3rc\\u0105 nazwy \\u201Eneoplastycyzm\\u201D jest Piet Mondrian, kt\\u00F3ry zafascynowany mistykiem \\u2013 Schoenmaekersem stworzy\\u0142 kierunek naznaczony pozytywn\\u0105 mistyk\\u0105. Tajemne dzia\\u0142anie \\u015Bwiata polega\\u0142o na zasadzie przeciwie\\u0144stw. Si\\u0142y aktywnej \\u2013 biernej, pion\\u00F3w \\u2013 poziom\\u00F3w."@pl ,
		"De Stijl (prononcer [d\\u0259.\'st\\u025Bil], en n\\u00E9erlandais \\u00AB le style \\u00BB) fut tout d\'abord une revue d\'arts plastiques et d\'architecture, publi\\u00E9e de 1917 \\u00E0 1928, sous l\'impulsion de  Theo van Doesburg et avec la participation active de Piet Mondrian."@fr ,
		"A revista \\"De Stijl\\" foi uma publica\\u00E7\\u00E3o iniciada em 1917 por Theo van Doesburg e alguns colegas que viriam a compor o movimento art\\u00EDstico conhecido por Neoplasticismo, movimento est\\u00E9tico que teve profunda influ\\u00EAncia sobre o design, artes pl\\u00E1sticas e sobre a poesia.Devido \\u00E0 influ\\u00EAncia dos textos da revista, que muitas vezes assumiam um aspecto de manifesto, o pr\\u00F3prio movimento neopl\\u00E1stico (e mais tarde, o Elementarismo) \\u00E9 confundido com o nome da revista."@pt ,
		"De Stijl (El Estilo, pronunciado [d\\u0259 \\u02C8st\\u025B\\u026Al]) era un movimiento art\\u00EDstico cuyo objetivo era la integraci\\u00F3n de las artes o el arte total, y se manifestaban a trav\\u00E9s de una revista del mismo nombre que se edit\\u00F3 hasta 1931. Constituido en Leiden, Holanda en 1917, pertenec\\u00EDan a este movimiento Vilmos Husz\\u00E1r, Cornelis Van Eesteren, Antony Kok, Piet Mondrian, Bart van der Leck, Gerrit Rietveld, Jacobus Johannes Pieter Oud y Theo van Doesburg."@es ,
		"De Stijl (/d\\u0259 \\u02C8sta\\u026Al/; Dutch pronunciation: [d\\u0259 \\u02C8st\\u025Bil]), Dutch for \\"The Style\\", also known as neoplasticism, was a Dutch artistic movement founded in 1917 in Amsterdam."@en ,
		"De Stijl (che in olandese significa Lo stile), anche conosciuto con il nome di Neoplasticismo (in olandese: Nieuwe Beeldende), \\u00E8 un movimento artistico fondato nei Paesi Bassi nel 1917.Il termine neoplasticismo \\u00E8 comparso per la prima volta nell\'ottobre del 1917 con la pubblicazione del primo numero della rivista De Stijl fondata da Theo van Doesburg."@it .

	rdfs:comment	"German idealism was a speculative philosophical movement that emerged in Germany in the late 18th and early 19th centuries. It was a reaction from Immanuel Kant\'s Critique of Pure Reason and was closely linked with both Romanticism and the revolutionary politics of the Enlightenment."@en ,
		"L\'Idealismo tedesco \\u00E8 una corrente filosofica sviluppatasi in Germania tra la fine del XVIII secolo e l\'inizio del XIX.I pi\\u00F9 celebri esponenti dell\'Idealismo tedesco sono, in ordine cronologico: Johann Gottlieb Fichte, Friedrich Schelling e Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel. Altri pensatori della corrente sono considerati Friedrich Heinrich Jacobi, Karl Leonhard Reinhold, e Friedrich Schleiermacher."@it ,
		"L\'id\\u00E9alisme allemand est le nom g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rique que l\'on a donn\\u00E9 \\u00E0 un ensemble de philosophies d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9es en Allemagne \\u00E0 la fin du XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle et au d\\u00E9but du XIXe si\\u00E8cle. Il commencerait avec Kant et la Critique de la raison pure, conna\\u00EEtrait un premier apog\\u00E9e avec la Doctrine de la science de Fichte, un seconde avec l\'Encyclop\\u00E9die des sciences philosophiques de Hegel, et s\'ach\\u00E8verait avec la Sp\\u00E4tphilosophie (philosophie \\"tardive\\") de Friedrich Schelling."@fr ,
		"Het Duitse idealisme is een filosofische stroming uit de geschiedenis van de moderne filosofie. De stroming is ontstaan in Duitsland in de late 18e en vroege 19e eeuw. Het Duitse idealisme is nauw verbonden met de Romantiek en met de revolutionaire idee\\u00EBn van de Verlichting en vindt zijn oorsprong in het werk van Immanuel Kant. Ze kwam echter pas tot haar bekende vorm in het werk van Fichte, Schelling en Hegel."@nl ,

		"El Idealismo alem\\u00E1n es una escuela filos\\u00F3fica que se desarroll\\u00F3 en Alemania a finales del siglo XVIII y comienzos del siglo XIX. Surgi\\u00F3 a partir de la obra de Immanuel Kant en los a\\u00F1os 1780 y 1790, vinculado estrechamente con el Romanticismo, la Ilustraci\\u00F3n y el contexto hist\\u00F3rico de la Revoluci\\u00F3n francesa y las posteriores Guerras Napole\\u00F3nicas. Los principales pensadores del movimiento fueron, adem\\u00E1s del propio Kant; Fichte, Schelling y Hegel."@es ,
		"O idealismo alem\\u00E3o foi (e em parte ainda \\u00E9) uma das orienta\\u00E7\\u00F5es filos\\u00F3ficas mais influentes da hist\\u00F3ria. Tem ra\\u00EDzes na hist\\u00F3ria da cultura alem\\u00E3. Mas nem por isso pode ser considerado um fen\\u00F4meno por assim dizer \\u201Cnacional\\u201D."@pt ,
		"Idealizm niemiecki \\u2013 filozofia nowo\\u017Cytna rozwijaj\\u0105ca si\\u0119 w XIX wieku w Niemczech, jej g\\u0142\\u00F3wnymi przedstawicielami byli Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel, Johann Gottlieb Fichte i Friedrich Wilhelm Joseph Schelling. Istot\\u0105 idealizmu niemieckiego (i idealizmu w og\\u00F3le) by\\u0142o za\\u0142o\\u017Cenie, \\u017Ce my\\u015Bl jest pierwotna w stosunku do bytu. G\\u0142\\u00F3wne cechy wyr\\u00F3\\u017Cniaj\\u0105ce filozof\\u00F3w niemieckich to zupe\\u0142ny brak zmys\\u0142u czynnika empirycznego wiedzy, brak realizmu i maksymalizm humanistyczny."@pl ,
		"\\u30C9\\u30A4\\u30C4\\u89B3\\u5FF5\\u8AD6\\uFF08\\u30C9\\u30A4\\u30C4\\u304B\\u3093\\u306D\\u3093\\u308D\\u3093\\u3001\\u30C9\\u30A4\\u30C4\\u8A9E: der deutsche Idealismus\\uFF09\\u306F18\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u672B\\u304B\\u308919\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u534A\\u3070\\u306B\\u30C9\\u30A4\\u30C4\\u306E\\u4E3B\\u306B\\u30EB\\u30BF\\u30FC\\u6D3E\\u5730\\u57DF\\u306B\\u304A\\u3044\\u3066\\u5C55\\u958B\\u3055\\u308C\\u305F\\u54F2\\u5B66\\u601D\\u60F3\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Als Deutscher Idealismus wird die Epoche der deutschen Philosophie von Kant bis zu Hegel und zum Sp\\u00E4twerk Schellings bezeichnet. Als zeitliche Rahmendaten gelten meist das Erscheinen von Kants Kritik der reinen Vernunft (1781) und der Tod Hegels (1831). Der Deutsche Idealismus gilt vielfach als Bl\\u00FCtezeit der deutschen Philosophie und wird hinsichtlich seiner philosophiegeschichtlichen Bedeutung mit der klassischen griechischen Philosophie verglichen."@de .

		"El g\\u00F3tico internacional es un estilo dentro del arte g\\u00F3tico que se desarroll\\u00F3 en Borgo\\u00F1a, Bohemia y el norte de Italia a finales del siglo XIV y principios del XV.Fue en este periodo cuando los artistas viajaron ampliamente por el continente, creando una est\\u00E9tica com\\u00FAn entre la realeza y la nobleza y eliminando as\\u00ED el concepto de un arte \\"extranjero\\". Las principales influencias estuvieron en el norte de Francia, los Pa\\u00EDses Bajos e Italia."@es ,
		"De internationale gotiek was een kunstuiting in de schilder- en beeldhouwkunst uit de bredere periode van de gotiek, die zich ontwikkelde aan het eind van de 14e en het begin van de 15e eeuw in onder meer Bourgondi\\u00EB, Bohemen, Frankrijk en Itali\\u00EB. 		"Le gothique international (ou style international, ou art europ\\u00E9en vers 1400) est une phase tardive de l\'art gothique qui s\'est simultan\\u00E9ment d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9e sur les terres franco-flamandes, en Bourgogne, en Boh\\u00EAme et dans le nord de l\'Italie entre la fin du XIVe si\\u00E8cle et le d\\u00E9but du XVe si\\u00E8cle avant de se propager largement \\u00E0 travers l\'ensemble de l\'Europe occidentale et centrale, justifiant ainsi le nom donn\\u00E9 \\u00E0 cette p\\u00E9riode par l\'historien d\'art fran\\u00E7ais Louis Courajod \\u00E0 la fin du XIXe si\\u00E8cle.Ce style, nomm\\u00E9 \\u00AB weicher Stil \\u00BB, ou \\u00AB style doux \\u00BB en allemand, et influenc\\u00E9 par l\'esprit courtois dont t\\u00E9moigne \\u00E9galement la litt\\u00E9rature, est marqu\\u00E9 par une recherche nouvelle de l\'\\u00E9l\\u00E9gance pr\\u00E9cieuse, et se traduit par l\'emploi de tons plus vifs, jouant volontiers sur des appariements de couleurs primaires, par un affinement des repr\\u00E9sentations humaines corrigeant les formes plus statiques et hi\\u00E9ratiques du gothique, par une plus grande attention aux d\\u00E9tails \\u2014 par exemple des \\u00E9toffes et des drap\\u00E9s \\u2014 et \\u00E0 l\'observation de la nature \\u2014 notamment des v\\u00E9g\\u00E9taux et des animaux. "@fr ,

		"L\'Art postal (Mail Art en anglais) est un moyen de communication, une correspondance artistique qui utilise les services de la poste: c\'est l\'art d\'envoyer des lettres d\\u00E9cor\\u00E9es. La lettre et l\\u2019enveloppe deviennent ainsi un support d\'expression artistique. Les courriers de Mail Art adressent donc un message tout autant par le texte que par l\'image. Il ne faut pas confondre le mail art avec l\'art postal."@fr ,
		"La mail art (o arte postale) \\u00E8 una forma artistica che usa il servizio postale come mezzo e crea un feed-back tra mittente e destinatario: si risponde in maniera artistica ad un inoltro artistico \\u2013 senza questo feed-back non esiste l\'arte postale.\\u00C8 uno dei pi\\u00F9 longevi movimenti artistici della storia."@it ,
		"Mail art (also known as Postal art and Correspondence art) is a populist artistic movement centered on sending small scale works through the postal service.  It initially developed out of the Fluxus movement in the 1950s and 60s, though it has since developed into a global movement that continues to the present."@en .

		"Neoromantiek is een synoniem van postromanticisme of laat romanticisme. Het is een langdurige beweging die begint aan het einde van de negentiende eeuw en het is een herleving van de romantiek in de kunst en de literatuur.Het is een reactie gebleken op het naturalisme. De naturalist in de kunst gaat uit van externe observatie, de neoromanticist voegt gevoelens en interne observatie aan zijn werk toe. Deze kunstenaars putten hun inspiratie uit werken van kunstenaars uit de tijd van de romantiek."@nl ,
		"O termo neorromantismo \\u00E9 utilizado para definir uma variedade de movimentos na filosofia, literatura, m\\u00FAsica, pintura e arquitetura, assim como movimentos sociais que existem depois e incorporam elementos da era do Romantismo. Tem sido usado como refer\\u00EAncia a compositores do final do s\\u00E9culo XIX e come\\u00E7o do s\\u00E9culo XX, tal como Richard Wagner particularmente por Carl Dahlhaus que descreve como \\"um florescimento tardio do romantismo numa \\u00E9poca positivista\\"."@pt ,
		"The term neo-romanticism is used to cover a variety of movements in philosophy, literature, music, painting, and architecture, as well as social movements, that exist after and incorporate elements from the era of Romanticism. It has been used with reference to late-19th-century composers such as Richard Wagner particularly by Carl Dahlhaus who describes his music as \\"a late flowering of romanticism in a positivist age\\"."@en ,
		"Le N\\u00E9oromantisme est un mouvement artistique (litt\\u00E9rature, peinture, musique\\u2026) n\\u00E9 \\u00E0 la fin du XIXe si\\u00E8cle en r\\u00E9action au naturalisme et au modernisme et cherchant \\u00E0 mettre l\'accent sur les sentiments et la vie int\\u00E9rieure."@fr ,

		"Neuromantik oder Neoromantik (\\u201Eliterarischer Jugendstil\\u201C) ist die Bezeichnung f\\u00FCr eine literarische Str\\u00F6mung um 1890\\u20131915, die sich als Gegenbewegung zum Naturalismus und der Moderne verstand und an die Inhalte der Romantik ankn\\u00FCpfte.Die neuromantischen Dichter zeigten Vorliebe f\\u00FCr exotische Schaupl\\u00E4tze (Mittelalter, Italien der Renaissance), f\\u00FCr Wunderbares und Geheimnisvoll-Magisches, f\\u00FCr das Skurrile, f\\u00FCr Sagen, Mythen und M\\u00E4rchen; sie schufen vor allem in der Lyrik Texte von gro\\u00DFer Formvollendung und verfeinerter Sprache.Anregungen empfing die Neuromantik von Symbolismus und Dekadenzdichtung; enge Ber\\u00FChrungspunkte gab es mit dem  Impressionismus und der Dichtung des Fin de si\\u00E8cle sowie mit dem Jugendstil, der von der Neuromantik wesentlich beeinflusst wurde.Bedeutende Vertreter der Neuromantik waren: der George-Kreis die Wiener Moderne Herbert Eulenberg Ernst Hardt Gerhart Hauptmann (u. "@de ,
		"El neorromanticismo fue un movimiento art\\u00EDstico desarrollado en Francia en los a\\u00F1os 1920-1930 y posteriormente en Gran Breta\\u00F1a entre 1930-1950. El primer grupo de artistas neorrom\\u00E1nticos surgi\\u00F3 en Par\\u00EDs de la mano de Christian B\\u00E9rard y los emigrantes rusos Pavel Tchelitchew y los hermanos Eug\\u00E8ne y Leonid Berman."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"O neo\\u00EDsmo (Do grego neo = \\"novo\\") \\u00E9 o conceito art\\u00EDsticonascido da necessidade de ponderar e afetar n\\u00E3o somente o meio em que se vive mas o livre fluxo de intera\\u00E7\\u00F5es do ser humano para com o mundo em que vive e do pr\\u00F3prio mundo para com o ser humano e todas as formas de vida e coabita\\u00E7\\u00E3o individuais, cabendo a este estabelecer suas prioridades, periodicidades e reciprocidades."@pt ,
		"Neoismus ist ein parodistischer -ismus. Er ist der Name eines subkulturellen Netzwerks k\\u00FCnstlerischer Aktionisten und Medienexperimentatoren und steht, in allgemeinerem Sinne, auch f\\u00FCr eine praktische Underground-Philosophie. Neoismus arbeitet mit kollektiven Pseudonymen und Identit\\u00E4ten, Streichen und Irritationen, Paradoxen, Plagiaten und F\\u00E4lschungen. Er hat zahlreiche widerspr\\u00FCchliche Definitionen seiner selbst gepr\\u00E4gt, um sich jeder Einordnung und Historisierung zu entziehen."@de ,
		"Neoism is a parodistic -ism. It refers both to a specific subcultural network of artistic performance and media experimentalists, and more generally to a practical underground philosophy. It operates with collectively shared pseudonyms and identities, pranks, paradoxes, plagiarism and fakes, and has created multiple contradicting definitions of itself in order to defy categorization and historization."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Il paleoconservatorismo (talvolta abbreviato in paleo o paleocon) \\u00E8 una corrente del conservatorismo americano di orientamento culturale e politico conservatore Old Right che si erge contro la tradizione mainstream della rivista National Review dei neocon specialmente nelle tematiche riguardanti l\'immigrazione, il sostegno economico americano alle azioni militari di Israele, interventismo militare nella politica estera e stato sociale.Sono anche fortemente critici verso la socialdemocrazia a causa delle politiche stataliste derivanti.Sono sostenitori del decentralismo in un quadro di nazionalismo e sono strenui difensori dei diritti dei singoli Stati sul Governo federale a Washington.Nella maggioranza dei casi si oppongono al libero mercato , criticano l\'immigrazione e tendono ad abbracciare una politica isolazionista.Il paleoconservatore contemporaneo pi\\u00F9 noto \\u00E8 probabilmente il commentatore Patrick Buchanan.Le riviste principali paleoconservatrici sono il Chronicles Magazine e The American Conservative."@it ,
		"Le pal\\u00E9o-conservatisme est un terme de la politique int\\u00E9rieure des \\u00C9tats-Unis d\'Am\\u00E9rique d\\u00E9signant les partisans d\'une ligne conservatrice traditionnelle ax\\u00E9e autour du protectionnisme \\u00E9conomique, de l\'anti-communisme, de l\'isolationnisme, d\'une interpr\\u00E9tation stricte du f\\u00E9d\\u00E9ralisme et des valeurs familiales traditionnelles."@fr ,
		"Paleoconservatism (sometimes shortened to paleocon) is a conservative political philosophy found primarily in the United States stressing tradition, limited government and civil society, along with religious, regional, national and Western identity.Paleoconservatives in the 21st century often highlight their points of disagreement with neoconservatives, especially regarding issues such as military interventionism, illegal immigration and high rates of legal immigration, as well as multiculturalism, affirmative action, free trade, and foreign aid. "@en ,
		"Paleokonserwatyzm \\u2013 nazwa tradycyjnego nurtu ameryka\\u0144skiej my\\u015Bli konserwatywnej, stoj\\u0105cego w opozycji do neokonserwatyzmu. Paleokonserwaty\\u015Bci pozostaj\\u0105 krytyczni wobec wsp\\u00F3\\u0142czesnego kszta\\u0142tu demokracji liberalnej, postuluj\\u0105c odrodzenie klasycznych cn\\u00F3t obywatelskich i zachowanie systemu wzajemnej kontroli i r\\u00F3wnowagi w\\u0142adzy ustawodawczej, wykonawczej i s\\u0105downiczej (checks and balances)."@pl ,
		"Pal\\u00E4okonservatismus (aus dem englischen Paleoconservatism) ist eine Str\\u00F6mung der konservativen politischen Philosophie; ihre Vertreter findet man haupts\\u00E4chlich in den USA. Die Pal\\u00E4okonservativen haben Wurzeln in der Alten Rechten (Old Right), welche in den 1930er und 1940er Jahren gegen den New Deal opponierte."@de ,
		"El paleoconservadurismo (a veces abreviado a paleo o paleocon cuando el contexto es claro) es un t\\u00E9rmino que define una filosof\\u00EDa pol\\u00EDtica conservadora establecida principalmente en los Estados Unidos. El paleoconservadurismo se caracteriza por su defensa de la tradici\\u00F3n, el gobierno limitado, una sociedad civil fuerte, el anticolonialismo, anticorporativismo y el antifederalismo. Esta filosof\\u00EDa pol\\u00EDtica defiende tambi\\u00E9n la identidad religiosa, local o regional, nacional y occidental."@es ,
		"Paleoconservatisme (Gr. \\u03C0\\u03B1\\u03BB\\u03B1\\u03B9\\u03CC\\u03C2 palaios, \\"oud\\") is een traditionalistische stroming binnen het Amerikaanse conservatisme. Het paleoconservatisme staat tegenover de nieuwe conservatieve stromingen binnen de Amerikaanse samenleving, zoals het neoconservatisme.De hoofdlijnen van de opvattingen van het paleoconservatisme zijn een isolationistisch beleid van de Amerikaanse overheid en geen (militaire) interventie in zaken die zich buiten Amerika afspelen."@nl .

El canto coral y el ballet son algunos ejemplos. Por lo general, los artistas participan en ensayos para su preparaci\\u00F3n."@es ,
		"Der Ausdruck Auff\\u00FChrung bezeichnet in der darstellenden Kunst die Darbietung eines B\\u00FChnenwerkes oder Konzerts vor einem Publikum. Anders als eine Darstellung, die in der Regel ein Werk der bildenden Kunst gleichsam statisch f\\u00FCr eine bestimmte Zeitdauer pr\\u00E4sentiert, bildet die Auff\\u00FChrung ein momentanes, dynamisches k\\u00FCnstlerisches Geschehen, das allein in unmittelbarer Pr\\u00E4senz (bzw. als Aufzeichnung) erfahren werden kann."@de ,
		"A performance, in the performing arts, generally comprises an event in which a performer or group of performers present one or more works of art to an audience.  Usually the performers participate in rehearsals beforehand. Afterwards audience members often applaud. After a performance, performance measurement sometimes occurs."@en ,

		"V\\u00E9ase Retrato pict\\u00F3rico para saber m\\u00E1s sobre el tema de los retratos.Un retrato (del lat\\u00EDn retractus) es una pintura o efigie principalmente de una persona. Tambi\\u00E9n se entiende por retrato la descripci\\u00F3n de la figura o car\\u00E1cter, o sea, de las cualidades f\\u00EDsicas o morales de una persona.Por lo tanto, la primera definici\\u00F3n de retrato es aquella que se refiere a la expresi\\u00F3n pl\\u00E1stica de una persona a imitaci\\u00F3n de la misma, lo que ocurre en la pintura, la escultura y la fotograf\\u00EDa."@es ,
		"Un portrait est une \\u0153uvre d\'art picturale, graphique, sculpturale, musicale, photographique, cin\\u00E9matographique ou litt\\u00E9raire repr\\u00E9sentant g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement une personne r\\u00E9elle ou un groupe. En tant qu\'\\u0153uvre d\'art, le portrait a connu des \\u00E9volutions, aussi bien dans les techniques et styles que dans son usage, \\u00E0 des fins de repr\\u00E9sentation officielle ou d\'agr\\u00E9ment."@fr ,
		"Een portret is een artistieke voorstelling van een persoon of een groep. Dit kan bijvoorbeeld een schilderij, een foto of een gebeeldhouwde weergave van iemands hoofd of buste zijn.Portretten zijn vaak eenvoudige afbeeldingen van het gezicht zonder veel creativiteit (zoals pasfoto\'s). De opzet is te tonen hoe de persoon eruit ziet, met soms wat artistiek inzicht in zijn of haar persoonlijkheid."@nl ,
		"\\u8096\\u50CF\\uFF08\\u3057\\u3087\\u3046\\u305E\\u3046\\uFF09\\u3068\\u306F\\u3001\\u7279\\u5B9A\\u306E\\u4EBA\\u9593\\u306E\\u5916\\u89B3\\u3092\\u8868\\u73FE\\u3057\\u305F\\u7D75\\u753B\\u3084\\u5199\\u771F\\u3001\\u5F6B\\u523B\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u305D\\u308C\\u305E\\u308C\\u8096\\u50CF\\u753B\\uFF08\\u7D75\\u753B\\uFF09\\u3001\\u8096\\u50CF\\u5199\\u771F\\uFF08\\u5199\\u771F\\uFF09\\u3001\\u8096\\u50CF\\u5F6B\\u523B\\u3068\\u547C\\u3070\\u308C\\u308B\\u3002\\u8096\\u4F3C\\u6027\\uFF08\\u985E\\u4F3C\\uFF09\\u304C\\u6C42\\u3081\\u3089\\u308C\\u308B\\u5834\\u5408\\u3082\\u3042\\u308C\\u3070\\u3001\\u7406\\u60F3\\u5316\\u304C\\u6C42\\u3081\\u3089\\u308C\\u308B\\u5834\\u5408\\u3082\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u82B8\\u8853\\u7684\\u306A\\u9020\\u5F62\\u3084\\u7CBE\\u795E\\u6027\\u3092\\u793A\\u3059\\u3053\\u3068\\u3082\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Il ritratto \\u00E8 in generale ogni rappresentazione di una persona secondo le sue reali fattezze e sembianze: propriamente si riferisce a un\'opera artistica realizzata nell\'\\u00E0mbito della pittura, della scultura, del disegno, della fotografia o anche, per estensione, una descrizione letteraria di una persona.Nell\'arte il ritratto non \\u00E8 mai una mera riproduzione meccanica delle fattezze, come lo \\u00E8 invece una maschera di cera modellata su un volto o una qualsiasi impressione fotografica, ma vi entra comunque in gioco, per definirsi tale, la sensibilit\\u00E0 dell\'artista che nel processo creativo della sua opera interpreta le fattezze del modelli secondo il proprio gusto e secondo le caratteristiche e dell\'arte del tempo in cui opera. "@it ,
		"Ein Portr\\u00E4t (von franz\\u00F6sisch portrait: \\u201ABrustbild\\u2018 oder \\u201ABildnis\\u2018; im Deutschen fr\\u00FCher auch \\u201APortrait\\u2018) ist ein Gem\\u00E4lde, eine Fotografie, eine Plastik oder eine andere k\\u00FCnstlerische Darstellung einer oder mehrerer Personen. Im \\u00FCbertragenen Sinne wird auch eine schriftliche Beschreibung eines Menschen, also eine kurze Biografie, als Portr\\u00E4t bezeichnet.Die Absicht eines Portr\\u00E4ts ist es, neben der Darstellung k\\u00F6rperlicher \\u00C4hnlichkeit auch das Wesen bzw."@de ,

		"A portrait is a painting, photograph, sculpture, or other artistic representation of a person, in which the face and its expression is predominant. The intent is to display the likeness, personality, and even the mood of the person. For this reason, in photography a portrait is generally not a snapshot, but a composed image of a person in a still position."@en ,
		"Um retrato \\u00E9 uma pintura, fotografia ou outra representa\\u00E7\\u00E3o art\\u00EDstica de uma pessoa. O mais famoso exemplo de um retrato \\u00E9 a La Gioconda de Leonardo da Vinci.Os fot\\u00F3grafos aprenderam com os artistas pl\\u00E1sticos, a famosa regra dos ter\\u00E7os, assim como os cineastas e a televis\\u00E3o.No retrato cl\\u00E1ssico, a regra dos ter\\u00E7os diz que os olhos da pessoa fotografada devem estar a altura de um ter\\u00E7o superior, assim como a linha do horizonte na paisagem."@pt .

dbr:Afrocentrism	rdfs:label	"Afrocentrisme"@nl ,
		"Afrocentrism"@en ,
		"Afrocentrismo"@pt ,
		"Afrocentrisme"@fr ,
		"Afrocentrismo"@es ,
		"Afrocentrismo"@it ;
	rdfs:comment	"El afrocentrismo (tambi\\u00E9n afrocentricidad y, ocasionalmente, africentrismo) es una visi\\u00F3n de la historia del mundo que enfatiza la importancia de los africanos, tom\\u00E1ndolos como un solo grupo y a menudo transform\\u00E1ndose en sin\\u00F3nimo de personas de raza negra, en la cultura, la filosof\\u00EDa y la historia."@es ,
		"Afrocentrism (also Afrocentricity) is a cultural ideology, worldview mostly limited to the United States and is dedicated to the history of Black people. It is a response to global (Eurocentric/Orientalist) attitudes about African people and their historical contributions and revisits their history with an African cultural and ideological focus."@en ,
		"Afrocentrisme is een wereldbeeld waarbij Afrika, Afrikanen en hun afstammelingen centraal worden geplaatst. Afrocentrisme is vooral in zwang in de academische wereld, afrocentristische onderzoekers menen dat Afrikanen een veel grotere rol in de wereldgeschiedenis hebben gespeeld dan voorheen is aangenomen."@nl ,
		"L\\u2019afrocentrismo, un esempio di etnocentrismo, si propone di distinguere i contributi di Europa ed Oriente da quelli africani nella storia e nella cultura e, pi\\u00F9 in particolare, di mettere al centro il contributo apportato dell\'Africa in opposizione alla visione eurocentrica.Per alcuni gruppi supremazisti neri, come le Black Panthers (che basano la propria ideologia sulla controversa teoria della melanina, ovvero che gli africani siano geneticamente ed evolutivamente superiori ad asiatici, europei ed amerindi), il termine assume connotati razzisti verso le altre culture ed etnie."@it ,
		"L\'afrocentrisme  est un paradigme cherchant \\u00E0 mettre en avant l\'identit\\u00E9 particuli\\u00E8re et les apports des cultures africaines \\u00E0 l\'histoire mondiale. Les afrocentristes soutiennent que la communaut\\u00E9 scientifique occidentale sous-estime les civilisations africaines, voire serait partie prenante, consciemment ou non, d\'un complot visant \\u00E0 masquer les apports africains \\u00E0 l\'histoire."@fr ,
		"Afrocentrismo \\u00E9 uma ideologia cultural, existente principalmente nos Estados Unidos e dedicada ao estudo da hist\\u00F3ria africana. Sua principal finalidade \\u00E9 buscar a auto-determina\\u00E7\\u00E3o e uma ideologia pan-africana na cultura, filosofia e hist\\u00F3ria."@pt .

dbr:Beaver_Hall_Group	rdfs:label	"Beaver Hall Group"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Beaver Hall Group refers to a Montreal based assemblage of Canadian female painters who met in the late 1910s while studying art at a school run by the Art Association of Montreal and continued their informal association into the early 1960s.Artistically, they painted a variety of subjects, including portraits, landscapes, urban scenes and still lifes, in a combination of Modernist and traditional styles."@en .

		"DIY (\\u0441\\u0443\\u0431\\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u0430)"@ru ;
	rdfs:comment	"DIY \\u00E9 uma abrevia\\u00E7\\u00E3o de Do It Yourself (do ingl\\u00EAs fa\\u00E7a voc\\u00EA mesmo), que traduz um esp\\u00EDrito anti-ideol\\u00F3gico que teria surgido com a cena punk, p\\u00F3s-punk e movimentos underground, revelando ambos os conceitos de Monarquia como a causa Punk/Pos-Punk ingl\\u00EAs, em paralelo ao idealismo pr\\u00E9-revolucion\\u00E1rio Anarquista dos Anarco-punks, que se difundiam na midia materialista (consumista) a nivel mundial.Basicamente \\u00E9 uma sigla usada para denotar que determinada banda faz todo o trabalho pelas suas pr\\u00F3prias m\\u00E3os, ou seja, tudo desde a organiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o de concertos, grava\\u00E7\\u00E3o e produ\\u00E7\\u00E3o dos \\u00E1lbuns, produ\\u00E7\\u00E3o e venda de merchandise, marketing, publicidade, etc... "@pt ,
		"Il DIY (abbreviazione di Do It Yourself, equivalente dell\'italiano fai da te) \\u00E8 un\'etica nata e diffusa all\'interno della cultura punk, che propugna il rifiuto per le major della distribuzione musicale, ritenute capitaliste, espresso nello slogan DIY not EMI, e la formazione di etichette indipendenti con cui pubblicare i propri album."@it ,
		"DIY ethic refers to the ethic of self-sufficiency through completing tasks without the aid of a paid expert. Literally meaning \\"do it yourself,\\" the DIY ethic promotes the idea that anyone is capable of performing a variety of tasks rather than relying on paid specialists. The DIY ethic requires that the adherent seeks out the knowledge required to complete a given task."@en ,
		"DIY (Do-It-Yourself) is de Engelse afkorting van \'doe-het-zelf\', in de gebruikelijke betekenis van doe-het-zelfwinkel, etc. Het is daarnaast een houding waarbij mensen de uitgave van muziek zelf in de hand nemen in plaats van het aan \'experts\' (zoals grote bedrijven) over te laten.Voorbeelden van DIY-culturen zijn de indiescene en de punk- en hardcorescene, waar veel platen worden uitgebracht op kleine onafhankelijke labels of in eigen beheer."@nl ,

		"\\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0635\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0630\\u0647\\u0628\\u064A \\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u064A (\\u0628\\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u064A\\u0629: Gouden Eeuw) \\u0643\\u0627\\u0646\\u062A \\u0641\\u062A\\u0631\\u0629 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u0627\\u0631\\u064A\\u062E \\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u064A\\u060C \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u064A \\u0627\\u0645\\u062A\\u062F\\u062A \\u0637\\u0648\\u0627\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0631\\u0646 17\\u0645\\u060C \\u062D\\u064A\\u062B \\u062A\\u0641\\u0648\\u0642\\u062A \\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u062C\\u0627\\u0631\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0644\\u0648\\u0645 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0648\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0633\\u0643\\u0631\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0641\\u0646 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645. \\u0648\\u062A\\u0645\\u064A\\u0632 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0646\\u0635\\u0641 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u0648\\u0644 \\u0628\\u062D\\u0631\\u0628 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062B\\u0645\\u0627\\u0646\\u064A\\u0646 \\u0639\\u0627\\u0645\\u0627\\u064B \\u062D\\u062A\\u0649 1648\\u0645. \\u062B\\u0645 \\u062A\\u0645\\u062A\\u0639 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0635\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0630\\u0647\\u0628\\u064A \\u0628\\u0648\\u0642\\u062A \\u0633\\u0644\\u0645 \\u062E\\u0644\\u0627\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062C\\u0645\\u0647\\u0648\\u0631\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0646\\u062F\\u064A\\u0629 \\u062D\\u062A\\u0649 \\u0646\\u0647\\u0627\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0631\\u0646."@ar ,
		"Das Goldene Zeitalter (niederl.: de Gouden Eeuw) bezeichnet in der Geschichte der Niederlande eine rund einhundert Jahre andauernde wirtschaftliche und kulturelle Bl\\u00FCtezeit, die ungef\\u00E4hr das 17. Jahrhundert ausf\\u00FCllt und in der Kunstgeschichte ohne Beispiel ist. Auf dem H\\u00F6hepunkt des Goldenen Zeitalters um 1650 arbeiteten in den Niederlanden circa 700 Maler, die j\\u00E4hrlich etwa 70.000 Gem\\u00E4lde fertigstellten."@de ,
		"La hegemon\\u00EDa neerlandesa del siglo XVII, tambi\\u00E9n conocida como Edad de Oro neerlandesa, fue un per\\u00EDodo de la historia de los Pa\\u00EDses Bajos en que este pa\\u00EDs se transform\\u00F3 en una potencia de Europa y en el que florecieron el comercio, la ciencia y la cultura neerlandesas. Ese poder hegem\\u00F3nico se perdi\\u00F3 primero ante Francia a finales del siglo XVII y despu\\u00E9s ante Inglaterra con el Tratado de Utrecht."@es ,

De noordelijke Nederlanden, die samen de Republiek der Zeven Verenigde Nederlanden vormden, maakten een bloeiperiode door op gebied van handel, wetenschap en kunsten. 		"The Dutch Golden Age (Dutch: Gouden Eeuw [\\u02C8\\u0263\\u028Cu\\u032Fd\\u0259(n) \\u02C8e\\u02D0u\\u032F]) was a period in Dutch history, roughly spanning the 17th century, in which Dutch trade, science, military, and art were among the most acclaimed in the world. 	rdfs:comment	"Une sc\\u00E8ne de genre, en peinture, est un type d\\u2019\\u0153uvre peinte ou dessin\\u00E9e qui figure des sc\\u00E8nes \\u00E0 caract\\u00E8re anecdotique ou familier. Elle est parfois appel\\u00E9e peinture de genre.Son classement dans la hi\\u00E9rarchie des genres est assez bas, mais elle a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 port\\u00E9e \\u00E0 un point de perfection au XVIIe si\\u00E8cle par Caravage et ses suiveurs. C\\u2019est \\u00E9galement un genre tr\\u00E8s appr\\u00E9ci\\u00E9 dans les pays du nord de l\'Europe."@fr ,
		"Malarstwo rodzajowe (fr. peinture de genre) \\u2013 odr\\u0119bny gatunek malarski, kt\\u00F3ry wyr\\u00F3\\u017Cnia tematyka zwi\\u0105zana z \\u017Cyciem codziennym, obyczajami, obrz\\u0119dami, prac\\u0105, wypoczynkiem i zabaw\\u0105."@pl ,
		"La pittura di genere, che si traduce nella pratica delle scene di genere, \\u00E8 una rappresentazione pittorica che ha per soggetto scene ed eventi tratti dalla vita quotidiana; ad esempio mercati, faccende domestiche, interni o feste.La pittura di genere, rappresentando aspetti della vita di tutti i giorni, fu a lungo considerata un genere \\"minore\\", decisamente inferiore per valore alla pittura storico-religiosa, ma nemmeno al pari della ritrattistica."@it ,
		"Een genrestuk of genretafereel is een begrip uit de Europese en Amerikaanse schilderkunst en duidt op een schilderij met een voorstelling uit het dagelijkse leven of uit de alledaagse omgeving. Genre als erkend schilderkundig onderwerp ontstond pas in de 16e eeuw in Brabant, met de schilderijen van Pieter Bruegel de Oude. In Nederland bloeide de genrekunst in de 17e eeuw met werk van onder meer Ter Borch, De Hooch, Vermeer en vele anderen."@nl ,
		"Genre art is the pictorial representation in any of various media of scenes or events from everyday life, such as markets, domestic settings, interiors, parties, inn scenes, and street scenes. Such representations (also called genre works, genre scenes, or genre views) may be realistic, imagined, or romanticized by the artist. Some variations of the term genre art specify the medium or type of visual work, as in genre painting, genre prints, genre photographs, and so on."@en ,
		"Ein Genrebild (franz.: Tableau de genre; zu lat.: genus \\u201AArt\\u2018, \\u201AGeschlecht\\u2018; veraltet: Sittenbild; entsprechend Sittenmalerei zum Begriff Genremalerei) ist die gemalte Abbildung einer Alltagsszene \\u2013 zum Beispiel Menschengruppen, Szenen und Handlungen \\u2013 als Schilderung von Lebensformen eines Volkes und seiner landschaftlichen Umgebung.Bisweilen ist der \\u00DCbergang zur Landschaftsmalerei flie\\u00DFend, insbesondere in der Epoche der Romantik. In Spanien und Lateinamerika wird die Genremalerei des 19."@de ,
		"A pintura de g\\u00EAnero (ou g\\u00E9nero, em Portugal) desenvolveu-se a meio do florescimento do Barroco na Europa Cat\\u00F3lica (s\\u00E9culo XVII) nos Pa\\u00EDses Baixos, sobretudo nos Pa\\u00EDses Baixos do Norte (a por\\u00E7\\u00E3o que hoje corresponde \\u00E0 Holanda). Trata-se de um estilo s\\u00F3brio, realista, comprometido com a descri\\u00E7\\u00E3o de cenas rotineiras, temas da vida di\\u00E1ria como homens dedicados ao seu of\\u00EDcio, mulheres cuidando dos afazeres dom\\u00E9sticos, ou at\\u00E9 mesmo paisagens."@pt ,

		"La pintura de g\\u00E9nero o pintura costumbrista es un tipo de obra art\\u00EDstica, principalmente pict\\u00F3rica, en la que se representa a personas normales en escenas cotidianas, de la calle o de la vida privada, contempor\\u00E1neas al autor. Lo que distingue a la pintura de g\\u00E9nero es que representa escenas de la vida diaria, como los mercados, interiores, fiestas, tabernas y calles. Tales representaciones pueden ser realistas, imaginarias o embellecidas por el artista."@es ,
