		"Als Vaganten (lateinisch vagare, \\u201Aumherstreifen\\u2018, \\u201Aziellos unterwegs sein\\u2018, daher clericus vagans \\u201Eumherziehender Geistlicher\\u201C, Plural clerici vagantes), deutsch auch \\u201Efahrende Sch\\u00FCler\\u201C oder \\u201Efahrende Scholaren\\u201C oder auch Goliarden werden umherziehende Kleriker auf der Suche nach einem geistlichen oder weltlichen Amt, Studenten und allgemein gelehrte Boh\\u00E8me des 12. und 13. Jahrhunderts bezeichnet."@de ,
		"El t\\u00E9rmino goliardo se utiliz\\u00F3 durante la Edad Media para referirse a cierto tipo de cl\\u00E9rigos vagabundos y a los estudiantes pobres p\\u00EDcaros que proliferaron en Europa con el auge de la vida urbana y el surgimiento de las universidades en el siglo XIII. La mayor parte de ellos estudiaron en las universidades de Francia, Alemania, Italia e Inglaterra. No obstante, la figura del goliardo puede rastrearse hasta \\u00E9pocas muy anteriores."@es ,
		"Goliarden waren vagebonderende studenten en geestelijken in de Late Middeleeuwen."@nl ,

		"The goliards were a group of clergy who wrote bibulous, satirical Latin poetry in the 12th and 13th centuries. They were mainly clerics at or from the universities of France, Germany, Spain, Italy, and England who protested the growing contradictions within the church through song, poetry and performance, often within a structured carnivalesque setting such as the Feast of Fools."@en ,
		"\\u0412\\u0430\\u0433\\u0430\\u0301\\u043D\\u0442\\u044B (\\u043E\\u0442 \\u043B\\u0430\\u0442. vagantes \\u2014 \\u0441\\u0442\\u0440\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0443\\u044E\\u0449\\u0438\\u0435) \\u2014 \\u00AB\\u0431\\u0435\\u0434\\u043D\\u044B\\u0435 \\u043B\\u044E\\u0434\\u0438\\u00BB \\u0432 \\u0421\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u0432\\u0435\\u043A\\u0430 (XI\\u2014XIV \\u0432\\u0435\\u043A\\u0430) \\u0432 \\u0417\\u0430\\u043F\\u0430\\u0434\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0415\\u0432\\u0440\\u043E\\u043F\\u0435, \\u0441\\u043F\\u043E\\u0441\\u043E\\u0431\\u043D\\u044B\\u0435 \\u043A \\u0441\\u043E\\u0447\\u0438\\u043D\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0443 \\u0438 \\u043A \\u0438\\u0441\\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u043D\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u044E \\u043F\\u0435\\u0441\\u0435\\u043D \\u0438\\u043B\\u0438, \\u0440\\u0435\\u0436\\u0435, \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0437\\u0430\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0445 \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0438\\u0437\\u0432\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0439."@ru ,
		"Goliardos, na Idade M\\u00E9dia eram  cl\\u00E9rigos pobres, egressos das universidades. Desamparados pela Igreja, tornavam-se  itinerantes (clerici vagantes), vagabundos, de esp\\u00EDrito transgressivo e provocador. Em meados do s\\u00E9culo XIII, perambulavam pelas tavernas, portas das universidades e outros lugares p\\u00FAblicos, cantando e declamando seus poemas sat\\u00EDricos, um tanto c\\u00EDnicos, muitas vezes denunciando os abusos e a corrup\\u00E7\\u00E3o da pr\\u00F3pria Igreja, ou poemas er\\u00F3ticos, frequentemente muito ousados."@pt .

		"Le Groupe des Sept (en anglais The Group of Seven) est cr\\u00E9\\u00E9 par de jeunes artistes canadiens qui se rassemblent d\\u00E8s 1913 dans un immeuble de trois \\u00E9tages de Toronto compos\\u00E9 d\'ateliers d\'artistes : le Studio Building. Ils s\'y rencontrent entre 1911 et 1913, mais le groupe n\'est baptis\\u00E9 qu\'en mars 1920 et est officiellement reconnu le 7 mai suivant lors de leur premi\\u00E8re exposition au mus\\u00E9e des beaux-arts de l\'Ontario."@fr ,
		"The Group of Seven, also known as the Algonquin School, was a group of Canadian landscape painters from 1920 to 1933, originally consisting of Franklin Carmichael (1890\\u20131945), Lawren Harris (1885\\u20131970), A. Y. Jackson (1882\\u20131974), Frank Johnston (1888\\u20131949), Arthur Lismer (1885\\u20131969), J. E. H. MacDonald (1873\\u20131932), and Frederick Varley (1881\\u20131969). Later, A. J."@en ,
		"El Grupo de los Siete, fue un grupo de pintores canadienses, en especial paisajistas, de la d\\u00E9cada de 1920, originalmente compuesto por Franklin Carmichael, Lawren Harris, A. Y. Jackson, Frank Johnston, Arthur Lismer, J. E. H. MacDonald y Federico Varley. Tom Thomson (que muri\\u00F3 en 1917) y Emily Carr tambi\\u00E9n estaban asociados al Grupo de los Siete, aunque ninguno de los dos lleg\\u00F3 a ser miembro oficial alguna vez. El Grupo de los Siete fue famoso por sus pinturas de paisajes canadienses."@es ,

		"Naive Kunst ist eine Sammelbezeichnung f\\u00FCr k\\u00FCnstlerische Arbeiten von Autodidakten, vorwiegend in der Malerei (auch Laienmaler genannt), mit betont einfacher, unbek\\u00FCmmerter, phantasievoller Wahl der Bildmotive. Die Art der Darstellung ist ebenfalls oft einfach, beispielsweise ohne Schattenw\\u00FCrfe, mit vereinfachter Darstellung der Lebewesen und Gegenst\\u00E4nde. Die Werke stellen oft die pers\\u00F6nlichen Wunschtr\\u00E4ume der Urheber dar."@de ,
		"L\\u2019art na\\u00EFf d\\u00E9signe la mani\\u00E8re d\'aborder la peinture par les , dont l\'une des principales caract\\u00E9ristiques plastiques consiste en un style pictural figuratif ne respectant pas \\u2014 volontairement ou non \\u2014 les r\\u00E8gles de la perspective sur les dimensions, l\'intensit\\u00E9 de la couleur et la pr\\u00E9cision du dessin. Le r\\u00E9sultat, sur le plan graphique, \\u00E9voque un univers d\'enfant, d\'o\\u00F9 l\'utilisation du terme \\"na\\u00EFf\\"."@fr ,
		"Per Arte na\\u00EFf (dal francese na\\u00EFf, ossia \\"ingenuo\\") si intende un certo tipo di produzione artistica priva di legami con la realt\\u00E0 culturale e accademica della societ\\u00E0 in cui \\u00E8 prodotta."@it ,
		"Na\\u00EFeve kunst is een vorm van beeldende kunst, meestal schilderkunst, die gekarakteriseerd wordt door een na\\u00EFeve en soms kinderlijk aandoende manier waarop het onderwerp wordt uitgebeeld en de technieken worden gebruikt. De term na\\u00EFeve kunst was oorspronkelijk een neerbuigende term waarmee critici over deze stijl spraken. Tegenwoordig heeft het genre haar plek veroverd, wordt deze serieus genomen en zijn er gewoon opleidingen in te volgen."@nl ,

		"La denominaci\\u00F3n na\\u00EDf (del franc\\u00E9s na\\u00EFf, \'ingenuo\') se aplica a la corriente art\\u00EDstica caracterizada por la ingenuidad y espontaneidad, el autodidactismo de los artistas, los colores brillantes y contrastados y la perspectiva acient\\u00EDfica captada por intuici\\u00F3n. 		"Na\\u00EFve art is a classification of art that is often characterized by a childlike simplicity in its subject matter and technique. While many na\\u00EFve artists appear, from their works, to have little or no formal art training, this is often not true. The words \\"na\\u00EFve\\" and \\"primitive\\" are regarded as pejoratives and are, therefore, avoided by many."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Het picturalisme was \\u00E9\\u00E9n van de vroegste stromingen binnen de fotografie, enigszins verwant aan het impressionisme. Deze stroming kende haar hoogtepunt tussen 1890 en 1910, maar raakte daarna in verval, vooral onder invloed van het modernisme."@nl ,
		"Pictorialism is the name given to an international style and aesthetic movement that dominated photography during the later 19th and early 20th centuries. There is no standard definition of the term, but in general it refers to a style in which the photographer has somehow manipulated what would otherwise be a straightforward photograph as a means of \\"creating\\" an image rather than simply recording it."@en ,

Ziel des Stiles war es, nicht lediglich ein blo\\u00DFes, einen Augenblick in der Realit\\u00E4t festhaltendes Abbild des Motivs herzustellen, sondern eine symbolische Darstellung von Gem\\u00FCtszust\\u00E4nden oder grundlegenden Werten zu erzielen.Seine Bl\\u00FCtezeit fand der Pictorialismus zwischen dem Ende des 19."@de ,

		"Le pictorialisme est un mouvement de photographes, en vogue \\u00E0 partir de 1885 environ, qui suivit la diffusion d\'un nouveau proc\\u00E9d\\u00E9 photographique dit \\u00AB \\u00E0 plaque s\\u00E8che \\u00BB ou \\u00AB g\\u00E9latino-bromure d\'argent \\u00BB (invent\\u00E9 par Richard Leach Maddox en 1871, l\\u2019enregistrement est obtenu \\u00E0 partir d\\u2019une suspension de bromure d\'argent dans de la g\\u00E9latine). Il atteint son apog\\u00E9e au d\\u00E9but du XXe si\\u00E8cle puis d\\u00E9cline rapidement apr\\u00E8s la Premi\\u00E8re Guerre mondiale."@fr ,
		"Il pittorialismo fu un movimento della fine del XIX secolo nato per elevare il mezzo fotografico al pari della pittura o della scultura. La fotografia venne spesso paragonata con disprezzo a semplice strumento di riproduzione della realt\\u00E0, a causa del procedimento meccanico e automatico richiesto per la produzione delle immagini."@it ,
		"El pictorialismo es un movimiento fotogr\\u00E1fico de pretensiones art\\u00EDsticas que se desarrolla a nivel mundial (aunque principalmente en Europa, Estados Unidos y Jap\\u00F3n) entre finales de los a\\u00F1os 1880 y el final de la Primera guerra mundial."@es .

		"Scientific skepticism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Scientific skepticism (also spelled scepticism) is the practice of questioning whether claims are supported by empirical research and have reproducibility, as part of a methodological norm pursuing \\"the extension of certified knowledge\\". For example, Robert K. Merton asserts that all ideas must be tested and are subject to rigorous, structured community scrutiny (see Mertonian norms)."@en ,
		"Wetenschappelijk skepticisme (ook gespeld als scepticisme, zie aldaar) is het nagaan of beweringen ondersteund worden door empirisch onderzoek. Hierbij wordt onder andere gekeken of de onderzoeksuitkomsten reproduceerbaar zijn, wanneer de methodologische norm wordt nageleefd. Wetenschappelijk skeptici streven naar \\"de uitbreiding van verzekerde kennis.\\"\\u00A8"@nl ,
		"L\'espressione scetticismo scientifico, o scetticismo razionale, \\u00E8 una forma di scetticismo metodologico ovvero un atteggiamento di analisi critica, guidato dal dubbio rivolto verso tutte quelle affermazioni, teorie o enunciati che pretendono di avere carattere di scientificit\\u00E0, ma che ancora non sono passate al vaglio rigoroso delle regole del metodo sperimentale."@it ,

		"Die Skeptikerbewegung ist ein internationales Netzwerk von Vereinigungen und Einzelpersonen mit dem Anspruch einer kritischen Auseinandersetzung mit abergl\\u00E4ubischen, alternativmedizinischen oder religi\\u00F6sen Themen, die sie den Pseudo- und Parawissenschaften zuordnen. Im Sinne einer sozialen Bewegung wird der Begriff auch als Eigenbezeichnung verwendet. Die Bewegung beruft sich auf wissenschaftliche Methodik und naturalistische Erkl\\u00E4rungen."@de ,

		"Ceticismo cient\\u00EDfico ou cepticismo cient\\u00EDfico \\u00E9 a pr\\u00E1tica de questionar se uma afirma\\u00E7\\u00E3o est\\u00E1 sustentada em pesquisa emp\\u00EDrica e se \\u00E9 reproduz\\u00EDvel, como parte da norma metodol\\u00F3gica que procura a \\"extens\\u00E3o do conhecimento certificado\\". O soci\\u00F3logo Robert K. Merton afirma que todas as ideias devem ser testadas e estar sujeitas ao escrut\\u00EDnio rigoroso e estruturado da comunidade. O ceticismo organizado \\u00E9 uma das normas b\\u00E1sicas de conduta cient\\u00EDfica."@pt ,

		"El escepticismo cient\\u00EDfico (o escepticismo racional) es una posici\\u00F3n pr\\u00E1ctica, filos\\u00F3fica, cient\\u00EDfica y epistemol\\u00F3gica, en la que se cuestiona a las pseudociencias y, en general, laveracidad de las afirmaciones que carecen de prueba emp\\u00EDrica suficiente. En la pr\\u00E1ctica, esta posici\\u00F3n suele aplicarse al examen de afirmaciones y teor\\u00EDas que van en contra del razonamiento l\\u00F3gico y del  m\\u00E9todo cient\\u00EDfico."@es ,
		"Le scepticisme scientifique, nomm\\u00E9 aussi scepticisme rationnel ou scepticisme contemporain, est une pratique et une position \\u00E9pist\\u00E9mologique qui remet en doute la v\\u00E9racit\\u00E9 de certaines all\\u00E9gations par manque de preuves empiriques ou de reproductibilit\\u00E9."@fr .

		"El espiritualismo es un movimiento religioso prominente de la d\\u00E9cada de 1840 a la de 1920. La caracter\\u00EDstica distintiva del movimiento es la creencia en que los expertos pueden hacer contacto con los esp\\u00EDritus de los muertos. Se cree que esos esp\\u00EDritus habitan un plano espiritual superior que los humanos, y pueden aconsejar sobre problemas tanto mundanos como espirituales."@es ,
		"Le spiritualisme moderne anglo-saxon est un mouvement religieux monoth\\u00E9iste. Fond\\u00E9 sur la croyance en Dieu, il se distingue par la croyance en une communication possible avec les d\\u00E9funts. Ceux-ci pouvant \\u00EAtre contact\\u00E9s par de simples individus ou par des m\\u00E9diums entra\\u00EEn\\u00E9s, dans le but de recueillir des informations sur la vie apr\\u00E8s la mort.Le spiritualisme moderne anglo-saxon s\\u2019est d\\u2019abord d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 aux \\u00C9tats-Unis au XIXe si\\u00E8cle suite aux t\\u00E9moignages des s\\u0153urs Fox."@fr ,
		"Espiritualismo \\u00E9 uma denomina\\u00E7\\u00E3o comum a v\\u00E1rias doutrinas filos\\u00F3ficas e/ou religiosas, e tem como fundamento b\\u00E1sico a afirma\\u00E7\\u00E3o da exist\\u00EAncia do esp\\u00EDrito (ou alma) como elemento primordial da realidade, bem como sua autonomia, independ\\u00EAncia e primazia sobre a mat\\u00E9ria. \\u00C9 o contr\\u00E1rio de materialismo, que s\\u00F3 admite a exist\\u00EAncia da mat\\u00E9ria."@pt ,
		"Spiritualism is a belief that spirits of the dead have both the ability and the inclination to communicate with the living. The afterlife, or \\"spirit world\\", is seen by Spiritualists, not as a static place, but as one in which spirits continue to evolve."@en ,
		"Spiritualisme, afgeleid van het latijnse spiritus (geest), komt in drie domeinen voor, het filosofische, het theologische en het occulte domein. In de filosofie is het een weinig gebruikt synoniem van ontologisch of metafysisch idealisme. In de theologie is het de grondhouding die een direct contact tussen de ziel en God als primair ziet, zonder tussenkomst van bemiddelende figuren, teksten of rituelen."@nl ,

		"Peinture am\\u00E9ricaine"@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"La pintura de los Estados Unidos tiene una historia de dos siglos, a partir de la independencia del pa\\u00EDs. A finales del siglo XVIII y principios del XIX, los artistas pintaron sobre todo paisajes y retratos en un estilo realista. Las tendencias del arte moderno en Europa llegaron a los Estados Unidos a trav\\u00E9s de exposiciones en Nueva York como el Armory Show de 1913. Con anterioridad, los artistas estadounidenses hab\\u00EDan basado la mayor\\u00EDa de su obra en la pintura occidental y las artes europeas."@es ,
		"La peinture am\\u00E9ricaine est l\'un des arts d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 aux \\u00C9tats-Unis par les premiers colons et leurs successeurs, \\u00E0 partir du XVIIe si\\u00E8cle. \\u00C0 l\'\\u00E9poque moderne, les artistes europ\\u00E9ens franchissent l\'Atlantique et cr\\u00E9ent les premiers tableaux sur le sol des Treize colonies."@fr ,
		"Apesar de possuir uma hist\\u00F3ria relativamente curta dentro da arte ocidental, a pintura nos Estados Unidos evoluiu t\\u00E3o r\\u00E1pido como a economia e sociedade desse grande pa\\u00EDs, para se tornar nos dias de hoje uma das mais insignes e ativas escolas nacionais em todo o mundo. 		"El Partido Internacional de la Juventud o Youth International Party, cuyos partidarios eran conocidos como \\"yippies\\", una variante frente a \\"hippies\\", fue un partido pol\\u00EDtico antiautoritario, pro libertad de expresi\\u00F3n y antimilitarista, altamente teatral, establecido en Estados Unidos de Am\\u00E9rica en 1967. Frente a la actitud pasiva y de autoexclusi\\u00F3n adoptada por los \\"hippies\\", retir\\u00E1ndose a zonas rurales para adoptar su modelo comunal de vida, los \\"yippies\\" eran eminentemente urbanos."@es ,
		"Lo Youth International Party (spesso abbreviato con la sigla YIP, in italiano Partito Internazionale dei Giovani), i cui aderenti vennero designati con il nome di yippie (una variante del termine hippie) fu un partito di estrema sinistra di orientamento pacifista, anarchico e socialista fondato negli Stati Uniti nel 1966.Nato dai movimenti contro la guerra degli anni sessanta, lo Youth International Party offr\\u00EC un\'alternativa pi\\u00F9 radicale, controculturale e orientata verso i giovani rispetto a tali movimenti.Gli yippie si configuravano come l\'ala politica movimentista degli hippy, dal momento che \\"non tutti gli hippy avevano gi\\u00E0 sviluppato una posizione politica (Jerry Rubin)\\".Gli yippie inscenarono delle trovate goliardiche, come ad esempio quella di candidare un maiale dal nome Pigasus the Immortal (\\"Pegaso l\'Immortale\\", facendo leva sul gioco di parole tra \\"Pegasus\\" e \\"pig\\", in inglese \\"maiale\\") alla Presidenza degli Stati Uniti nel 1968, allo scopo di prendersi beffa dell\'establishment.Sebbene lo Youth International Party fosse ben conosciuto per le sue iniziative politiche teatrali, e forse per questo metodo, originale per l\'epoca, di polarizzare l\'attenzione pubblica, la maggior parte dei tradizionali partiti politici di sinistra americani lo ignorarono o lo avversarono. "@it ,
		"Die Youth International Party (deren Anh\\u00E4nger als Yippies bekannt waren, eine Variation von Hippies) war in den 1960er-Jahren eine hoch theatralische, anarchisch ausgerichtete politische Partei in den USA."@de ,
		"Youth International Party \\u2013 ameryka\\u0144ska partia polityczna, kt\\u00F3rej cz\\u0142onkowie okre\\u015Blani s\\u0105 jako Yippies, b\\u0119d\\u0105ca ugrupowaniem kontrkulturowym powsta\\u0142ym z protest\\u00F3w antywojennych i promuj\\u0105cych wolno\\u015B\\u0107 s\\u0142owa. 		"The Piwnica pod Baranami (English: The Basement, or the Cellar under the Rams) is a Polish literary cabaret located in Krak\\u00F3w, Poland. For over thirty years, in the People\'s Republic of Poland, Piwnica pod Baranami served as the most renowned political cabaret in the country, until the end of (and beyond) the communist era. Created by Piotr Skrzynecki in 1956, the cabaret continues its activities, contrary to rumours that it has been closed after the death of its founder in 1997."@en ,
		"Die Piwnica pod Baranami (Keller zu den Widdern) ist eine Kleinkunstb\\u00FChne am Hauptmarkt in Krakau. Das Theater entstand in dem gleichnamigen ehemaligen Adelspalais im Zuge der Liberalisierungspolitik unter W\\u0142adys\\u0142aw Gomu\\u0142ka im Jahre 1956. Gr\\u00FCnder war eine Gruppe von Studenten an den Krakauer Kunstakademien."@de .

	rdfs:comment	"De School van Barbizon is een Franse school die in de periode 1830 tot 1870 werkte in de omgeving van het Franse plaatsje Barbizon bij Fontainebleau. Deze stroming staat ook bekend als de Tweede School van Fontainebleau.Uitgangspunt was het schilderen van landschappen, zonder opsmuk, als reactie op de romantiek. Er werd geschilderd in de vrije natuur, waarbij veel aandacht besteed werd aan het neerzetten van kleuren die een bepaalde stemming aangaven."@nl ,

		"Con il termine scuola di Barbizon o Barbisonniers si identifica un gruppo di pittori e una corrente paesaggista del realismo collegata alla localit\\u00E0 di Barbizon in Francia, non lontana dalla foresta di Fontainebleau."@it ,
		"The Barbizon school of painters were part of an art movement towards Realism in art, which arose in the context of the dominant Romantic Movement of the time. The Barbizon school was active roughly from 1830 through 1870. It takes its name from the village of Barbizon, France, near the Forest of Fontainebleau, where many of the artists gathered. Some of the most prominent features of this school are its tonal qualities, color, loose brushwork, and softness of form."@en ,
		"Barbizo\\u0144czycy, Szko\\u0142a z Barbizon \\u2013 grupa francuskich malarzy, dzia\\u0142aj\\u0105ca w latach 1830-1860 w okolicach Barbizon (st\\u0105d nazwa) i tworz\\u0105ca g\\u0142\\u00F3wnie pejza\\u017Ce.Grupa malarzy, pod przewodnictwem Th\\u00E9odora Rousseau, uciek\\u0142a od ekspansywnego miasta na wie\\u015B, aby unikn\\u0105\\u0107 zwi\\u0105zanej nieod\\u0142\\u0105cznie z cywilizacj\\u0105 dehumanizacji. Jako swoje miejsce odosobnienia wybrali wiosk\\u0119 Barbizon w okolicach Fontainebleau, gdzie mogli bez skr\\u0119powania szuka\\u0107 natchnienia w naturze podczas spacer\\u00F3w po tamtejszych lasach."@pl ,
		"Die Schule von Barbizon wurde von einer Gruppe franz\\u00F6sischer Landschaftsmaler Mitte des 19. Jahrhunderts gebildet. Die K\\u00FCnstler hielten sich in dem Dorf Barbizon im Wald von Fontainebleau auf. Es handelt sich nicht um eine Schule im engeren Sinne. Die Maler strebten weder eine einheitliche \\u00C4sthetik noch eine feste Schulstruktur an."@de ,
		"L\'\\u00C9cole de Barbizon d\\u00E9signe le centre g\\u00E9ographique et spirituel d\'une colonie de peintres paysagistes d\\u00E9sirant travailler \\u00AB d\\u2019apr\\u00E8s nature  \\u00BB. L\'appellation tient son nom du village de Barbizon, situ\\u00E9 en lisi\\u00E8re de la for\\u00EAt de Fontainebleau (Seine-et-Marne), autour duquel certains artistes peintres afflu\\u00E8rent pendant pr\\u00E8s de cinquante ans entre 1825 et 1875."@fr ,
		"A chamada escola de Barbizon foi um movimento art\\u00EDstico que se sucedeu entre os anos de 1830 e 1870, integrado por um conjunto de pintores franceses que se estabeleceram pr\\u00F3ximo ao povoado de Barbizon, nas cercanias do bosque de Fontainebleau, deixando Paris, numa atitude de aberta oposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o ao sistema vigente.Os pintores de Babizon integram o Realismo pict\\u00F3rico franc\\u00EAs, que com Jean-Baptiste Camille Corot, Jean-Fran\\u00E7ois Millet e Th\\u00E9odore Rousseau reagiu ao formalismo do Romantismo de um Delacroix."@pt ,
		"La Escuela de Barbizon de pintura (aprox. 1830\\u20131870) fue el conjunto de pintores franceses reunidos en torno al pueblo de Barbizon, cercano al bosque de Fontainebleau, donde llegaron a establecerse los artistas de este c\\u00EDrculo. El hecho de que los pintores de Barbizon dejaran Par\\u00EDs para refugiarse en un peque\\u00F1o pueblo ya es una actitud de abierta oposici\\u00F3n al sistema vigente, no s\\u00F3lo en el \\u00E1mbito pl\\u00E1stico, sino tambi\\u00E9n en el orden social."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Als Hochrenaissance bezeichnet man die zweite Phase der Renaissance in der Zeit von etwa 1500 bis 1530 in Italien und 1555 bis 1590 in den deutschen Staaten. Die Kunstmeister dieser Periode strebten nach h\\u00F6chster k\\u00FCnstlerischer Vollkommenheit und Harmonie: Leonardo da Vinci, Michelangelo und Tizian beherrschten meisterhaft die Darstellung des menschlichen K\\u00F6rpers, Raffael die problemlose Handhabung der r\\u00E4umlichen Perspektive, Tizian und Leonardo da Vinci schufen zudem virtuose Farbeins\\u00E4tze."@de ,
		"De naam hoogrenaissance wordt gegeven aan de korte periode van ongeveer 1495 tot 1520 toen de renaissance op haar hoogtepunt was. In die tijd was het pauselijke Rome het centrum van artistieke bedrijvigheid."@nl ,

		"A Alta Renascen\\u00E7a, Alto Renascimento ou Alto Renascentismo representa, na hist\\u00F3ria da arte, o ponto culminante da arte da Renascen\\u00E7a italiana entre 1450 e 1527. Devido ao Papa J\\u00FAlio II ter patrocinado muitos artistas durante este tempo, o movimento foi centrado em Roma, que anteriormente tinha sido organizado em Floren\\u00E7a."@pt ,
		"In art history, High Renaissance, is the period denoting the apogee of the visual arts in the Italian Renaissance. The High Renaissance period is traditionally taken to begin in the 1490s, with Leonardo\'s fresco of the Last Supper in Milan and the death of Lorenzo de\' Medici in Florence, and to have ended in 1527 with the sacking of Rome by the troops of Charles V."@en .

		"Die Reportagefotografie, der Fotojournalismus oder die Bildberichterstattung verwenden die Ausdrucksformen und Mittel der Fotografie, um Reportagen (vom Lateinischen reportare, siehe Reporter), das hei\\u00DFt Berichterstattungen \\u00FCber Hintergr\\u00FCnde in Politik, Kultur und anderen Bereichen von gesellschaftlichem Belang (z. B. Gerichtsverhandlungen, Ungl\\u00FCcksf\\u00E4lle oder Verbrechen), zu illustrieren oder ausschlie\\u00DFlich in bildhafter Weise darzustellen."@de ,
		"O fotojornalismo vem do ramo da Fotografia, onde a informa\\u00E7\\u00E3o \\u00E9 clara e objetivada, atrav\\u00E9s das imagens fotogr\\u00E1ficas. Pode tamb\\u00E9m ser considerada uma especializa\\u00E7\\u00E3o do Jornalismo.Atrav\\u00E9s do fotojornalismo, a fotografia pode exibir toda a sua capacidade de transmitir informa\\u00E7\\u00F5es. Essas informa\\u00E7\\u00F5es s\\u00E3o transmitidas pelo enquadramento, distancia focal, composi\\u00E7\\u00E3o, escolhidos pelo rep\\u00F3rter-fotogr\\u00E1fico  diante dos fatos."@pt ,
		"Photojournalism is a particular form of journalism (the collecting, editing, and presenting of news material for publication or broadcast) that employs images in order to tell a news story. It is now usually understood to refer only to still images, but in some cases the term also refers to video used in broadcast journalism."@en ,

		"El arte africano es un conjunto de manifestaciones art\\u00EDsticas producidas por los pueblos del \\u00C1frica negra a lo largo de la historia.El continente africano acoge una gran variedad de culturas, caracterizadas cada una de ellas por un idioma propio, unas tradiciones y unas formas art\\u00EDsticas caracter\\u00EDsticas."@es ,

		"\\u0410\\u0444\\u0440\\u0438\\u043A\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0435 \\u0438\\u0441\\u043A\\u0443\\u0441\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u043E \\u2014 \\u043E\\u0431\\u044A\\u0435\\u0434\\u0438\\u043D\\u0451\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0435 \\u043D\\u0430\\u0437\\u0432\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0434\\u0435\\u044F\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438 \\u0440\\u0430\\u0437\\u043B\\u0438\\u0447\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u044D\\u0442\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u043E\\u0432, \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0436\\u0438\\u0432\\u0430\\u044E\\u0449\\u0438\\u0445 \\u043D\\u0430 \\u0430\\u0444\\u0440\\u0438\\u043A\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u043C \\u043A\\u043E\\u043D\\u0442\\u0438\\u043D\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0435."@ru ,
		"L\'arte africana \\u00E8 l\'arte prodotta nel continente africano, dalla nascita dell\'uomo all\'et\\u00E0 contemporanea.Bench\\u00E9 molto variegata, l\'arte dell\'Africa \\u00E8 accomunata da un forte senso religioso, legato allo spiritualismo delle differenti fedi locali. I colori maggiormente impiegati sono il rosso, simbolo della fecondit\\u00E0 e della vita, il bianco ed il nero, rappresentando la vita eterna e l\'oscurit\\u00E0."@it ,
		"African art is a term typically used for the art of Sub-Saharan Africa. Often, casual observers tend to generalize \\"traditional\\" African art, but the continent is full of people, societies and civilizations, each with a unique visual culture. The definition may also include the art of the African Diasporas, such as the art of African Americans."@en ,

	rdfs:comment	"El arte computacional o arte por computadora es el que consta del tratamiento de im\\u00E1genes creadas con un ordenador para determinados procesos creativos, siendo desde fotograf\\u00EDas manipuladas hasta el dise\\u00F1o de paisajes y retratos.Para lograr su cometido se utiliza software especial combinado con dispositivos interactivos como esc\\u00E1neres, c\\u00E1maras digitales, bol\\u00EDgrafos y tabletas digitalizadoras. 		"Computer art is any art in which computers play a role in production or display of the artwork.  Such art can be an image, sound, animation, video, CD-ROM, DVD-ROM, videogame, web site, algorithm, performance or gallery installation. Many traditional disciplines are now integrating digital technologies and, as a result, the lines between traditional works of art and new media works created using computers has been blurred."@en ,

,
		"The fathers\' rights movement is a movement whose members are primarily interested in issues related to family law, including child custody and child support that affect fathers and their children. Many of its members are fathers who desire to share the parenting of their children equally with their children\'s mother\\u2014either after divorce or as unwed fathers, and the children of the terminated marriage."@en ,
		"Die V\\u00E4terbewegung ist ein in den 1970ern und 80ern entstandener Teil der M\\u00E4nnerrechtsbewegung mit besonderem thematischen Schwerpunkt im Bereich des Sorge- und Unterhaltsrechts."@de ,
		"De vaderbeweging is de benaming voor mensen die de emancipatie en/of gelijke rechten voor vaders nastreven."@nl ,
		"El movimiento derechos de los padres es un movimiento de hombres cuyos miembros est\\u00E1n interesados  principalmente en temas relacionados con el derecho de familia, incluyendo la custodia de los hijos y su manutenci\\u00F3n o pensi\\u00F3n alimentaria que afectan a los padres y sus ni\\u00F1os. Muchos de sus miembros son padres que desean compartir la crianza de sus hijos por igual con la madre de los mismos, ya sea despu\\u00E9s de un divorcio, con relaci\\u00F3n a los hijos del matrimonio terminado, o como padres  solteros."@es .

Literatura irlandzka pisana jest wsp\\u00F3\\u0142cze\\u015Bnie przewa\\u017Cnie w j\\u0119zyku angielskim, aczkolwiek od \\u015Bredniowiecza a\\u017C po XVII wiek jej przewa\\u017Caj\\u0105ca cz\\u0119\\u015B\\u0107 obejmuje utwory napisane w j\\u0119zyku irlandzkim i cz\\u0119sto nawi\\u0105zuje do tradycji celtyckiej."@pl ,

		"Ierse literatuur verwijst naar de literatuur van Ierse schrijvers.Voor een relatief klein eiland, heeft Ierland een onevenredig grote bijdrage geleverd aan de wereldliteratuur. Ierse literatuur omvat de Ierse en Engelse talen. Verreweg de bekendste werken van auteurs afkomstig uit Ierland zijn echter in het Engels geschreven."@nl ,
		"Irish literature comprises writings in the Irish, Latin, and English (including Ulster Scots) languages on the island of Ireland. The earliest recorded Irish writing dates from the seventh century and was produced by monks writing in both Latin and Early Irish. In addition to scriptural writing, the monks of Ireland recorded both poetry and mythological tales."@en ,
		"Die irische Literatur umfasst die literarische Produktion Irlands, in einem weiteren Sinne auch die Literatur der irischen Diaspora. Bisweilen bezieht sich der Begriff auch nur auf die Literatur in irischer (g\\u00E4lischer) Sprache."@de ,

		"La litt\\u00E9rature irlandaise est \\u00E9tonnamment prolifique. Pour un pays relativement petit, l\\u2019Irlande a fait une contribution disproportionn\\u00E9e au monde litt\\u00E9raire dans tous ses domaines. Les \\u0153uvres les plus connues en dehors du pays sont de langue anglaise ; les \\u0153uvres en irlandais continuent \\u00E0 constituer une partie de la litt\\u00E9rature produite, m\\u00EAme si l\'ampleur de la litt\\u00E9rature \\u00E9crite en irlandais s\'est radicalement r\\u00E9duite depuis le XVIIe si\\u00E8cle."@fr ,
		"Se considera literatura irlandesa a aquella literatura escrita en irland\\u00E9s o bien a la literatura escrita en ingl\\u00E9s por autores nacidos en Irlanda, identificados con la forma de vida y la cultura irlandesas. Se solapa en parte con la literatura inglesa, por cuanto la mayor\\u00EDa de autores irlandeses escriben en ingl\\u00E9s, y muchos fueron conocidos tras haber emigrado a centros culturales propiamente ingleses, como Londres."@es ,
		"Con il termine letteratura irlandese si intende sia la produzione letteraria antica dell\\u2019Irlanda in lingua gaelica, nelle sue diverse fasi fra il VII e il XVI secolo, che quella moderna, in gaelico e in inglese, espressa a partire dal XVII secolo da autori di origine irlandese, alcuni dei quali residenti oltre i confini del Paese.Con l\\u2019indipendenza dal secolare dominio della Corona Britannica (1922), l\\u2019isola si \\u00E8 divisa in due entit\\u00E0 politiche separate: la Repubblica d\'Irlanda (\\u00C9ire) e l\\u2019Irlanda del Nord (Ulster). "@it .

		"Letteratura post coloniale \\u00E8 un\'espressione che pu\\u00F2 indicare due diverse categorizzazioni letterarie:secondo alcuni corrisponde a tutta la produzione letteraria in qualche modo in contrapposizione a tutto ci\\u00F2 che vi era di \\"coloniale\\", cio\\u00E8 legato ad un\'egemonia politica, linguistica e culturale delle potenze coloniali europee sulle colonie;secondo altri il \\"post coloniale\\" va inteso in senso cronologico, riferendosi a tutto ci\\u00F2 che viene prodotto nel periodo successivo a quello coloniale."@it .

		"La straight photography (\\"fotografia diretta\\") \\u00E8 una tendenza del linguaggio fotografico che nasce nella prima met\\u00E0 del Novecento in opposizione alla corrente del pittorialismo e in generale a ogni forma di manipolazione dell\'immagine estranea alle specificit\\u00E0 linguistiche del mezzo, o a quelle che venivano riconosciute come tali. La locuzione compare per la prima volta nel 1904, sulla rivista fondata da Alfred Stieglitz, Camera Work, in un articolo del critico d\'arte Sadakichi Hartmann."@it ,
		"La photographie pure (straight photography) d\\u00E9signe un style de photographie tentant de d\\u00E9peindre une sc\\u00E8ne de fa\\u00E7on aussi r\\u00E9aliste et objective, renon\\u00E7ant \\u00E0 toute manipulation. Le Mouvement photographique de la c\\u00F4te Ouest (en) (The West Coast Photographic Movement) est connu principalement pour l\'utilisation de ce style."@fr ,
		"Pure photography or straight photography refers to photography that attempts to depict a scene or subject in sharp focus and detail, commensurate with the qualities that distinguish photography from other visual media, particularly painting. Originating as early as 1904, the term was used by critic Sadakichi Hartmann in the magazine Camera Work, and later promoted by its editor, Alfred Stieglitz, as a more pure form of photography than Pictorialism."@en ,
		"Der Begriff Reine Fotografie oder englisch straight photography bezeichnet die sachliche Fotografie und den neuen Realismus. Die Bilder zeigen keine Unsch\\u00E4rfe, die Positive wurden nicht manipuliert. Die Fotografie wurde voll ausgesch\\u00F6pft: nat\\u00FCrlicher Tonwertreichtum, Sch\\u00E4rfe, Licht."@de .

		"Per street dance (danza di strada o danza urbana) si intende un insieme di stili di danza evolutisi al di fuori delle scuole di ballo tradizionali, in spazi aperti quali strade, dance party, feste di quartiere, parchi, cortili scolastici, rave party, night club, ecc... In genere sono basate sull\'improvvisazione e sulla socializzazione, incoraggiando l\'interazione e il contatto con gli spettatori e con gli altri ballerini."@it ,
		"Street dance, formally known as vernacular dance, refers to dance styles\\u2014regardless of country of origin\\u2014that evolved outside of dance studios in any available open space such as streets, dance parties, block parties, parks, school yards, raves, and nightclubs. They are often improvisational and social in nature, encouraging interaction and contact with spectators and other dancers. These dances are a part of the vernacular culture of the geographical area that they come from."@en ,
		"La street dance (litt\\u00E9ralement \\u00AB danse de rue \\u00BB) est un ensemble de danses originaires principalement des \\u00C9tats-Unis (et d\'Allemagne pour la clip dance). Le new style (en France) ou new school (aux \\u00C9tats-Unis) est une des danses les plus connues et se pratique sur des musiques hip-hop, (rap) ou autres qui sont tr\\u00E8s rythmiques et comportant beaucoup de basses. Les mouvements sont rapides et m\\u00E9lang\\u00E9s \\u00E0 d\'autres mouvements comme ceux du poppin, du boogaloo ou encore de la wave dance."@fr .

		"L\\u2019ufologie (baptis\\u00E9e ovniologie ou ovnilogie par l\'Office qu\\u00E9b\\u00E9cois de la langue fran\\u00E7aise) est une discipline qui consiste \\u00E0 recueillir, analyser et interpr\\u00E9ter les donn\\u00E9es se rapportant au ph\\u00E9nom\\u00E8ne ovni, par exemple des photographies, des t\\u00E9moignages ou des traces au sol.L\'acronyme anglais UFO (unidentified flying object) appara\\u00EEt dans certains documents de l\'arm\\u00E9e de l\'air am\\u00E9ricaine d\\u00E8s la fin de l\'ann\\u00E9e 1947 m\\u00EAme si de nombreux auteurs attribuent l\'invention du terme au capitaine Edward J. "@fr ,
		"Ufology is the study of reports, visual records, physical evidence, and other phenomena related to unidentified flying objects (UFO). UFOs have been subject to various investigations over the years by governments, independent groups, and scientists.  However, ufology, as a field, is rejected by modern academia and is considered a pseudoscience."@en ,
		"La ufolog\\u00EDa (calco del ingl\\u00E9s ufology, palabra formada a partir de las siglas UFO, Unidentified Flying Object, en espa\\u00F1ol \\"OVNI\\" por \\u2018Objeto Volador No Identificado\\u2019), tambi\\u00E9n conocido en espa\\u00F1ol como ovnilog\\u00EDa, es el estudio del fen\\u00F3meno ovni a partir del an\\u00E1lisis del material relativo al mismo: fotograf\\u00EDas, v\\u00EDdeos, presuntos testimonios sobre avistamientos, informes de radar, etc., con el objeto de proponer hip\\u00F3tesis sobre su procedencia.La ufolog\\u00EDa es un movimiento de investigaci\\u00F3n de fen\\u00F3menos aeroespaciales an\\u00F3malos, que pueden estar asociados a fen\\u00F3menos meteorol\\u00F3gicos, tecnolog\\u00EDa aeroespacial humana o posible tecnolog\\u00EDa espacial de origen extraterrestre; esta se encuentra relacionada con temas tales como los presuntos reportes de abducci\\u00F3n, las visitas de dormitorio y los fen\\u00F3menos de tiempo perdido, as\\u00ED como los c\\u00EDrculos en los cultivos\\" o Crop Circles (ya que una hip\\u00F3tesis atribuye su creaci\\u00F3n a tecnolog\\u00EDa extraterrestre), mutilaciones de ganado ocurridas en diferentes pa\\u00EDses, el proyecto Majestic 12, etc.Si bien en algunos casos puede no haber de momento una explicaci\\u00F3n cient\\u00EDfica coherente, en muchos otros se ha demostrado que se trataba de hechos falsos o tergiversados, preparados para enga\\u00F1ar a la sociedad y tener repercusi\\u00F3n p\\u00FAblica."@es ,
		"Ufologie (Ableitung von UFO, Abk. f\\u00FCr Unidentifiziertes Flug-Objekt, und griechisch \\u03BB\\u03CC\\u03B3\\u03BF\\u03C2 logos, \\u201ELehre\\u201C) ist eine Protowissenschaft, die sich mit der Untersuchung und dem Studium von UFO-Sichtungen und den damit zusammenh\\u00E4ngenden Ph\\u00E4nomenen besch\\u00E4ftigt. Ufologie ist keine ausgewiesene akademische Wissenschaft und wird gr\\u00F6\\u00DFtenteils von privaten Organisationen (vielfach von Wissenschaftlern gegr\\u00FCndet) und Einzelforschern betrieben."@de ,
		"Ufologie betreft het onderzoek van ufomeldingen en de mogelijke verklaringen die hieraan kunnen worden gegeven. In de loop der jaren werden door regeringen en onafhankelijke wetenschappers uit verschillende landen onderzoek naar het fenomeen opgestart. De bekendste studie was waarschijnlijk Project Blue Book, een onderzoek dat de United States Air Force voerde van 1947 tot 1969."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"L\'Art punk \\u00E8 un sottogenere del punk rock caratterizzato da un\'attitudine sperimentale, oppure collegato all\'avanguardia o al mondo dell\'arte. Tra le molte band appartenenti al punk d\'avanguardia, spiccano maggiormente i The Blood Brothers, i Savage Republic e i Gang of Four.I primissimi gruppi ad essere definiti in questo modo, ossia New York Dolls, Ramones e Patti Smith, appartenevano alla scena punk di New York della fine degli anni settanta."@it ,
		"Art punk is een vorm van experimentele punkrock waarbij kunstzinnige of avant-gardistische opvattingen het doel van de punkmuziek vormen. Bekende bands die deze muziekstijl beoefenen, zijn Sonic Youth en Half Japanese."@nl ,
		"L\'art punk, ou avant punk, d\\u00E9signe un genre musical de rock punk et post-punk avec un penchant exp\\u00E9rimental, ou en lien avec l\'\\u00E9cole d\'art, la critique d\'art, ou la musique d\'avant-garde.Les premiers groupes du genre, d\\u00E9crits , sont des groupes originaires de la sc\\u00E8ne musicale new-yorkaise des ann\\u00E9es 1970 tels que New York Dolls, Television, et Patti Smith."@fr ,

dbr:Baroque_sculpture	rdfs:label	"Scultura barocca"@it ,
		"Escultura barroca"@es ,
		"Baroque sculpture"@en ,
		"Escultura do Barroco"@pt ;
	rdfs:comment	"Escultura barroca es la denominaci\\u00F3n historiogr\\u00E1fica de las producciones escult\\u00F3ricas de la \\u00E9poca barroca (de comienzos del siglo XVII a mediados del siglo XVIII).Sus caracter\\u00EDsticas generales son: Naturalismo, es decir, representaci\\u00F3n de la naturaleza tal y como es, sin idealizarla. Integraci\\u00F3n en la arquitectura, que proporciona intensidad dram\\u00E1tica. Esquemas compositivos libres del geometrismo y la proporci\\u00F3n equilibrada propia de la escultura del Renacimiento pleno."@es ,
		"Baroque sculpture is the sculpture associated with the Baroque cultural movement. In Baroque sculpture, groups of figures assumed new importance, and there was a dynamic movement and energy of human forms\\u2014 they spiralled around an empty central vortex, or reached outwards into the surrounding space."@en ,
		"A escultura barroca \\u00E9 marcada por um intenso dramatismo, pela exuber\\u00E2ncia das formas, pelas express\\u00F5es teatrais, pelo jogo de luz, sombra  e movimento. As figuras que exibem dramatismo, faces expressivas e roupas esvoa\\u00E7antes. Na It\\u00E1lia, destacou-se o trabalho de Bernini. Em Portugal, Ant\\u00F3nio Ferreira e Machado de Castro foram os escultores de maior relevo."@pt ,
		"La Scultura barocca \\u00E8 la scultura associata al movimento culturale barocco, nato a Roma fra gli ultimi anni del XVI secolo e il terzo decennio del Seicento.  La caratteristica comune a tutto quel movimento artistico \\u00E8 il linguaggio forte, viscerale, alla ricerca dell\'effetto e dell\'attenzione della platea: una poetica fatta per scuotere e convincere i fedeli e sudditi: gli uni dell\'eternit\\u00E0 ed inviolabilit\\u00E0 dell\'istituzione ecclesiastica; gli altri dell\'enorme potenza raggiunta dai Regnanti."@it .

		"Colagem \\u00E9 a composi\\u00E7\\u00E3o feita a partir do uso de mat\\u00E9rias de diversas texturas, ou n\\u00E3o, superpostas ou colocadas lado a lado, na cria\\u00E7\\u00E3o de um motivo ou imagem. Foi utilizada por Picasso e Georges Braque, entre outros. Ela \\u00E9 uma t\\u00E9cnica n\\u00E3o muito antiga, criativa e bem divertida, que tem por procedimento juntar numa mesma imagem outras imagens de origens diferentes.A colagem j\\u00E1 era conhecida antes do S\\u00E9culo XX, mas era considerada uma brincadeira de crian\\u00E7as."@pt ,

,
		"Collage (from the French:  coller, \\"to glue\\"; French pronunciation: \\u200B[k\\u0254.la\\u02D0\\u0292]) is a technique of an art production, primarily used in the visual arts, where the artwork is made from an assemblage of different forms, thus creating a new whole.A collage may sometimes include magazine and newspaper clippings, ribbons, paint, bits of colored or handmade papers, portions of other artwork or texts, photographs and other found objects, glued to a piece of paper or canvas."@en ,
		"Een collage is een kunstvorm die gebruikmaakt van uitgeknipte of gescheurde stukken papier, die met lijm op steviger papier of op schildersdoek geplakt worden. De gebruikte materialen kunnen bijvoorbeeld zijn: knipsels uit tijdschriften (tekst, foto\'s, advertenties), delen van originele foto\'s, tekeningen, gescheurde stukjes van een mislukte aquarel. Het woord collage komt uit het Frans, van het werkwoord coller, waar het plakken of kleven betekent."@nl ,
		"Le collage  est une technique de cr\\u00E9ation artistique qui consiste \\u00E0 organiser une cr\\u00E9ation plastique par la combinaison d\'\\u00E9l\\u00E9ments s\\u00E9par\\u00E9s, de toute nature : extraits de journaux avec texte et photogravures, papier peint, documents, objets divers. Ce qui le distingue des papiers coll\\u00E9s qui n\'emploient que du papier."@fr ,
		"El collage es una t\\u00E9cnica art\\u00EDstica que consiste en ensamblar elementos diversos en un tono unificado. El t\\u00E9rmino se aplica sobre todo a la pintura, pero por extensi\\u00F3n se puede referir a cualquier otra manifestaci\\u00F3n art\\u00EDstica, como la m\\u00FAsica, el cine, la literatura o el videoclip. Viene del franc\\u00E9s coller, que significa pegar."@es ,
		"Die Collage ist sowohl eine Technik der bildenden Kunst als auch ein in dieser Technik geschaffenes Kunstwerk. Herk\\u00F6mmlich wird ein neues Ganzes geschaffen, indem verschiedene Elemente auf eine Unterlage aufgeklebt werden, daher die Bezeichnung (von frz. coller, \\u201Ekleben\\u201C). Collage gibt es auch jenseits der Grenzen der bildenden Kunst, n\\u00E4mlich als Musikvideos im Stile von Yes We Can oder in literarischen Collagen im Stil von Walter Kempowski oder in Text-Bild-Collagen von Herta M\\u00FCller."@de ,
		"\\u041A\\u043E\\u043B\\u043B\\u0430\\u0436 (\\u043E\\u0442 \\u0444\\u0440."@ru ,
		"Il termine collage (dal francese) indica la tecnica utilizzata per la realizzazione di opere di ogni livello (scolastico, ludico, artigianale, artistico, per esempio di arte povera, etc.) prodotte per mezzo di sovrapposizione di carte, fotografie, oggetti, ritagli di giornale o di rivista."@it .

		"Kustom Kulture"@pt ,

		"Kustom Kulture"@de ,

		"Kustom Kulture"@es ;
	rdfs:comment	"\\"Kustom Kulture\\" o \\"Kultura Kustom\\" es un neologismo estadounidense que se usa para englobar todo un estilo de vida, que abarca desde veh\\u00EDculos hasta arte pl\\u00E1stica, pasando por peinados, m\\u00FAsica y moda. La gente que se incluye en este estilo son, por lo general, amantes de la construcci\\u00F3n y modificaci\\u00F3n de coches, motos y similares."@es ,
		"Kustom Kulture ist ein Oberbegriff f\\u00FCr Kunst, Fahrzeuge, Frisuren und Kleidungsstil von Angeh\\u00F6rigen der Customizing-Szene, die Autos und Motorr\\u00E4der umbaut und veredelt. Aus den Anf\\u00E4ngen des \\u201Ehot rodding\\u201C in den USA der 1950er Jahre haben sich verschiedene Modetrends und Stile entwickelt, die auch heute noch unser t\\u00E4gliches Leben beeinflussen."@de ,
		"Kustom Kulture (no Brasil, tratada como Kultura Kustom) \\u00E9 uma cultura surgida na d\\u00E9cada de 1950, onde o pilar principal \\u00E9 a customiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o, ou seja, a altera\\u00E7\\u00E3o das partes originais, para modifica\\u00E7\\u00E3o desejada pelo autor. Empregada em diversas \\u00E1reas art\\u00EDstica e profissionais como customiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o de autos e motos, (aerografia, pinstriping), artes como tatuagem, m\\u00FAsica, entre outros meio, al\\u00E9m de caracterizar um estilo de vida."@pt ,
		"Kustom Kulture is an American neologism used to describe the artworks, vehicles, hairstyles, and fashions of those who drove and built custom cars and motorcycles in the United States of America from the 1950s through today. It was born out of the hot rod culture of Southern California of the 1960s.In the early days of hot rodding, many fashions and styles developed. Over time, each of these distinct styles of customizing have blended and reshaped our everyday life."@en ,
		"Kustom Kulture \\u00E8 una sottocultura di origine statunitense sviluppatasi a partire dagli anni cinquanta e tuttora in vita. Si basa sulla customizzazione e si esprime in diversi contesti, come la Pittura, il Tuning di auto e moto, la Moda e i Graffiti.Uno dei padri universalmente riconosciuti di questa espressione \\u00E8 Von Dutch, che divenne famoso per aver modificato e decorato diverse Harley-Davidson, Triumph, una Mercedes-Benz Ali di gabbiano e diverse pistole e coltelli."@it ,
		"La Kustom Kulture est un mouvement venu des \\u00C9tats-Unis qui rassemble toute la culture du Hot rodding, du rockabilly, des fifties de la customisation de voitures anciennes et des pin-up, ainsi qu\'un certain style de vie, de fa\\u00E7on de s\'habiller et d\'art."@fr .

		"Philosophy is the study of the general and fundamental nature of reality, existence, knowledge, values, reason, mind, and language. The Ancient Greek word \\u03C6\\u03B9\\u03BB\\u03BF\\u03C3\\u03BF\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1 (philosophia) was probably coined by Pythagoras and literally means \\"love of wisdom\\" or \\"friend of wisdom\\". Philosophy has been divided into many sub-fields."@en ,
		"La philosophie, du grec ancien \\u03C6\\u03B9\\u03BB\\u03BF\\u03C3\\u03BF\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1 (compos\\u00E9 de \\u03C6\\u03B9\\u03BB\\u03B5\\u1FD6\\u03BD, philein : \\u00AB aimer \\u00BB ; et de \\u03C3\\u03BF\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1, sophia : \\u00AB sagesse \\u00BB), signifie litt\\u00E9ralement : \\u00AB l\'amour de la sagesse \\u00BB. C\'est une activit\\u00E9 et une discipline existant depuis l\'Antiquit\\u00E9 en Occident et en Orient, se pr\\u00E9sentant comme un questionnement, une interpr\\u00E9tation et une r\\u00E9flexion sur le monde et l\'existence humaine."@fr ,
		"De filosofie of wijsbegeerte is de oudste theoretische discipline die het verlangen en het streven uitdrukt naar kennis en wijsheid. Zij kwam voor het eerst echt op in de 6e eeuw v.Chr.."@nl ,
		"La filosofia (in greco antico \\u03C6\\u03B9\\u03BB\\u03BF\\u03C3\\u03BF\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1, traslitterato in philosoph\\u00EDa, composto di \\u03C6\\u03B9\\u03BB\\u03B5\\u1FD6\\u03BD (phile\\u00EEn), \\"amare\\", e \\u03C3\\u03BF\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1 (soph\\u00EDa), \\"sapienza\\", ossia \\"amore per la sapienza\\") \\u00E8 un campo di studi che si pone domande e riflette sul mondo e sull\'uomo, indaga sul senso dell\'essere e dell\'esistenza umana, tenta di definire la natura e analizza le possibilit\\u00E0 e i limiti della conoscenza."@it ,
		"La filosof\\u00EDa (del lat\\u00EDn philosoph\\u012Da, y este del griego antiguo \\u03C6\\u03B9\\u03BB\\u03BF\\u03C3\\u03BF\\u03C6\\u03AF\\u03B1, \\u00ABamor por la sabidur\\u00EDa\\u00BB) es el estudio de una variedad de problemas fundamentales acerca de cuestiones como la existencia, el conocimiento, la verdad, la moral, la belleza, la mente y el lenguaje."@es ,

dbr:Quilt_art	rdfs:label	"Quilt art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Quilt art, sometimes known as art quilting, is an art form that uses both modern and traditional quilting techniques to create art objects. Practitioners of quilt art create it based on their experiences, imagery, and ideas rather than traditional patterns. Quilt art generally has more in common with the fine arts than it does with traditional quilting. This art is generally either wall hung or mounted as sculpture, though exceptions exist."@en .

		"The Yoruba people (Yoruba: \\u00C0w\\u1ECDn \\u1ECDm\\u1ECD Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1) are an ethnic group of Southwestern and North central Nigeria as well as Southern and Central Benin in West Africa. The Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1 constitute over 35 million people in total; the majority of this population is from Nigeria and make up 21% of its population, according to the CIA World Factbook, making them one of the largest ethnic groups in Africa."@en ,
		"Les Yorubas ou Yoroubas (Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1) sont un grand groupe ethnique d\'Afrique, surtout pr\\u00E9sent au Nigeria, sur la rive droite du fleuve Niger, mais \\u00E9galement au B\\u00E9nin, au Ghana, en C\\u00F4te d\'Ivoire o\\u00F9 ils sont appel\\u00E9s Anango, et au Togo."@fr ,

		"\\u0419\\u043E\\u0440\\u0443\\u0431\\u0430 (\\u0439\\u043E\\u0440\\u0443\\u0431\\u0430 \\u1ECCm\\u1ECD Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1) \\u2014 \\u0433\\u0440\\u0443\\u043F\\u043F\\u0430 \\u0440\\u043E\\u0434\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u043D\\u0435\\u0433\\u0440\\u043E\\u0438\\u0434\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u043D\\u0430\\u0440\\u043E\\u0434\\u043E\\u0432, \\u043D\\u0430\\u0441\\u0435\\u043B\\u044F\\u044E\\u0449\\u0438\\u0445 \\u0437\\u0430\\u043F\\u0430\\u0434\\u043D\\u0443\\u044E \\u0410\\u0444\\u0440\\u0438\\u043A\\u0443 (\\u043E\\u0442 \\u0443\\u0441\\u0442\\u044C\\u044F \\u0440\\u0435\\u043A\\u0438 \\u041D\\u0438\\u0433\\u0435\\u0440 \\u0434\\u043E \\u0413\\u0432\\u0438\\u043D\\u0435\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0437\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0432\\u0430): \\u0433\\u043E\\u0441\\u0443\\u0434\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0430 \\u041D\\u0438\\u0433\\u0435\\u0440\\u0438\\u044F, \\u0422\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E, \\u0411\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u043D, \\u0413\\u0430\\u043D\\u0430)."@ru ,
		"Gli Yoruba (Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1 nell\'ortografia Yoruba) sono un vasto gruppo etno-linguistico di circa 40 milioni di persone e diffuso nell\'Africa occidentale. Sono presenti soprattutto in Nigeria (costituiscono il 30% della popolazione nigeriana), ma anche in Benin, Togo e Sierra Leone."@it ,
		"De Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1 zijn een van de omvangrijkste etnische groepen van  West-Afrika en met 21 procent de op twee na grootste etnische groep van Nigeria. Zij hebben een eigen taal (Yoruba), Yorubareligie en Yoruba Scheppingsverhaal.De meerderheid van Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1 leeft in het zuidwesten van Nigeria, in de Oyo, Ogun, Ondo, Kwara, Lagos, Ekiti en westelijke Kogi-staten. Maar er zijn ook Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1 gemeenschappen in zuidwest Benin en centraal Togo (Atakpame)."@nl ,

		"Die Yoruba (Yor\\u00F9b\\u00E1) sind ein westafrikanisches Volk, das vor allem im S\\u00FCdwesten Nigerias lebt. Dort stellen sie 21 % der Bev\\u00F6lkerung. Sie leben haupts\\u00E4chlich in den s\\u00FCdwestlichen Bundesstaaten Oyo, Ogun, Lagos, Ondo, Osun, Ekiti und Kwara, aber auch in den Nachbarstaaten Benin, Ghana und Togo. Das Siedlungsgebiet ist noch heute das dicht besiedelte Kerngebiet Nigerias."@de ,

dbr:Haida_manga	rdfs:label	"Haida manga"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Haida Manga is a contemporary style of Haida comics and print cartoons that explores the elements of both traditional North Pacific indigenous arts and narrative, while also adapting contemporary techniques of artistic design from the western portion of the North Pacific, namely the Japanese manga from which its name derives. Haida manga have so far been published in several countries including Japan, South Korea, China, Taiwan, Macao, France, and Canada."@en .

(chinoiserie) \\u3068\\u3088\\u3070\\u308C\\u308B\\u4E2D\\u56FD\\u6587\\u5316\\u306E\\u30D6\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u304C\\u5230\\u6765\\u3057\\u305F\\u308A\\u3082\\u3057\\u305F\\u3002\\u3057\\u304B\\u3057\\u4E00\\u65B9\\u3067\\u3001\\u5F8C\\u9032\\u3086\\u3048\\u306E\\u65FA\\u76DB\\u306A\\u77E5\\u7684\\u597D\\u5947\\u5FC3\\u3082\\u5099\\u3048\\u3066\\u304A\\u308A\\u3001\\u3053\\u308C\\u304C\\u30A4\\u30AE\\u30EA\\u30B9\\u306E\\u5BFE\\u5916\\u81A8\\u5F35\\u306E\\u4E00\\u56E0\\u3068\\u306A\\u3063\\u305F\\u306E\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"La Literatura augusta (en ingl\\u00E9s, Augustan Literature) es un estilo de literatura inglesa que se corresponde aproximadamente con los reinados de la reina Ana, el rey Jorge I, y Jorge II. Los cr\\u00EDticos se refieren con este nombre a la literatura desarrollada entre 1700 y 1760 (o, para algunos, hasta 1789)."@es ,
		"For the period of Latin literature for which the English style is named, see Augustan literature (ancient Rome).Augustan literature (sometimes referred to misleadingly as Georgian literature) is a style of English literature produced during the reigns of Queen Anne, King George I, and George II in the first half of the 18th century and ending in the 1740s with the deaths of Pope and Swift (1744 and 1745, respectively)."@en .
<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Group_(artists)>	rdfs:label	"Birmingham Group (artists)"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Birmingham Group, sometimes called the Birmingham School, was an informal collective of painters and craftsmen associated with the Arts and Crafts Movement, that worked in Birmingham, England in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. All of its members studied or taught at the Birmingham School of Art after the reorganisation of its teaching methods by Edward R. Taylor in the 1880s, and it was the School that formed the group\'s primary focus."@en .

<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hussards_(literary_movement)>	rdfs:label	"Les Hussards (mouvement litt\\u00E9raire)"@fr ,
		"Ussari (movimento letterario)"@it ,
		"Los H\\u00FAsares"@es ,
		"Hussards (literary movement)"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Hussards was a French literary movement in the 1950s which opposed Existentialism and the figure of the politically engaged intellectual as personified by Jean-Paul Sartre."@en ,
		"Furono definiti Ussari i membri di un movimento letterario francese degli anni cinquanta che si opponeva all\'esistenzialismo e alla figura dell\'intellettuale impegnato personificata da Jean-Paul Sartre."@it ,
		"Durante la Francia de posguerra, nace un grupo de escritores bien olvidado, m\\u00E1s por su oposici\\u00F3n al bloque de izquierda sartriana, llamados com\\u00FAnmente como \\"les Hussards\\" (los H\\u00FAsares). Se reun\\u00EDan com\\u00FAnmente en el caf\\u00E9 \\"Aux Assassins\\" (lo de los asesinos) y en torno a la \\"Revue de la table ronde\\" (revista de la mesa redonda). Eran opuestos al Nouveau roman y defend\\u00EDan un estilo corto e incisivo, (Ils se d\\u00E9lectent de la phrase courte dont ils se croient les inventeurs."@es ,
		"L\'expression les Hussards d\\u00E9signe un courant litt\\u00E9raire fran\\u00E7ais qui, dans les ann\\u00E9es 1950 et 60, s\'opposa aux existentialistes et \\u00E0 la figure de l\'intellectuel engag\\u00E9 qu\'incarnait Jean-Paul Sartre. Le roman de Roger Nimier Le Hussard bleu a donn\\u00E9 son nom au mouvement.Si le mouvement apparaissait comme assez h\\u00E9t\\u00E9roclite, les Hussards se distinguaient notamment par leur opposition \\u00E0 Sartre et leur antigaullisme de droite."@fr .

dbr:Psychedelic_art	rdfs:label	"Arte psichedelica"@it ,
		"Psychedelische Kunst"@de ,
		"Arte psicod\\u00E9lico"@es ,
		"Psychedelic art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Psychedelic art is any art inspired by psychedelic experiences known to follow the ingestion of psychoactive drugs such as LSD and psilocybin. The word \\"psychedelic\\" (coined by British psychologist Humphry Osmond) means \\"mind manifesting\\".  By that definition, all artistic efforts to depict the inner world of the psyche may be considered \\"psychedelic\\".  In common parlance \\"psychedelic art\\" refers above all to the art movement of the late 1960s counterculture."@en ,
		"L\'arte psichedelica \\u00E8 qualsiasi tipo di arte visiva ispirata alle esperienze psichedeliche indotte da droghe come LSD, mescalina e psilocibina. Essa infatti \\u00E8 informata dal concetto che gli stati alterati di coscienza, prodotti da droghe psichedeliche, sono una fonte di ispirazione artistica. Tutti gli sforzi di rappresentare in modo artistico il mondo interiore della psiche possono essere considerati psichedelici."@it ,
		"Arte psicod\\u00E9lico o arte lis\\u00E9rgico es el arte inspirado por la experiencia inducida por drogas alucin\\u00F3genas como el LSD, el peyote u otras. El t\\u00E9rmino \\"lis\\u00E9rgico\\" hace referencia a la denominaci\\u00F3n qu\\u00EDmica del LSD. El t\\u00E9rmino \\"psicod\\u00E9lico\\" fue acu\\u00F1ado por el psic\\u00F3logo brit\\u00E1nico Humphry Osmond y significa \\"manifestando el alma\\".El arte psicod\\u00E9lico se ha dado en la literatura, la m\\u00FAsica y las artes visuales."@es ,
		"Psychedelische Kunst oft auch englisch Psychedelic Art oder Psychedelia genannt, bezeichnet eine nicht eindeutig definierte Stilrichtung der Gegenwartskunst, die auf der experimentellen Verwendung bewusstseinserweiternder Drogen (Psychedelika) wie beispielsweise LSD, Mescalin oder Psilocybin basiert und versucht, diese Sinneseindr\\u00FCcke in bildender Kunst, Film, Musik und Literatur wiederzugeben, zu beschreiben, emotional zu manifestieren oder dem Betrachter unter Drogeneinfluss eine zus\\u00E4tzliche Stimulanz zu bieten. "@de .

		"La litt\\u00E9rature noire am\\u00E9ricaine est un courant litt\\u00E9raire des \\u00C9tats-Unis produit par des \\u00E9crivains afro-am\\u00E9ricains. Elle a ses origines dans les auteurs de la fin du XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle tels que Phillis Wheatley et Olaudah Equiano et atteint son apog\\u00E9e avec les t\\u00E9moignages sur l\\u2019esclavage et la Renaissance de Harlem dans l\\u2019entre-deux-guerres. Aujourd\\u2019hui, les plus grands noms de la cette litt\\u00E9rature sont Toni Morrison, Maya Angelou et Walter Mosley."@fr ,
		"Als Afroamerikanische Literatur ist die m\\u00FCndliche \\u00DCberlieferung und die schriftliche Literatur der nordamerikanischen Autoren zu verstehen, die ganz oder zum Teil von Afrikanern abstammen und meist in den USA oder Kanada leben."@de ,
		"African-American  literature is the body of literature produced in the United States by writers of African descent.  It begins with the works of such late 18th-century writers as Phillis Wheatley. Before the high point of slave narratives, African-American literature was dominated by autobiographical spiritual narratives. African-American literature reached early high points with slave narratives of the nineteenth century."@en ,
		"Con letteratura afroamericana si definisce il corpus letterario prodotto negli Stati Uniti d\'America da scrittori di discendenza africana."@it ,
		"La literatura afroamericana de Estados Unidos es literatura escrita en ese pa\\u00EDs por, sobre, y en algunos casos tambi\\u00E9n para afroamericanos. Este g\\u00E9nero se inici\\u00F3 en el siglo XVIII con escritores como la poeta Phillis Wheatley y el orador Frederick Douglass, alcanzando su primer gran nivel con el Renacimiento de Harlem, y continuando hoy con autoras como Toni Morrison y Maya Angelou, consideradas entre los mejores escritores de los Estados Unidos."@es ,

		"Geometric abstraction is a form of abstract art based on the use of geometric forms sometimes, though not always, placed in non-illusionistic space and combined into non-objective (non-representational) compositions."@en ,
		"Abstracci\\u00F3n geom\\u00E9trica se ha denominado a un cap\\u00EDtulo del arte abstracto desarrollado a partir de los a\\u00F1os 1920, y se basa en el uso de formas geom\\u00E9tricas simples combinadas en composiciones subjetivas sobre espacios irreales. Surge como una reacci\\u00F3n frente al excesivo subjetivismo de los artistas pl\\u00E1sticos de \\u00E9pocas anteriores en un intento de distanciarse de lo puramente emocional."@es ,
		"Abstrakcja geometryczna - kierunek w sztuce polegaj\\u0105cy na operowaniu r\\u00F3\\u017Cnymi formami geometrii. Stanowi przeciwie\\u0144stwo abstrakcji organicznej."@pl .

		"\\u0413\\u0435\\u0440\\u043A\\u043E\\u043C\\u0435\\u0440, \\u0413\\u0443\\u0431\\u0435\\u0440\\u0442 \\u0444\\u043E\\u043D"@ru ;
	rdfs:comment	"Sir Hubert von Herkomer CVO RA (born as Hubert  Herkomer; 26 May 1849 \\u2013 31 March 1914) was a British painter of German descent, and also a pioneering film-director and composer. Though a very successful portraitist, especially of men, he is mainly remembered for his earlier works that took a realistic approach to the conditions of life of the poor. Hard Times, showing the family of a travelling day-labourer at the side of a road, is probably his best known work."@en ,
		"Sir Hubert von Herkomer (26 mai 1849 \\u2013 31 mars 1914), est un peintre germano-britannique. Il \\u00E9tait aussi sculpteur, musicien, \\u00E9crivain et un pionnier en tant que r\\u00E9alisateur de films et compositeur. Bien qu\'ayant \\u00E9t\\u00E9 un remarquable portraitiste, surtout pour hommes, on se souvient de lui principalement pour ses premi\\u00E8res \\u0153uvres qui d\\u00E9peignaient de mani\\u00E8re tr\\u00E8s r\\u00E9aliste l\'exploitation et les conditions de vie inhumaines des employ\\u00E9s paysans et ouvriers de l\'\\u00E9poque."@fr ,
		"Sir Hubert von Herkomer RA (* 26. Mai 1849 in Waal, Bayern; \\u2020 31. M\\u00E4rz 1914 in Budleigh Salterton, Devonshire, England) war ein britisch-deutscher Maler und Bildhauer, Musiker, Theater- und Filmemacher und Schriftsteller. Au\\u00DFerdem gilt er als einer der Wegbereiter des Automobilsports in Deutschland."@de ,
		"Hubert von Herkomer, pierwotnie Hubert Herkommer (ur. 26 maja 1849 w Waal, w Bawarii, zm. 31 marca 1914 w Budleigh Salterton, w Anglii) \\u2013 brytyjski malarz pochodzenia niemieckiego, tak\\u017Ce grafik, kompozytor i pionier techniki filmowej."@pl ,
		"Hubert von Herkomer fue un pintor alem\\u00E1n nacido en 1849 y muerto en 1914. De padre inmigrante ingl\\u00E9s, tuvo amplia participaci\\u00F3n en la ense\\u00F1anza de la pintura en divesas instituciones, fundando una escuela de artes cuyos dos m\\u00E1s famosos pupilos fueron Robert Baden-Powell y Lucy Kemp-Welsh. En 1899 recibe el t\\u00EDtulo de nobleza \\"von Herkomer\\" de parte del K\\u00E1iser Wilhelm II, y el t\\u00EDtulo \\"Sir\\" de parte de la Reina Victoria."@es ,

		"Vanguardia rusa es un t\\u00E9rmino usado para definir la enorme e influyente oleada de arte moderno que emergi\\u00F3 en Rusia (o de manera m\\u00E1s exacta, el Imperio Ruso y la Uni\\u00F3n Sovi\\u00E9tica) aproximadamente entre 1890 y 1930, aunque en algunos lugares comienza de manera m\\u00E1s temprana, en 1850 , y acaba m\\u00E1s tarde, en 1960. El t\\u00E9rmino cubre muchos movimientos art\\u00EDsticos coet\\u00E1neos, independientes pero intensamente relacionados como el Neo-primitivismo, el Suprematismo, el Constructivismo y el Futurismo."@es ,
		"The Russian avant-garde was a large, influential wave of modern art that flourished in the Russian Empire and Soviet Union, approximately 1890 to 1930\\u2014although some have placed its beginning as early as 1850 and its end as late as 1960. The term covers many separate, but inextricably related, art movements that flourished at the time; namely Suprematism, Constructivism, Russian Futurism, Cubo-Futurism, Zaum and Neo-primitivism."@en ,
		"L\'avant-garde russe est un terme g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rique d\\u00E9signant un large courant tr\\u00E8s influent d\'art moderne qui est apparu en Russie, plus pr\\u00E9cis\\u00E9ment dans l\'Empire russe et en Union sovi\\u00E9tique."@fr ,
		"A vanguarda russa \\u00E9 um termo comumente utilizado para se referir a uma s\\u00E9rie de movimentos art\\u00EDsticos e culturais que ocorreram na R\\u00FAssia, aproximadamente entre as d\\u00E9cadas de 1890 e 1930, especialmente durante a primeira fase da Revolu\\u00E7\\u00E3o Russa.Apesar da variedade de artistas e escolas que o termo pode abranger, normalmente ele est\\u00E1 mais associado aos movimentos construtivista e suprematista, que em geral ocorreram paralelas \\u00E0 Revolu\\u00E7\\u00E3o pol\\u00EDtica e os quais inserem-se no contexto das vanguardas art\\u00EDsticas europ\\u00E9ias.Entre os participantes do movimento se destacam Gustav Klutsis, Vladimir e Giorgi Stenberg, Nikolai Prusakov, Alexandr Rodchenko e El Lissitzky, Vladimir Mayakovsky, Kazimir Malevich, al\\u00E9m de Dziga Vertov e Sergei Eisenstein na \\u00E1rea cinematogr\\u00E1fica. dbr:Assam_Movement	rdfs:label	"Konflikt etniczno-religijny w Asamie"@pl ,
		"Assam Movement"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Konflikt etniczno-religijny w Asamie \\u2013 konflikt o pod\\u0142o\\u017Cu etnicznym i religijnym, pomi\\u0119dzy ludno\\u015Bci\\u0105 p\\u00F3\\u0142nocno-wschodniego indyjskiego stanu o nazwie Asam a imigrantami z teren\\u00F3w Bengalu."@pl ,
		"The Assam Movement (or Assam Agitation) (1979-1985) was a popular movement against undocumented immigrants in Assam. The movement, led by All Assam Students Union (AASU) and the \'All Assam Gana Sangram Parishad\' (AAGSP), developed a program of protests and demonstration to compel the government to identify and expel illegal immigrants. The agitation programs were largely non-violent, but the Nellie massacre was a case of extreme violence."@en .
dbr:Glitch_art	rdfs:label	"Glitch art"@en ,
		"Glitch art"@fr ,
		"Glitch Art"@pt ;
	rdfs:comment	"Glitch Art \\u00E9 a explora\\u00E7\\u00E3o est\\u00E9tica do erro da m\\u00E1quina anal\\u00F3gica ou digital. Atrav\\u00E9s da introdu\\u00E7\\u00E3o de erros nos dados e c\\u00F3digos de artefatos digitais ou da manipula\\u00E7\\u00E3o f\\u00EDsica de objectos eletr\\u00F3nicos, nasce a Glitch Art.Alguns autores relacionados com o tema, como por exemplo Jonas Downey, afirmam que o conceito de Glitch Art como arte ainda est\\u00E1 por definir.Os processos mais conhecidos na realiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o desta arte s\\u00E3o o Databending, Datamoshing e o Image Hacking."@pt ,
		"Le glitch art est l\'esth\\u00E9tisation d\'erreurs analogiques ou num\\u00E9riques, comme des art\\u00E9facts ou des bugs, par corruption de code ou de donn\\u00E9es ou manipulations d\'appareils \\u00E9lectroniques (comme le circuit bending)."@fr ,
		"Glitch art is the aestheticization of digital or analog errors, such as artifacts and other \\"bugs\\", by either corrupting digital code/data or by physically manipulating electronic devices (for example by circuit bending)."@en .

		"The Hague School is the name given to a group of artists who lived and worked in The Hague between 1860 and 1890. Their work was heavily influenced by the realist painters of the French Barbizon school. The painters of the Hague school generally made use of relatively somber colors, which is why the Hague School is sometimes called the Gray School."@en ,
		"Szko\\u0142a haska (hol. Haagse School) \\u2013 grupa artystyczna malarzy holenderskich dzia\\u0142aj\\u0105cych w Hadze w latach 1860\\u20131890. Malarze ze szko\\u0142y haskiej tworzyli pod wp\\u0142ywem francuskiej Szko\\u0142y z Barbizon, malowali w plenerze realistyczne i naturalistyczne sceny rodzajowe, kt\\u00F3re \\u0142\\u0105czyli z pejza\\u017Cem. Wiod\\u0105cym tematem ich prac by\\u0142y pejza\\u017Ce, martwe natury i sceny rodzajowe z \\u017Cycia prostych ludzi: mieszczan, ch\\u0142op\\u00F3w i rybak\\u00F3w."@pl ,
		"La Escuela de La Haya es el nombre dado a un grupo de artistas que vivieron y trabajaron en La Haya entre 1860 y 1890. Fueron fuertemente influenciados por los pintores del Realismo franc\\u00E9s de la Escuela de Barbizon.Los pintores de la Escuela de La Haya utilizan frecuentemente colores obscuros, poco brillantes, raz\\u00F2n por la cual en ocasiones se les llama la Escuela gris."@es ,
		"De Haagse School was een beweging van gelijkgestemde Nederlandse kunstschilders die grofweg tussen 1860 en 1900 in Den Haag werkten, dan wel anderszins verbonden waren met de residentiestad."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"A arte da \\u00CDndia (\\u0915\\u0932\\u093E \\u092D\\u093E\\u0930\\u0924, kal\\u0101 rata) se caracteriza, principalmente, por ser um reflexo da complexa sociedade indiana, multi\\u00E9tnica e multicultural. \\u00C9 marcada por um car\\u00E1ter essencialmente religioso, servindo como um meio de propaga\\u00E7\\u00E3o das distintas religi\\u00F5es que marcaram a \\u00CDndia: hindu\\u00EDsmo, budismo, islamismo, cristianismo, etc."@pt ,
		"Sztuka indyjska od zarania dziej\\u00F3w by\\u0142a przepojona warto\\u015Bciami religijnymi, stanowi\\u0105cymi odzwierciedlenie idei i poj\\u0119\\u0107, kt\\u00F3rych oddzia\\u0142ywanie przyczyni\\u0142o si\\u0119 do powstania w kraju tym hinduizmu, d\\u017Ainizmu i buddyzmu. 		"Indian Art consists of a variety of art forms, including plastic arts (e.g., pottery and sculpture), visual arts (e.g., cave paintings), and textile arts (e.g., woven silk). Geographically, it spans the entire Indian subcontinent, including what is now India, Pakistan and Bangladesh. A strong sense of design is characteristic of Indian art and can be observed in its modern and traditional forms.The origin of Indian art can be traced to pre-historic Hominid settlements in the 3rd millennium BC."@en ,
		"El arte de la India (\\u0915\\u0932\\u093E \\u092D\\u093E\\u0930\\u0924, kal\\u0101 bh\\u0101rata) se caracteriza principalmente por ser un reflejo de la compleja sociedad india, multi\\u00E9tnica y multicultural. Asimismo tiene un car\\u00E1cter principalmente religioso, sirviendo el arte como medio de transmisi\\u00F3n de las distintas religiones que han jalonado la India: hinduismo, budismo, islamismo, cristianismo, etc."@es ,
		"La vaste port\\u00E9e de l\'art indien est fortement li\\u00E9e avec l\'histoire culturelle, les religions et les philosophies qui placent la production d\'art et le m\\u00E9c\\u00E9nat dans des contextes sociaux et culturels propres \\u00E0 l\'histoire de cette vaste partie du monde. Sachant que par \\u00AB art indien \\u00BB on consid\\u00E8re l\'art des soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9s et des cultures du sous-continent indien et des espaces de l\'Asie du Sud-Est o\\u00F9 se manifestent influences et \\u00E9changes culturels avec les cultures issues du sous-continent indien ."@fr .
dbr:Jindyworobak_Movement	rdfs:label	"Jindyworobak Movement"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Jindyworobak Movement was a nationalistic Australian literary movement whose white members sought to promote Indigenous Australian ideas and customs, particularly in poetry. They were active from the 1930s to around the 1950s. The movement intended to combat the influx of \\"alien\\" culture, which was threatening local art.The Jindyworobak movement was begun in Adelaide during 1937 by the poet Rex Ingamells and the other members of the Jindyworobak club."@en .

		"The Dutch Golden Age painting is the painting of the Dutch Golden Age, a period in Dutch history generally spanning the 17th century, during and after the later part of the Eighty Years\' War (1568\\u20131648) for Dutch independence.The new Dutch Republic was the most prosperous nation in Europe, and led European trade, science, and art."@en ,
		"L\'\\u00E2ge d\'or de la peinture n\\u00E9erlandaise est le nom donn\\u00E9 \\u00E0 la peinture des Pays-Bas durant le si\\u00E8cle d\'or n\\u00E9erlandais, une p\\u00E9riode de l\'histoire de ce pays qui correspond \\u00E0 peu pr\\u00E8s au XVIIe si\\u00E8cle. Les Provinces-Unies forment alors la nation la plus prosp\\u00E8re d\'Europe et dominent le commerce, l\'art et la science du continent."@fr ,
		"La pintura del Siglo de oro neerland\\u00E9s o pintura barroca holandesa se desarroll\\u00F3 durante un per\\u00EDodo de la historia holandesa que abarca el siglo XVII, durante y despu\\u00E9s de la Guerra de los Ochenta A\\u00F1os (1568-1648) por la independencia holandesa. Las Provincias Unidas eran la naci\\u00F3n m\\u00E1s pr\\u00F3spera de Europa, liderando el comercio, la ciencia y el arte. El arte holand\\u00E9s tuvo que reinventarse por completo despu\\u00E9s del brusco corte con las tradiciones culturales cat\\u00F3licas y de la antigua monarqu\\u00EDa."@es ,

		"L\\u2019hominisme (presque syst\\u00E9matiquement appel\\u00E9 masculinisme dans les m\\u00E9dias et par les organisations f\\u00E9ministes) est un mouvement issu de pays francophones dont le but est d\'int\\u00E9grer la pr\\u00E9occupation de la condition masculine \\u00E0 la pr\\u00E9occupation de la condition humaine en g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ral. Ce qui explique le choix de ce n\\u00E9ologisme, fond\\u00E9 sur deux racines : la racine fran\\u00E7aise \\"homme\\", au sens d\'individu masculin, et la racine latine \\"homo, hominis\\", qui signifie \\"humain\\"."@fr ,
		"Los movimientos de hombres son movimientos sociales que consisten en grupos y organizaciones de hombres que se centran en cuestiones de g\\u00E9nero  y cuyas actividades van desde la autoayuda y el apoyo al cabildeo y activismo."@es ,
		"The men\'s movement is a social movement consisting of groups and organizations of men and their allies who focus on gender issues and whose activities range from self-help and support to lobbying and activism. Despite the term \\"men\'s movement\\" implying a single, unified movement, the men\'s movement is actually several movements that have differing and often antithetical goals."@en ,
		"Met de naam mannenbeweging wordt meestal een groep mannen en een streven aangeduid dat zich richt op emancipatie en bevrijding van mannen. Er zijn drie belangrijke richtingen te onderscheiden;een komt uit de vaderbeweging een de andere uit de vrouwenbeweging en een derde beweging meer vanuit de new age.Deze indeling is uiteraard te grof om alle nuances tot hun recht te laten komen. In de literatuur worden beide hoofdstromingen zelden tegelijkertijd besproken."@nl .

dbr:Angry_Penguins	rdfs:label	"Angry Penguins"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Angry Penguins was an Australian literary and artistic avant-garde movement of the 1940s. The movement was stimulated by a modernist magazine of the same name published by the surrealist poet Max Harris, who founded the magazine in 1940, at the age of 18.Angry Penguins was first published in the South Australian capital of Adelaide."@en .

dbr:Heroic_realism	rdfs:label	"R\\u00E9alisme h\\u00E9ro\\u00EFque"@fr ,
		"Heroic realism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Le r\\u00E9alisme h\\u00E9ro\\u00EFque est un terme quelquefois utilis\\u00E9 pour d\\u00E9signer une forme d\\u2019art de propagande, tel que le r\\u00E9alisme socialiste sovi\\u00E9tique associ\\u00E9 aux r\\u00E9gimes communistes et une forme tr\\u00E8s similaire associ\\u00E9e aux r\\u00E9gimes fascistes.Le r\\u00E9alisme h\\u00E9ro\\u00EFque fut d\'abord un vecteur de la r\\u00E9volution sovi\\u00E9tique au temps de L\\u00E9nine. D\'abord, L\\u00E9nine douta que les populations illettr\\u00E9es comprendraient le message d\\u2019images abstraites."@fr ,
		"Heroic realism is a term which has sometimes been used to describe art used as propaganda. Examples include the Socialist realism style associated with Communist regimes, and the very similar art style associated with Fascism.  Its characteristics are realism and the depiction of figures as ideal types or symbols, often with explicit rejection of modernism in art (as \\"bourgeois\\" or \\"degenerate\\")."@en .

		"Literary nonsense"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Literary nonsense (or nonsense literature) is a broad categorization of literature that balances elements that make sense with some that do not, with the effect of subverting language conventions or logical reasoning.  Even though the most well-known form of literary nonsense is nonsense verse, the genre is present in many forms of literature.The effect of nonsense is often caused by an excess of meaning, rather than a lack of it."@en ,
