	rdfs:comment	"Noucentisme war eine kulturelle Str\\u00F6mung in Katalonien, die im politischen Umfeld der 1906 von Enric Prat de la Riba gegr\\u00FCndeten katalanistischen Bewegung Solidaritat Catalana aufkam. Sie endete 1923 mit dem Staatsstreich Primo de Riveras. In der Kunst erwies sich der Noucentisme als die katalanische Form des Neoklassizismus und war weitgehend eine Reaktion auf das \\u201Eromantische Chaos\\u201C des Modernisme."@de ,
		"\\u041D\\u043E\\u0432\\u0435\\u0441\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C (\\u043A\\u0430\\u0442\\u0430\\u043B\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A. Noucentisme) \\u2014 \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u043D\\u043E\\u0435 \\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u0432 \\u041A\\u0430\\u0442\\u0430\\u043B\\u043E\\u043D\\u0438\\u0438, \\u0432\\u043E\\u0437\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0448\\u0435\\u0435 \\u0432 \\u0441\\u0440\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435 \\u0432\\u043E\\u043A\\u0440\\u0443\\u0433 \\u0441\\u043E\\u0437\\u0434\\u0430\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0432 1906 \\u0433\\u043E\\u0434\\u0443 \\u042D\\u043D\\u0440\\u0438\\u043A\\u043E\\u043C \\u041F\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u043E\\u043C-\\u0434\\u0435-\\u043B\\u0430-\\u0420\\u0438\\u0431\\u0430 \\u043D\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u043E\\u043D\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0439 \\u043E\\u0440\\u0433\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0437\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u0438 \\u041A\\u0430\\u0442\\u0430\\u043B\\u043E\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0441\\u043E\\u043B\\u0438\\u0434\\u0430\\u0440\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u044C (Solidaritat Catalana). \\u0417\\u0430\\u0432\\u0435\\u0440\\u0448\\u0438\\u043B\\u043E\\u0441\\u044C \\u043F\\u043E\\u0441\\u043B\\u0435 \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0438\\u0437\\u043E\\u0448\\u0435\\u0434\\u0448\\u0435\\u0433\\u043E \\u0432 \\u0418\\u0441\\u043F\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0438 \\u0432 1923 \\u0433\\u043E\\u0434\\u0443 \\u0432\\u043E\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u043F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0432\\u043E\\u0440\\u043E\\u0442\\u0430 \\u041C\\u0438\\u0433\\u0435\\u043B\\u044F \\u041F\\u0440\\u0438\\u043C\\u043E \\u0434\\u0430 \\u0420\\u0438\\u0432\\u0435\\u0440\\u044B."@ru ,
		"Novecentismo[cita requerida] es la denominaci\\u00F3n de un movimiento est\\u00E9tico, inicialmente art\\u00EDstico y literario, pero extendido a otros \\u00E1mbitos de la cultura, que se asocia gen\\u00E9ricamente a las vanguardias art\\u00EDsticas y literarias de comienzos del siglo XX."@es ,
		"Generacja 14 lub Novecentisme to katalo\\u0144ski ruch kulturowy powsta\\u0142y na zasadzie reakcji kontra modernizmowi. Eugeni d\'Ors, pod\\u0105\\u017Caj\\u0105c za w\\u0142osk\\u0105 tradycj\\u0105 czerpania nazwy stylu z wieku, w kt\\u00F3rym funkcjonowa\\u0142 oraz wykorzystuj\\u0105c dwuznaczno\\u015B\\u0107 s\\u0142owa \\"nou\\" po katalo\\u0144sku novu i nuovo (dziewi\\u0119\\u0107 oraz nowy), okre\\u015Bli\\u0142 Generacj\\u0119 14 terminem Novecentisme. Ruch ten jednoczy\\u0142 artyst\\u00F3w, g\\u0142\\u00F3wnie eseist\\u00F3w, z pogranicza Generacji 98 oraz Generacji 27."@pl ,
		"Noucentisme (Catalan pronunciation: [\\u02CCn\\u0254ws\\u0259n\\u02C8tizm\\u0259], noucentista being its adjective) was a Catalan cultural movement of the early 20th century that originated largely as a reaction against Modernisme, both in art and ideology, and was, simultaneously, a perception of art almost opposite to that of avantgardists."@en ,
		"Novecentismo, Generaci\\u00F3n del 14 ou Vanguardias \\u00E9 o nome de um movimento cultural, art\\u00EDstico e pol\\u00EDtico que se desenvolveu na Catalunha no in\\u00EDcio do s\\u00E9culo XX, por oposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o ao modernismo catal\\u00E3o, que dominou o per\\u00EDodo precedente.A n\\u00EDvel liter\\u00E1rio, a est\\u00E9tica novecentista agrupa um conjunto de autores na sua maioria ensa\\u00EDstas situados entre a Gera\\u00E7\\u00E3o de 98 e a Gera\\u00E7\\u00E3o de 27. O termo novecentismo foi cunhado em catal\\u00E3o por Eugeni d\'Ors como noucentisme."@pt ,
		"Con Noucentisme s\'intende il movimento culturale cha caratterizz\\u00F2 la Catalogna dei primi anni del XX secolo, in contrapposizione con il modernismo che aveva dominato il periodo precedente.Il nome venne coniato nel 1906 da Eugeni d\'Ors seguendo la tradizione italiana di chiamare gli stili con il nome dei secoli in cui si erano sviluppati (ad esempio, il Quattrocento, il Cinquecento, ecc..) e sfruttando l\'equivalenza fonetica del termine nou che in catalano significa sia \\"nove\\" che \\"nuovo\\"."@it ,
		"Le Noucentisme est le mouvement culturel et politique qui se d\\u00E9veloppa en Catalogne au d\\u00E9but du XXe si\\u00E8cle, par opposition au modernisme qui avait domin\\u00E9 la p\\u00E9riode pr\\u00E9c\\u00E9dente."@fr .

dbr:D\xc3\xa9primisme	rdfs:label	"D\\u00E9primisme"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"D\\u00E9primisme (\\"depressionism\\") is a contemporary French art and literary movement, in which authors dwell on the failures of society. The movement can be identified as a cross between expressionism and symbolism. Originally a French movement, the term has later been extended to refer to direct commentary on any contemporary, particularly western or American culture."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Mit Schweizer Typografie bezeichnet man die auf der Neuen Typografie aufbauende Gestaltungsrichtung der Typografie seit etwa 1955.Kennzeichnend f\\u00FCr diese Richtung sind Gestaltungsraster, asymmetrische sachliche Darstellung, Groteskschriften in wenigen Schriftgraden, extreme Weissr\\u00E4ume und der Verzicht auf Schmuckelemente.Bekannte Typografen, die den Schweizer Stil gepr\\u00E4gt haben, sind Max Bill, Adrian Frutiger, Karl Gerstner, Walter Haettenschweiler, Armin Hofmann, Hans Eduard Meier, Max Miedinger, Josef M\\u00FCller-Brockmann, Bruno Pf\\u00E4ffli, Emil Ruder, Helmut Schmid und Anton Stankowski.Auch in der Ausbildung zum Schriftsetzer an der Z\\u00FCrcher Kunstgewerbeschule wurde dieser Stil in den 1950er- und 1960er-Jahren noch gelehrt. "@de ,
		"El Estilo Tipogr\\u00E1fico Internacional, tambi\\u00E9n conocido como International Typographic Style, Escuela suiza o Swiss Style, es un estilo de dise\\u00F1o gr\\u00E1fico, desarrollado en Su\\u00EDza en la d\\u00E9cada de 1950, y que tuvo una gran fuerza y repercusi\\u00F3n durante m\\u00E1s de dos d\\u00E9cadas, llegando incluso a tener gran influencia en la actualidad."@es ,
		"Le style typographique international (ou style international), \\u00E9galement connu sous le nom de style suisse, est un courant du design graphique d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 en Suisse dans les ann\\u00E9es 1950, notamment par Armin Hofmann."@fr ,
		"Lo Stile tipografico internazionale (International Typographic Style), detto anche Stile svizzero  (Swiss Style), o Scuola svizzera, \\u00E8 uno stile grafico che si \\u00E8 sviluppato in Svizzera negli anni cinquanta e i cui punti cardinali sono la chiarezza, la leggibilit\\u00E0 e l\\u2019obiettivit\\u00E0, senza alcun accenno al decorativismo.Caratteristiche ricorrenti di questo stile sono l\\u2019utilizzo di caratteri bastone come l\\u2019Akzidenz Grotesk (da cui derivarono due dei caratteri pi\\u00F9 conosciuti e utilizzati, come l\\u2019Univers e l\\u2019Helvetica), l\\u2019uso di gabbie e una preferenza per la fotografia al posto delle illustrazioni o dei disegni.Molti dei primi lavori afferenti allo Stile tipografico internazionale utilizzano la tipografia come elementi di design assieme al bodycopy. "@it ,

		"The International Typographic Style, also known as the Swiss Style, is a graphic design style developed in Switzerland in the 1950s that emphasizes cleanliness, readability and objectivity. Hallmarks of the style are asymmetric layouts, use of a grid, sans-serif typefaces like Akzidenz Grotesk, and flush left, ragged right text. The style is also associated with a preference for photography in place of illustrations or drawings."@en ,

		"Antirassismus ist eine Bezeichnung f\\u00FCr alle Ans\\u00E4tze, die auf die Beseitigung von Rassismus abzielen. Seine Ziele sind die Freiheit und Gleichberechtigung aller Menschen ohne Diskriminierung und Apartheid."@de ,
		"Anti-racism includes beliefs, actions, movements, and policies adopted or developed to oppose racism. In general, anti-racism is intended to promote an egalitarian society in which people do not face discrimination on the basis of their race, however defined.By its nature, anti-racism tends to promote the view that racism in a particular society is both pernicious and socially pervasive, and that particular changes in political, economic, and/or social life are required to eliminate it."@en ,
		"El antirracismo o el contrarracismo se refiere a la creencia, los movimientos, y a las pol\\u00EDticas adoptadas o desarrolladas para oponerse al racismo. En general, el antirracismo se piensa para promover a una sociedad igualitaria donde las personas no hagan frente a la discriminaci\\u00F3n por raz\\u00F3n de su raza."@es ,
		"L\'antiracisme inclut les opinions, actions, mouvements et les politiques adopt\\u00E9es ou d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9e pour s\'opposer au racisme. En g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ral l\'antiracisme promeut une soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 dans laquelle les individus ne subissent pas de discrimination sur la base de leur ethnie dont la d\\u00E9finition peut varier."@fr ,

		"Escuela pict\\u00F3rica de D\\u00FCsseldorf"@es ;
	rdfs:comment	"La escuela de D\\u00FCsseldorf engloba a un grupo de pintores que ense\\u00F1aron o que estudiaron en la Academia de Bellas Artes de D\\u00FCsseldorf durante los a\\u00F1os 1830 y 1840, cuando el pintor Wilhelm von Schadow fue el director. Las obras de la escuela de D\\u00FCsseldorf son caracterizadas por paisajes muy detallados pero a\\u00FAn extravagantes, a menudo con cuentos religiosos o aleg\\u00F3ricos. Miembros destacados de la escuela recomendaron el pleinairismo, y sol\\u00EDan utilizar una paleta con colores bajos y uniformes."@es ,
		"The D\\u00FCsseldorf school of painting refers to a group of painters who taught or studied at the D\\u00FCsseldorf Academy (now the Staatliche Kunstakademie D\\u00FCsseldorf or D\\u00FCsseldorf State Art Academy) in the 1830s and 1840s, when the Academy was directed by the painter Wilhelm von Schadow. The work of the D\\u00FCsseldorf School is characterized by finely detailed yet still fanciful landscapes, often with religious or allegorical stories set in the landscapes."@en ,
		"La cosiddetta Scuola di D\\u00FCsseldorf o Scuola di pittura di D\\u00FCsseldorf fu un gruppo di pittori che avevano insegnato o studiato all\'Accademia di D\\u00FCsseldorf (denominata poi Kunstakademie D\\u00FCsseldorf) tra gli anni 1830 - 1840 quando la scuola era diretta dal pittore Wilhelm von Schadow. L\'identificazione del movimento si estese nell\'arco temporale. (dal 1819 al 1918)."@it ,
		"\\u0414\\u044E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u0434\\u043E\\u0440\\u0444\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u0430\\u044F \\u0448\\u043A\\u043E\\u043B\\u0430 \\u2014 \\u043E\\u0434\\u043D\\u0430 \\u0438\\u0437 \\u0441\\u0430\\u043C\\u044B\\u0445 \\u0432\\u043B\\u0438\\u044F\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u0435\\u0439\\u0448\\u0438\\u0445 \\u043D\\u0435\\u043C\\u0435\\u0446\\u043A\\u0438\\u0445 \\u0438 \\u0435\\u0432\\u0440\\u043E\\u043F\\u0435\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0445 \\u0436\\u0438\\u0432\\u043E\\u043F\\u0438\\u0441\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u0448\\u043A\\u043E\\u043B, \\u0441\\u0444\\u043E\\u0440\\u043C\\u0438\\u0440\\u043E\\u0432\\u0430\\u043D\\u043D\\u0430\\u044F \\u0433\\u0440\\u0443\\u043F\\u043F\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u043E\\u0432, \\u043A\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u044B\\u0435 \\u043F\\u0440\\u0435\\u043F\\u043E\\u0434\\u0430\\u0432\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438 \\u0438\\u043B\\u0438 \\u0443\\u0447\\u0438\\u043B\\u0438\\u0441\\u044C \\u0432 \\u0414\\u044E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u0434\\u043E\\u0440\\u0444\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0430\\u043A\\u0430\\u0434\\u0435\\u043C\\u0438\\u0438 \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432 \\u0432 \\u043F\\u0435\\u0440\\u0432\\u043E\\u0439 \\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u043E\\u0432\\u0438\\u043D\\u0435 XIX \\u0432\\u0435\\u043A\\u0430."@ru ,
		"Der kunsthistorische Begriff D\\u00FCsseldorfer Malerschule bezeichnet eine Gruppe von Malern, die vor allem im 19."@de ,
		"Ce que l\'histoire de l\'art appelle  l\'\\u00C9cole de peinture de D\\u00FCsseldorf est un groupe de peintres du XIXe si\\u00E8cle (1819-1918) form\\u00E9s \\u00E0 l\'Acad\\u00E9mie des beaux-arts de D\\u00FCsseldorf, qui y ont enseign\\u00E9, de professeurs qui y ont suivi des le\\u00E7ons priv\\u00E9es ou qui ont travaill\\u00E9 dans l\'environnement proche de l\'Acad\\u00E9mie.Les premiers directeurs de l\'Acad\\u00E9mie, Peter de Cornelius et Wilhelm von Schadow ont orient\\u00E9 l\'\\u00C9cole vers le mouvement nazar\\u00E9en, qui donne priorit\\u00E9 \\u00E0 une peinture historique, religieuse, id\\u00E9aliste et \\u00E0 la peinture monumentale.Cependant, sous l\'influence du Vorm\\u00E4rz, le programme de l\'acad\\u00E9mie et de son environnement artistique s\'\\u00E9largit bient\\u00F4t vers les courants romantiques et autres, donnant ainsi plus de place et de notori\\u00E9t\\u00E9 \\u00E0 une approche r\\u00E9aliste et de critique sociale de l\'art ainsi qu\'\\u00E0 la peinture de paysage et de genre.Parmi les th\\u00E8mes picturaux et stylistiques de l\'\\u00E9cole, on retrouve dans toutes leurs facettes, la peinture historique, le paysage, les sc\\u00E8nes de genre, la nature morte qui ont jou\\u00E9 un r\\u00F4le d\\u00E9terminant dans l\'art bourgeois du XIXe si\\u00E8cle.Gr\\u00E2ce \\u00E0 des comptes rendus, publications et expositions, \\u00E0 la diffusion des \\u0153uvres sur le march\\u00E9 international de l\'art, aux voyages, aux liens amicaux et familiaux, aux carri\\u00E8res scolaires et professionnelles des diff\\u00E9rents protagonistes, les \\u0153uvres de l\'\\u00C9cole de peinture de D\\u00FCsseldorf ont \\u00E9t\\u00E9 largement diffus\\u00E9es, surtout dans la p\\u00E9riode entre 1830 et 1870, mais \\u00E9galement dans les derni\\u00E8res d\\u00E9cennies du XIXe si\\u00E8cle.Les peintres form\\u00E9s \\u00E0 D\\u00FCsseldorf ont transmis leurs techniques artistiques, positions, m\\u00E9thodes d\'enseignement, sujets, arguments et d\\u00E9bats, dans le monde entier, vers les autres \\u00E9coles des beaux-arts et l\'art naissant des colonies. "@fr .

		"La produzione cinematografica (in inglese filmmaking o film production) \\u00E8 una materia estremamente complessa e costosa. L\'eterogeneo mondo del cinema ha portato da una parte ad avere film che mobilitano una macchina produttiva molto elaborata, dall\'altra ad avere dei film che, prescindendo dall\'aspetto industriale, tendono all\'esercizio artistico, o sono meglio concepibili come oggetti artigianali."@it ,
		"Producci\\u00F3n audiovisual es la producci\\u00F3n de contenidos para medios de comunicaci\\u00F3n audiovisuales; especialmente el cine y la televisi\\u00F3n; independientemente del soporte utilizado (film, v\\u00EDdeo, v\\u00EDdeo digital) y del g\\u00E9nero (ficci\\u00F3n, documental, publicidad, etc.).En relaci\\u00F3n con la creaci\\u00F3n audiovisual, la producci\\u00F3n audiovisual es el resultado de la combinaci\\u00F3n de varias necesidades: industriales, comerciales, de entretenimiento, culturales o art\\u00EDsticas."@es ,
		"Die Filmproduktion ist der Herstellungsprozess eines Kino-, Werbe- oder Fernsehfilms, der sich in die Phasen Projektentwicklung, Vorproduktion, Dreharbeiten, Postproduktion und Filmverwertung gliedert. Filmproduktionen entstehen \\u00FCberall auf der Welt in wirtschaftlichem, sozialem, politischem und k\\u00FCnstlerischem Kontext und benutzen dabei eine Vielzahl an Techniken. Typischerweise ist an der Filmherstellung eine hohe Anzahl an Menschen beteiligt."@de ,
		"Filmmaking (or in an academic context, film production) is the process of making a film. Filmmaking involves a number of discrete stages including an initial story, idea, or commission, through scriptwriting, casting, shooting, sound recording and reproduction, editing, and screening the finished product before an audience that may result in a film release and exhibition."@en .

dbr:Woodlands_style	rdfs:label	"Woodlands style"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Woodland School Of Art, also named Woodlands style, Woodlands School, or Anishnabe painting, is a genre of painting among First Nations and Native American artists from the Great Lakes area - including northern Ontario and southwestern Manitoba. The majority of the Woodland artists belong to the Anishinaabeg - notably the Ojibwe (also Ojibwa), Odawa, and Potawatomi, as well as the Oji-Cree and the Cree. The style is also known as Legend Painting or Medicine Painting."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Caricatura \\u00E9 um desenho de um personagem da vida real, tal como pol\\u00EDticos e artistas. Por\\u00E9m, a caricatura enfatiza e exagera as caracter\\u00EDsticas da pessoa de uma forma humor\\u00EDstica, assim como em algumas circunst\\u00E2ncias acentua gestos, v\\u00EDcios e h\\u00E1bitos particulares em cada indiv\\u00EDduo. Ser caricato \\u00E9 ser objeto de comicidade, ironia ou ter algo peculiar na face ou no corpo, levados ao exagero, \\u00E0 s\\u00E1tira jocosa ou como cr\\u00EDtica de costumes."@pt ,
		"Een karikatuur is een humoristische voorstelling van een persoon of zaak, waarbij de meest kenmerkende trekken sterk overdreven worden. Ze kunnen zowel ter amusement of ter belediging bedoeld zijn. Karikaturen worden vooral geassocieerd met cartoonisten (\'karikatuur\' wordt ook wel als synoniem voor cartoon gebruikt), maar ook in het poppenspel, theater en typetjes kan men karikaturale personen, situaties of gedragingen terugvinden."@nl ,
		"Une caricature est un portrait peint, dessin\\u00E9 ou sculpt\\u00E9 qui amplifie certains traits caract\\u00E9ristiques du sujet. Souvent humoristique, la caricature est un type de satire graphique quand elle charge des aspects ridicules ou d\\u00E9plaisants."@fr ,

		"Karykatura (w\\u0142. caricatura) \\u2013 przedstawienie osoby, wydarzenia lub przedmiotu, kt\\u00F3re cechuje si\\u0119 przesad\\u0105 w oddaniu charakterystycznych element\\u00F3w, w\\u0142a\\u015Bciwo\\u015Bci, cech. 		"La caricatura \\u00E8 un disegno di solito a carattere umoristico o satirico che rappresenta una persona. Il disegno della caricatura, solitamente molto semplice ed essenziale, storpia volutamente l\'immagine della persona rappresentata, caricandone (da qui il termine) alcuni tratti caratteristici della fisionomia. Solitamente il particolare esagerato ha gi\\u00E0 in s\\u00E9 un contenuto sarcastico, come il naso pronunciato."@it ,
		"A caricature is a rendered image showing the features of its subject in a simplified or exaggerated way.In literature, a caricature is a description of a person using exaggeration of some characteristics and oversimplification of others.Caricatures can be insulting or complimentary and can serve a political purpose or be drawn solely for entertainment."@en ,
		"Karikatur (von lateinisch carrus \\u201AKarren\\u2018, also: \\u00DCberladung, und italienisch caricare \\u201A\\u00FCberladen\\u2018, \\u201A\\u00FCbertreiben\\u2018) bedeutet die komisch \\u00FCberzeichnete Darstellung von Menschen oder gesellschaftlichen Zust\\u00E4nden, auch mit politischem bzw. propagandistischem Hintergrund. Die Zeichner von (bildlichen) Karikaturen nennt man Karikaturisten, das Zeichnen karikieren. Die Entsprechung im englischsprachigen Raum ist caricature."@de ,

Tambi\\u00E9n puede tratarse de alegor\\u00EDas."@es .

		"Concrete art is an art movement with a strong emphasis on abstraction. The artist Theo van Doesburg, closely associated with the De Stijl art movement, coined the term \\"concrete art\\" as he in 1930 founded the group Art Concret and articulated its features in a manifesto titled \\"The Basis of Concrete Art\\", signed by four other artists of the group, including Otto G. Carlsund, Jean H\\u00E9lion and Leon Tutundjian."@en ,
		"El arte concreto o concretismo es una tendencia dentro de la pintura abstracta que se desarroll\\u00F3 durante los a\\u00F1os 1930 a partir de la obra de De Stijl, los futuristas y Kandinsky en torno al pintor suizo Max Bill (1908-1994). La expresi\\u00F3n arte concreto fue introducida por primera vez por Theo van Doesburg en su \\u00ABManifiesto de arte concreto\\u00BB (1930)."@es ,
		"Concrete kunst is een aanduiding die in 1930 ge\\u00EFntroduceerd werd door Theo van Doesburg voor abstracte kunst die universeel duidelijk moest zijn en het product moest zijn van de bewuste, rationele geest van een kunstenaar. De wortels van de concrete kunst liggen in het Constructivisme, Suprematisme, Neoplasticisme en Elementarisme. In de praktijk is Concrete kunst synoniem geworden voor abstract geometrische kunst. Door sommige kunstkenners wordt Concrete kunst ook wel Concretivisme genoemd."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"Decadentismo \\u00E9 uma corrente art\\u00EDstica, filos\\u00F3fica e, principalmente, liter\\u00E1ria que teve sua origem na Fran\\u00E7a nas duas \\u00FAltimas d\\u00E9cadas do s\\u00E9culo XIX e se desenvolveu por quase toda Europa e alguns pa\\u00EDses da Am\\u00E9rica. A denomina\\u00E7\\u00E3o   \\"decadentismo\\", que tinha, a princ\\u00EDpio, um sentido depreciativo e ir\\u00F4nico, dado pela cr\\u00EDtica acad\\u00EAmica,   terminou por ser adotada pelos pr\\u00F3prios participantes do movimento."@pt ,
		"The Decadent movement was a late 19th-century artistic and literary movement of Western Europe.  It flourished in France, but also had devotees in England and throughout Europe, as well as in the United States."@en ,
		"Dekadenzdichtung (franz\\u00F6sisch d\\u00E9cadence \\u201EVerfall\\u201C) ist die vage und umstrittene Bezeichnung f\\u00FCr eine Vielzahl an literarischen Str\\u00F6mungen und Einzelwerken um die Jahrhundertwende (1900), deren Gemeinsamkeit in ihrer entschiedenen Ablehnung des Naturalismus liegt."@de ,
		"El decadentismo es una corriente art\\u00EDstica, filos\\u00F3fica y, principalmente, literaria que tuvo su origen en Francia en las dos \\u00FAltimas d\\u00E9cadas del siglo XIX y se desarroll\\u00F3 por casi toda Europa y algunos pa\\u00EDses de Am\\u00E9rica.La denominaci\\u00F3n de decadentismo surgi\\u00F3 como un t\\u00E9rmino despectivo e ir\\u00F3nico empleado por la cr\\u00EDtica acad\\u00E9mica, sin embargo, la definici\\u00F3n fue adoptada por aquellos a quienes iba destinada."@es ,
		"Decadentisme, ook wel d\\u00E9cadence of decadentie genaamd, is een geestelijke stroming die in het laatste kwart van de negentiende eeuw vooral onder de ontwikkelden in West-Europa aanhang vond. Karakteristiek is de teleurstelling over de teloorgang van zekerheden, van verlies van duidelijkheid over de na te streven toekomst, maar ook van weerzin tegenover de blinde geldzucht van de burgerlijke maatschappij en het geloof dat de wetenschap en industrie alle problemen zullen oplossen."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"Figura\\u00E7\\u00E3o Livre \\u00E9 um movimento art\\u00EDstico do in\\u00EDcio dos anos 1980, aparecido em reac\\u00E7\\u00E3o \\u00E0 Arte Minimalista e Conceptual.Em v\\u00E1rios pa\\u00EDses, jovens artistas prop\\u00F5em uma pintura figurativa e colorida: N\\u00E9o Expressionistas ou Novos fauves na Alemanha, Transvanguarda na It\\u00E1lia, Bad Painting nos Estados Unidos, Figura\\u00E7\\u00E3o livre na Fran\\u00E7a. Este movimento frequentemente \\u00E9 associado ao fen\\u00F3meno graffiti."@pt ,
		"Figuration Libre (vrije figuratie) is een kunststroming uit Frankrijk uit de jaren 80 van de 20e eeuw. De stroming valt binnen het neo-expressionisme en kwam gelijktijdig op met de Nieuwe Wilden en de Transavanguardia Italiana. Het was een reactie op de rationaliteit van de conceptuele kunst."@nl ,
		"Figuration Libre (Free figuration) is a French art movement of the 1980s. It is the French equivalent of Bad Painting and Neo-expressionism in America and Europe, Junge Wilde in Germany and Transvanguardia in Italy. The term was coined by Fluxus artist Ben Vautier. The group was formed in 1981 by Robert Combas, Remi Blanchard, Fran\\u00E7ois Boisrond and  Herv\\u00E9 Di Rosa. Other figures include Richard Di Rosa and Louis Jammes."@en ,
		"Figuration Libre [figyrasj\\u00F5\\u02C8libr\\u0259;] bezeichnet eine in den 1980er Jahren in Frankreich entstandene Richtung der bildenden Kunst. Die Figuration Libre ist als Reaktion auf die als zu rational empfundene Konzeptkunst entstanden."@de ,
		"Figuraci\\u00F3n Libre o Figuraci\\u00F3n libre popular es un movimiento pict\\u00F3rico que surge en Francia a finales de los a\\u00F1os setenta. Es el equivalente franc\\u00E9s a la Bad Painting y el Neoexpresionismo en Estados Unidos y Europa, Junge Wilde en Alemania y Transvanguardia en Italia. El t\\u00E9rmino Figuration Libre fue acu\\u00F1ado por Ben Vautier, artista Fluxus. Cultivan una pintura figurativa, espont\\u00E1nea, primitiva, con gran intensidad crom\\u00E1tica."@es ,
		"La figuration libre est un mouvement artistique du d\\u00E9but des ann\\u00E9es 1980, apparu dans un contexte d\'art \\u00AB s\\u00E9rieux \\u00BB, minimaliste et conceptuel."@fr ,

		"Es gibt weltweit viele unterschiedliche Gesetze, welche die Beziehungen zwischen Menschen des gleichen Geschlechts zu regeln versuchen. Viele dieser Gesetze formulieren Verbote, wobei h\\u00E4ufig nur das gleichgeschlechtliche Sexualverhalten unter M\\u00E4nnern behandelt wird. Eine weitere h\\u00E4ufige Auspr\\u00E4gung von Gesetzen zum Thema Homosexualit\\u00E4t behandelt Alltagsaspekte, zum Beispiel den G\\u00FCterstand, von gleichgeschlechtlichen Paaren."@de ,
		"A legisla\\u00E7\\u00E3o sobre pessoas LGBT varia de acordo com a cultura de cada pa\\u00EDs. Na atualidade existe uma enorme variedade no alcance das leis que afetam as pessoas do grupo LGBT no mundo. Essas diferen\\u00E7as nos direitos relativos a pessoas LGBT estiveram presentes ao longo da hist\\u00F3ria das civiliza\\u00E7\\u00F5es humanas, persistindo at\\u00E9 aos tempos atuais."@pt ,
		"Laws affecting lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT) people vary greatly by country or territory\\u2014everything from legal recognition of same-sex marriage or other types of partnerships, to the death penalty as punishment for same-sex romantic/sexual activity or identity.LGBT rights are considered human rights by the Amnesty International and civil rights by some."@en ,
		"Questa voce presenta una panoramica delle leggi inerenti alle persone e i comportamenti omosessuali in diversi paesi del mondo; queste possono variare, anche di molto, da paese a paese: dalla completa equiparazione del matrimonio omosessuale a quello eterosessuale da una parte alla pena di morte come condanna per i comportamenti omosessuali o anche solo per l\'espressione della propria identit\\u00E0 di genere dall\'altra.I diritti per le persone lesbiche, gay, omosessuali o transgender (LGBT) fanno parte del pi\\u00F9 ampio spettro dei diritti umani e dei diritti civili e includono (ma non sono limitati a):una legislazione anti bullismo, contro la discriminazione e il bullismo omofobico all\'interno dell\'ambito scolastico a protezione degli adolescenti omosessuali.il riconoscimento dell\'omogenitorialit\\u00E0.l\'uguaglianza in materia di immigrazione.leggi anti discriminatorie in materia di occupazione ed alloggio.leggi contro i crimini d\'odio che prevedano sanzioni alla violenza contro le persone LGBT motivata da pregiudizio.parificazione dell\'et\\u00E0 del consenso.legislazione relativa all\'orientamento sessuale e al servizio militare.riconoscimento delle relazioni omosessuali, tramite unioni civili o matrimonio tra persone dello stesso sesso.la possibilit\\u00E0 di adozione da parte di coppie dello stesso sesso.parit\\u00E0 di accesso alle tecniche di procreazione assistita.il riconoscimento giuridico del transessualismo e la possibilit\\u00E0 di riassegnazione del sesso a partir dall\'identit\\u00E0 di genere.l\'accesso alla transizione (transgenderismo), ad un riassegnazione chirurgica del sesso e ad una terapia ormonale sostitutiva.\\u2191 \\u2191"@it ,
		"En las sociedades, culturas y estados que cuentan con c\\u00F3digos legales escritos, los comportamientos sexuales de diferente \\u00EDndole reciben sanci\\u00F3n p\\u00FAblica jur\\u00EDdica a trav\\u00E9s de leyes. dbr:Quantum_fiction	rdfs:label	"Quantum fiction"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Quantum fiction is a literary genre that reflects modern experience of the material world and reality as influenced by quantum theory and new principles in quantum physics. The genre is not necessarily science-themed and blurs the line separating science fiction and fantasy into a broad scope of mainstream literature that transcends the mechanical model of science and involves the fantasy of human perception or imagination as realistic components affecting the every day physical world."@en .

		"Avanguardia \\u00E8 la denominazione attribuita ai fenomeni del comportamento o dell\'opinione intellettuale, soprattutto artistici e letterari, pi\\u00F9 estremisti, audaci, innovativi, in anticipo sui gusti e sulle conoscenze, sviluppatisi nel Novecento ma derivanti da tendenze politico-culturali ottocentesche, connotata dal costituirsi di raggruppamenti di artisti sotto un preciso manifesto da loro firmato.La nozione di \\"avanguardia\\" pu\\u00F2 essere analizzata da due diversi punti di vista: sotto il profilo storico-critico o sotto quello teorico."@it ,

		"Avant-garde verwijst in het algemeen naar een generatie jonge kunstenaars die met nieuwe vormen experimenteren in de schilderkunst, muziek, literatuur, po\\u00EBzie, film, theater en moderne dans. Bij uitbreiding heeft het begrip ook betrekking op de vernieuwende stromingen zelf. 		"The avant-garde (from French, \\"advance guard\\" or \\"vanguard\\", literally \\"fore-guard\\") are people or works that are experimental or innovative, particularly with respect to art, culture, and politics.The avant-garde pushes the boundaries of what is accepted as the norm or the status quo, primarily in the cultural realm. The avant-garde is considered by some to be a hallmark of modernism, as distinct from postmodernism."@en ,
		"Le terme avant-garde d\\u00E9signe, depuis le XIXe si\\u00E8cle, des personnes qui entreprennent des actions nouvelles ou exp\\u00E9rimentales, en particulier dans les arts et la culture."@fr ,
		"El vanguardismo, o avant-garde en franc\\u00E9s, se refiere a las personas o a las obras que son experimentales o innovadoras, en particular en lo que respecta al arte, la cultura, la pol\\u00EDtica y la literatura.El vanguardismo representa un empuje de los l\\u00EDmites de lo que se acepta como la norma o statu quo, sobre todo en el \\u00E1mbito cultural. La noci\\u00F3n de la existencia del vanguardismo es considerado por algunos como una caracter\\u00EDstica del modernismo, a diferencia de la posmodernidad."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Acme\\u00EDsmo se refere a um movimento liter\\u00E1rio modernista russo que tem origem na palavra grega akme (\\"cume\\", \\"\\u00E1pice\\", \\"fast\\u00EDgio\\"). Trazia um certo espiritinovismo \\u00E0 poesia, em contrapartida a algumas tend\\u00EAncias vanguardistas demolidoras, em prol da linguagem simples, clara e usual. Dois membros importantes deste movimento foram Anna Akhmatova e Osip Mandelstam.O acme\\u00EDsmo foi anunciado por Mikhail Kuzmin no seu ensaio Sobre a formosa claridade (1910)."@pt ,
		"Akmeizm (od akme, gr. akm\\u1E17 \\u2013 szczyt, wy\\u017Cszy stopie\\u0144 czego\\u015B, pora rozkwitu; tak\\u017Ce adamizm, klaryzm) \\u2013 modernistyczny kierunek w poezji i literaturze rosyjskiej przypadaj\\u0105cy na lata 1912\\u20131932, odmiana neoklasycyzmu. Wyszed\\u0142 on od krytyki symbolizmu przeprowadzonej przez m\\u0142odych tw\\u00F3rc\\u00F3w z istniej\\u0105cej w latach 1911-1914 grupy \\u201ECech poet\\u00F3w\\u201D. Inicjatorem powstania ruchu by\\u0142 Niko\\u0142aj Gumilow, a g\\u0142\\u00F3wnymi jego przedstawicielami byli Osip Mandelsztam, Anna Achmatowa, Michai\\u0142 Kuzmin, Siergiej Gorodiecki."@pl ,
		"L\'acmeismo \\u00E8 un movimento letterario russo che nato nel 1910 ebbe termine alla fine della seconda guerra mondiale. Il suo nome deriva dal greco acm\\u00E9 (culmine). Nacque in opposizione al simbolismo, sviluppando una diversa tematica e un nuovo stile espressivo fondati sulla chiarezza rappresentativa, sulla concretezza dei contenuti e sullo studio dei valori formali del verso."@it ,
		"Acme\\u00EDsmo. Corriente literaria rusa que surgi\\u00F3 en 1911, durante la llamada Edad de Plata de la literatura rusa, en respuesta al simbolismo ruso (en:Russian symbolism). La denominaci\\u00F3n, que proviene del griego \\u03AC\\u03BA\\u03BC\\u03B7, acm\\u00E9, es decir apogeo o cumbre, fue adoptada por Nikol\\u00E1i Gumiliov y Sergu\\u00E9i Gorodetski. Anna Ajm\\u00E1tova y \\u00D3sip Mandelshtam fueron asimismo componentes del grupo de los acme\\u00EDstas."@es ,
		"\\u30A2\\u30AF\\u30E1\\u30A4\\u30BA\\u30E0\\uFF08\\u30ED\\u30B7\\u30A2\\u8A9E:\\u0410\\u043A\\u043C\\u0435\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C\\u3001\\u82F1\\u8A9E:Acmeism\\uFF09\\u306F\\u3001\\u30ED\\u30B7\\u30A2\\u5E1D\\u56FD\\uFF08\\u73FE:\\u30ED\\u30B7\\u30A2\\uFF09\\u30671910\\u5E74\\u304B\\u30891912\\u5E74\\u306B\\u304B\\u3051\\u3066\\u6210\\u7ACB\\u3057\\u305F\\u6587\\u5B66\\u6D41\\u6D3E\\u307E\\u305F\\u306F\\u6587\\u5B66\\u904B\\u52D5\\u3002\\u300C\\u30A2\\u30AF\\u30E1\\u300D\\u3068\\u306F\\u30AE\\u30EA\\u30B7\\u30A2\\u8A9E\\u3067\\u9802\\u70B9\\u3092\\u610F\\u5473\\u3059\\u308B\\u300CAcme\\u300D\\u3067\\u3001\\u30A2\\u30AF\\u30E1\\u30A4\\u30BA\\u30E0\\u3092\\u8A69\\u306E\\u30B9\\u30BF\\u30A4\\u30EB\\u3068\\u3059\\u308B\\u4EBA\\u3092\\u30A2\\u30AF\\u30E1\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30C8\\u3068\\u547C\\u3093\\u3060\\u3002\\u30ED\\u30B7\\u30A2\\u306E\\u8A69\\u4EBA\\u3001\\u4F5C\\u5BB6\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u30CB\\u30B3\\u30E9\\u30A4\\u30FB\\u30B0\\u30DF\\u30EA\\u30E7\\u30D5\\u3001\\u30DF\\u30CF\\u30A4\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30AF\\u30BA\\u30DF\\u30F3\\u304C\\u6307\\u5C0E\\u8005\\u3068\\u306A\\u308A\\u3001\\u8C61\\u5FB4\\u4E3B\\u7FA9\\u304B\\u3089\\u8A69\\u306E\\u6280\\u6CD5\\u3092\\u5B66\\u3073\\u3064\\u3064\\u3082\\u3001\\u795E\\u79D8\\u6027\\u3092\\u5426\\u5B9A\\u3057\\u3066\\u660E\\u6670\\u306A\\u5851\\u50CF\\u6027\\u3068\\u53E4\\u5178\\u7684\\u8ABF\\u548C\\u3092\\u8FFD\\u6C42\\u3057\\u305F\\u3002\\u30B0\\u30DF\\u30EA\\u30E7\\u30D5\\u3001\\u30AF\\u30BA\\u30DF\\u30F3\\u306F\\u30B0\\u30DF\\u30EA\\u30E7\\u30D5\\u306E\\u59BB\\u3001\\u30A2\\u30F3\\u30CA\\u30FB\\u30A2\\u30D5\\u30DE\\u30FC\\u30C8\\u30F4\\u30A1\\u3084\\u540C\\u56FD\\u51FA\\u8EAB\\u306E\\u8A69\\u4EBA\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u30AA\\u30B7\\u30C3\\u30D7\\u30FB\\u30DE\\u30F3\\u30C7\\u30EA\\u30B7\\u30E5\\u30BF\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u3001\\u30BB\\u30EB\\u30B2\\u30A4\\u30FB\\u30B4\\u30ED\\u30C7\\u30C4\\u30AD\\u30FC\\u3001\\u30DF\\u30CF\\u30A4\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30BC\\u30F3\\u30B1\\u30F4\\u30A3\\u30C3\\u30C1\\u3001\\u30A6\\u30E9\\u30B8\\u30FC\\u30DF\ 		"L\\u2019acm\\u00E9isme (en russe \\u0410\\u043A\\u043C\\u0435\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C, Akm\\u00E9ism) est un mouvement po\\u00E9tique russe qui a connu son heure de gloire au d\\u00E9but des ann\\u00E9es 1910 sous la direction de Nikola\\u00EF Goumilev et Sergue\\u00EF Gorodetski. Le mot tire son origine du mot grec \\u1F00\\u03BA\\u03BC\\u03AE acm\\u00E9 qui signifie \\u00AB pointe, comble, apog\\u00E9e \\u00BB. Reprochant aux symbolistes leur go\\u00FBt pour l\'incompr\\u00E9hensibilit\\u00E9 et pour des r\\u00EAveries sur d\'autres mondes, les artistes de ce mouvement aspirent \\u00E0 l\'unit\\u00E9 indivisible de la Terre et de l\'homme."@fr ,
		"Akmeismus (von griechisch \\u03B1\\u03BA\\u03BC\\u03B7 \\u201ASpitze\\u2018, \\u201AReife\\u2018, \\u201AH\\u00F6hepunkt einer Entwicklung\\u2018, russisch \\u0430\\u043A\\u043C\\u0435\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C (siehe Akme)) bezeichnet eine russische Literaturstr\\u00F6mung der Moderne zwischen 1910 und 1920.Die Gruppe der Akmeisten bildete sich ab 1911 und wollte mit der Sch\\u00F6pfung einer neuen \\u00C4sthetik in Russland die Mystik, die komplizierte Mehrdeutigkeit und den Okkultismus des Symbolismus abl\\u00F6sen. Im Gegensatz zum Symbolismus bem\\u00FChte sich der Akmeismus um Gegenst\\u00E4ndlichkeit und Klarheit der Darstellung."@de ,
		"Acmeism, or the Guild of Poets, was a transient poetic school, which emerged in 1910 in Russia under the leadership of Nikolay Gumilev and Sergei Gorodetsky. Their ideals were compactness of form and clarity of expression. The term was coined after the Greek word akme, i.e., \\"the best age of man\\".The acmeist mood was first announced by Mikhail Kuzmin in his 1910 essay \\"Concerning Beautiful Clarity\\"."@en ,

		"Het Acme\\u00EFsme (Russisch: a\\u043A\\u043C\\u0435\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C) was een beweging in de Russische dichtkunst die in 1910 ontstond onder leiding van Nikolaj Goemiljov en Sergej Gorodetski. De acme\\u00EFsten verzetten zich tegen het symbolisme en streefden in hun verzen naar opperste helderheid. Acme\\u00EFsme komt van het Griekse woord \'acme\' dat \'hoogtepunt\' betekent. Vertegenwoordigers van deze stroming zijn onder anderen Osip Mandelstam en Anna Achmatova."@nl .

	rdfs:comment	"Canadian literature is literature originating from Canada. Some criticism of Canadian literature has focused on nationalistic and regional themes, although this is only a small portion of Canadian Literary criticism."@en ,
		"A Literatura do Canad\\u00E1, como a literatura de outros pa\\u00EDses, \\u00E9 influenciada por seu contexto s\\u00F3cio-pol\\u00EDtico, os escritores do Canad\\u00E1 produziram textos em uma ampla variedade de g\\u00EAneros. As influ\\u00EAncias dos escritores do Canad\\u00E1 s\\u00E3o amplas, tanto geogr\\u00E1fica quanto historicamente.A cultura dominante do Canad\\u00E1 era originalmente brit\\u00E2nica e francesa, bem como abor\\u00EDgene."@pt ,
		"La literatura en Canad\\u00E1 se escribi\\u00F3 en varias lenguas, no solo en diversos dialectos del ingl\\u00E9s y el franc\\u00E9s (el joual, por ejemplo); tambi\\u00E9n existe una rica literatura oral en lenguas amerindias e inuit, todav\\u00EDa podo divulgada y conocida, que es patrimonio de las diversas naciones indias que viven en su territorio."@es ,

		"Der Begriff Kanadische Literatur bezeichnet Prosa, Dichtung, Drama in englischer und franz\\u00F6sischer Sprache aus Kanada. Nicht zur kanadischen Literatur werden die traditionellen Literaturen der indianischen Ureinwohner, der Esquimaux (Inuit, Yupik) und der anderen First Nations gez\\u00E4hlt."@de ,
		"La litt\\u00E9rature canadienne est habituellement divis\\u00E9e en trois grandes traditions : La litt\\u00E9rature canadienne-anglaise La litt\\u00E9rature canadienne-fran\\u00E7aise (dans les provinces hors Qu\\u00E9bec) La litt\\u00E9rature qu\\u00E9b\\u00E9coise"@fr ,
		"Le prime tracce di letteratura canadese risalgono alla seconda met\\u00E0 del Settecento.La letteratura canadese pu\\u00F2 essere divisa in due parti, a seconda della propria origine: una basata sulla cultura e letteratura della Francia, l\'altra dell\'Inghilterra. Ognuna di queste \\u00E8 scritta nel linguaggio della propria cultura di origine, in presenza di scarsi contatti e legami con l\'altra etnia e di forti dipendenze con la letteratura europea."@it ,

dbr:Cassette_culture	rdfs:label	"Culture cassette"@fr ,
		"Cassette culture"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"La culture cassette est une sous-culture musicale d\\u00E9di\\u00E9e \\u00E0 la cr\\u00E9ation et \\u00E0 l\'\\u00E9change de cassettes audio maisons g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement de rock ou de musique alternative. D\\u00E9riv\\u00E9e de l\'art postal des ann\\u00E9es 1970 et 1980, la culture cassette s\'est d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9e aux \\u00C9tats-Unis et au Royaume-Uni dans la suite du mouvement punk."@fr ,
		"Cassette culture, or the cassette underground, refers to the practices surrounding amateur production and distribution of recorded music that emerged in the late 1970s via home-made audio cassettes. It is characterized by the adoption of home recording by independent artists, and involvement in ad-hoc self-distribution and promotion networks - primarily conducted through mail (though there were a few retail outlets, such as Rough Trade and Falling A in the UK) and fanzines."@en .

		"Sztuka wsp\\u00F3\\u0142czesna \\u2013 aktualny okres w dziejach sztuki, kt\\u00F3rego pocz\\u0105tek umownie wyznaczono na po\\u0142ow\\u0119 XX wieku (po II wojnie \\u015Bwiatowej). 		"Hedendaagse kunst is alle beeldende kunst die \\"nu\\" gemaakt wordt. Ook galeries en kunstenaarsinitiatieven houden zich bezig met de presentatie ervan.In de kunstbeschouwing wordt de recente kunst vanaf de jaren 1960 of 1970 meestal hedendaagse kunst of actuele kunst genoemd."@nl ,

		"Il termine arte contemporanea si riferisce di regola, incontestata, a tutte le forme di arte iconografica dal periodo post-impressionista ai giorni nostri."@it ,
		"Contemporary art is art produced at the present period in time. Contemporary art includes, and develops from, Postmodern art, which is itself a successor to Modern art. In vernacular English, \\"modern\\" and \\"contemporary\\" are synonyms, resulting in some conflation of the terms \\"modern art\\" and \\"contemporary art\\" by non-specialists."@en ,
		"El arte contempor\\u00E1neo, en sentido literal, es el que se ha producido en nuestra \\u00E9poca: el arte actual. No obstante, el hecho de que la fijaci\\u00F3n del concepto se hizo hist\\u00F3ricamente en un determinado momento, el paso del tiempo le hace alejarse cada vez m\\u00E1s en el pasado del espectador contempor\\u00E1neo."@es ,
		"L\'expression \\u00AB art contemporain \\u00BB d\\u00E9signe de fa\\u00E7on g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rale et globale l\'ensemble des \\u0153uvres produites depuis 1945 \\u00E0 nos jours, et ce quels qu\'en soient le style et la pratique esth\\u00E9tique. Dans cette classification p\\u00E9riodique, l\'art contemporain succ\\u00E8de \\u00E0 l\'art moderne (1850-1945)."@fr ,
		"Zeitgen\\u00F6ssische Kunst ist Kunst, insbesondere Bildende Kunst, die von Zeitgenossen hergestellt und von anderen Zeitgenossen als bedeutend wahrgenommen wird. In der Regel \\u2212 falls nicht ausdr\\u00FCcklich ein definierter, zur\\u00FCckliegender, Zeitrahmen genannt wird (\\u201EZeitgen\\u00F6ssische Kunst des 19. Jahrhunderts\\u201C) \\u2212 ist damit die jeweilige Gegenwartskunst gemeint. Vergleichbare Benennungen in diesem Zusammenhang sind aktuelle Kunst sowie der englischsprachige Begriff contemporary art."@de .

		"Una cooperativa es una asociaci\\u00F3n aut\\u00F3noma de personas que se hanunido voluntariamente para formar una organizaci\\u00F3n democr\\u00E1tica cuya administraci\\u00F3n y gesti\\u00F3n debe llevarse a cabo de la forma que acuerden los socios, generalmente en el contexto de la econom\\u00EDa de mercado o la econom\\u00EDa mixta, aunque las cooperativas se han dado tambi\\u00E9n como parte complementaria de la econom\\u00EDa planificada."@es ,
		"A cooperative (\\"coop\\") or co-operative (\\"co-op\\") is an autonomous association of people who voluntarily cooperate for their mutual social, economic, and cultural benefit."@en ,
		"Per il codice civile italiano, una societ\\u00E0 cooperativa \\u00E8 una societ\\u00E0 costituita per gestire in comune un\'impresa che si prefigge lo scopo di fornire innanzitutto agli stessi soci (scopo mutualistico) quei beni o servizi per il conseguimento dei quali la cooperativa \\u00E8 sorta.Fino al 2001 il codice civile della Repubblica Italiana prevedeva che per costituire una cooperativa ci volesse un minimo di 9 soci, mentre dal 2001 con un numero di soci da 3 a 8 si poteva costituire una piccola societ\\u00E0 cooperativa con la stessa operativit\\u00E0: con la riforma del diritto societario l\'istituto giuridico della piccola cooperativa \\u00E8 stato abrogato e si \\u00E8 prevista la possibilit\\u00E0 di costituire societ\\u00E0 cooperative anche con un numero minimo di 3 soci.Capisaldi del sistema cooperativo sono i principi di mutualit\\u00E0, solidariet\\u00E0, democrazia."@it ,
		"De co\\u00F6peratie is een vorm van zelforganisatie van producenten of verbruikers, gericht op het vergroten van economische macht en het behalen van schaalvoordeel. De wet in Belgi\\u00EB, Nederland en andere landen maakt het bestaan van een \\u2018co\\u00F6peratieve vereniging\\u2019 mogelijk.Co\\u00F6peraties hebben een belangrijke rol gespeeld in de economische emancipatie van grote groepen van de bevolking, vooral rond de eeuwwisseling van de 19de naar de 20e eeuw."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"Das Wort Krimi ist umgangssprachlich und steht abk\\u00FCrzend f\\u00FCr \\u201EKriminalfilm, Kriminalroman\\u201C, also ein Genre, das vor allem in den popul\\u00E4ren Medien bzw. in der Unterhaltungsindustrie verbreitet ist und einen aufkl\\u00E4rerischen Spannungsbogen hat. Krimis werden h\\u00E4ufig als Serien dargeboten und k\\u00F6nnen u. a. in Detektiv-, Gangster-, Polizei- und Spionagegeschichten unterteilt werden. Dabei sind die Grenzen zu anderen Genres oft flie\\u00DFend, z. B. zum Drama oder Thriller."@de ,
		"Crime fiction is the literary genre that fictionalises crimes, their detection, criminals, and their motives. It is usually distinguished from mainstream fiction and other genres such as historical fiction or science fiction, but the boundaries are indistinct."@en ,
		"Krimi (van Duits Kriminal, \\"crimineel\\") is de Duitstalige benaming van het misdaadgenre. In het Nederlands wordt de term \\"krimi\\" gebruikt om de typisch Duitse kijk op het genre te onderscheiden van de typisch Britse variant (detective) en de Amerikaanse variant (thriller). In het Nederlands spreken we ook wel van een politieserie."@nl ,

		"Grawerstwo (inaczej rytownictwo) \\u2013 zaw\\u00F3d zaliczany do rzemios\\u0142 metalowych. 	rdfs:comment	"M\\u00FAsica industrial \\u00E9 um termo usado para definir o g\\u00EAnero de alguns estilos musicais eletr\\u00F4nicos e experimentais criados desde o final da d\\u00E9cada de 1970 at\\u00E9 os dias de hoje, como o som experimental de Throbbing Gristle, Einst\\u00FCrzende Neubauten ou at\\u00E9 o neofolk de bandas como Forseti.O industrial n\\u00E3o \\u00E9 necessariamente eletr\\u00F4nico, mas sempre prima pela utiliza\\u00E7\\u00E3o de ru\\u00EDdos, sons inesperados e estruturas anti-mel\\u00F3dicas."@pt ,
		"M\\u00FAsica industrial es un estilo de m\\u00FAsica experimental que hace uso de temas transgresivos y suele estar asociada con angustia e ira contraculturales. Aunque ideol\\u00F3gicamente asociada al punk, la m\\u00FAsica industrial es generalmente m\\u00E1s compleja y diversa, tanto a nivel sonoro como l\\u00EDrico."@es ,
		"Industrial \\u2013 awangardowy styl w muzyce elektronicznej, czerpi\\u0105cy inspiracje z fascynacji, a jednocze\\u015Bnie rozczarowania zdehumanizowan\\u0105 cywilizacj\\u0105 przemys\\u0142ow\\u0105, z jednej strony d\\u0105\\u017C\\u0105c\\u0105 do technicznej doskona\\u0142o\\u015Bci, a z drugiej spychaj\\u0105c\\u0105 jednostk\\u0119 ludzk\\u0105 na dalszy plan."@pl ,
		"La musique industrielle est un style de musique \\u00E9lectronique aux th\\u00E8mes transgressifs et provocateurs."@fr ,
		"Industrial is een muziekstijl die aan de gevestigde conventies van de rock wilde ontsnappen. Door verregaande experimenten met geluid, tapeloops en vroege elektronische instrumenten wilde men tot een nieuwe vorm van muziek komen."@nl ,
		"Industrial music is a genre of experimental music that draws on transgressive and provocative themes. The term was coined in the mid-1970s with the founding of Industrial Records by Genesis P-Orridge of Throbbing Gristle and Monte Cazazza; on Throbbing Gristle\'s debut album The Second Annual Report, they coined the slogan \\"industrial music for industrial people\\". In general, the style is harsh and challenging."@en ,
		"\\u30A4\\u30F3\\u30C0\\u30B9\\u30C8\\u30EA\\u30A2\\u30EB\\uFF08Industrial\\uFF09\\u306F\\u3001\\u96FB\\u5B50\\u97F3\\u697D\\u306E\\u4E00\\u7A2E\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u30CE\\u30A4\\u30BA\\u30DF\\u30E5\\u30FC\\u30B8\\u30C3\\u30AF\\u3068\\u95A2\\u9023\\u6027\\u304C\\u5927\\u304D\\u3044\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Industrial ist eine Kunst- und Musikrichtung, die sich ab der Mitte der 1970er-Jahre weltweit aus Elementen der experimentellen und Avantgarde-Musik sowie der Konzept- und Aktionskunst entwickelte. Der Begriff entstammt urspr\\u00FCnglich dem englischen Label Industrial Records, das kollektiv von den Mitgliedern der Band Throbbing Gristle gegr\\u00FCndet und gef\\u00FChrt wurde, die eine zentrale Position im fr\\u00FChen Industrial innehatten."@de ,
		"La musica industriale, conosciuta spesso con il nome inglese industrial music (o semplicemente industrial), \\u00E8 uno stile di musica sperimentale nato negli anni \'70 intorno all\'etichetta discografica Industrial Records dei Throbbing Gristle e sviluppato da una ristretta cerchia di artisti inglesi ed americani."@it .

Les Automatistes were so called because they were influenced by Surrealism and its theory of automatism."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Il mosaico \\u00E8 una composizione pittorica ottenuta mediante l\'utilizzo di frammenti di materiali (tessere) di diversa natura e colore (pietre, vetro, conchiglie), che pu\\u00F2 essere decorata con oro e pietre preziose."@it ,
		"Mosaic is the art of creating images with an assemblage of small pieces of colored glass, stone, or other materials. It is a technique of decorative art or interior decoration. Most mosaics are made of small, flat, roughly square, pieces of stone or glass of different colors, known as tesserae; but some, especially floor mosaics, may also be made of small rounded pieces of stone, and called \\"pebble mosaics\\".Mosaic has a long history, starting in Mesopotamia in the 3rd millennium BC."@en ,

		"Moza\\u00EFek is een kunstvorm waarbij een grote afbeelding wordt vervaardigd uit een groot aantal kleine gekleurde steentjes (tesserae), die in een vloer of wand worden gemetseld. Met glas is het mogelijk een glas in lood-moza\\u00EFek te maken.In de Griekse en Romeinse tijd werden in luxe villa\'s moza\\u00EFeken gemaakt, waarop afbeeldingen van keizers, goden of taferelen van alledag te zien waren."@nl ,
		"Mosaico  \\u00E9 possivelmente uma palavra de origem grega  (de \\u00B5\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1\\u03B9\\u03BA\\u03CC\\u03BD, transl. mousaik\\u00F3n, \\"obra das musas\\"),  embora a t\\u00E9cnica seja antiqu\\u00EDssima. \\u00C9 um embutido de pequenas pe\\u00E7as (tesselas) de pedra ou de outros materiais como (pl\\u00E1stico, areia, papel ou conchas), formando determinado desenho. O objetivo do desenho \\u00E9 preencher algum tipo de plano (geralmente, piso ou parede).\\u00C9 uma modalidade de arte decorativa milenar, que nos remete \\u00E0  Antiguidade  greco-romana, quando teve seu apogeu."@pt ,
		"La mosa\\u00EFque est un art d\\u00E9coratif dans lequel on utilise des fragments de pierre color\\u00E9es, d\'\\u00E9mail, de verre, de pierre (marbre, granito) ou encore de c\\u00E9ramique, assembl\\u00E9s \\u00E0 l\'aide de mastic ou d\'enduit, pour former des motifs ou des figures."@fr ,
		"Un mosaico (del lat\\u00EDn mosa\\u012Dcum [opus], \\u2018[obra] relativa a las Musas, art\\u00EDstica\\u2019) es una obra pict\\u00F3rica elaborada con peque\\u00F1as piezas de piedra, cer\\u00E1mica, vidrio u otros materiales similares de diversas formas y colores, llamadas teselas, unidas mediante yeso, u otro aglomerante, para formar composiciones decorativas geom\\u00E9tricas o figurativas. Cuando las piezas empleadas son de madera se denomina taracea."@es ,
		"Mosaik ist eine schon im Altertum bekannte Gattung der Maltechnik, bei der durch Zusammenf\\u00FCgen von verschiedenfarbigen oder verschieden geformten Teilen (Stein- oder Glasst\\u00FCcken, auch Teilen von Papier oder Stoffen) Muster oder Bilder entstehen. Das Wort Mosaik leitet sich aus dem sp\\u00E4tlateinischen Musaicum (opus) (Werk den Musen gewidmet) ab. Als musivische Technik bezeichnet man das Zusammensetzen von verschiedenfarbigen flachen Pl\\u00E4ttchen (aus Stein, Metall, Holz, etc.) zu dekorativen Mustern."@de ,

		"\\u041D\\u043E\\u0439\\u0437"@ru ,
		"\\u30CE\\u30A4\\u30BA\\u30DF\\u30E5\\u30FC\\u30B8\\u30C3\\u30AF"@ja ,

		"Noise"@pl ,
		"Noise (Musik)"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"Noise music is a category of music that is characterised by the expressive use of noise within a musical context. This type of music tends to challenge the distinction that is made in conventional musical practices between musical and non-musical sound. Noise music includes a wide range of musical styles and sound-based creative practices that feature noise as a primary aspect."@en ,
		"\\u041D\\u043E\\u0439\\u0437 (\\u043E\\u0442 \\u0430\\u043D\\u0433\\u043B. \\u00ABnoise\\u00BB \\u2014 \\u0448\\u0443\\u043C) \\u2014 \\u043E\\u0434\\u0438\\u043D \\u0438\\u0437 \\u0441\\u0442\\u0430\\u0440\\u0435\\u0439\\u0448\\u0438\\u0445 \\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u043B\\u0435\\u0439 \\u0432 \\u0438\\u043D\\u0434\\u0430\\u0441\\u0442\\u0440\\u0438\\u0430\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u043C\\u0443\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u0435; \\u043C\\u0443\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u0430\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u044B\\u0439 \\u0436\\u0430\\u043D\\u0440, \\u0432 \\u043A\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u043E\\u043C \\u0438\\u0441\\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u044C\\u0437\\u0443\\u044E\\u0442\\u0441\\u044F \\u0440\\u0430\\u0437\\u043D\\u043E\\u043E\\u0431\\u0440\\u0430\\u0437\\u043D\\u044B\\u0435 \\u0437\\u0432\\u0443\\u043A\\u0438 (\\u0447\\u0430\\u0449\\u0435 \\u0432\\u0441\\u0435\\u0433\\u043E \\u0438\\u0441\\u043A\\u0443\\u0441\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0438 \\u0442\\u0435\\u0445\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0438\\u0441\\u0445\\u043E\\u0436\\u0434\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u044F), \\u043D\\u0435\\u043F\\u0440\\u0438\\u044F\\u0442\\u043D\\u044B\\u0435 \\u0438 \\u0434\\u0430\\u0436\\u0435 \\u0431\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0437\\u043D\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u044B\\u0435 \\u0434\\u043B\\u044F \\u0447\\u0435\\u043B\\u043E\\u0432\\u0435\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0441\\u043B\\u0443\\u0445\\u0430."@ru ,

		"Il termine rumorismo, bruitismo (dal francese bruitisme, a sua volta derivato da bruit, rumore) o noise music (traduzione in lingua inglese), designa l\'\\u201Carte dei rumori\\u201D inaugurata negli anni dieci del Novecento dal compositore e pittore futurista Luigi Russolo. Queste arti sonore sono caratterizzate dall\'impiego di elementi come cacofonia, dissonanza, atonalit\\u00E0, rumore, indeterminazione e ripetizione nella propria realizzazione."@it ,
		"Noise \\u00E9 o nome dado a um estilo musical que utiliza majoritariamente sons considerados, em circunst\\u00E2ncias comuns, desconfort\\u00E1veis ou irritantes. 		"Noise is een kunstmuziekstroming die uitstekend wordt gekenschetst door de Engelse naam: noise betekent ruis. Het is vaak moeilijk te beluisteren muziek waarbij wordt gezondigd tegen alle regels die traditioneel in de muziek gelden. Veel geluiden van niet-muzikale bronnen worden gebruikt in noise-muziek, zie ook soundscapes."@nl ,
		"Noise \\u2014en espa\\u00F1ol: ruido\\u2014, tambi\\u00E9n conocido como ruidismo, es una categor\\u00EDa de m\\u00FAsica que se caracteriza por el uso expresivo del ruido dentro de un contexto musical. Este tipo de m\\u00FAsica tiende a cuestionar la distinci\\u00F3n que se hace en las pr\\u00E1cticas musicales convencionales entre el sonido musical y no musical. La m\\u00FAsica noise incluye una amplia gama de estilos musicales y pr\\u00E1cticas creativas basadas en sonidos, que cuentan con el ruido como un aspecto primordial."@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"Queer is een parapluterm voor onder andere homoseksualiteit en/of travestie, maar ook mensen uit de punkscene identificeren zich vaak als queer. De term is meestal bedoeld om zich af te zetten tegen de standaard heteronorm en trekt tegelijkertijd elk mogelijk hokje in twijfel. Progressieve queers beschouwen de homowereld als rolbevestigend en commercieel."@nl ,
		"Queer is an umbrella term for sexual and gender minorities that are not heterosexual or cisgender. Originally meaning strange or peculiar, queer came to be deployed pejoratively against those with same-sex desires or relationships in the late-19th century. Beginning in the late-1980s, queer scholars and activists began to reclaim the word to establish community and assert a politicized identity distinct from the gay political identity."@en ,
		"Queer es un t\\u00E9rmino global para designar las minor\\u00EDas sexuales que no son heterosexuales, heteronormadas o de g\\u00E9nero binario. En el contexto de la identidad pol\\u00EDtica occidental, la gente que se identifica como queer suele buscar situarse aparte del discurso, la ideolog\\u00EDa y el estilo de vida que tipifican las grandes corrientes en las comunidades LGBT (lesbianas, gais, bisexuales y transexuales), que consideran opresivas o con tendencia a la asimilaci\\u00F3n."@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"Le r\\u00E9alisme socialiste sovi\\u00E9tique est un mouvement artistique impos\\u00E9 d\'abord en Union sovi\\u00E9tique puis dans les autres pays dits \\u00AB socialistes \\u00BB, \\u00AB communistes \\u00BB ou \\u00AB d\\u00E9mocraties populaires \\u00BB qui, officiellement, a pour objectif de peindre la \\u00AB r\\u00E9alit\\u00E9 sociale \\u00BB en accord avec l\'id\\u00E9ologie communiste, cette r\\u00E9alit\\u00E9 sociale \\u00E9tant la vie des classes populaires, d\\u00E9peinte dans toute sa mis\\u00E8re tant que les partis socialistes ou communistes \\u00E9taient dans l\'opposition ou en lutte pour le pouvoir, puis de mani\\u00E8re fallacieusement idyllique \\u00E0 travers le \\u00AB Proletkoult \\u00BB stalinien, une fois ce pouvoir conquis.Expression de conflits id\\u00E9ologiques d\'une grande violence, le r\\u00E9alisme socialiste sovi\\u00E9tique prend sa source dans les ann\\u00E9es 1910. "@fr ,
		"Socialist realism is a style of realistic art that was developed in the Soviet Union and became a dominant style in various other socialist countries.  Socialist realism is characterized by the glorified depiction of communist values, such as the emancipation of the proletariat, in a realistic manner. Although related, it should not be confused with social realism, a broader type of art that realistically depicts subjects of social concern."@en ,
		"El realismo socialista es una corriente est\\u00E9tica cuyo prop\\u00F3sito es expandir el conocimiento de los problemas sociales y las vivencias de las personas por medio del arte. Fue la tendencia art\\u00EDstica impuesta oficialmente durante gran parte de la historia de la Uni\\u00F3n Sovi\\u00E9tica, particularmente durante el gobierno de I\\u00F3sif Stalin, en la Rep\\u00FAblica Popular China y, en general, en la mayor\\u00EDa de los pa\\u00EDses socialistas."@es ,

		"Het socialistisch realisme (Russisch: \\u0421\\u043E\\u0446\\u0438\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0439 \\u0440\\u0435\\u0430\\u043B\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C) was de offici\\u00EBle en ook in de praktijk toonaangevende kunst- en literatuurstroming in de Sovjet-Unie, vanaf de jaren \'20 tot de opheffing van de Sovjet-Unie in 1991. De stroming kreeg na de Tweede Wereldoorlog grote invloed in de DDR en de andere staten van het Warschaupact."@nl ,
		"\\u793E\\u4F1A\\u4E3B\\u7FA9\\u30EA\\u30A2\\u30EA\\u30BA\\u30E0\\uFF08\\u3057\\u3083\\u304B\\u3044\\u3057\\u3085\\u304E\\u30EA\\u30A2\\u30EA\\u30BA\\u30E0\\uFF09\\u3068\\u306F\\u3001\\u30BD\\u30D3\\u30A8\\u30C8\\u9023\\u90A6\\u306A\\u3069\\u306E\\u793E\\u4F1A\\u4E3B\\u7FA9\\u56FD\\u306B\\u304A\\u3044\\u3066\\u516C\\u5F0F\\u3068\\u3055\\u308C\\u305F\\u7F8E\\u8853\\u30FB\\u97F3\\u697D\\u30FB\\u6587\\u5B66\\u306A\\u3069\\u306E\\u8868\\u73FE\\u65B9\\u6CD5\\u3001\\u8A55\\u8AD6\\u306E\\u6307\\u91DD\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u793E\\u4F1A\\u4E3B\\u7FA9\\u3092\\u79F0\\u8CDB\\u3057\\u3001\\u9769\\u547D\\u56FD\\u5BB6\\u304C\\u52DD\\u5229\\u306B\\u5411\\u304B\\u3063\\u3066\\u9032\\u3093\\u3067\\u3044\\u308B\\u73FE\\u72B6\\u3092\\u5E73\\u6613\\u306B\\u63CF\\u304D\\u3001\\u4EBA\\u6C11\\u3092\\u601D\\u60F3\\u7684\\u306B\\u56FA\\u3081\\u9769\\u547D\\u610F\\u8B58\\u3092\\u6301\\u305F\\u305B\\u308B\\u3079\\u304F\\u6559\\u80B2\\u3059\\u308B\\u76EE\\u7684\\u3092\\u6301\\u3063\\u305F\\u82B8\\u8853\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Il realismo socialista fu un movimento artistico e culturale nato nell\'Unione Sovietica nel 1934 e poi allargatosi a tutti i paesi socialisti del centro ed est Europa. La funzione principale era quella di avvicinare l\'espressione artistica alla cultura delle classi proletarie e celebrare il progresso socialista.La prima formulazione ufficiale si ebbe al Congresso degli Scrittori e degli Artisti Sovietici a Mosca nel 1934, ad opera di Maksim Gor\'kij."@it ,
		"Sozialistischer Realismus (kurz auch Sozrealismus genannt) war eine ideologisch begr\\u00FCndete Stilrichtung der Kunst des 20. Jahrhunderts mit dem Versuch einer starken Wirklichkeitsn\\u00E4he und dem Fehlen von Abstraktion und \\u00C4sthetisierung. Der sozialistische Realismus stellte Themen aus dem Arbeitsleben und der Technik des sozialistischen Alltags in den Vordergrund, etwa optimistisch nach vorn blickende Arbeiter eines Kolchos auf einem Traktor."@de ,

		"A tape\\u00E7aria \\u00E9 a arte de se fazer tapetes para enfeitar, sendo uma forma de arte extremamente rica. O termo tamb\\u00E9m \\u00E9 utilizado para denominar o of\\u00EDcio do tapeceiro que forra e cria pe\\u00E7as de mobili\\u00E1rio.O tapete de Arraiolos \\u00E9 a forma mais famosa em Portugal de tape\\u00E7aria. As Tape\\u00E7arias de Pastrana s\\u00E3o um exemplo espetacular de arte da tape\\u00E7aria. A Tape\\u00E7aria tambem \\u00E9 da mesma forma usada em carros, em montagem desmontagens e etc.."@pt ,
		"La tapisserie est un tissu fabriqu\\u00E9 sur un m\\u00E9tier \\u00E0 tisser ou bien \\u00E0 la main, dont le tissage repr\\u00E9sente des motifs ornementaux. Le tissage se compose de deux ensembles de fils entrelac\\u00E9s, ceux parall\\u00E8les \\u00E0 la longueur, les fils de cha\\u00EEne, et ceux parall\\u00E8les \\u00E0 la largeur, les fils de trame. Les fils de cha\\u00EEne sont mis en place sous tension sur un m\\u00E9tier, et le fil de trame est transmis par un mouvement m\\u00E9canique de va-et-vient sur tout ou partie de l\'ouvrage."@fr ,

		"Tapestry is a form of textile art,  traditionally woven on a vertical loom. However, it can also be woven on a floor loom.  It is composed of two sets of interlaced threads, those running parallel to the length (called the warp) and those parallel to the width (called the weft); the warp threads are set up under tension on a loom, and the weft thread is passed back and forth across part or all of the warps."@en ,
		"El tapiz (del franc\\u00E9s tapis, que a su vez deriva del griego bizantino \\u03C4\\u03AC\\u03C0\\u03B7\\u03C2) es una obra de tejido tradicionalmente hecha a mano en la que se producen figuras semejantes a las de una pintura utilizando hilos de distintos colores."@es ,
		"Der von der Wissenschaft wiederaufgenommene mittelalterliche Ausdruck Bildwirkerei bezeichnet sowohl die Technik des Einwirkens von Bildern und Motiven in ein textiles Fl\\u00E4chengebilde als auch das Erzeugnis dieser Technik, die Tapisserie. Die Bildwirkerei ist nicht zu verwechseln mit der Teppichwirkerei, bei der Motive in orientalische Flachteppiche gewirkt werden."@de ,
		"Een wandtapijt is een handgeweven tapijt, waarbij echter niet, zoals bij gewoon weven, de inslagdraad over de gehele breedte van de ketting of schering loopt, maar in korte stukjes, zo lang totdat er weer van kleur gewisseld wordt. Ieder stukje wordt twee keer over de ketting gelegd: \\u00E9\\u00E9n keer over de even draden en dan terugwerkend over de oneven kettingdraden."@nl ,

		"Teatro dell\'assurdo \\u00E8 la denominazione di un particolare tipo di opere scritte da alcuni drammaturghi, soprattutto europei, sul finire degli anni \'40, \'50 e \'60. Con lo stesso termine si identifica anche tutto lo stile teatrale nato dall\'evoluzione dei loro lavori.Il termine \\u00E8 stato coniato dal critico Martin Esslin, che ne fece il titolo di una sua pubblicazione del 1961: \\"The Theatre of the Absurd\\"."@it ,
		"Teatro do absurdo foi a designa\\u00E7\\u00E3o criada em 1961 pelo cr\\u00EDtico h\\u00FAngaro, radicado na Inglaterra, Martin Esslin (1918-2002), tentando sintetizar uma defini\\u00E7\\u00E3o que agrupasse as obras de dramaturgos de diversos pa\\u00EDses que, apesar de serem completamente diferentes em suas formas, tinham como centro de sua obra o tratamento  inusitado de aspectos inesperados da vida humana."@pt ,
		"El Teatro del absurdo abarca un conjunto de obras escritas por ciertos dramaturgos estadounidenses y europeos durante las d\\u00E9cadas de 1940, 1950 y 1960 y, en general, el que surgi\\u00F3 a partir de la obra de aquellos. Se caracteriza por tramas que parecen carecer de significado, di\\u00E1logos repetitivos y falta de secuencia dram\\u00E1tica que a menudo crean una atm\\u00F3sfera on\\u00EDrica. El teatro del absurdo tiene fuertes rasgos existencialistas y cuestiona la sociedad y al hombre."@es ,

		"Das absurde Theater ist eine Richtung des Theaters des 20. Jahrhunderts, die die Sinnfreiheit der Welt und den darin orientierungslosen Menschen darstellen will."@de ,
		"Le th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre de l\\u2019absurde est un style de th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre apparu au XXe si\\u00E8cle, \\u00E0 l\'\\u00E9poque de la Seconde Guerre mondiale, qui se caract\\u00E9rise par une rupture totale par rapport aux genres plus classiques, tels que le drame ou la com\\u00E9die. C\'est un genre traitant fr\\u00E9quemment de l\\u2019absurdit\\u00E9 de l\\u2019Homme et de la vie en g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ral, celle-ci menant toujours \\u00E0 la mort. L\\u2019origine de ce mouvement est sans conteste intrins\\u00E8quement li\\u00E9e \\u00E0 la chute de l\\u2019humanisme et au traumatisme caus\\u00E9 par la Premi\\u00E8re Guerre mondiale."@fr ,
		"Absurd toneel (ook anti-theater of nouveau th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre) is een toneelgenre waarin de onlogische en irrationele aspecten van het leven benadrukt worden, vaak om de doelloosheid van het leven aan te tonen. Het absurd toneel werd populair in het eerste decennium na de Tweede Wereldoorlog, gelijktijdig met de absurdistische filosofische stroming.In het absurd toneel wordt vaak uitgegaan van realistische karakters, situaties en theatrale conventies."@nl ,

		"The Theatre of the Absurd (French: Th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre de l\'Absurde) is a designation for particular plays of absurdist fiction written by a number of primarily European playwrights in the late 1950s, as well as one for the style of theatre which has evolved from their work. Their work expressed what happens when human existence has no meaning or purpose and therefore all communication breaks down, in fact alerting their audiences to pursue the opposite."@en ,

		"Hardboiled (or hard-boiled) fiction is a literary genre that shares some of its characters and settings with crime fiction (especially detective stories). Derived from the romantic tradition which emphasized the emotions of apprehension, awe, horror and terror, hardboiled fiction deviates from that tradition in the detective\'s cynical attitude towards those emotions."@en ,
		"L\'espressione inglese hard boiled (anche hard-boiled o hardboiled) si riferisce ad un genere letterario che trova le proprie radici nei romanzi di Dashiell Hammett verso la fine degli anni venti e che venne perfezionato da Raymond Chandler nei tardi anni trenta."@it .

dbr:Poporanism	rdfs:label	"Poporanism"@en ,
		"Poporanismus"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"The word \\u201Cpoporanism\\u201D is derived from \\u201Cpopor\\u201D, meaning \\u201Cpeople\\u201D in the Romanian language. Founded by Constantin Stere in the early 1890s, poporanism is distinguished by its opposition to socialism, promotion of voting rights for all, and intent to reform the parliament and farming system.  Regarding Romania\\u2019s agrarian situation, poporanists wished to form cooperative farms for the peasants, intending to remove them from aristocratic control."@en ,
		"Der Poporanismus (von rum\\u00E4nisch popor, deutsch Volk) war mit dem S\\u00E4m\\u00E4n\\u00E4torismus eine ideologische und k\\u00FCnstlerische Str\\u00F6mung in Rum\\u00E4nien vom Ende des 19. Jahrhunderts bis \\u00FCber die Zwischenkriegszeit hinaus, welche eine Aufwertung des l\\u00E4ndlichen Raums und der traditionellen b\\u00E4uerlichen Welt gegen\\u00FCber der europ\\u00E4isch gepr\\u00E4gten modernen st\\u00E4dtischen Zivilisation zum Kern hatte."@de .
dbr:Serb-Catholic_movement_in_Dubrovnik	rdfs:label	"Serb-Catholic movement in Dubrovnik"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Serb-Catholic movement in Dubrovnik (Serbo-Croatian: Dubrova\\u010Dki srbokatoli\\u010Dki pokret) was a pan-Serb cultural and political campaign in Dubrovnik active at various periods between the 1830s and the interwar period. The group of local Catholic intellectuals, known as Serb-Catholics, espoused a Serb sentiment."@en .

dbr:Four_Masters_of_the_Ming_dynasty	rdfs:label	"\\u660E\\u56DB\\u5BB6"@zh ,
		"Four Masters of the Ming dynasty"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Four Masters of the Ming dynasty (Chinese: \\u660E\\u56DB\\u5BB6; Pinyin: M\\u00EDng S\\u00EC Ji\\u0101; \\"S\\u00EC\\" in Chinese is \\"four\\") are a traditional grouping in Chinese art history of four famous Chinese painters during the Ming dynasty.  The group are Shen Zhou (1427-1509), Wen Zhengming (1470-1559), both of the Wu School, Tang Yin (1470-1523), and Qiu Ying (c.1494-c.1552). They were approximate contemporaries, with Shen Zhou the teacher of Wen Zhengming, while the other two studied with Zhou Chen (\\u5468\\u81E3)."@en .

dbr:Funk_art	rdfs:label	"Funk art"@en ,
		"Funk art"@es ;
	rdfs:comment	"Funk art is an American art movement that was a reaction against the nonobjectivity of abstract expressionism. An anti-establishment movement, Funk art brought figuration back as subject matter in painting again rather than limiting itself to the non-figurative, abstract forms that abstract expressionists such as Jackson Pollock and Mark Rothko were depicting. The movement\\u2019s name was derived from the jazz musical term \\"funky\\", describing the passionate, sensuous, and quirky."@en ,
		"El Funk art es un movimiento art\\u00EDstico bastante inspirado por la cultura popular que usa una improbable mezcla de materiales y t\\u00E9cnicas, incluyendo \\u00ABobjetos encontrados\\u00BB. Fue una reacci\\u00F3n frente a la falta de objetividad del expresionismo abstracto. El nombre del movimiento deriva del t\\u00E9rmino musical \\u00ABfunky\\u00BB, que describe lo apasionado, sensual y estrafalario. En este contexto, significa \\u00ABgallina, maloliente, escandaloso, s\\u00F3rdido\\u00BB."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Memphis, noto anche come Gruppo Memphis, Memphis Design o Memphis Milano, \\u00E8 stato un collettivo italiano di design e architettura fondato da Ettore Sottsass, attivo tra il 1981 e il 1987.Il gruppo emerse come uno dei massimi esponenti della scena postmodernista degli anni ottanta, grazie a progetti audaci che traevano spunto dal design passato e presente; suoi tratti distintivi furono il ricorso a colori vivaci e forme geometriche, con un sapiente recupero del kitsch."@it ,

		"De Memphisgroep was een groep vormgevers uit de jaren 1981-1988,  opgericht door Ettore Sottsass.De naam van de beweging Memphis, is afkomstig van een lied van Bob Dylan: \\u2018Stuck Inside of Mobile with the Memphis Blues Again\\u2019. De plaat met dit nummer lag op de draaitafel toen op een avond in de herfst van 1981 de plannen voor de nieuwe onderneming hun definitieve vorm kregen."@nl ,
		"Le Groupe de Memphis a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 cr\\u00E9\\u00E9 en Italie au cours des ann\\u00E9es 1980 un mouvement de design et d\'architecture influent."@fr ,
		"The Memphis Group was an Italian design and architecture group founded in Milan by Ettore Sottsass in 1981 that designed Postmodern furniture, fabrics, ceramics, glass and metal objects from 1981 to 1987.The Memphis group\'s work often incorporated plastic laminate and was characterized by ephemeral design featuring colourful decoration and asymmetrical shapes, sometimes arbitrarily alluding to exotic or earlier styles."@en ,
		"El Grupo Memphis fue un movimiento de arquitectura y dise\\u00F1o industrial con mucha influencia de los a\\u00F1os 1980s.El grupo fue fundado por Ettore Sottsass en diciembre de 1980, y se resolvi\\u00F3 que los integrantes se reunir\\u00EDan otra vez con sus dise\\u00F1os en febrero de 1981 El resultado fue un debut altamente aclamado en el \\"Salone del Mobile\\" (En espa\\u00F1ol, Sal\\u00F3n del Mueble) de Mil\\u00E1n, la feria de mobiliario m\\u00E1s prestigiosa del mundo."@es ,
		"Die Mail\\u00E4nder Gruppe Memphis war ein 1980  gegr\\u00FCndeter Zusammenschluss von M\\u00F6bel-, Textil und Keramikdesignern. Ebenso bezeichnet Memphis die Kollektion der Gruppe sowie deren Firma (1981-88). \\u00C4hnlich der Vorg\\u00E4ngerbewegung Studio Alchimia brach Memphis mit den vorherrschenden Regeln des Funktionalismus. Im Gegensatz zu Alchimia wollte Memphis jedoch aus der internationalen Anerkennung des Italienischen Anti-Designs Profit schlagen und seine Produkte gewinnbringend vermarkten."@de .

	rdfs:comment	"Scar literature or literature of the wounded (Chinese: \\u4F24\\u75D5\\u6587\\u5B66; pinyin: sh\\u0101ngh\\u00E9n w\\u00E9nxu\\u00E9) is a genre of Chinese literature which emerged in the late 1970s, soon after the death of Mao Zedong, portraying the sufferings of cadres and intellectuals during the tragic experiences of the Cultural Revolution and the rule of the Gang of Four.The first exemplar of the genre is generally agreed to be Lu Xinhua\'s 1978 story \\"Scar\\", which attacked official hypocrisy and corruption."@en ,
		"Narbenliteratur (chinesisch: \\u4F24\\u75D5\\u6587\\u5B66; Pinyin: sh\\u0101ngh\\u00E9n w\\u00E9nxu\\u00E9) ist ein Begriff aus der chinesischen Literatur. Er fasst die unmittelbar nach der Kulturrevolution entstandenen literarischen Werke, in denen mit den Verbrechen der Kulturrevolution abgerechnet wird. Namensgeberin f\\u00FCr diese literarische Bewegung ist die Erz\\u00E4hlung Narben (\\u4F24\\u75D5 \\u201AShanghen\\u2018), in deren Mittelpunkt das Schicksal eines zu Beginn der Kulturrevolution sechzehnj\\u00E4hrigen M\\u00E4dchens namens Xiaohua steht."@de ,
		"La litt\\u00E9rature des cicatrices (chinois simplifi\\u00E9 : \\u4F24\\u75D5\\u6587\\u5B66 ; chinois traditionnel : \\u50B7\\u75D5\\u6587\\u5B78 ; pinyin : Sh\\u0101ngh\\u00E9n w\\u00E9nxu\\u00E9)  est apparue en Chine \\u00E0 la fin des ann\\u00E9es 1970, alors qu\'un regain de libert\\u00E9 voyait le jour vis-\\u00E0-vis des intellectuels et des \\u00E9crivains notamment, \\u00E0 la suite du proc\\u00E8s de la bande des quatre et la critique officielle de Mao Zedong, apr\\u00E8s sa mort en 1976."@fr .

		"O tradicionalismo \\u00E9 um sistema filos\\u00F3fico ou pol\\u00EDtico que coloca a tradi\\u00E7\\u00E3o como crit\\u00E9rio e regra de decis\\u00E3o, entendendo-a como o conjunto de h\\u00E1bitos e tend\\u00EAncias que procuram manter uma sociedade no equil\\u00EDbrio das for\\u00E7as que lhe deram origem. Segundo os tradicionalistas, as sociedades n\\u00E3o resultam de um acto de exclusiva vontade pessoal ou de uma imposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o deliberada de um grupo. Consideram que a sociedade \\u00E9 uma cria\\u00E7\\u00E3o e n\\u00E3o uma constru\\u00E7\\u00E3o ou um mecanismo."@pt ,
		"Tradicionalismo, en la historia de la filosof\\u00EDa, es la tendencia a valorar la tradici\\u00F3n en cuanto conjunto de normas y costumbres heredadas del pasado. El tradicionalismo se basa en que la verdad proviene de una fuente divina (revelaci\\u00F3n)."@es ,
		"Traditioneel conservatisme wordt door sommige mensen genoemd als een stroming binnen het Amerikaans conservatisme."@nl ,
		"Il tradizionalismo e (in Canada e nel Regno Unito) come toryismo, descrive una filosofia politica e culturale situata nell\'alveo del conservatorismo, che sottolinea la necessit\\u00E0 - filosofica, etica e pratica - dei principi della legge naturale e dell\'ordine morale trascendente, della tradizione, dell\'unit\\u00E0 organica e gerarchica, della vita rurale, del classicismo e della cultura elevata, e della fedelt\\u00E0."@it .

		"Ein Abstract ist eine pr\\u00E4gnante Inhaltsangabe, ein Abriss ohne Interpretation und Wertung einer wissenschaftlichen Arbeit. In DIN 1426 wird das (oder auch der) Abstract als Kurzreferat (auch als Synonym verwandt) zur Inhaltsangabe beschrieben."@de ,
		"Um abstract \\u00E9 um breve resumo de um artigo de pesquisa, tese, revis\\u00E3o, confer\\u00EAncia, proceeding ou qualquer an\\u00E1lise aprofundada sobre um determinado assunto ou disciplina, e \\u00E9 frequentemente usado para ajudar o leitor a tomar conhecimento rapidamente do prop\\u00F3sito do artigo. Quando utilizado, um abstract sempre aparece no in\\u00EDcio de um manuscrito, que actua como o ponto de entrada para qualquer artigo cient\\u00EDfico ou pedido de patente dado."@pt ,
		"El resumen documental o abstract (t\\u00E9rmino anglosaj\\u00F3n aceptado internacionalmente) es una representaci\\u00F3n abreviada, objetiva y precisa del contenido de un documento o recurso, sin interpretaci\\u00F3n cr\\u00EDtica y sin menci\\u00F3n expresa del autor del resumen.Es la parte inicial, donde formalmente se da a conocer el ambiente en el que la historia se va a desarrollar."@es ,
		"Nella documentazione con il termine abstract si fa riferimento a due diverse forme di scrittura.Per abstract si intende l\'indice (o sommario) di un documento, senza l\'aggiunta di interpretazioni e valutazioni. L\'abstract si limita a riassumere, in un determinato numero di parole, gli aspetti fondamentali del documento esaminato."@it .
