		"Die Farbfeldmalerei (auch: Color Field Painting oder Post-painterly-abstraction, dt. Nachmalerische Abstraktion) ist eine Ausdrucksform der zeitgen\\u00F6ssischen Kunst, die sich durch gro\\u00DFfl\\u00E4chige, homogen gef\\u00FCllte Farbfelder auszeichnet. Diese Kunstrichtung entwickelte sich Mitte der 1950er Jahre in Amerika aus dem Abstrakten Expressionismus. Mark Rothko, Barnett Newman (Who\'s afraid of red, yellow and blue) und Clyfford Still sind bedeutende Vorl\\u00E4ufer bzw."@de ,
		"Colorfieldpainting is een variant binnen de abstract expressionistische schilderkunst in de Verenigde Staten. Er wordt gewerkt met kleurvlakken of kleurvelden om een meditatieve stemming te wekken bij de kijker. De nadruk wordt gelegd op grote monochromatische (eenkleurige) vlakken, om op die wijze aan het fenomeen kleur een zo groot mogelijke uitdrukkingskracht te geven."@nl ,
		"Il Color field (o color field painting. In inglese: Pittura a campi di colore) \\u00E8 un movimento pittorico caratterizzato dall\'uso di grandi tele di canapa coperte interamente da estensioni invariate di colore, che escludono qualsiasi interesse per il valore del segno, della forma o della materia."@it ,
		"Color Field painting is a style of abstract painting that emerged in New York City during the 1940s and 1950s. It was inspired by European modernism and closely related to Abstract Expressionism, while many of its notable early proponents were among the pioneering Abstract Expressionists. Color Field is characterized primarily by large fields of flat, solid color spread across or stained into the canvas creating areas of unbroken surface and a flat picture plane."@en ,

		"Southern Gothic is a subgenre of Gothic fiction in American literature that takes place exclusively in the American South.Common themes in Southern Gothic literature include deeply flawed, disturbing or eccentric characters who may or may not dabble in hoodoo, ambivalent gender roles, decayed or derelict settings, grotesque situations, and other sinister events relating to or stemming from poverty, alienation, crime, or violence."@en ,

	rdfs:comment	"Apocalypticism is the religious belief that there will be an apocalypse, a term which originally referred to a revelation of God\'s will, but now usually refers to the belief that the world will come to an end very soon, even within one\'s own lifetime."@en ,
		"El apocalipticismo es la creencia religiosa en la pronta llegada del apocalipsis, es decir, el inminente fin del mundo o de la civilizaci\\u00F3n actual. Asimismo, esta convicci\\u00F3n viene acompa\\u00F1ada de la esperanza en la pr\\u00F3xima llegada de un mes\\u00EDas o salvador, y de un juicio final tumultuoso debido a alg\\u00FAn tipo de evento global catastr\\u00F3fico."@es ,
		"Apocaliticismo \\u00E9 a cren\\u00E7a religiosa de que haver\\u00E1 um apocalipse, um termo que originalmente se referia \\u00E0 revela\\u00E7\\u00E3o da vontade de Deus, mas que no sentido contempor\\u00E2neo se refere \\u00E0 cren\\u00E7a de que o mundo terminar\\u00E1 em breve, provavelmente at\\u00E9 durante a pr\\u00F3pria vida. Esta cren\\u00E7a est\\u00E1 geralmente associada \\u00E0 no\\u00E7\\u00E3o de que a civiliza\\u00E7\\u00E3o se aproxima de um final tumultuoso como consequ\\u00EAncia de algum evento catastr\\u00F3fico global.== Refer\\u00EAncias =="@pt ,
		"Apokalyptik ist ein von Apokalypse (griechisch: \\u03B1\\u03C0\\u03BF\\u03BA\\u03AC\\u03BB\\u03C5\\u03C8\\u03B9\\u03C2, \\u201EEnth\\u00FCllung\\u201C, \\u201EOffenbarung\\u201C) abgeleiteter Kunstbegriff, der auf Ph\\u00E4nomene angewendet wird, die \\u00E4hnliches Gedankengut hervorbringen, wie sie in den j\\u00FCdischen und christlichen Apokalypsen der Antike zu finden sind. Im Vordergrund stehen dabei meist Weltuntergangsvorstellungen. Eine eindeutige, in der Wissenschaft unumstrittene Definition von Apokalyptik gibt es nicht."@de ,
		"\\u555F\\u793A\\u6587\\u5B78\\uFF08\\u82F1\\u6587\\uFF1AApocalyptic\\uFF09\\uFF0C\\u53EF\\u6307\\u4E00\\u500B\\u795E\\u5B78\\u904B\\u52D5\\uFF0C\\u6216\\u662F\\u8A72\\u904B\\u52D5\\u7684\\u4EE3\\u8868\\u6027\\u6587\\u9AD4\\u3002\\u9019\\u7A2E\\u7279\\u5225\\u7684\\u73FE\\u8C61\\u4E0D\\u662F\\u4E00\\u7A2E\\u7FA4\\u9AD4\\u672C\\u8EAB\\uFF0C\\u800C\\u662F\\u5728\\u8A31\\u591A\\u4E0D\\u540C\\u7FA4\\u9AD4\\u88E1\\u51FA\\u73FE\\u7684\\u7279\\u5225\\u89C0\\u9EDE\\u3002\\u5B83\\u7522\\u751F\\u51FA\\u5927\\u91CF\\u5F15\\u4EBA\\u5165\\u52DD\\u7684\\u6587\\u5B78\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\uFF0C\\u6709\\u7684\\u5B58\\u7559\\u81F3\\u4ECA\\u3002\\u4ED6\\u5011\\u76F8\\u4FE1\\u4E16\\u4E0A\\u7684\\u90AA\\u60E1\\u65E5\\u4EA6\\u589E\\u591A\\u3001\\u6642\\u4EE3\\u7684\\u7D42\\u7D50\\u8DA8\\u8FD1\\uFF0C\\u4E26\\u4E14\\u795E\\u5C07\\u6703\\u6C7A\\u5B9A\\u6027\\u7684\\u4ECB\\u5165\\uFF0C\\u4EE5\\u5C55\\u958B\\u65B0\\u7684\\u6642\\u4EE3\\u3002\\u7336\\u592A\\u6559\\u8207\\u57FA\\u7763\\u6559\\u7686\\u6709\\u555F\\u793A\\u6587\\u5B78\\uFF0C\\u5B83\\u7684\\u7368\\u7279\\u6027\\u53EF\\u898B\\u65BC\\u300A\\u8056\\u7D93\\u300B\\u820A\\u7D04\\u88E1\\u7684\\u4F46\\u4EE5\\u7406\\u66F8\\u3001\\u6492\\u8FE6\\u5229\\u4E9E\\u66F8\\u3001\\u4EE5\\u897F\\u7D50\\u66F8\\u3001\\u4EE5\\u8CFD\\u4E9E\\u66F8\\u3001\\u7D04\\u73E5\\u66F8\\uFF0C\\u4EE5\\u53CA\\u300A\\u8056\\u7D93\\u300B\\u65B0\\u7D04\\u88E1\\u7684\\u99AC\\u592A\\u798F\\u97F3\\u548C\\u555F\\u793A\\u9304\\u3002\\u300A\\u8056\\u7D93\\u300B\\u5148\\u77E5\\u6216\\u5176\\u4F5C\\u8005\\u900F\\u904E\\u7279\\u6B8A\\u7684\\u7570\\u8C61\\u6216\\u7570\\u5922\\uFF0C\\u5076\\u7136\\u770B\\u5230\\u5929\\u4E0A\\u7684\\u4E8B\\u3001\\u8D85\\u81EA\\u7136\\u7684\\u666F\\u8C61\\uFF0C\\u751A\\u81F3\\u88AB\\u63D0\\u5230\\u5929\\u5EAD\\uFF0C\\u795E\\u85C9\\u6B64\\u5411\\u4ED6\\u5011\\u63ED\\u793A\\u5C07\\u4F86\\uFF0C\\u5C24\\u5176\\u662F\\u95DC\\u65BC\\u672B\\u4E16\\u7684\\u96B1\\u85CF\\u4E4B\\u5967\\u79D8\\u4FE1\\u606F\\u3002\\u8056\\u7D93\\u555F\\u793A\\u6587\\u5B78\\u901A\\u5E 	rdfs:comment	"Het caravaggisme is een stroming in de 17de-eeuwse schilderkunst, naar aanleiding van de revolutionaire stijl van de Italiaanse meester Caravaggio. De stroming is niet te beschrijven als een groep, noch als een school, zeker niet als gestructureerde beweging, maar hoogstens als Italiaanse navolging, als be\\u00EFnvloeding."@nl ,
		"Le caravagisme, ou \\u00E9cole caravagesque, est un courant pictural de la premi\\u00E8re moiti\\u00E9 du XVIIe si\\u00E8cle.Apparu \\u00E0 la suite du travail du Caravage \\u00E0 la fin du XVIe si\\u00E8cle, le caravagisme est parfois assimil\\u00E9 \\u00E0 une forme de baroque romain face au classicisme des Carrache. Cette id\\u00E9e est cependant \\u00E0 nuancer en raison des nombreuses similitudes qui rapprochent ces deux \\u00E9coles romaine et bolonaise."@fr ,
		"El caravaggismo o caravagismo es una corriente pict\\u00F3rica dentro del barroco, que designa el estilo de los artistas que se inspiraron en la obra de Caravaggio. Estos pintores tambi\\u00E9n son conocidos como tenebristas, por su uso de la t\\u00E9cnica del claroscuro. En otras ocasiones, se hace referencia a su naturalismo o realismo."@es ,
		"The Caravaggisti (or the \\"Caravagesques\\") were stylistic followers of the 16th-century Italian Baroque painter Caravaggio. His influence on the new Baroque style that eventually emerged from Mannerism was profound. Caravaggio never established a workshop as most other painters did, and thus had no school to spread his techniques. Nor did he ever set out his underlying philosophical approach to art, the psychological realism which can only be deduced from his surviving work."@en ,
		"O Caravagismo foi uma corrente seguidora do barroco, que ocorreu principalmente no s\\u00E9culo XVI, que designa o estilo dos artistas que se inspiraram na obra do pintor italiano, Michelangelo Merisi da Caravaggio. Estes artistas tamb\\u00E9m s\\u00E3o conhecidos como tenebristas, na sua utiliza\\u00E7\\u00E3o da t\\u00E9cnica do claro-escuro. Em outras ocasi\\u00F5es, referindo-se ao seu naturalismo ou realismo."@pt ,
		"Il caravaggismo \\u00E8 una corrente pittorica nata a cavallo del XVI e XVII secolo che si rif\\u00E0 agli schemi artistici introdotti da Caravaggio.L\'influenza di Caravaggio sulla nuova pittura barocca fu profonda e rivoluzionaria. La resa della realt\\u00E0 attraverso l\'uso dei forti contrasti di luce ed ombra, non era mai stata tanto veritiera e vitale."@it ,
		"Caravaggionizm \\u2013 formu\\u0142a stylistyczna w malarstwie barokowym wprowadzona i rozwini\\u0119ta ok. 1605-1640 przez w\\u0142oskich kontynuator\\u00F3w i na\\u015Bladowc\\u00F3w Caravaggia."@pl ,

		"Johannes Liechtenauer (aussi appel\\u00E9 Lichtenauer) \\u00E9tait un ma\\u00EEtre escrimeur germain du XIVe si\\u00E8cle. Il est vraisemblablement n\\u00E9 au d\\u00E9but ou au milieu du XIVe si\\u00E8cle.Le peu que l\\u2019on sait \\u00E0 son propos est conserv\\u00E9, \\u00E0 la fois dans ses enseignements, dans MS 3227a  et plus tard dans les recueils de ses propres \\u00E9tudiants. 		"Johannes Liechtenauer (tambi\\u00E9n escrito Lichtenauer) fue un instructor de esgrima alemana durante el siglo XIV. dbr:Post-expressionism	rdfs:label	"Post-expressionism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Post-expressionism is a term coined by the German art critic Franz Roh to describe a variety of movements in the post-war art world which were influenced by expressionism but defined themselves through rejecting its aesthetic. Roh first used the term in an essay in 1925, \\"Magic Realism: Post-Expressionism\\", to contrast to Gustav Friedrich Hartlaub\'s \\"New Objectivity\\", which more narrowly characterized these developments within German art."@en .

		"\\u30EC\\u30F4\\u30E5\\u30FC\\uFF08revue\\uFF09\\u306F\\u5927\\u8846\\u5A2F\\u697D\\u6F14\\u82B8\\u306E\\u3053\\u3068\\u3002\\u88C5\\u7F6E\\u30FB\\u8863\\u88C5\\u30FB\\u7167\\u660E\\u3068\\u3044\\u3063\\u305F\\u8996\\u899A\\u7684\\u306A\\u8981\\u7D20\\u306B\\u91CD\\u70B9\\u3092\\u7F6E\\u304D\\u3001\\u97F3\\u697D\\u3001\\u821E\\u8E0F\\u3001\\u5BF8\\u5287\\u3001\\u66F2\\u82B8\\u306A\\u3069\\u306E\\u6F14\\u76EE\\u3092\\u5C55\\u958B\\u3059\\u308B\\u3002\\u5143\\u6765\\u30EC\\u30F4\\u30E5\\u30FC\\u306F\\u30D5\\u30E9\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u8A9E\\u3067\\u6279\\u8A55\\u30FB\\u8ABF\\u67FB\\u3092\\u610F\\u5473\\u3057\\u3001\\u305D\\u306E\\u5E74\\u306E\\u51FA\\u6765\\u4E8B\\u306B\\u3064\\u3044\\u3066\\u98A8\\u523A\\u7684\\u306B\\u63CF\\u304F\\u6B4C\\u3084\\u8E0A\\u308A\\u306A\\u3069\\u3092\\u610F\\u5473\\u3057\\u300119\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u672B\\u9803\\u304B\\u3089\\u5927\\u3044\\u306B\\u6D41\\u884C\\u3057\\u305F\\u3002"@ja ,
		"A revue is a type of multi-act popular theatrical entertainment that combines music, dance and sketches. The revue has its roots in 19th century popular entertainment and melodrama but grew into a substantial cultural presence of its own during its golden years from 1916 to 1932. Though most famous for their visual spectacle, revues frequently satirized contemporary figures, news or literature."@en ,
		"Il teatro di rivista, o pi\\u00F9 comunemente rivista, fu un genere di spettacolo teatrale di carattere leggero che in Italia conobbe la massima popolarit\\u00E0 tra la fine degli anni trenta e la met\\u00E0 degli anni cinquanta, collegato tra la progressiva sparizione dei vecchi generi teatrali come il variet\\u00E0, il Caf\\u00E9-chantant, l\'operetta e l\'avanspettacolo, fino alla grande affermazione della commedia musicale.Il teatro di rivista era un misto di prosa, musica, danza e scenette umoristiche ispirate all\'attualit\\u00E0 spicciola e ai tradizionali clich\\u00E9 erotico-sentimentali, uniti da un tenue filo conduttore e dalla presenza di personaggi fissi come la soubrette. "@it ,
		"Rewia (z fr. la revue) \\u2013 widowisko teatralne czerpi\\u0105ce z r\\u00F3\\u017Cnych estetyk i gatunk\\u00F3w, m.in. spektaklu, kabaretu, opery, operetki, baletu. Wykorzystuje elementy gry aktorskiej, ta\\u0144ca i \\u015Bpiewu. Cz\\u0119sto charakteryzuje si\\u0119 przepychem dekoracji i kostium\\u00F3w artyst\\u00F3w w niej wyst\\u0119puj\\u0105cych.Gatunek rewiowy wykszta\\u0142ci\\u0142 si\\u0119 w XIX wieku w Stanach Zjednoczonych. \\u015Awiatowymi centrami sztuki rewiowej sta\\u0142y si\\u0119 Pary\\u017C i Las Vegas."@pl ,
		"Revista (franc\\u00E9s: Revue) es un subg\\u00E9nero dram\\u00E1tico de la comedia que se desenvuelve en un tipo de espect\\u00E1culo que combina m\\u00FAsica, baile y, muchas veces, tambi\\u00E9n breves escenas teatrales o sketches humor\\u00EDsticos o sat\\u00EDricos. La revista combina elementos dram\\u00E1ticos del burlesque, el vaudeville, la extravaganza y la comedia musical."@es ,
		"Die Revue (franz\\u00F6sisch f\\u00FCr \\u201AZeitschrift\\u2018, \\u201A\\u00DCbersicht\\u2018) ist eine Unterform des Musiktheaters und geh\\u00F6rt damit zur Darstellenden Kunst. \\u00C4hnlich den verwandten Unterformen Operette und Musical vereinigt die Revue Musik-, Tanz- und Wortbeitr\\u00E4ge zu einer Gesamtdarbietung; es fehlt jedoch im Gegensatz zu diesen ein durchgehender Handlungsstrang."@de ,
		"Een revue is een vorm van amusementstheater die bestaat uit groots opgezette dans-, zang- en vari\\u00E9t\\u00E9nummers en lichtvoetige komische sketches.Het genre ontstond aan het einde van de negentiende eeuw in Frankrijk. In zo\'n Franse revue werden recente gebeurtenissen uit het politieke en maatschappelijke leven met satirische liedjes en sketches opnieuw onder de aandacht gebracht."@nl .

Il aura \\u00E9t\\u00E9 avec Lee Strasberg et Stella Adler, l\'un des professeurs les plus importants du XXe si\\u00E8cle, en mati\\u00E8re de technique d\'interpr\\u00E9tation apr\\u00E8s Constantin Stanislavski."@fr ,

		"Sanford Meisner (August 31, 1905 \\u2013 February 2, 1997), also known as Sandy, was an American actor and acting teacher who developed an approach to acting instruction that is now known as the Meisner technique. While Meisner was exposed to method acting at the Group Theatre, his approach differed markedly in that he, like Konstantin Stanislavski, completely abandoned the use of affective memory, a distinct characteristic of method acting."@en .

		"Potere nero (in inglese \\"Black Power\\") \\u00E8 uno slogan politico e il nome di diverse ideologie associate all\'orgoglio delle persone con la pelle nera per le proprie origini.Viene usato in tutto il mondo dalle persone che vantano una discendenza dalle popolazioni nere africane sebbene abbia avuto origine tra gli afroamericani degli Stati UnitiIl movimento ebbe il proprio apogeo tra la fine degli anni sessanta e l\'inizio degli anni settanta, enfatizzando una sorta di orgoglio razziale e sostenendo la creazione di istituzioni politiche e culturali per promuovere gli interessi della collettivit\\u00E0 nera e portare avanti i \\"valori neri\\"."@it ,
		"Black Power is a political slogan and a name for various associated ideologies aimed at achieving self-determination for people of African/Black descent. It is used by  African Americans in the United States."@en ,
		"Black Power was een politieke beweging onder zwarte Amerikanen aan het eind van de jaren zestig en het begin van de jaren zeventig.Sjabloon:Bron?Black Power benadrukte de uiting van een nieuw raciaal bewustzijn onder de zwarten in de Verenigde Staten."@nl ,
		"Le terme Black Power a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 lanc\\u00E9 par Stokely Carmichael, du Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee (SNCC) en 1966 et recouvrait la position de divers mouvements politiques, culturels et sociaux noirs aux \\u00C9tats-Unis, actifs principalement dans les ann\\u00E9es 1960 et les ann\\u00E9es 1970, qui luttaient contre la s\\u00E9gr\\u00E9gation raciale.L\'expression existait auparavant, la premi\\u00E8re trace de celle-ci ayant \\u00E9t\\u00E9 d\\u00E9couverte chez Richard Wright, qui intitula en 1954 un livre Black Power."@fr ,
		"Black Power (Poder negro ) es un eslogan pol\\u00EDtico y el t\\u00E9rmino asociado a varias ideolog\\u00EDas asociadas al mismo. El t\\u00E9rmino ha sido utilizado por diversos movimientos en defensa de los derechos de personas de raza negra por todo el mundo, aunque especialmente por los afroamericanos de los Estados Unidos."@es ,
		"Black Power (em portugu\\u00EAs: Poder negro) foi um movimento entre pessoas negras no mundo ocidental, especialmente nos Estados Unidos."@pt .

		"German Expressionism refers to a number of related creative movements beginning in Germany before the First World War that reached a peak in Berlin, during the 1920s."@en ,
		"Expressionistische film is een stijlrichting binnen de filmkunst die in het begin van de jaren twintig in Duitsland ontstond, in de \'filmhoofdstad\' Berlijn. Het waren stomme films. In Oostenrijk waren er al enkele jaren eerder expressionistische tendensen in de filmkunst doorgedrongen, die zich vanuit literatuurverfilmingen ontwikkelden. Als onderwerp van handeling werden vaak verhalen als volksverhalen, legendes en mythen gebruikt."@nl ,
		"Cine expresionista alem\\u00E1n es el nombre que se le da a un grupo de producciones cinematogr\\u00E1ficas con ciertos aspectos en com\\u00FAn. Este estilo de hacer cine tiene su correspondencia con la corriente expresionista, llamada as\\u00ED por contraste con la corriente impresionista del siglo XIX en pintura, es decir, con aquel tipo de pintura en la que prima la \\u00ABexpresi\\u00F3n subjetiva\\u00BB sobre la representaci\\u00F3n de la objetividad. Esta pintura recurr\\u00EDa a colores hirientes y ritmos lineales muy fuertes."@es ,
		"O expressionismo alem\\u00E3o foi um estilo cinematogr\\u00E1fico cujo auge se deu na d\\u00E9cada de 1920, que caracterizou-se pela distor\\u00E7\\u00E3o de cen\\u00E1rios e personagens, atrav\\u00E9s da maquiagem, dos recursos de fotografia e de outros mecanismos, com o objetivo de expressar a maneira como os realizadores viam o mundo.Pedro Monteiro, que mostra as origens e anseios do movimento:O expressionismo, cuja origem podemos remontar a fortes evid\\u00EAncias em Van Gogh."@pt ,
		"Il cinema espressionista \\u00E8 una delle avanguardie del cinema tedesco degli anni dieci e venti del XX secolo."@it ,

		"Ekspresjonizm \\u2013 nurt w niemieckiej kinematografii, kt\\u00F3rego pocz\\u0105tki si\\u0119gaj\\u0105 roku 1913, kiedy to powsta\\u0142 Student z Pragi w re\\u017Cyserii Stellana Rye. 		"Der expressionistische Film entstand im Wesentlichen in Deutschland, speziell in dessen \\u201EFilmhauptstadt\\u201C Berlin, in der Stummfilmzeit der ersten H\\u00E4lfte der 1920er-Jahre. Oft spricht man deshalb auch vom Deutschen Expressionismus. Doch auch in den Jahren zuvor tauchten bereits erste expressionistische Elemente in \\u00F6sterreichischen Produktionen auf \\u2212 den sogenannten \\u201Evorexpressionistischen\\u201C Filmen, die sich aus den vielseits beliebten Literaturverfilmungen entwickelten."@de .

		"A caligrafia \\u00E1rabe (em \\u00E1rabe: \\u0641\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062E\\u0637; transl.: fann al-ja\\u1E6D\\u1E6D, \\"arte da linha\\"), tamb\\u00E9m conhecida como caligrafia isl\\u00E2mica, \\u00E9 uma arte decorativa pr\\u00F3pria dos povos que utilizam o alfabeto \\u00E1rabe e suas variantes, na escrita, e por extens\\u00E3o, na confec\\u00E7\\u00E3o de livros. Como parte da cultura \\u00E1rabe, essa caligrafia foi utilizada por s\\u00E9culos na preserva\\u00E7\\u00E3o do Alcor\\u00E3o."@pt ,
		"\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30E9\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u306E\\u66F8\\u6CD5\\uFF08\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30E9\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u306E\\u3057\\u3087\\u307B\\u3046\\uFF09\\u3067\\u306F\\u3001\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30E9\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u3068\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u8A9E\\u304C\\u4E92\\u3044\\u306B\\u5F71\\u97FF\\u3092\\u53CA\\u307C\\u3057\\u5408\\u3063\\u3066\\u9032\\u5316\\u3057\\u305F\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u6587\\u5B57\\u306E\\u66F8\\u9053\\u306B\\u3064\\u3044\\u3066\\u89E3\\u8AAC\\u3059\\u308B\\u3002\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30E9\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u306B\\u304A\\u3051\\u308B\\u4E3B\\u8981\\u306A\\u82B8\\u8853\\u3067\\u3042\\u308A\\u3001\\u72ED\\u7FA9\\u306B\\u306F\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u8A9E\\u306B\\u9650\\u5B9A\\u3059\\u308B\\u3002\\u82F1\\u8A9E\\u3067\\u306F\\u300C\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30E9\\u30FC\\u30E0\\u66F8\\u9053\\u300D\\u3092\\u610F\\u5473\\u3059\\u308B \\"Islamic Calligraphy\\" \\u3068\\u547C\\u3076\\u3053\\u3068\\u304C\\u591A\\u3044\\u304C\\u3001Persian calligraphy\\u3068\\u306E\\u9055\\u3044\\u3092\\u306F\\u3063\\u304D\\u308A\\u3068\\u3055\\u305B\\u308B\\u70BA\\u306B\\u300C\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u66F8\\u9053\\u300D\\u3092\\u610F\\u5473\\u3059\\u308B \\"Arabic calligraphy\\" \\u306A\\u3069\\u3068\\u3082\\u547C\\u3070\\u308C\\u308B\\u3002\\u65E5\\u672C\\u8A9E\\u3067\\u306E\\u6C7A\\u307E\\u3063\\u305F\\u547C\\u3073\\u540D\\u306F\\u7121\\u3044\\u304C\\u3001\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u66F8\\u9053(\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u3057\\u3087\\u3069\\u3046)\\u3068\\u547C\\u3070\\u308C\\u308B\\u4E8B\\u304C\\u591A\\u3044\\u3002\\u672C\\u9805\\u3067\\u306F\\u307E\\u305F\\u3001\\u30A2\\u30E9\\u30D3\\u30A2\\u6587\\u5B57\\u306B\\u304A\\u3051\\u308B\\u4E3B\\u8981\\u306A\\u66F8\\u4F53\\u306B\\u3064\\u3044\\u3066\\u3082\\u8A18\\u8FF0\\u3059\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Les styles calligraphiques arabes se sont d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9s d\\u00E8s les premiers temps de l\'islam, avec la diffusion des livres de tous types dans l\'aire g\\u00E9ographique de dar al-islam.La calligraphie est d\'ailleurs tr\\u00E8s d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9e dans les arts d\'Islam, et prend m\\u00EAme parfois une valeur symbolique."@fr ,
		"La caligraf\\u00EDa \\u00E1rabe (en idioma \\u00E1rabe, \\u0641\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062E\\u0637  [fann al-ja\\u1E6D\\u1E6D], \\u00ABarte de la l\\u00EDnea\\u00BB; en persa, \\u062E\\u0648\\u0634\\u0646\\u0648\\u06CC\\u0633\\u06CC [joshnevis\\u00ED], \\u00ABescritura bella\\u00BB) es un arte decorativo propio de los pueblos que utilizan el alfabeto \\u00E1rabe y sus variantes. Se suele considerar como la principal de las artes isl\\u00E1micas."@es ,
		"L\'arte calligrafica araba \\u00E8 l\'arte di scrivere in maniera codificata ed esteticamente ricercata usando l\'alfabeto arabo o alfabeti di sua derivazione (persiano, turco osmanli, ecc.). L\'arte della calligrafia \\u00E8 particolarmente considerata nell\'Islam, ed \\u00E8 per questo che alcuni usano parlare anche di calligrafia islamica."@it ,
		"Islamic calligraphy, or Arabic calligraphy, is the artistic practice of handwriting and calligraphy, based upon the Arabic language and alphabet in the lands sharing a common Islamic cultural heritage.It is derived from the Persian calligraphy."@en ,
		"Die Islamische Kalligrafie ist ein Aspekt der islamischen Kunst, der sich aus der arabischen Schrift in engem Zusammenhang mit dem Islam entwickelt hat. Sie ist, bedingt durch das Bilderverbot im Islam, die traditionelle bildende Kunst in der islamischen Welt. Mit der eckigen Kufi- und der kursiven Naschi-Schrift entwickelten sich schon fr\\u00FCh zwei Stilarten."@de ,

		"A literary magazine is a periodical devoted to literature in a broad sense. Literary magazines usually publish short stories, poetry and essays along with literary criticism, book reviews, biographical profiles of authors, interviews and letters. Literary magazines are often called literary journals, or little magazines, terms intended to contrast these with larger, commercial magazines."@en ,

		"Le riviste letterarie sono riviste che si occupano di letteratura e che offrono spazi a scrittori e poeti, affermati o esordienti, per proporre al pubblico le loro opere. dbr:Liverpool_poets	rdfs:label	"Liverpool poets"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Liverpool Poets are a number of influential 1960s poets from Liverpool, England, influenced by 1950s Beat poetry. They were involved in the 1960s Liverpool scene that gave rise to The Beatles.Their work is characterised by its directness of expression, simplicity of language, suitability for live performance and concern for contemporary subjects and references. There is often humour, but the full range of human experience and emotion is addressed."@en .

		"Norwegian romantic nationalism  (Nasjonalromantikken) was a movement in Norway between 1840 and 1867 in art, literature, and popular culture that emphasized the aesthetics of Norwegian nature and the uniqueness of the Norwegian national identity.  A subject of much study and debate in Norway, it was characterized by nostalgia."@en ,

		"El nacionalismo rom\\u00E1ntico noruego fue un movimiento en Noruega entre 1840 y 1867 en el arte, la literatura y la cultura popular que enfatiz\\u00F3 la est\\u00E9tica de la naturaleza noruega y la singularidad de la identidad nacional de Noruega. Un sujeto de mucho estudio y debate en Noruega, fue caracterizado por la nostalgia.El contexto e impacto del nacionalismo rom\\u00E1ntico noruego provino desde la historia reciente y la situaci\\u00F3n pol\\u00EDtica."@es .

	rdfs:comment	"Le Mouvement pour le Pakistan ou Tehrik-e-Pakistan (\\u062A\\u062D\\u0631\\u06CC\\u06A9 \\u067E\\u0627\\u06A9\\u0633\\u062A\\u0627\\u0646 \\u2014 Ta\\u1E25r\\u012Bk-i P\\u0101kist\\u0101n) d\\u00E9signe un ancien mouvement politique qui vise l\'ind\\u00E9pendance du Pakistan vis-\\u00E0-vis de l\'Empire britannique, pour former un \\u00E9tat-nation par l\'union des quatre provinces situ\\u00E9es au nord-ouest du sous-continent indien, de l\'\\u00E9tat princier du Jammu-et-Cachemire et de la r\\u00E9gion nord-est du Bengale.Le mouvement a \\u00E9volu\\u00E9 en parall\\u00E8le du mouvement pour l\'ind\\u00E9pendance de l\'Inde, avec lequel il partage des vues et motifs similaires. 		"\\u041F\\u0430\\u043A\\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0435 \\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 (\\u0430\\u043D\\u0433\\u043B. Pakistan Movement ; \\u0443\\u0440\\u0434\\u0443 \\u062A\\u062D\\u0631\\u06CC\\u06A9 \\u067E\\u0627\\u06A9\\u0633\\u062A\\u0627\\u0646) \\u2014 \\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0435 \\u0434\\u0432\\u0438\\u0436\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u043C\\u0443\\u0441\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u043C\\u0430\\u043D \\u0411\\u0440\\u0438\\u0442\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0418\\u043D\\u0434\\u0438\\u0438, \\u0433\\u043B\\u0430\\u0432\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0446\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u044E \\u043A\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0431\\u044B\\u043B\\u043E \\u0441\\u043E\\u0437\\u0434\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u043D\\u0435\\u0437\\u0430\\u0432\\u0438\\u0441\\u0438\\u043C\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0438\\u0441\\u043B\\u0430\\u043C\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0433\\u043E\\u0441\\u0443\\u0434\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0430 \\u041F\\u0430\\u043A\\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u0430\\u043D \\u043D\\u0430 \\u0441\\u0435\\u0432\\u0435\\u0440\\u043E-\\u0437\\u0430\\u043F\\u0430\\u0434\\u043D\\u044B\\u0445 \\u0437\\u0435\\u043C\\u043B\\u044F\\u0445 \\u0418\\u043D\\u0434\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u0441\\u0443\\u0431\\u043A\\u043E\\u043D\\u0442\\u0438\\u043D\\u0435\\u043D\\u0442\\u0430."@ru ,
		"The Pakistan Movement or Tehrik-e-Pakistan (Urdu: \\u062A\\u062D\\u0631\\u06CC\\u06A9 \\u067E\\u0627\\u06A9\\u0633\\u062A\\u0627\\u0646\\u200E \\u2014 Ta\\u1E25r\\u012Bk-i P\\u0101kist\\u0101n) was a historic and subsequently successful political movement that aimed for the independence of Pakistan from the British Empire, to form the new independent nation state by the union of the four provinces located in the far  northwest of the Indian subcontinent, the princely state of Jammu and Kashmir, as well as the far eastern region of Bengal.The movement progressed alongside with the Indian independence movement which had the similar views and motives, but the Pakistan Movement sought to establish a nation-state that protected the religious identity and political interests of Muslims in South Asia. "@en ,

It also refers to a subject of research in electronic and electrical engineering which deals with the design, control, computation and integration of nonlinear, time-varying energy-processing electronic systems with fast dynamics.The first high power electronic devices were mercury-arc valves."@en ,

		"Vermogenselektronica is een deelgebied van de elektronica waar men elektronische componenten gebruikt voor het schakelen, sturen en omvormen van grote elektrische vermogens zoals die in de energietechniek worden gebruikt.Vermogenselektronica is ontstaan bij de ontwikkeling van elektrische tractie zoals bij locomotieven. Men zocht naar mogelijkheden om de snelheid van een trein te kunnen regelen."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"Art therapy is a creative method of expression used as a therapeutic technique.  Arts therapy originated in the fields of Art and Psychotherapy and may vary in definition.  It may focus on the creative art-making process itself as therapy  or on the analysis of expression gained through an exchange of patient/therapist interaction.  The psychoanalytic approach was one of the earliest forms of art psychotherapy."@en ,
		"Beeldende therapie is een van de vijf therapievormen van vaktherapie, voorheen creatieve therapie genoemd. Het doel is door beeldende middelen zoals tekenen, boetseren, schilderen, etc. een veranderingsproces te bewerkstelligen.  Het is een therapie die als doel acceptatie-, veranderings- en ontwikkelingsprocessen wil behalen. Deze verandering vindt plaats in het beeldend werken.Belangrijk is de dialoog tussen de cli\\u00EBnt, de werkstukken en de beeldende therapeut."@nl ,

		"Die Kunsttherapie ist eine junge, sich von Impulsen aus den USA und Europa aus der Mitte des 20. Jahrhunderts herleitende K\\u00FCnstlerische Therapie. In der Kunsttherapie wird haupts\\u00E4chlich mit Medien der bildenden Kunst gearbeitet. dbr:Hysterical_realism	rdfs:label	"Hysterical realism"@en ,
		"R\\u00E9alisme hyst\\u00E9rique"@fr ,
		"Realismo isterico"@it ;
	rdfs:comment	"Le r\\u00E9alisme hyst\\u00E9rique, \\u00E9galement appel\\u00E9  \\u00AB recherch\\u00E9 postmodernism \\u00BB ou \\u00AB maximalisme \\u00BB est un mouvement litt\\u00E9raire caract\\u00E9ris\\u00E9 par une longueur chronique, des personnages maniaques, une action fr\\u00E9n\\u00E9tique et des digressions fr\\u00E9quentes sur des sujets accessoires par rapport \\u00E0 l\'histoire."@fr ,
		"Hysterical realism, also called recherch\\u00E9 postmodernism, is a term coined in 2000 by English critic James Wood to describe what he sees as a literary genre typified by a strong contrast between elaborately absurd prose, plotting, or characterization, on the one hand, and careful, detailed investigations of real, specific social phenomena on the other.Wood introduced the term in an essay on Zadie Smith\'s White Teeth, which appeared in the July 24, 2000 issue of The New Republic."@en ,
		"Il realismo isterico, anche chiamato recherch\\u00E9 postmodernism o postmodernismo ricercato, \\u00E8 un genere letterario caratterizzato da lunghezza cronica, personaggi maniacali e frequenti digressioni su argomenti secondari rispetto alla storia, secondo il critico James Wood che lo defin\\u00EC in un saggio su Denti bianchi di Zadie Smith. Wood us\\u00F2 la locuzione per denotare il concetto contemporaneo di \\"grande, ambizioso romanzo\\" che persegue la vitalit\\u00E0 \\"a tutti i costi\\"."@it .

dbr:Literary_fiction	rdfs:label	"Literary fiction"@en ,
		"Literaire fictie"@nl ;
	rdfs:comment	"Literary fiction is a term principally used for certain fictional works that hold literary merit.  In other words, they are works that offer deliberate social commentary, political criticism, or focus on the individual to explore some part of the human condition. Literary fiction is deliberately written in dialogue with existing works created with the above aims in mind."@en ,
		"Met literaire fictie worden bepaalde fictiewerken aangeduid waarvan wordt beweerd dat zij literaire verdienste hebben. Het beste werk van schrijvers die literair gewaardeerd worden, literaire prijzen ontvingen en gunstige kritieken kregen, wordt mogelijk opgenomen in de literaire canon van dat land of van die taal."@nl .

		"Neodada\\u00EDsmo"@pt ,

		"Neo-Dada"@en ,
		"\\u041D\\u0435\\u043E\\u0434\\u0430\\u0434\\u0430"@ru ;
	rdfs:comment	"Mit Neo-Dada wird eine Ende der 1950er Jahre entstandene und bis in die 1960er Jahre reichende k\\u00FCnstlerische Bewegung bezeichnet, die in Anlehnung an Marcel Duchamp und die Dada-Bewegung durch neu entwickelte Ausdrucksformen die Kunst mit dem Leben verbinden will. Der abstrakte Expressionismus wurde dabei von den Vertretern des Neo-Dadaismus abgelehnt."@de ,
		"Le N\\u00E9o-Dada est un mouvement artistique contemporain qui pr\\u00E9sente des similitudes dans ses m\\u00E9thodes et ses intentions avec le mouvement Dada. Bien qu\'il ait principalement les m\\u00EAmes objectifs que ce dernier, le N\\u00E9o-Dada \\u00AB met l\'accent sur la production de l\'oeuvre d\'art plut\\u00F4t que sur le concept g\\u00E9n\\u00E9r\\u00E9 par celle-ci \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"Neo-Dada is a minor audio and visual art movement that has similarities in method or intent to earlier Dada artwork. While it revived some of the objectives of dada, it put \\"emphasis on the importance of the work of art produced rather than on the concept generating the work\\". It is the foundation of Fluxus, Pop Art and Nouveau r\\u00E9alisme. Neo-Dada is exemplified by its use of modern materials, popular imagery, and absurdist contrast."@en ,
		"El movimiento neodad\\u00E1 o neodada\\u00EDsmo surge a finales de los a\\u00F1os 50 y principios de los 60 como reacci\\u00F3n al arte del expresionismo abstracto, el cual hab\\u00EDa absorbido plenamente al artista en una experiencia m\\u00EDstica respecto a su obra de arte, y la carga emotiva de \\u00E9sta y su discurso te\\u00F3rico, resultaban tan ininteligibles que, se hab\\u00EDa creado un distanciamiento del arte como arte-vida-social."@es ,

		"Neodada\\u00EDsmo \\u00E9 um movimento de artes sonoras visuais que tem semelhan\\u00E7as no m\\u00E9todo e no prop\\u00F3sito do movimento anterior, o dada\\u00EDsmo. Apesar de reviver alguns dos objetivos do dada\\u00EDsmo, o neodada\\u00EDsmo coloca \\"\\u00EAnfase na import\\u00E2ncia da obra de arte produzida em vez de no conceito de gera\\u00E7\\u00E3o de trabalho\\". \\u00C9 o fundamento de movimentos como Fluxus, Pop Art e Nouveau r\\u00E9alisme. O neodada\\u00EDsmo \\u00E9 exemplificado por seu uso de materiais modernos, do imagin\\u00E1rio popular do contraste absurdista."@pt .

		"Neoimpression\\u00EDsmo \\u00E9 um termo que foi utilizado pela primeira vez em 1886, pelo cr\\u00EDtico de arte e activista pol\\u00EDtico F\\u00E9lix F\\u00E9neon, para descrever um estilo de pintura p\\u00F3s-impressionista, em voga em Fran\\u00E7a entre 1886 e 1906, e cujo pioneiro foi Georges Seurat. Uma das caracter\\u00EDsticas deste movimento \\u00E9 a renuncia \\u00E0 espontaneidade do Impressionismo, e a utiliza\\u00E7\\u00E3o pensada, com base na ci\\u00EAncia, da cor."@pt ,
		"Neoimpresionismo  es una palabra creada por el cr\\u00EDtico de arte franc\\u00E9s F\\u00E9lix F\\u00E9n\\u00E9on en 1887 para caracterizar el movimiento art\\u00EDstico de fines del siglo XIX liderado por Georges Seurat y Paul Signac, quienes primero exhibieron sus trabajos en 1884 en la muestra de la Soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 des Artistes Ind\\u00E9pendants en Par\\u00EDs."@es ,
		"Neo-impressionisme is een benaming voor een schilderstijl die in het midden van de jaren 1880 ontstond in Frankrijk met Georges Seurat en Paul Signac als belangrijkste initiators. Het neo-impressionisme gaat uit van een schildertechniek waarbij geen streken of vlakken op het doek worden aangebracht, maar stippen (pointillisme) of eventueel streepjes (divisionisme)."@nl ,
		"Neoimpressionismus bezeichnet eine Stilrichtung in der Malerei. Der Begriff wurde von dem Kritiker F\\u00E9lix F\\u00E9n\\u00E9on 1886 in einem Beitrag f\\u00FCr die belgische Zeitschrift L\\u2019art Moderne gepr\\u00E4gt. Er wollte damit die Malweise Georges Seurats von der der Impressionisten unterscheiden. Die Stilrichtung sollte sp\\u00E4ter auch unter der von Paul Signac gepr\\u00E4gten Bezeichnung Pointillismus (Punktierstil) bekannt werden. Seurat dagegen bevorzugte die Bezeichnungsweise Divisionismus (Teilungsmalerei)."@de ,
		"\\u65B0\\u5370\\u8C61\\u6D3E\\uFF08Neo-impressionism\\uFF09\\u662F\\u6CD5\\u570B\\u85DD\\u8853\\u8A55\\u8AD6\\u5BB6\\u8CBB\\u5229\\u514B\\u65AF\\u00B7\\u8CBB\\u5167\\u7FC1\\uFF08F\\u00E9lix F\\u00E9n\\u00E9on\\uFF09\\u57281886\\u5E74\\u5275\\u9020\\u7684\\u4E00\\u500B\\u8853\\u8A9E\\uFF0C\\u7528\\u4F86\\u5F62\\u5BB9\\u7531\\u6CD5\\u570B\\u756B\\u5BB6\\u55AC\\u6CBB\\u00B7\\u79C0\\u62C9\\u5F15\\u767C\\u7684\\u85DD\\u8853\\u904B\\u52D5\\u3002"@zh ,

		"Neo-Impressionism is a term coined by French art critic F\\u00E9lix F\\u00E9n\\u00E9on in 1886 to describe an art movement founded by Georges Seurat. Seurat\\u2019s greatest masterpiece, A Sunday Afternoon on the Island of La Grande Jatte, marked the beginning of this movement when it first made its appearance at an exhibition of the Soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 des Artistes Ind\\u00E9pendants (Salon des Ind\\u00E9pendants) in Paris. Around this time, the peak of France\\u2019s modern era emerged and many painters were in search of new methods."@en ,
		"Il neoimpressionismo \\u00E8 un movimento pittorico ispirato alla ripresa delle teorie dell\'impressionismo. Nasce dalle riflessioni della \\"Soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 des Ind\\u00E9pendants\\" presieduta da Odilon Redon e composta da Paul Signac, Georges Seurat, Henri-Edmond Cross, Charles Ongrand, Albert Dubois-Pillet, Hippolyte Petitjean, Th\\u00E9o van Rysselberghe e altri ancora."@it .

	rdfs:comment	"Arte Povera (de l\'italien : \\u00AB art pauvre \\u00BB) est un mouvement artistique italien, qui, au d\\u00E9part de Turin et de Rome, est apparu sur la sc\\u00E8ne internationale dans les ann\\u00E9es 1960. Plus pr\\u00E9cis\\u00E9ment en septembre 1967, \\u00E0 Turin, l\\u2019exposition collective \\u00AB Arte povera \\u00BB, qui donnera son nom au mouvement, se d\\u00E9roule avec la participation de Alighiero Boetti, Mario Merz, Jannis Kounellis, Luciano Fabro, Michelangelo Pistoletto et Giulio Paolini."@fr ,
		"Arte povera (pronuncia-se arte p\\u00F3vera; em portugu\\u00EAs \\"arte pobre\\") foi uma express\\u00E3o criada pelo cr\\u00EDtico e curador italiano Germano Celant, para referir-se ao movimento art\\u00EDstico que se desenvolveu originalmente na segunda metade da d\\u00E9cada de 1960 na It\\u00E1lia."@pt ,
		"Arte Povera (pronounced [\\u02C8arte \\u02C8p\\u0254\\u02D0vera]; literally poor art) is a modern art movement. The Arte Povera movement was during 1967-1972 and took place in cities throughout Italy: Turin, Milan, Rome, Genoa, Venice, Naples and Bologna. The term was coined by Italian art critic Germano Celant and introduced in Italy during the period of upheaval at the end of the 1960s, when artists were taking a radical stance."@en ,
		"De term arte povera (arme kunst) werd voor het eerst gebruikt in 1967 door de Italiaanse kunstcriticus Germano Celant om het werk van een aantal jonge kunstenaars te beschrijven die installaties maakten met eenvoudige materialen. Arte povera was een invloedrijke kunststroming in de jaren zeventig met raakvlakken aan de internationale fenomenen zoals land art, minimal art en conceptuele kunst."@nl ,
		"Arte povera (w\\u0142. sztuka uboga, sztuka biedna) \\u2013 ruch artystyczny rozwijaj\\u0105cy si\\u0119 w latach 1967-77. W 1967 roku w\\u0142oski krytyk sztuki Germano Celant u\\u017Cy\\u0142 tego terminu opisuj\\u0105c prace grupy w\\u0142oskich artyst\\u00F3w, kt\\u00F3rych cech\\u0105 charakterystyczn\\u0105 by\\u0142o eksponowanie surowo\\u015Bci materia\\u0142\\u00F3w \\u2013 metalu, ga\\u0142\\u0119zi, szk\\u0142a, kamienia, gazet, szmat. Pos\\u0142ugiwanie si\\u0119 przedmiotami pospolitymi mia\\u0142o by\\u0107 odwrotem od tradycyjnej tzw. wysokiej sztuki.Przez u\\u017Cywanie w procesie tw\\u00F3rczym \\"bezwarto\\u015Bciowych\\" materia\\u0142\\u00F3w, nieartyst."@pl ,
		"El t\\u00E9rmino arte povera (del italiano \\"arte pobre\\") es una tendencia dada a conocer a finales de la [d\\u00E9cada de 1960], (aunque el espa\\u00F1ol Josep Maria Jujol ya realiz\\u00F3 obras que encajan dentro de su descripci\\u00F3n a principios de siglo)  cuyos creadores utilizan materiales considerados \'pobres\', de muy f\\u00E1cil obtenci\\u00F3n, como madera, hojas o rocas, vajilla, placas de plomo o cristal, vegetales, telas, carb\\u00F3n o arcilla, o tambi\\u00E9n materiales de desecho y, por lo tanto, carentes de valor.En un esfuerzo por huir de la comercializaci\\u00F3n del objeto art\\u00EDstico, ocupan el espacio y exigen la intervenci\\u00F3n del p\\u00FAblico. "@es ,

		"Kulturkritik"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"Cultuurkritiek is kritiek op cultuur. Dit kan holistische cultuurkritiek zijn, men vat dan de cultuur als eenduidig en eenvormig op. Deze benadering is sterk positivistisch. Cultuurkritiek kan daarentegen ook commentaar leveren op een aspect van een cultuur. Aan de persoonlijke invulling die men aan de cultuurkritiek geeft ligt een wetenschapsfilosofie, levensovertuiging of visie op kunst ten grondslag. De criticus opereert vanuit een subjectief kader."@nl ,
		"A cultural critic is a critic of a given culture, usually as a whole and typically on a radical basis. There is significant overlap with social and cultural theory."@en ,
		"Se entiende por \\"Cr\\u00EDtica Cultural\\" o Cr\\u00EDtica Socio-cultural la aplicaci\\u00F3n de la cr\\u00EDtica a fin de entender la realidad social de un medio o cultura determinada. Por ejemplo, un an\\u00E1lisis sociocultural de la educaci\\u00F3n da una visi\\u00F3n m\\u00E1s compleja y completa de los hechos tales como son."@es ,

		"Kulturkritik ist die Kritik an (einer) Kultur, die als disparat zu menschlichen Bed\\u00FCrfnissen verstanden wird. Sie kann Kulturpessimismus beinhalten und Kultur als Form einer Verstellung, Entstellung (Deformation), Entfremdung, Degeneration, Dekadenz, Unvollst\\u00E4ndigkeit oder Fremdbestimmtheit menschlicher Seinsweisen bzw. Lebensverh\\u00E4ltnisse sehen. Sie hat die Lebensweise der Menschen und den Sinn ihrer Lebensgestaltungen zum Gegenstand. Kulturkritik kennt viele Ausdrucksformen."@de .

		"Elfpunk \\u00E8 un sottogenere dello urban fantasy, nello specifico consiste in racconti e storie in cui fate e elfi vengono trasportati da un ambiente rurale e folkloristico in un ambiente urbano moderno.Durante la cerimonia di premiazione per il 2007 del National Book Award, il giurato Elizabeth Partridge ha spiegato la differenza tra elfpunk e urban fantasy, citando l\'amico giurato Scott Westerfeld ha detto \\"Nell\'Elfpunk c\'\\u00E8 abbastanza spesso la presenza di elfi e fate e tradizione (..."@it .
dbr:Edmonia_Lewis	dbo:movement	dbr:Neoclassicism .
dbr:Fiber_art	rdfs:label	"Fiber art"@it ,
		"Fiber art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"La Fiber Art \\u00E8 una corrente artistica sviluppatasi nel corso del XX secolo che si avvale di tecniche e materiali tessili, indaga l\\u2019uso di materiali flessibili e fibrosi e, in alcuni casi, si riferisce all\\u2019universo di miti e tradizioni che hanno relazione con essi.La Fiber Art si \\u00E8 sviluppata come evoluzione dell\'arazzeria: dal 1962 al 1995 il Centre International de la Tapisserie Ancienne et Moderne (CITAM), ha organizzato a Losanna una mostra Biennale dell\'arazzeria che ha visto il progressivo spostarsi dell\'attenzione verso forme autonome d\'espressione artistica e l\'imporsi della cos\\u00EC detta Nouvelle Tapisserie, con il superamento della tradizionale divisione del lavoro nella produzione di arazzi. "@it ,
		"Fiber art refers to fine art whose material consists of natural or synthetic fiber and other components, such as fabric or yarn.  It focuses on the materials and on the manual labour on the part of the artist as part of the works\' significance, and prioritizes aesthetic value over utility."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"O Renascimento em Fran\\u00E7a come\\u00E7ou depois de a Fran\\u00E7a ter recuperado da Guerra dos Cem anos com a Inglaterra, a guerra acabou em 1453. O jovem rei Francisco I (reinado de 1515-1547) tinha uma paix\\u00E3o pelo Renascimento italiano, pois era colecionador de escultura, pintura, manuscritos e livros, o rei Francisco trouxe v\\u00E1rios artistas de It\\u00E1lia para Fran\\u00E7a, como Leonardo da Vinci. O rei possu\\u00EDa tamb\\u00E9m quadros de Miguel \\u00C2ngelo e Rafael no seu castelo."@pt ,
		"La Renaissance fran\\u00E7aise est un mouvement artistique et culturel situ\\u00E9 en France entre le XVe si\\u00E8cle et le d\\u00E9but du XVIIe si\\u00E8cle. La Renaissance appara\\u00EEt en France apr\\u00E8s le d\\u00E9but du mouvement en Italie et sa propagation dans d\'autres pays europ\\u00E9ens."@fr ,
		"Franse renaissance is een term die gebruikt wordt om er de culturele en artistieke beweging in Frankrijk mee te omschrijven uit de late 15e eeuw tot het begin van de 17e eeuw. Historici zijn van oordeel dat zoals voor vele andere Europese landen de oorsprong ervan in het 14e-eeuwse Noord-Itali\\u00EB ligt."@nl ,

		"Th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre \\"In-Yer-Face\\""@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"Nowy brutalizm (ang. In-yer-face theatre) \\u2013 termin okre\\u015Blaj\\u0105cy ekstremalny nurt w dramaturgii, jaki pojawi\\u0142 si\\u0119 w Wielkiej Brytanii w latach 90. XX wieku. Termin zosta\\u0142 ukuty przez brytyjskiego krytyka teatralnego Aleksa Sierza, kt\\u00F3ry w 2001 r. wyda\\u0142 ksi\\u0105\\u017Ck\\u0119 pod tytu\\u0142em In-yer-face theatre. Sierz u\\u017Cy\\u0142 tego terminu w celu okre\\u015Blenia dramat\\u00F3w pisanych przez m\\u0142odych, kontrowersyjnych pisarzy, prezentuj\\u0105cych tre\\u015Bci wulgarne i szokuj\\u0105ce publiczno\\u015B\\u0107."@pl ,
		"In-yer-face theatre describes a style of drama that emerged in Great Britain in the 1990s.  This term was coined by British theatre critic Aleks Sierz as the title of his book, In-Yer-Face Theatre, first published by Faber and Faber in March 2001."@en .

		"Neomodernizm \\u2013 styl architektoniczny prze\\u0142omu XX i XXI w., nawi\\u0105zuj\\u0105cy do repertuaru form przestrzennych i detalu modernizmu, jednak w od\\u0142\\u0105czeniu od jego idei spo\\u0142eczno-politycznych i zwykle urbanistycznych. 		"Il Nouveau R\\u00E9alisme \\u00E8 un movimento artistico dei primi anni del decennio 1960-1970. In quegli anni si vedono scatenarsi sulla scena delle arti visive movimenti come la Op Art in Europa, la Pop Art negli Stati Uniti, il Nouveau Realisme in Francia.Soprattutto di artisti francesi, che ha per oggetto \\"materiali desunti dalla realt\\u00E0, anche quella pi\\u00F9 banale\\", anche rifiuti, che vengono raccolti per esempio in sculture tridimensionali. Il suo critico pi\\u00F9 importante \\u00E8 Pierre Restany."@it ,

El Nuevo Realismo fue, junto con Fluxus y otros grupos, una de las numerosas tendencias de la vanguardia de los a\\u00F1os 1960."@es ,

	rdfs:comment	"Picturesque ist ein \\u00E4sthetisches Ideal, das 1782 von William Gilpin in die englische Kulturdebatte eingef\\u00FChrt wurde. Mit seinem Buch Observations on the River Wye, and Several Parts of South Wales, etc. Relative Chiefly to Picturesque Beauty; made in the Summer of the Year 1770 leitete er die feinere Gesellschaft an, bei ihren Lustreisen das \\u201EAntlitz der Landschaft nach den Regeln der malerischen Sch\\u00F6nheit zu untersuchen\\u201C."@de ,
		"Con il termine pittoresco si intende tutto ci\\u00F2 che, prestandosi ad una  rappresentazione pittorica, \\u00E8 dotato di determinate qualit\\u00E0: variet\\u00E0 e un gradevole disordine."@it ,
		"Le terme de pittoresque correspond \\u00E0 une notion[Laquelle ?] esth\\u00E9tique n\\u00E9e au XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle : elle concerne non seulement la repr\\u00E9sentation du paysage, mais aussi les trait\\u00E9s d\\u2019esth\\u00E9tique, les voyages pittoresques, l\\u2019art des jardins et m\\u00EAme la cr\\u00E9ation de jardins."@fr ,
		"Pitoresco \\u00E9 um conceito da Est\\u00E9tica que faz refer\\u00EAncia \\u00E0s impress\\u00F5es subjetivas desencadeadas pela contempla\\u00E7\\u00E3o de uma cena paisag\\u00EDstica em rela\\u00E7\\u00E3o \\u00E0 pintura. Surgiu como um intermedi\\u00E1rio entre as id\\u00E9ias do Sublime e do Belo, durante o desenvolvimento do Romantismo. A palavra deriva do italiano pittoresco, \\"semelhante ou feito como uma pintura\\".A express\\u00E3o alla pittoresca no Maneirismo tinha uma acep\\u00E7\\u00E3o literal, e significava algo feito \\u00E0 maneira da pintura, como \\u00E9 usada por Vasari."@pt ,

		"Lo pintoresco es una categor\\u00EDa est\\u00E9tica surgida en el siglo XVIII en el Reino Unido, \\u00EDntimamente relacionada con el movimiento rom\\u00E1ntico. El t\\u00E9rmino proviene del vocablo italiano pittoresco, que significa \\u2018similar a la pintura\\u2019, \\u2018a la manera del pintor\\u2019, queriendo expresar una propiedad de los objetos, paisajes, o cualquier otro elemento del mundo de los sentidos, que por sus caracter\\u00EDsticas, cualidades, belleza o singularidad es digno de ser pintado, de ser representado en una obra de arte."@es ,

		"Picturesque is an aesthetic ideal introduced into English cultural debate in 1782 by William Gilpin in Observations on the River Wye, and Several Parts of South Wales, etc. Relative Chiefly to Picturesque Beauty; made in the Summer of the Year 1770, a practical book which instructed England\\u2019s leisured travelers to examine \\u201Cthe face of  a country by the rules of picturesque beauty\\u201D."@en .

Chr. in Athen entwickelt und war bis zum Ende des 3. vorchristlichen Jahrhunderts in Gebrauch. Sie l\\u00F6ste im Verlauf weniger Jahrzehnte die zuvor vorherrschende Schwarzfigurige Vasenmalerei ab."@de ,

C. y fue utilizado hasta el siglo III a. C. Reemplaz\\u00F3 al estilo previo predominante de la cer\\u00E1mica de figuras negras al cabo de unas d\\u00E9cadas."@es ,

		"De roodfigurige stijl is een van de belangrijkste vormen van beschildering van Oud-Grieks aardewerk. Het ontstond rond 530 v.Chr. in Athene en duurde voort tot de later 3e eeuw v.Chr. De stijl verving na de introductie binnen enkele decennia de daarvoor dominerende zwartfigurige stijl."@nl ,
		"Red-figure vase painting is one of the most important styles of figural Greek vase painting. It developed in Athens around 520 B.C. and remained in use until the late 3rd century B.C. It replaced the previously dominant style of black-figure vase painting within a few decades. Its modern name is based on the figural depictions in red colour on a black background, in contrast to the preceding black-figure style with black figures on a red background."@en ,

	rdfs:comment	"Ausdruckstanz (niem. \\"Ausdruck\\" \\u2013 \\"wyra\\u017Canie\\", \\"Tanz\\" \\u2013 \\"taniec\\"), zwany te\\u017C \\"wolnym ta\\u0144cem\\" (niem. Freier Tanz) \\u2013 powsta\\u0142y w Niemczech nurt ekspresjonistyczny w ta\\u0144cu.Ausdruckstanz ukszta\\u0142towa\\u0142 si\\u0119 w latach 20. XX wieku na gruncie \\u00F3wczesnych poszukiwa\\u0144 nowych \\u015Brodk\\u00F3w wyrazu w sztuce i nowych warto\\u015Bci humanistycznych. Wyr\\u00F3s\\u0142 z poczucia zagubienia w \\u015Bwiecie zdominowanym przez maszyny, konflikty i rodz\\u0105c\\u0105 si\\u0119 komercjalizacj\\u0119."@pl ,
		"Der Ausdruckstanz wird im Gegensatz zum Gesellschaftstanz nicht zur \\u201Eoberfl\\u00E4chlichen\\u201C Unterhaltung getanzt, sondern dient dem individuellen und k\\u00FCnstlerischen Darstellen (und zum Teil auch Verarbeiten) von Gef\\u00FChlen. Er entstand als Gegenbewegung zum klassischen Ballett zu Beginn des 20."@de ,
		"Expressionist dance (German: Ausdruckstanz, also translated as \\"expressive dance\\") is a European dance form that is part of the German Expressionist movement.Although the Expressionist dance has had origins in the modern dance pioneered by Rudolf von Laban, his student Mary Wigman is considered the pioneer of Expressionist dance proper.Other names for it that have fallen out of use include Moderner Tanz, Absoluter Tanz, Freier Tanz, Tanzkunst and Bewegungskunst."@en ,
		"Klassiek modern ballet behelst de danstechnische vaardigheden van klassiek ballet die deels in een \'modern jasje\' worden gestoken. Uitsluitend Modern ballet houdt in dat de traditioneel-klassieke wijze van ballet ook wel deels wordt losgelaten en er vrijere manieren worden gebruikt om emoties en bijvoorbeeld maatschappelijke situaties vrijer en expressiever tot uiting te brengen."@nl ,
		"La danse expressionniste (en allemand, Ausdruckstanz, parfois traduit par \\u00AB danse expressive \\u00BB) est une forme de danse qui faisait partie du mouvement expressionniste allemand.Bien que la danse expressionniste ait ses origines dans la danse moderne initi\\u00E9e par Rudolf Laban, c\'est plut\\u00F4t son \\u00E9l\\u00E8ve Mary Wigman qui est consid\\u00E9r\\u00E9e comme sa vraie fondatrice.La danse expressionniste allemande est li\\u00E9e \\u00E0 la danse-th\\u00E9\\u00E2tre.D\'autres danseurs et chor\\u00E9graphes sont associ\\u00E9s \\u00E0 la danse expressionniste :  Pina Bausch Gertrud Bodenwieser Hertha Feist Hilde Holger Kurt Jooss  Rudolf Laban Jo Mihaly  Alwin Nikolais Gret Palucca Staluse Pera\\u2191"@fr .

dbr:Colonial_Revival_Movement	rdfs:label	"Colonial Revival Movement"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Colonial Revival movement was a national expression of early North American culture, primarily the built and artistic environments of the east coast colonies.  The Colonial Revival is generally associated with the eighteenth-century provincial fashion for the Georgian and Neoclassical styles.  The movement inspired a variety of expressions to fulfill symbolic and functional needs during times of great change."@en .

		"Engelse literatuur verwijst naar literatuur in de Engelse taal, inbegrepen de literaire productie van schrijvers die niet noodzakelijk uit Engeland afkomstig zijn. Zo was Joseph Conrad Pools, Robert Burns was Schots, James Joyce was van Ierse afkomst, Dylan Thomas was Welsh, Edgar Allan Poe Amerikaans, Salman Rushdie Indisch, V.S. Naipaul werd geboren in Trinidad en Vladimir Nabokov in Rusland."@nl .

	rdfs:comment	"Quranism (Arabic: \\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0631\\u0622\\u0646\\u064A\\u0629\\u200E; al-Qur\'\\u0101niyyat) is an Islamic view that holds the Qur\'an to be the most authentic criterion in Islam. Qur\'anists reject the religious authority of the Hadith. This is in contrast to the Shia, Sunni, and Ibadi forms of Islam, which view the Hadith as essential to religious practice.Liberal movements within Islam include Quranists who interpret Islam as \\"a belief system committed to the liberal values of a democratic world\\"."@en ,
		"Le coranisme est un courant de l\'islam scripturaliste, car fond\\u00E9 sur le Coran seul et le refus des hadiths. Le coranisme est la version musulmane du \\"Sola scriptura\\" des protestants et du kara\\u00EFsme dans le juda\\u00EFsme.Les coranistes (ou coranites) se fondent uniquement sur le Coran, contrairement aux sunnites et chiites qui croient au Coran et aux hadiths."@fr ,

		"I coranisti (in arabo: \\u0642\\u0631\\u0622\\u0646\\u064A\\u0648\\u0646\\u200E, Qur\\u02BE\\u0101niyy\\u016Bn), o \\"coraniti\\", o \\"musulmani coranici\\", o \\"musulmani anti-\\u1E25ad\\u012Bth\\" sono quei musulmani che accettano esclusivamente il Corano (Qur\\u02BE\\u0101n), testo sacro dell\'Islam, rifiutando i \\u1E25ad\\u012Bth (parole, silenzi, fatti e inazioni attribuiti al profeta Maometto, riprendendo forse inconsapevolmente quanto sostenuto in periodo abbaside dal poeta, teologo e giurista  Ibr\\u0101h\\u012Bm al-Nazz\\u0101m che fond\\u00F2 un movimento, chiamato  Nazz\\u0101miyya, che rifiutava l\'autorit\\u00E0 dei hadith, facendo riferimento al solo Corano.Essi quindi costituiscono la versione islamica del Caraismo ebraico e del movimento cristiano protestante Sola scriptura.\\u00C8 impossibile fornire una cifra sufficientemente affidabile circa la loro consistenza numerica, vista la riottosit\\u00E0 dei coranisti di mostrarsi apertamente in dissenso col resto dei musulmani \\"ortodossi\\", ricorrendo quindi a una specie di precauzionale taqiya.Le differenze dottrinarie tra questi musulmani \\"riformisti\\" e gli altri musulmani \\"tradizionali\\" (sunniti e sciiti) spaziano da questioni di secondaria importanza al nucleo delle credenze fondamentali, come i cinque pilastri dell\'Islam. "@it ,

		"Skrypturalizm (albo Islam koraniczny) - ruch religijny za jedyne \\u017Ar\\u00F3d\\u0142o islamu uznaj\\u0105cy Koran. Skrypturalizm opiera si\\u0119 w ca\\u0142o\\u015Bci lub w znacznej mierze na autorytecie wy\\u0142\\u0105cznie samego Koranu. Tym samym odrzuca ca\\u0142kowicie lub w cz\\u0119\\u015Bci Sunn\\u0119 (Tradycj\\u0119) - nie traktuj\\u0105c jej jako \\u017Ar\\u00F3d\\u0142a objawienia. Nurt ten wywodzi si\\u0119 z opozycji wyros\\u0142ej w Sunnizmie, ma swoich zwolennik\\u00F3w w Arabii Saudyjskiej i innych krajach muzu\\u0142ma\\u0144skich, takich jak Iran, Pakistan czy Egipt."@pl ,
		"Koranisme (Arabisch: \\u0642\\u0631\\u0622\\u0646\\u064A\\u0648\\u0646, Qur\\u02BE\\u0101niy\\u016Bn, Engels: Quranism), ook wel bekend als Quran alone Islam, is een overtuiging die de religieuze autoriteit van de Hadith-verzamelingen geheel of gedeeltelijk afwijst en de Koran beschouwt als meest (of enige) gezaghebbende tekst in de islam. De Hadith-verzamelingen zijn in de 8e eeuw en 9e eeuw neergeschreven overleveringen over het doen en laten en de uitspraken van Mohammed."@nl .

		"Anti-art"@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"L\\u2019Anti-art est un ensemble de concepts et d\'attitudes qui rejettent l\\u2019art et peuvent prendre la forme d\'art ou non. Le terme a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 utilis\\u00E9 pour la premi\\u00E8re fois par Marcel Duchamp[r\\u00E9f. n\\u00E9cessaire].Certaines formes d\'anti-art \\u00AB rejettent seulement certains aspects de l\'art \\u00BB. Selon le cas, elles rejettent les normes artistiques conventionnelles, le march\\u00E9 de l\\u2019art, la haute culture, l\\u2019individualisme en art ou l\\u2019universalit\\u00E9 de l\\u2019art.D\\u2019autres formes d\\u2019anti-art \\u00AB rejettent l\\u2019art enti\\u00E8rement \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"\\u53CD\\u82B8\\u8853\\uFF08\\u306F\\u3093\\u3052\\u3044\\u3058\\u3085\\u3064\\u3001Anti-art\\uFF09\\u306F\\u82B8\\u8853\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\u306B\\u5BFE\\u3059\\u308B\\u5B9A\\u7FA9\\u3067\\u3001\\u4F1D\\u7D71\\u7684\\u306A\\u5C55\\u89A7\\u4F1A\\u306E\\u6587\\u8108\\u306E\\u4E2D\\u3067\\u5C55\\u793A\\u3055\\u308C\\u306A\\u304C\\u3089\\u3001\\u771F\\u5263\\u306A\\u82B8\\u8853\\u3092\\u3042\\u3056\\u7B11\\u3046\\u304B\\u306E\\u3088\\u3046\\u306A\\u5185\\u5BB9\\u3092\\u6301\\u3064\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\u3001\\u307E\\u305F\\u82B8\\u8853\\u3068\\u3044\\u3046\\u3082\\u306E\\u306E\\u672C\\u8CEA\\u3092\\u554F\\u3044\\u76F4\\u3057\\u5909\\u8CEA\\u3055\\u305B\\u3066\\u3057\\u307E\\u3046\\u3088\\u3046\\u306A\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\u306E\\u3053\\u3068\\u3002\\u3055\\u3089\\u306B\\u65E2\\u5B58\\u306E\\u82B8\\u8853\\u3068\\u3044\\u3046\\u67A0\\u7D44\\u307F\\u3092\\u9038\\u8131\\u3059\\u308B\\u3088\\u3046\\u306A\\u82B8\\u8853\\u601D\\u60F3\\u3084\\u82B8\\u8853\\u904B\\u52D5\\u306E\\u3053\\u3068\\u3002\\u30C0\\u30C0\\u30A4\\u30B9\\u30E0\\u306B\\u3088\\u308B\\u30AA\\u30D6\\u30B8\\u30A7\\u3084\\u81EA\\u52D5\\u7B46\\u8A18\\u306B\\u3088\\u308B\\u6587\\u5B66\\u3001\\u30CA\\u30F3\\u30BB\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u8A69\\u306A\\u3069\\u3001\\u6311\\u767A\\u7684\\u306A\\u82B8\\u8853\\u5F62\\u614B\\u304C\\u300C\\u53CD\\u82B8\\u8853\\u300D\\u3068\\u547C\\u3070\\u308C\\u305F\\u304C\\u3001\\u82B8\\u8853\\u306E\\u67A0\\u304C\\u3042\\u308B\\u9650\\u308A\\u3001\\u53CD\\u82B8\\u8853\\u306F\\u3044\\u3064\\u3067\\u3082\\u3069\\u3053\\u3067\\u3082\\u51FA\\u73FE\\u3059\\u308B\\u53EF\\u80FD\\u6027\\u304C\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u307E\\u305F20\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u7F8E\\u8853\\u306E\\u6B74\\u53F2\\u306F\\u3001\\u53CD\\u82B8\\u8853\\u304C\\u82B8\\u8853\\u306E\\u7BC4\\u56F2\\u3092\\u62BC\\u3057\\u5E83\\u3052\\u305F\\u7D50\\u679C\\u3068\\u3082\\u3044\\u3048\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Para aclarar la idea de lo que es un movimiento antiarte se debe definir primero lo que es \\"arte\\". Una de las definiciones m\\u00E1s aceptadas, menciona al arte como el acto ligado a las emociones, relacionado estrechamente con la creaci\\u00F3n y apreciaci\\u00F3n de la belleza, entendiendo la belleza como aquella cualidad contenida en un objeto que satisface las necesidades de un sujeto."@es ,
		"Anti-art is a loosely used term applied to an array of concepts and attitudes that reject prior definitions of art and question art in general. Somewhat paradoxically, anti-art tends to conduct this questioning and rejection from the vantage point of art. The term is associated with the Dada movement and is generally accepted as attributable to Marcel Duchamp pre-World War I around 1914, when he began to use found objects as art. It was used to describe revolutionary forms of art."@en ,
		"Anti-arte \\u00E8 qualsiasi opera che pu\\u00F2 essere esposta in un contesto \\"tradizionale\\" ma che di fatto denigra l\'arte stessa o ne stravolge la natura. Il termine \\u00E8 da attribuirsi all\'artista franco-americano Marcel Duchamp, il cui lavoro Fountain - un urinale - fu il primo esempio del genere. Con la sua opera, Duchamp metteva in discussione la funzione stessa dell\'arte e dell\'artista in un momento storico in cui restava poco spazio di azione per l\'artista nella societ\\u00E0."@it ,

	rdfs:comment	"\\u062A\\u0645\\u062B\\u0644 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0635\\u062D\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u064A\\u0629 (\\u0628\\u0627\\u0644\\u0625\\u0646\\u062C\\u0644\\u064A\\u0632\\u064A\\u0629: Global Health) \\u0635\\u062D\\u0629 \\u0633\\u0643\\u0627\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645 \\u0623\\u062C\\u0645\\u0639 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0633\\u064A\\u0627\\u0642 \\u0639\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u064A \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u062A\\u064A \\u062A\\u062A\\u062C\\u0627\\u0648\\u0632 \\u0623\\u0628\\u0639\\u0627\\u062F \\u0648\\u0627\\u0647\\u062A\\u0645\\u0627\\u0645\\u0627\\u062A \\u0643\\u0644 \\u062F\\u0648\\u0644\\u0629 \\u0623\\u0648 \\u0623\\u0645\\u0629 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u062D\\u062F\\u0629."@ar ,
		"Global health is the health of populations in a global context; it has been defined as \\"the area of study, research and practice that places a priority on improving health and achieving equity in health for all people worldwide\\". Problems that transcend national borders or have a global political and economic impact are often emphasized. Thus, global health is about worldwide health improvement, reduction of disparities, and protection against global threats that disregard national borders."@en .

dbr:New_Weird	rdfs:label	"New Weird"@de ,
		"New Weird"@it ,
		"New Weird"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The New Weird is a literary genre that began in the 1990s and developed in a series of novels and stories published from 2001 to 2005. The writers involved are mostly novelists who are considered to be parts of the horror and/or speculative fiction genres but who often cross genre boundaries. Notable authors include China Mi\\u00E9ville, Jeff VanderMeer,K. J. Bishop and Steph Swainston."@en ,
		"Der Begriff New Weird bezeichnet eine Tendenz oder Str\\u00F6mung in den Werken einiger Schriftsteller der neueren phantastischen Literatur. Es handelt sich dabei zumeist um Romanciers, die in den Genres der Science Fiction oder der Speculative Fiction zuhause sind. Mit dem Begriff ist keine feste Gruppe von Autoren gemeint: Es existiert kein gemeinsames Manifest, die Bandbreite der Stile und Inhalte ist gro\\u00DF, und die gemeinten Autoren sehen sich nicht als Teil einer \\u201EBewegung\\u201C."@de ,
		"Il new weird \\u00E8 un sottogenere della narrativa fantastica, soprattutto fantasy, sviluppatosi a partire dagli anni novanta."@it .
dbr:Progressivism_in_the_United_States	rdfs:label	"Progressivism in the United States"@en ,
		"\\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0433\\u0440\\u0435\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0432\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C \\u0432 \\u0421\\u0428\\u0410"@ru ;
	rdfs:comment	"Progressivism in the United States is a broadly based reform movement that reached its height early in the 20th century and is generally considered to be middle class and reformist in nature. It arose as a response to the vast changes brought by modernization, such as the growth of large corporations and railroads, and fears of corruption in American politics.  In the 21st century, progressives continue to embrace concepts such as environmentalism and social justice."@en ,

		"Proletkult \\u00E9 a abreviatura da express\\u00E3o russa \\"proletarskaya kultura\\" (\\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u0430), que significa \\"cultura prolet\\u00E1ria\\". ,
		"Proletkult (Russian: \\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u043A\\u0443\\u0301\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442; IPA: [pr\\u0259l\\u02B2\\u026At\\u02C8kul\\u02B2t]), a portmanteau of the Russian words \\"proletarskaya kultura\\" (proletarian culture), was an experimental Soviet artistic institution which arose in conjunction with the Russian Revolution of 1917. This organization, a federation of local cultural societies and avant-garde artists, was most prominent in the visual, literary, and dramatic fields."@en ,
		"Proletkult (en ruso: \\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u043A\\u0443\\u0301\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442) una contracci\\u00F3n de las palabras rusas \\"proletarskaya kultura\\", fue una Instituci\\u00F3n art\\u00EDstica experimental sovi\\u00E9tica que se levant\\u00F3 en conjunto con la Revoluci\\u00F3n Rusa de 1917. Esta organizaci\\u00F3n, una federaci\\u00F3n de asociaciones culturales locales y artistas de vanguardia, fue m\\u00E1s prominente en los campos visuales, literarios y dram\\u00E1ticos."@es ,
		"Proletkult (in russo: \\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u043A\\u0443\\u0301\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442?, traslitterato:  Proletk\\u00FAl\'t) \\u00E8 l\'abbreviazione di \\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u043A\\u0438\\u0435 \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u00AD\\u043D\\u043E-\\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0441\\u0432\\u0435\\u0442\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u043B\\u044C\\u043D\\u044B\\u0435 \\u043E\\u0440\\u0433\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0437\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u0438 (traslitterato: Proletarskie kul\'tur\\u00ADno-prosvetitel\'nye organizacii, \\u00ABOrganizzazione Culturale-educativa Proletaria\\u00BB), un organismo fondato in Unione Sovietica nel 1917 con lo scopo, secondo le formulazioni teoriche del critico marxista Aleksandr Bogdanov, di fornire le basi di una vera arte proletaria, vale a dire di un\'arte creata dai proletari per i proletari, priva di tutte le vestigia della cultura borghese."@it ,
		"Proletkult  (russisch \\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442) ist ein Kurzwort aus \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u0430 (proletarskaja kultura \\u2013 proletarische Kultur). Es bezeichnet eine kulturrevolution\\u00E4re Bewegung der russischen Oktoberrevolution. Vom damaligen Petrograd ausgehend versuchte sie zwischen 1917 und 1925 eine Kultur der neuen herrschenden proletarischen Klasse ohne jeden bourgeoisen Einfluss zu erschaffen. Hierbei nahm sie erkenntnistheoretisch eine radikale Standpunkt-Theorie ein. Der Haupttheoretiker war Alexander A."@de ,
		"Proletkoult (ou Proletkult) est un mot-valise pour Proletarska\\u00EFa koultoura (\\u041F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u0430), ce qui signifie en russe \\u00AB Culture du prol\\u00E9tariat \\u00BB.Le Proletkoult est une organisation artistique et litt\\u00E9raire active en Union sovi\\u00E9tique de 1917 \\u00E0 1925 voulant fournir les fondations d\'un vrai art prol\\u00E9tarien absous de toute influence bourgeoise."@fr ,
		"Proletkoelt (kort voor het Russische: \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u043B\\u0435\\u0442\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043A\\u0443\\u043B\\u044C\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u0430; proletarskaja kultura - proletarische Cultuur) is een beweging die in Rusland ontstond kort na de revolutie van 1917. Doelstelling was het tot stand brengen van een cultuur voor en door proletari\\u00EBrs en het tegengaan van de bourgeoiscultuur, via verenigingen en zogenaamde volksuniversiteiten."@nl .

		"L\'\\u00E9cole Rimpa (\\u7433\\u6D3E), transcrite \\u00E9galement sous la forme Rinpa, est une des \\u00E9coles historiques majeures de la peinture japonaise d\\u00E9corative. Elle fut cr\\u00E9\\u00E9e au XVIIe si\\u00E8cle par les artistes Hon\'ami K\\u014Detsu (1558-1637) et Tawaraya S\\u014Dtatsu (mort aux alentours de 1643). Une cinquantaine d\'ann\\u00E9es plus tard, ce style fut encore affirm\\u00E9 par les fr\\u00E8res Ogata K\\u014Drin et Kenzan."@fr ,
		"Rinpa (\\u7433\\u6D3E, Rinpa), is one of the major historical schools of Japanese painting. It was created in 17th century Kyoto by Hon\'ami K\\u014Detsu (1558\\u20131637) and Tawaraya S\\u014Dtatsu (d. c.1643). Roughly fifty years later, the style was consolidated by brothers Ogata K\\u014Drin (1658\\u20131716) and Ogata Kenzan (1663\\u20131743).The term \\"Rinpa\\" is an abbreviation consisting of the last syllable from \\"K\\u014Drin\\" with the word for school (\\u6D3E, ha) (with rendaku changing this to \\"pa\\"), coined in the Meiji period."@en ,
		"Rinpa (\\u7433\\u6D3E, Rinpa?), tambi\\u00E9n romanizado como Rimpa, es una de las escuelas m\\u00E1s importantes de la pintura japonesa. Surgi\\u00F3 en el siglo XVII con los artistas Honami K\\u014Detsu (1558 - 1637) y Tawaraya S\\u014Dtatsu (1643)."@es ,
		"La scuola Rinpa (\\u7433\\u6D3E?) \\u00E8 una delle pi\\u00F9 importanti scuole storiche della pittura giapponese. Fu creata nel XVII secolo a Kyoto da Hon\'ami K\\u014Detsu e Tawaraya S\\u014Dtatsu. Circa cinquant\'anni pi\\u00F9 tardi, lo stile fu consolidato dai fratelli Ogata K\\u014Drin e Ogata Kenzan. Il termine \\"Rinpa\\" \\u00E8 un\'abbreviazione composta dall\'ultima sillaba di \\"K\\u014Drin\\" e dalla parola \\"scuola\\" (\\u6D3E ha?, poi trasformatasi in pa), e fu coniata nel periodo Meiji."@it ,
		"Rimpa (jap. \\u7433\\u6D3E), auch K\\u014Drin-ha (\\u5149\\u7433\\u6D3E) oder S\\u014Dtatsu-K\\u014Drin-ha (\\u5B97\\u9054\\u5149\\u7433\\u6D3E), ist eine Schule der japanischen Malerei, benannt nach ihrem bedeutenden Vertreter Ogata K\\u014Drin bzw. auch Tawaraya S\\u014Dtatsu, die vom Ende des 16. Jahrhunderts bis in das 19. Jahrhundert bl\\u00FChte, ohne dass in jedem Fall ein direktes Lehrer-Sch\\u00FCler-Verh\\u00E4ltnis bestand.Stilistisch zeichnet sie sich durch die Verwendung von leuchtenden Farben, einschlie\\u00DFlich Gold- und Silberfarbe aus."@de .

		"A Escola de Paris (\\u00C9cole de Paris) se refere a dois distintos grupos de artistas: um grupo de iluminadores medievais e um grupos de artistas n\\u00E3o-franceses que trabalhavam em Paris antes da Primeira Guerra Mundial. Tamb\\u00E9m se refere a outro grupo de artistas que trabalhou na cidade entre as duas guerras."@pt ,
		"Se denomina Escuela de Par\\u00EDs a un grupo heterodoxo de artistas que trabajaron en Par\\u00EDs (Francia) en el periodo de entreguerras (1915-1940), vinculados a diversos estilos art\\u00EDsticos como el posimpresionismo, el expresionismo y el surrealismo. El t\\u00E9rmino engloba a una gran variedad de artistas, tanto franceses como extranjeros, que resid\\u00EDan en la capital francesa en el intervalo entre las dos guerras mundiales."@es ,
		"\\u00C9cole de Paris (franz\\u00F6sisch f\\u00FCr: \\"Schule von Paris\\") bezeichnet verschiedene Gruppen von K\\u00FCnstlern zu unterschiedlichen Zeiten: Eine Gruppe von mittelalterlichen Buchmalern, eine Gruppe von nicht-franz\\u00F6sischen K\\u00FCnstlern in Paris vor dem Ersten Weltkrieg und eine \\u00E4hnliche Gruppe zwischen den beiden Weltkriegen sowie eine Gruppe zeitgen\\u00F6ssischer Maler nach dem Zweiten Weltkrieg."@de ,
		"Il termine Scuola di Parigi (in francese \\u00C9cole de Paris) viene utilizzato per indicare il gruppo di artisti non francesi che visse e lavor\\u00F2 a Parigi nel periodo seguente allo scoppio della Prima guerra mondiale e che diedero vita al Postimpressionismo, al Cubismo, Fauvismo.Tra questi bisogna ricordare, non solo artisti non francesi come Pablo Picasso, Marc Chagall, Amedeo Modigliani, Piet Mondrian, Mo\\u00EFse Kisling ma anche altri francesi come Pierre Bonnard e Henri Matisse.Molti di questi artisti continuarono ad operare a Parigi anche nel periodo del primo dopoguerra e a loro si aggiunsero Hans Arp, Robert Delaunay, Sonia Delaunay, Joan Mir\\u00F3, Constantin Br\\u00E2ncu\\u0219i, Raoul Dufy, Ren\\u00E9 Ich\\u00E9, Tsuguharu Foujita e Chaim Soutine e che diedero vita a nuovi stili compreso il Surrealismo e il Dadaismo."@it ,
		"School of Paris (French: \\u00C9cole de Paris) refers to three distinct groups of artists: a group of medieval manuscript illuminators; a group of French and non-French artists working in Paris before World War I; and a group of both French and non-French artists living in Paris between the two world wars and beyond."@en ,

		"La literatura en yidis o literatura y\\u00EDdica es la escrita en yidis, la lengua de los jud\\u00EDos askenaz\\u00EDes, emparentada con el alem\\u00E1n medieval. Suele considerarse que la literatura en yidis ha tenido tres etapas: antigua literatura y\\u00EDdica (1300-1780); literatura has\\u00EDdica y de la Haskal\\u00E1 (1780- h. 1890); y literatura y\\u00EDdica moderna (1864-actualidad)."@es ,
		"Yiddish literature encompasses all those belles-lettres written in Yiddish, the language of Ashkenazic Jewry which is related to Middle High German. The history of Yiddish, with its roots in central Europe and locus for centuries in Eastern Europe, is evident in its literature.It is generally described as having three historical phases: Old Yiddish literature; Haskalah and Hasidic literature; and modern Yiddish literature."@en ,
		"Jiddische literatuur is de, vaak in Hebreeuws schrift opgestelde literatuur in het Jiddisch."@nl ,
		"Jiddische Literatur ist die mit hebr\\u00E4ischen Schriftzeichen niedergeschriebene Literatur der jiddischen Sprache."@de ,

La langue yiddish prend ses racines en Europe centrale, et a migr\\u00E9 au cours des si\\u00E8cles vers l\'Europe de l\'Est."@fr .

	rdfs:comment	"El manga alternativo son las historietas japonesas publicadas fuera del mercado m\\u00E1s comercial de manga, o tambi\\u00E9n el manga que posee estilos, temas o narrativa diferente al com\\u00FAnmente utilizado en las revistas antol\\u00F3gicas de manga m\\u00E1s populares."@es ,
		"Alternative Manga oder Underground-Manga sind japanische Comics, die nicht prim\\u00E4r f\\u00FCr den kommerziellen Manga-Markt produziert werden. Auch Manga, die sich in Zeichen- bzw. Erz\\u00E4hlstil oder Thema von \\u00FCblicherweise in Manga-Magazinen vorkommenden Manga unterscheiden, werden als \\u201Ealternativ\\u201C bezeichnet."@de ,
		"Alternative manga are Japanese comics that are published outside of the more commercial manga market, or which have different art styles, themes, and narratives to those found in the more popular manga magazines.Alternative manga originated in the lending libraries of post-war Japan, which charged a small fee for borrowing books.  This market was essentially its own marketplace with many manga being printed exclusively for it."@en .

dbr:Capitalist_realism	rdfs:label	"Kapitalistischer Realismus"@de ,

	rdfs:comment	"Kapitalistisch realisme (Duits: Kapitalistischer Realismus) is een richting binnen de Duitse beeldende kunst."@nl ,
		"The term \\"Capitalist realism\\" has several meanings or uses. It has been used, particularly in Germany, to describe commodity-based art, from Pop Art in the 1950s and 1960s to the commodity art of the 1980s and 1990s. Alternatively, it has been used to describe the ideological-aesthetic aspect of contemporary corporate capitalism in the West. When used in this way, it is a play on the term \\"Socialist realism\\"."@en ,
		"Der Begriff Kapitalistischer Realismus wurde zwischen 1963 und 1966 von den Malern Gerhard Richter (damals noch Gerd Richter), Konrad Lueg (K\\u00FCnstlername des sp\\u00E4teren Galeristen Konrad Fischer), Sigmar Polke und Manfred Kuttner eingef\\u00FChrt, um unter diesem Titel Selbsthilfeausstellungen und Performances zu veranstalten."@de .

dbr:Classical_sculpture	rdfs:label	"Classical sculpture"@en ,
		"Sculpture classique"@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"Classical sculpture refers loosely to the forms of sculpture from Ancient Greece and Ancient Rome, as well as the Hellenized and Romanized civilizations under their rule or influence from about 500 BC to around 200 AD. More precisely it refers to Ancient Greek sculpture from around 500 BC to the onset of the Hellenistic style around 323 BC. It may also refer stylistically to later sculpture done in a Neoclassical or classical style. Classical sculptures have been popular since the Renaissance."@en ,
		"Le terme de sculpture classique d\\u00E9signe une forme et un style sculpture correspondant \\u00E0 celle produite dans la Gr\\u00E8ce antique, la Rome antique et les civilisations sous le contr\\u00F4le ou l\'influence hell\\u00E9nistique et romaine entre le V e s avant notre \\u00E8re et la chute de Rome en 476. Cela d\\u00E9signe \\u00E9galement des sculptures plus r\\u00E9centes r\\u00E9alis\\u00E9e selon un style classique, c\'est-\\u00E0-dire inspir\\u00E9 de l\'Antiquit\\u00E9."@fr .

dbr:Marxist_literary_criticism	rdfs:label	"Cr\\u00EDtica literaria marxista"@es ,
		"Critica letteraria marxista"@it ,
		"Marxist literary criticism"@en ,
		"Marxistische Literaturtheorie"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"Cr\\u00EDtica literaria marxista es un enfoque m\\u00E1s de la cr\\u00EDtica literaria y se agrupa en el campo de la sociolog\\u00EDa de la literatura. Su an\\u00E1lisis de la obra se basa en las relaciones de producci\\u00F3n, tanto econ\\u00F3micas, pol\\u00EDticas como sociales enmarcadas en un momento hist\\u00F3rico. En otras palabras, la cr\\u00EDtica literaria marxista escruta y expone las implicaciones sociales e ideol\\u00F3gicas de una obra literaria, las cuales no son visibles a veces para el lector."@es ,
		"Critica letteraria marxista \\u00E8 un termine che indica la critica letteraria influenzata dal pensiero filosofico e politico marxista. La sua storia risale alla nascita del marxismo stesso, infatti sia Karl Marx e Friedrich Engels erano appassionati lettori (Marx leggeva molto Shakespeare, come anche le opere a lui contemporanee, per esempio quelle di Heinrich Heine)."@it ,
		"Marxist literary criticism is a loose term describing literary criticism based on socialist and dialectic theories. Marxist criticism views literary works as reflections of the social institutions from which they originate. According to Marxists, even literature itself is a social institution and has a specific ideological function, based on the background and ideology of the author."@en ,
		"Die marxistische Literaturtheorie z\\u00E4hlt zu den kontextzentrierten Literaturtheorien. Der Sammelbegriff fasst diejenigen Literaturtheorien zusammen, welche sich auf die Theorie des Marxismus berufen bzw. die Literatur vom Standpunkt der marxistischen Weltanschauung aus betrachten. Die verschiedenen marxistischen Literaturkritiken versuchen deshalb die Rolle herauszuarbeiten, welche die Literatur, und die Kunst im Allgemeinen, in der Gesellschaft spielen."@de .
