	rdfs:comment	"The Euston Road School is a term applied to a group of English painters, active either as staff or students at the School of Drawing and Painting in London between 1937 and 1939. The School opened in October 1937 at premises in Fitzroy Street before moving to 314/316 Euston Road in February 1938. The School was founded by William Coldstream, Victor Pasmore and Claude Rogers."@en .

		"I-Novel (\\u79C1\\u5C0F\\u8AAC, Shish\\u014Dsetsu, Watakushi sh\\u014Dsetsu) is a literary genre in Japanese literature used to describe a type of confessional literature where the events in the story correspond to events in the author\'s life.   This genre was founded based on the Japanese reception of Naturalism during the Meiji period. Many authors believed form reflected greater individuality and a less constrained method of writing."@en ,

		"New British Sculpture est le nom donn\\u00E9 \\u00E0 un groupe d\'artistes, sculpteurs et auteurs d\'installations qui ont commenc\\u00E9 \\u00E0 exposer ensemble \\u00E0 Londres, au d\\u00E9but des ann\\u00E9es 1980, et comprenant Edward Allington, Stephen Cox, Tony Cragg, Grenville Davey, Richard Deacon, Barry Flanagan, Anthony Gormley, Shirazeh Houshiary, Anish Kapoor, Julian Opie, Boyd Webb, Richard Wentworth, Rachel Whiteread, Alison Wilding et Bill Woodrow."@fr ,
		"New British Sculpture is the name given to the work of a group of artists, sculptors and installation artists who began to exhibit together in London, England, in the early 1980s, including Tony Cragg, Richard Deacon and Richard Wentworth.Tim Woods has characterized the movement by identifying four major themes, \\"(a) a synthesis of pop and kitsch, (b) a bricolage (assemblage) of the decaying UK urban environment and the waste of consumer society, (c) an exploration of the way in which objects are assigned meanings, and (d) a play of colour, wit and humour.\\" An early champion was art dealer Nicholas Logsdail who exhibited many of the artists at his Lisson Gallery."@en .

		"The Generation of \'36 (Spanish: Generaci\\u00F3n del 36)  is the name given to a group of Spanish artists, poets and playwrights who were working about the time of the Spanish Civil War (1936 and 1939).The Generation of \'36 was a literary movement that suffered harsh criticism and persecution that followed from the division of neighbors into winners and losers in the various battles of that struggle, as well as the physical hardships and moral miseries arising from social instability and political chaos. 		"G\\u00E9n\\u00E9ration de 36, en espagnol : Generaci\\u00F3n del 36, et \\u00E9galement appel\\u00E9e \\u00AB promoci\\u00F3n de 1936 \\u00BB \\u2014 promotion de 1936 \\u2014, est la d\\u00E9nomination attribu\\u00E9e, dans l\'histoire de la litt\\u00E9rature espagnole, \\u00E0 un mouvement litt\\u00E9raire espagnol par des \\u00E9crivains, po\\u00E8tes et dramaturges de l\'\\u00E9poque de la guerre civile espagnole qui eut lieu entre 1936 et 1939."@fr .

dbr:Contemporary_Indigenous_Australian_art	rdfs:label	"Arte contempor\\u00E2nea ind\\u00EDgena da Austr\\u00E1lia"@pt ,
		"Contemporary Indigenous Australian art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"cA arte contempor\\u00E2nea ind\\u00EDgena da Austr\\u00E1lia s\\u00E3o as obras de arte moderna produzida por ind\\u00EDgenas australianos. \\u00C9 geralmente considerado como origin\\u00E1rio de um movimento de pintura que come\\u00E7ou a Papunya, a noroeste de Alice Springs, Territ\\u00F3rio do Norte em 1971, facilitada pelo professor australiano branco e oper\\u00E1rio da arte Geoffrey Bardon."@pt ,
		"Contemporary Indigenous Australian art (also known as Contemporary Aboriginal Australian art) is the modern art work produced by indigenous Australians. It is generally regarded as beginning in 1971 with a painting movement that started at Papunya, northwest of Alice Springs, Northern Territory, involving artists such as Clifford Possum Tjapaltjarri and Kaapa Tjampitjinpa, and facilitated by white Australian teacher and art worker Geoffrey Bardon."@en .

dbr:Colourist_painting	rdfs:label	"Colourist painting"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Colourist painting is characterised by the use of intense colour, which becomes the dominant feature of the resultant work of art, more important than its other qualities. This tendency in painting was foreshadowed by French Impressionism in the late 19th century, and came to prominence in the work of the Fauvists in the early 20th century."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Rhondda ist ein ehemaliges Kohlerevier  in S\\u00FCdwales mit etwa 59.900 Einwohnern. Die Kohlevorkommen wurden Mitte des 19. Jahrhunderts entdeckt. Durch Eisenbahnstrecken in den Gruben und zu den H\\u00E4fen (Cardiff, Barry und Neath Port Talbot) entwickelte sich die Agrarregion schnell zu einem industriellen Zentrum und die Einwohnerzahl stieg von 542 Einwohnern im Jahr 1801 auf 113.000 im Jahr 1901."@de ,
		"Rhondda /\\u02C8r\\u0252n\\u00F0\\u0259/, or the Rhondda Valley (Welsh: Cwm Rhondda [k\\u028Am \\u02C8r\\u0325\\u0254n\\u00F0a]), is a former coal mining valley in Wales, formerly a local government district, consisting of 16 communities built around the River Rhondda. The valley is made up of two valleys, the larger Rhondda Fawr valley (mawr large) and the smaller Rhondda Fach valley (bach small). Both the singular term \'Rhondda Valley\' and the plural \'Rhondda Valleys\' are commonly used."@en ,
		"Rhondda, Rhondda Valley (IPA: \'r\\u0252n\\u00F0\\u0258; wal.: Cwm Rhondda) \\u2013 dolina w Walii, dawniej obszar intensywnego wydobycia w\\u0119gla. W sk\\u0142ad doliny Rhondda wchodz\\u0105: wi\\u0119ksza dolina Rhondda Fawr oraz mniejsza Rhondda Fach. Do 1996 roku obszar doliny stanowi\\u0142 oddzielny dystrykt Rhondda. Obecnie dolina nale\\u017Cy do dystryktu Rhondda Cynon Taf. Ludno\\u015B\\u0107 zamieszkuj\\u0105ca obszar Rhonddy wynosi 72 443 mieszka\\u0144c\\u00F3w (2001)."@pl ,
		"Localidad del Reino Unido, en el sur de Gales. Situada en el condado ceremonial gal\\u00E9s de Mid Glamorgan, a orillas del r\\u00EDo Rhondda, en una zona productora de carb\\u00F3n y de hierro, productos destinados a los puertos de Barry y Cardiff. Cabecera del condado de Rhondda Cynon Taf, creado el 1 de abril de 1996, de 231 800 habitantes.Destacan sus industrias sider\\u00FArgicas y de transformados met\\u00E1licos, sectores que tuvieron que pasar por una grave crisis en los a\\u00F1os 1980 que afect\\u00F3 a todo el sur de Gales."@es .

		"O Cloisonnisme \\u00E9 um estilo da pintura p\\u00F3s-impressionista caracterizado por cores lisas delimitadas por contornos escuros. O termo foi utilizado pelo cr\\u00EDtico \\u00C9douard Dujardin por ocasi\\u00E3o do Sal\\u00E3o dos Independentes, em Mar\\u00E7o de 1888. Os artistas \\u00C9mile Bernard, Louis Anquetin, Paul Gauguin, Paul S\\u00E9rusier, e outros, come\\u00E7arama pintar com este estilo no final do s\\u00E9culo XIX."@pt ,
		"Der Cloisonismus (von franz. cloison \\u201EScheidewand\\u201C) ist eine Kunststr\\u00F6mung innerhalb der Malerei der Moderne, die im Jahr 1888 im Kreis der K\\u00FCnstler der Schule von Pont-Aven entwickelt wurde.  Der Begriff wurde von dem franz\\u00F6sischen Kunstkritiker \\u00C9douard Dujardin gepr\\u00E4gt und von ihm erstmals in einem am 9. Mai 1888 in der Revue Ind\\u00E9pendante erschienenen Artikel verwendet."@de ,
		"\\u30AF\\u30ED\\u30EF\\u30BE\\u30CB\\u30B9\\u30E0\\uFF08\\u307E\\u305F\\u306F\\u30AF\\u30ED\\u30EF\\u30BE\\u30CB\\u30BA\\u30E0\\u3001\\u30AF\\u30ED\\u30EF\\u30BD\\u30CB\\u30B9\\u30E0\\u3001\\u30AF\\u30ED\\u30EF\\u30BD\\u30CB\\u30BA\\u30E0\\u3001Cloisonnism\\uFF09\\u3068\\u306F\\u3001\\u6697\\u3044\\u8F2A\\u90ED\\u7DDA\\u306B\\u3088\\u3063\\u3066\\u5206\\u3051\\u3089\\u308C\\u305F\\u304F\\u3063\\u304D\\u308A\\u3057\\u305F\\u30D5\\u30A9\\u30EB\\u30E0\\u3067\\u63CF\\u304B\\u308C\\u305F\\u3001\\u30DD\\u30B9\\u30C8\\u5370\\u8C61\\u6D3E\\u306E\\u69D8\\u5F0F\\u306E\\u3053\\u3068\\u3002\\u8A55\\u8AD6\\u5BB6\\u306E\\u30A8\\u30C9\\u30A5\\u30A2\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30C7\\u30E5\\u30B8\\u30E3\\u30EB\\u30C0\\u30F3\\uFF08\\u00C9douard Dujardin\\uFF09\\u306E\\u9020\\u8A9E\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u3053\\u306E\\u69D8\\u5F0F\\u306F19\\u4E16\\u7D00\\u5F8C\\u671F\\u306B\\u3001\\u30A8\\u30DF\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30D9\\u30EB\\u30CA\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u3001\\u30DD\\u30FC\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30B4\\u30FC\\u30AE\\u30E3\\u30F3\\u306A\\u3069\\u306B\\u3088\\u3063\\u3066\\u59CB\\u3081\\u3089\\u308C\\u305F\\u3002\\u3053\\u306E\\u540D\\u79F0\\u306F\\u7D20\\u5730\\u306B\\u91D1\\u5C5E\\u7DDA\\uFF08cloisons\\uFF1D\\u4ED5\\u5207\\u308A\\uFF09\\u3092\\u8CBC\\u308A\\u4ED8\\u3051\\u3001\\u7C89\\u672B\\u30AC\\u30E9\\u30B9\\u3092\\u6E80\\u305F\\u3057\\u3066\\u304B\\u3089\\u713C\\u304F\\u300C\\u30AF\\u30ED\\u30EF\\u30BE\\u30CD (cloisonn\\u00E9)\\u300D\\u3092\\u601D\\u3044\\u8D77\\u3053\\u3055\\u305B\\u308B\\u3002\\u30AF\\u30ED\\u30EF\\u30BE\\u30CB\\u30B9\\u30E0\\u306E\\u4EE3\\u8868\\u3068\\u3057\\u3066\\u3042\\u3052\\u3089\\u308C\\u308B\\u306E\\u304C\\u300E\\u9EC4\\u8272\\u3044\\u30AD\\u30EA\\u30B9\\u30C8\\u300F\\uFF081889\\u5E74\\uFF09\\u3067\\u3001\\u30B4\\u30FC\\u30AE\\u30E3\\u30F3\\u306F\\u7D75\\u3092\\u9ED2\\u3044\\u8F2A\\u90ED\\u7DDA\\u3067\\u533A\\u5207\\u3063\\u305F\\u5358\\u8272\\u306E\\u90E8\\u5206\\u306B\\u5207\\u308A\\u8A70\\u3081\\u305F\\u3002\\u3053\\u3046\\u3057\\u305F\\u4F5C\\u54C1\\u3067\\u3001\\u30B4\\u30FC\\u30AE\\u30E3\\u30F3\\u306F\\u30DD\\u30B9\\u30C8\\uFF1D\\u30EB\\u30CD\\u30B5\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u7D75\\u753B\\u3067\\u6700\\u3082\\u91CD\\u8981\\u306A2\\u3064\\u306E\\u8981\\u7D20\\u3001\\u3064\\u307E\\u308A\\u300C\\u53E4\\u5178\\u7684\\u306A\\u9060\\u8FD1\\u6CD5\\u300D\\u3092\\u307B\\u3068\\u3093\\u3069\\u6C17\\u306B\\u3068\\u3081\\u305A\\u3001\\u307E\\u305F\\u300C\\u5FAE\\u5999\\u306A\\u8272\\u306E\\u30B0\\u30E9\\u30C7\\u30FC\\u30B7\\u30E7\\u30F3\\u300D\\u306F\\u5927\\u80C6\\u306B\\u7701\\u3044\\u305F\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Le cloisonnisme est une technique picturale invent\\u00E9e en 1886 par un jeune peintre, Louis Anquetin.Cette technique s\'inspire de la technique du vitrail, des estampes japonaises (japonisme), des images d\'\\u00C9pinal et des arts primitifs.Le cloisonnisme se caract\\u00E9rise par des zones de couleur cern\\u00E9es d\\u2019un trait plus fonc\\u00E9. Ce cerne permet de d\\u00E9limiter les aplats de couleur les uns par rapport aux autres."@fr ,
		"Cloisonizm (kluazonizm) \\u2013 spos\\u00F3b malowania opracowany przez Louisa Anquetina, \\u00C9mile\'a Bernarda i Paula Gauguina, kontynuowany przez malarzy skupionych wok\\u00F3\\u0142 szko\\u0142y z Pont-Aven. Polega\\u0142 na stosowaniu plam o jednolitej barwie otoczonych konturem.Nazwa wywodzi si\\u0119 od techniki zdobniczej cloisonn\\u00E9, polegaj\\u0105cej na oddzielaniu element\\u00F3w zdobniczych (np. szk\\u0142a, kamieni szlachetnych itp.) za pomoc\\u0105 cienkich blaszek lub drut\\u00F3w, a utworzy\\u0142 j\\u0105 \\u00C9douard Dujardin w 1888."@pl ,
		"Het cloisonnisme of synthetisme is een door het symbolisme be\\u00EFnvloede postimpressionistische schilderstijl. De benaming is afgeleid van email cloisonn\\u00E9, een decoratietechniek voor bijvoorbeeld vazen. De term cloisonnisme werd op 9 mei 1888 voor het eerst gebruikt door kunstcriticus \\u00C9douard Dujardin in een artikel in de Revue Ind\\u00E9pendante. Kenmerkend voor het cloisonnisme zijn vooral de grote heldere kleurvlakken die worden gescheiden door donkere contourlijnen."@nl ,
		"Il cloisonnisme (compartimentismo, divisione in compartimenti) \\u00E8 una tecnica pittorica che consiste nel racchiudere le campiture cromatiche entro il limite netto di un contorno, senza effetti chiaroscurali, creando in questo modo delle stesure compatte di colore.Il termine, utilizzato la prima volta dal critico d\'arte \\u00C9douard Dujardin, evoca la tecnica, risalente al medioevo, di costruzione delle vetrate dove i contorni delle figure formano dei compartimenti (cloisons) i quali contornano i singoli pezzi di vetro colorato; un effetto simile lo si ottiene con la tecnica dello smalto su metallo, dove a ogni colore \\u00E8 riservato uno spazio che viene riempito con polvere di vetro, il manufatto \\u00E8 poi sottoposto ad alte temperature che fondono il vetro, andando a formare colori compatti e privi di effetti chiaroscurali. "@it ,
		"Cloisonnism is a style of post-Impressionist painting with bold and flat forms separated by dark contours. The term was coined by critic Edouard Dujardin on the occasion of the Salon des Ind\\u00E9pendants, in March 1888. Artists \\u00C9mile Bernard, Louis Anquetin, Paul Gauguin, Paul S\\u00E9rusier, and others started painting in this style in the late 19th century."@en ,
		"El cloisonismo es una t\\u00E9cnica desarrollada en la segunda mitad del siglo XIX por \\u00C9mile Bernard, uno de los primeros integrantes de la Escuela de Pont Aven y por Gauguin. Su influencia proced\\u00EDa principalmente del japonismo y de Louis Anquetin. Es un estilo de pintura postimpresionista donde se utilizan colores planos, en contornos oscuros silueteados perfectamente delimitados. Se caracteriza por su efecto decorativo, su calidad formal y sus pinturas no tienen profundidad ni sombras."@es .

		"In Western European academic traditions, fine art is art developed primarily for aesthetics, distinguishing it from applied art that also has to serve some practical function.Historically, the five main fine arts were painting, sculpture, architecture, music and poetry, with performing arts including theatre and dance. Today, the fine arts commonly include additional forms, such as film, photography, conceptual art, and printmaking."@en ,
		"O conceito de belas-artes est\\u00E1 associado \\u00E0 ideia de que um certo conjunto de suportes e manifesta\\u00E7\\u00F5es art\\u00EDsticas \\u00E9 superior aos demais. At\\u00E9 meados do s\\u00E9culo XIX, as academias classificavam as artes em basicamente dois tipos:  as belas-artes   as artes aplicadas ou artes secund\\u00E1rias  As belas-artes eram aquelas que, segundo o ponto de vista do per\\u00EDodo, possu\\u00EDam a dignidade da nobreza."@pt ,
		"Con l\'espressione belle arti si indica ogni forma d\'arte sviluppata principalmente con scopi estetici e concettualmente distinti dalla utilit\\u00E0. Tale forma d\'arte \\u00E8 solitamente espressa nella produzione di manufatti artistici utilizzando forme di arte visiva, arti figurative e forme di arte scenica o arte teatrale: pittura e scultura, musica e danza, teatro, architettura, fotografia, letteratura, cinema, nel loro chiamati anche sette arti."@it ,

		"Mit Repr\\u00E4sentation (von lat. repraesentare \\u201Avergegenw\\u00E4rtigen\\u2018) bezeichnet man in der Philosophie die Vergegenw\\u00E4rtigung von nicht unmittelbar Gegebenem in der Vorstellung. Neurowissenschaftlich werden Repr\\u00E4sentationen als mentale Zust\\u00E4nde aufgefasst. Zur Bezeichnung von Repr\\u00E4sentationen werden auch Ausdr\\u00FCcke wie \\u201AVorstellung\\u2018, \\u201ADarstellung\\u2018 oder \\u201AAbbild\\u2018 verwendet. Als Medium kommen das Gehirn, Texte, Bilder, Dateien oder Algorithmen in Betracht."@de ,

	rdfs:comment	"A tondo (plural \\"tondi\\" or \\"tondos\\") is a Renaissance term for a circular work of art, either a painting or a sculpture. The word derives from the Italian rotondo, \\"round.\\"  The term is usually not used in English for small round paintings, but only those over about 60 cm (two feet) in diameter, thus excluding many round portrait miniatures \\u2013 for sculpture the threshold is rather lower.Artists have created tondi since Greek antiquity."@en ,

		"Ein Tondo (das oder der Tondo; Mehrzahl: Tondi oder Tondos) oder Rundbild ist ein kreisrundes Bildwerk. Ein Tondo kann als Gem\\u00E4lde oder Relief gestaltet sein. Das Wort ist abgeleitet vom italienischen rotondo f\\u00FCr \\u201Erund\\u201C (lateinisch rotundus) und davon eine abgek\\u00FCrzte Form.Tondi waren bereits in der griechischen Antike und im Alten Rom beliebt. Das Tondo war auch ein h\\u00E4ufig verwendetes Gestaltungselement in der Architektur, seit der Antike bis in die Epoche des Historismus."@de ,
		"Le tondo (tondi au pluriel) est un profil, g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement sculpt\\u00E9 en faible relief, mais qui peut aussi \\u00EAtre peint, r\\u00E9alis\\u00E9 sur un support de format rond ou \\u00E0 l\'int\\u00E9rieur d\'un  disque, et non en rectangle comme il est plus courant. Le terme provient de l\'italien, c\'est une  aph\\u00E9r\\u00E8se du mot rotondo (rond)."@fr ,
		"Een tondo is een rond schilderij of reli\\u00EBf. De naam komt van het Italiaanse woord rotondo, dat \\"rond\\" betekent.Rotondo\'s bestaan al sinds de Griekse oudheid, maar waren vooral geliefd bij kunstenaars van de renaissance en bij de kubisten.Een kenmerk van een tondo is dat de achtergrond vaak niet is opgevuld en geen rol speelt in het schilderij."@nl ,
		"Tondo (no plural tondi) \\u00E9 uma composi\\u00E7\\u00E3o de pintura ou escultura realizada sobre um suporte de formato redondo no interior de um  disco, e n\\u00E3o em ret\\u00E2ngulo como \\u00E9 corrente na pintura. O termo prov\\u00E9m da l\\u00EDngua italiana, sendo uma af\\u00E9rese da palavra rotondo (redondo)."@pt ,
		"Tondo (z w\\u0142. talerz, kr\\u0105g) to w sztuce obraz b\\u0105d\\u017A p\\u0142askorze\\u017Aba w kszta\\u0142cie ko\\u0142a. 		"El tondo (tondi en plural) es una composici\\u00F3n pict\\u00F3rica que est\\u00E1 realizada en forma de disco, y no en rect\\u00E1ngulo como es tradicional. El t\\u00E9rmino proviene del italiano rotondo, \\"redondo\\".Los tondi fueron creados en la Antig\\u00FCedad cl\\u00E1sica, por ejemplo abunda en la cer\\u00E1mica griega de figuras rojas, sobre todo en el fondo de las copas llamadas k\\u00EDlix (de la que deriva la palabra \\u00ABc\\u00E1liz\\u00BB). Bench\\u00E9 il termine indichi propriamente la tecnica, esso viene usato, in ambiente anglosassone utilizzando le convenzionali iniziali maiuscole, anche per indicare lo stile ceramografico tipico del VI secolo a.C., che di questa tecnica si avvalse prevalentemente. 		"O registro de pintura negra na cer\\u00E2mica grega \\u00E9 um estilo em que as figuras negras encontram-se desenhadas num fundo vermelho. Originou-se em Corinto durante o s\\u00E9culo VII a.C, espalhou-se para outras cidades e regi\\u00F5es, incluindo Esparta, e chegou \\u00E0 \\u00C1tica uma gera\\u00E7\\u00E3o depois. 		"La c\\u00E9ramique \\u00E0 figures noires est un type de c\\u00E9ramique grecque antique, dans lequel le motif se d\\u00E9tache en noir sur un fond clair. dbr:Absurdist_fiction	rdfs:label	"\\u0627\\u0644\\u0639\\u0628\\u062B\\u064A\\u0629 \\u0641\\u064A \\u0627\\u0644\\u0623\\u062F\\u0628"@ar ,
		"Literatura del absurdo"@es ,
		"Absurdist fiction"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Absurdist fiction is a genre of fictional narrative (traditionally, literary fiction), most often in the form of a novel, play, poem, or film, that focuses on the experiences of characters in situations where they cannot find any inherent purpose in life, most often represented by ultimately meaningless actions and events that call into question the certainty of existential concepts such as truth or value."@en ,
		"La literatura del absurdo se inspira en el surrealismo y la filosof\\u00EDa del absurdo para crear obras literarias marcadas por el humor y la sorpresa para denunciar situaciones sociales o reflexionar de una manera diferente sobre cuestiones existenciales."@es ,

		"Het Wilde Westen is de benaming voor de pionierssamenleving in de periode 1865-1890 in het noordwesten van de Verenigde Staten, grotendeels ten westen van de Mississippi, waar de eerste Europese kolonisten zich vestigden. Deze denkbeeldige grens (frontier) schoof steeds verder naar het westen op. De verovering en bezetting van het westen van de Verenigde Staten begon na het einde van de Amerikaanse Burgeroorlog in 1865."@nl ,
		"La conqu\\u00EAte de l\'Ouest est le processus de colonisation par des populations essentiellement d\\u2019origine europ\\u00E9enne et le gouvernement des \\u00C9tats-Unis, au XIXe si\\u00E8cle, de l\'immense territoire qui s\'\\u00E9tend en Am\\u00E9rique du Nord entre le Mississippi et l\'oc\\u00E9an Pacifique, habit\\u00E9 jusqu\'alors par les peuples am\\u00E9rindiens.De l\\u2019achat de la Louisiane \\u00E0 la France en 1803 jusqu\\u2019aux derniers territoires c\\u00E9d\\u00E9s par le Mexique en 1853, les \\u00C9tats-Unis acqui\\u00E8rent leurs fronti\\u00E8res actuelles \\u00E0 l\\u2019Ouest (hormis l\\u2019Alaska) et s\\u2019assurent la possession d\\u2019une fa\\u00E7ade sur l\\u2019oc\\u00E9an Pacifique. 		"Velho oeste, Oeste selvagem ou faroeste (em ingl\\u00EAs: old west, wild west ou far west), s\\u00E3o os termos com que se denomina popularmente o per\\u00EDodo e epis\\u00F3dios hist\\u00F3ricos que tiveram lugar no s\\u00E9culo XIX (principalmente entre os anos de 1860 a 1890) durante a expans\\u00E3o da fronteira dos Estados Unidos para a costa do Oceano Pac\\u00EDfico."@pt ,
		"The American frontier comprises the geography, history, folklore, and cultural expression of life in the forward wave of American westward expansion that began with English colonial settlements in the early 17th century and ended with the admission of the last mainland territories as states in 1912. The folklore mostly concerns the 19th century, especially west of the Mississippi River."@en ,

	rdfs:comment	"A defesa dos direitos dos animais, assim como a dos direitos animais[carece de fontes?] ou da liberta\\u00E7\\u00E3o animal[carece de fontes?] constitui um movimento que luta contra qualquer uso de animais n\\u00E3o-humanos que os transforme em propriedades de seres humanos, ou seja, meios para fins humanos.\\u00C9 um movimento social radical que n\\u00E3o se contenta em regular o uso \\"humanit\\u00E1rio\\" de animais, mas que procura inclu\\u00ED-los na comunidade moral de modo a garantir que seus interesses b\\u00E1sicos sejam respeitados e tenham igual considera\\u00E7\\u00E3o em rela\\u00E7\\u00E3o aos interesses humanos. "@pt ,
		"\\u52D5\\u7269\\u306E\\u6A29\\u5229\\uFF08\\u3069\\u3046\\u3076\\u3064\\u306E\\u3051\\u3093\\u308A\\u3001\\u30A2\\u30CB\\u30DE\\u30EB\\u30FB\\u30E9\\u30A4\\u30C4\\u3001Animal rights\\uFF09\\u3068\\u306F\\u3001\\u52D5\\u7269\\u306B\\u306F\\u4EBA\\u9593\\u304B\\u3089\\u643E\\u53D6\\u3055\\u308C\\u305F\\u308A\\u6B8B\\u8650\\u306A\\u6271\\u3044\\u3092\\u53D7\\u3051\\u308B\\u3053\\u3068\\u306A\\u304F\\u3001\\u305D\\u308C\\u305E\\u308C\\u306E\\u52D5\\u7269\\u306E\\u672C\\u6027\\u306B\\u5F93\\u3063\\u3066\\u751F\\u304D\\u308B\\u6A29\\u5229\\u304C\\u3042\\u308B\\u3068\\u3059\\u308B\\u8003\\u3048\\u65B9\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Animal rights is the idea that some, or all, non-human animals are entitled to the possession of their own lives and that their most basic interests\\u2014such as the need to avoid suffering\\u2014should be afforded the same consideration as similar interests of human beings. Advocates oppose the assignment of moral value and fundamental protections on the basis of species membership alone\\u2014an idea known since 1970 as speciesism, when the term was coined by Richard D."@en ,
		"Tierrechte sind subjektive Rechte von Tieren. Die Tierethik untersucht, inwiefern Tiere, ggf. einschlie\\u00DFlich des Menschen, aus moralischer Sicht \\u00FCber solche Rechte verf\\u00FCgen. Dar\\u00FCber hinaus werden Tierrechte als Teile einer staatlichen Rechtsordnung diskutiert. Die Art der vorgeschlagenen Rechte und die davon betroffenen Tiere variieren zwischen verschiedenen Positionen.Vertreter von unver\\u00E4u\\u00DFerlichen und vergleichsweise weitgehenden Rechten von Tieren werden als Tierrechtler bezeichnet."@de ,

	rdfs:comment	"Le Central Saint Martins College of Art and Design, surnomm\\u00E9e Central Saint Martins ou CSM, est une des composantes de l\'universit\\u00E9 des arts de Londres, n\\u00E9e en 1989 de la fusion de la Central School of Art and Design, fond\\u00E9e en 1896, et de la Saint Martins School of Art, fond\\u00E9e en 1854."@fr ,
		"Central Saint Martins College of Art and Design is een belangrijk opleidingsinstituut voor kunst en design aan de Southampton Row in Londen.Het instituut ontstond in 1989 uit een fusie tussen de Central School of Art and Design (1896) en Saint Martins School of Art (1854). Central Saint Martins werd in 1986 een onderdeel van het London Institute, dat in 2004 universitaire status en een naamwijziging kreeg: University of the Arts London."@nl ,
		"Central Saint Martins, often abbreviated to CSM, is a public tertiary art school in London, England. It is a constituent college of the University of the Arts London. It offers full-time courses at foundation, undergraduate and postgraduate levels, and a variety of short and summer courses.It was formerly known as Central Saint Martins College of Arts and Design, and before that as Central Saint Martins College of Art and Design."@en ,

		"Latim cl\\u00E1ssico (sermo urbanus, lit. \\"fala urbana\\") \\u00E9 o nome dado \\u00E0 variante do latim usada pelos antigos romanos naquela que \\u00E9 considerada a literatura latina \\"cl\\u00E1ssica\\". Seu uso perdurou por toda a chamada Era de Ouro da literatura latina (aproximadamente entre o s\\u00E9culo I a.C. e o s\\u00E9culo I d.C.), e possivelmente chegou at\\u00E9 a Era de Prata (s\\u00E9culos I e II)."@pt ,
		"Das klassische Latein war eine hochstilisierte Literatursprache, welche sich eigenst\\u00E4ndig aus dem Altlateinischen entwickelte. Klassisches Latein war die Sprache der Bildungsb\\u00FCrger des R\\u00F6mischen Reichs. Das vom Volk gesprochene Latein (sermo vulgaris oder sermo plebeius) wird Vulg\\u00E4rlatein genannt.Die fr\\u00FCheste lateinische Literatur (z. B. Cato der \\u00C4ltere, Plautus und Terenz) geh\\u00F6rt noch nicht zum klassischen Latein."@de ,
		"Classical Latin is the modern term used to describe the form of the Latin language recognized as standard by writers of the late Roman Republic and the Roman Empire. In some later periods it was regarded as \\"good\\" Latin, with later versions being viewed as debased or corrupt. The word \\"Latin\\" is now taken by default as meaning \\"Classical Latin\\", so that, for example, modern Latin textbooks describe classical Latin."@en ,

dbr:Combine_painting	rdfs:label	"Combine Painting"@de ,
		"Combine (pintura)"@pt ,
		"Combine painting"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Combine Painting bzw. Combinepainting oder auch Kombinierte Malerei ist die von Robert Rauschenberg in Anlehnung an den Dadaismus und Surrealismus entwickelte Technik, auf abstrakte Gem\\u00E4lde dreidimensionale Gebrauchsgegenst\\u00E4nde oder Fotoreproduktionen zu montieren. Hierbei wird die gestische Malerei des abstrakten Expressionismus mit Alltagszitaten des t\\u00E4glichen Lebens konfrontiert."@de ,
		"Combine \\u00E9 um termo ingl\\u00EAs (\\"combinar\\" em portugu\\u00EAs) inventado por Robert Rauschenberg (1925\\u20132008) para referir-se \\u00E0s obras de assemblage que produziu em 1950. Trata-se de um h\\u00EDbrido de pintura e escultura. Os itens enxertados nos suportes podem tamb\\u00E9m incluir imagens fotogr\\u00E1ficas, roupas, recortes de jornais e qualquer sorte de objetos tridimensionais."@pt ,
		"A combine painting is an artwork that incorporates various objects into a painted canvas surface, creating a sort of hybrid between painting and sculpture. Items attached to paintings might include photographic images, clothing, newspaper clippings, ephemera or any number of three-dimensional objects. The term is most closely associated with the artwork of American artist Robert Rauschenberg (1925\\u20132008) who coined the phrase to describe his own creations."@en .

		"Dolce stil nuovo"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"De Dolce stil novo is een Italiaanse dichtstroming die ontstond uit de ballades van de Provence, gecombineerd met traditionele dichtwerken. Het betekent zoete, nieuwe stijl in het Italiaans.De hoofdgedachte van deze stroming is dat wanneer een man liefde voor een vrouw voelt, zij hem verheft en een belangrijke bron van levensvreugde voor hem wordt, een bemiddelaar tussen mens en God. Vaak wordt er een hoofse liefde beschreven, zoals men kende uit de Arthursage."@nl ,

		"Dolce stil novo (w\\u0142. s\\u0142odki nowy styl) - nazwa grupy poet\\u00F3w w\\u0142oskich dzia\\u0142aj\\u0105cych na prze\\u0142omie XIII i XIV wieku we Florencji (Dante Alighieri, Cino da Pistoia, Lapo Gianni, Guido Cavalcanti, Guido Guinizelli) b\\u0105d\\u017A stylu tych poet\\u00F3w. Pisali oni liryczne utwory opiewaj\\u0105ce mi\\u0142o\\u015B\\u0107 idealn\\u0105, charakteryzuj\\u0105ce si\\u0119 wytwornym j\\u0119zykiem. Nawi\\u0105zywali do liryki prowansalskiej, preferowanymi gatunkami dolce stil novo by\\u0142y sonet, canzona i ballada. Terminu u\\u017Cy\\u0142 po raz pierwszy Dante w Vita nuova."@pl ,
		"Dolce Stil Novo (Italian pronunciation: [\\u02C8dolt\\u0283e stil \\u02C8n\\u0254vo]; Italian for \\"sweet new style\\", modern Italian stile nuovo), or stilnovismo [stilno\\u02C8vizmo], is the name given to the most important literary movement of the 13th century in Italy. Influenced by the Sicilian School and Tuscan poetry, its main theme is Love (Amore). Gentilezza (Noblemindedness) and Amore are indeed topoi in the major works of the period."@en ,
		"Le Dolce Stil Novo (\\u00AB Nouveau style doux \\u00BB en fran\\u00E7ais) est un courant litt\\u00E9raire italien majeur qui a pris naissance au XIIIe si\\u00E8cle et s\'est poursuivi jusqu\'au XVe si\\u00E8cle. C\'est le c\\u00E9l\\u00E8bre po\\u00E8te et \\u00E9crivain italien Dante Alighieri qui est le premier \\u00E0 nommer ce courant dans le 24e chants de son Purgatoire. Ce courant na\\u00EEt et se d\\u00E9veloppe \\u00E0 Bologne et \\u00E0 Florence qui sont alors deux cit\\u00E9s en pleine \\u00E9mulation culturelle et politique."@fr ,
		"Der dolce stil nuovo (auch: dolce stil novo, dt.: \\u201Es\\u00FC\\u00DFer neuer Stil\\u201C; Stilnovismus) ist eine literarische Bewegung im Italien des 13. und 14. Jahrhundert. Kennzeichnend f\\u00FCr diese Stilrichtung, die im norditalienischen Raum (vor allem in Florenz) unter Einfluss der Sizilianischen Dichterschule und der Trobadordichtung entstand, war die Liebesthematik."@de ,
		"Con la expresi\\u00F3n toscana Dolce stil novo (\\u00ABDulce estilo nuevo\\u00BB), Francesco de Sanctis denomin\\u00F3 en el siglo XIX a un grupo de poetas italianos de la segunda mitad del siglo XIII, integrado por Guido Guinizelli, Guido Cavalcanti, Dante Alighieri, Lapo Gianni, Cino da Pistoia, Guianni Alfani y Dino Frescobaldi.El Stil Nuovo tiene la particularidad de que su insipiraci\\u00F3n religiosa no es \\u00FAnicamente m\\u00EDstica sino que es subjetivista en grado sumo."@es ,

		"Com a express\\u00E3o toscana Dolce stil novo ou Dolce stil nuovo (\\"Doce estilo novo\\u201D), Francesco de Sanctis denominou no s\\u00E9culo XIX um grupo de poetas italianos da segunda metade do s\\u00E9culo XIII, integrado por Guido Guinizelli, Guido Cavalcanti, Dante Alighieri, Lapo Gianni, Cino da Pistoia, Guianni Alfani e Dino Frescobaldi.A express\\u00E3o Dolce stil novo provem da Divina Com\\u00E9dia de Dante, especificamente do Purgat\\u00F3rio, canto XXIV, v 57, (\\u00ABDi qua dal dolce stil novo ch\' i\' odo\\u00BB) e \\u00E9 da\\u00ED que o poeta florentino Bonagiunta da Lucca assim denomina a obra de Dante, em contraposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o \\u00E0 l\\u00EDrica trovadoresca."@pt ,

		"Fluxus\\u2014a name taken from a Latin word meaning \\"flow, flux\\" (noun); \\"flowing, fluid\\" (adj.)\\u2014is an international network of artists, composers and designers noted for blending different artistic media and disciplines in the 1960s. They have been active in performance, Neo-Dada noise music and visual art as well as literature, urban planning, architecture, and design. Fluxus is sometimes described as intermedia.The Fluxus movement..."@en ,
		"Fluxus is een kunststroming die is ontstaan in New York in het begin van de jaren 60. De beweging die later de naam Fluxus kreeg, werd door George Maciunas eerst als \\"neo-dada uit de Verenigde Staten\\" gepresenteerd, maar dat was niet het oordeel van critici of latere kunsthistorici. Het woord fluxus komt uit het Latijn en betekent \\"het stromen\\", \\"vloeiend\\", \\"vloeibaar\\", voortdurende verandering suggererend."@nl ,
		"Fluxus (palabra latina que significa flujo) es un movimiento art\\u00EDstico de las artes visuales pero tambi\\u00E9n de la m\\u00FAsica y la literatura. Tuvo su momento m\\u00E1s activo entre la d\\u00E9cada de los sesenta y los setenta del siglo XX. Se declar\\u00F3 contra el objeto art\\u00EDstico tradicional como mercanc\\u00EDa y se proclam\\u00F3 a s\\u00ED mismo como el antiarte. Fluxus fue informalmente organizado en 1962 por George Maciunas (1931-1978). Este movimiento art\\u00EDstico tuvo expresiones en M\\u00E9xico, Estados Unidos, Europa y Jap\\u00F3n."@es ,
		"Fluxus est un mouvement d\'art contemporain n\\u00E9 dans les ann\\u00E9es 1960 qui touche aussi bien les arts visuels que la musique et la litt\\u00E9rature, par la r\\u00E9alisation de concerts, d\'events, la production de livres, de revues, la confection d\'objets."@fr ,

		"Functionalisme is een stroming in de architectuur die inhoudt dat constructie en uiterlijk bepaald (moeten) worden door de functie van het gebouw.Alle uiterlijke kenmerken moeten een afspiegeling zijn van functionele elementen. Schoonheid is hierbij dus geen doel op zich. Daarom geen versiering zonder dat deze een functie voor het gebouw heeft. De idee achter het functionalisme is dat de schoonheid van een gebouw is gelegen in zijn functie. Form Follows Function wordt het ook wel genoemd."@nl ,

		"Evoluci\\u00F3n de la arquitectura entre 1919 y 1945, en Funcionalismo.Los or\\u00EDgenes del funcionalismo arquitect\\u00F3nico se pueden remontar a la tr\\u00EDada del arquitecto romano Vitruvio, donde la utilitas (traducida tambi\\u00E9n como comodidad o utilidad) va de la mano de venustas (belleza) y de firmitas (solidez) como una de las tres metas cl\\u00E1sicas de la arquitectura y su influencia fue particularmente notable en los Pa\\u00EDses Bajos, la Uni\\u00F3n Sovi\\u00E9tica, Alemania y Checoslovaquia.En los primeros a\\u00F1os del siglo XX, el arquitecto de la Escuela de Chicago Louis Sullivan populariz\\u00F3 el lema la forma sigue siempre a la funci\\u00F3n para recoger su creencia de que el tama\\u00F1o de un edificio, la masa, la distribuci\\u00F3n del espacio y otras caracter\\u00EDsticas deben decidirse solamente por la funci\\u00F3n de este. 		"Functionalism, in architecture, is the principle that architects should design a building based on the purpose of that building. This statement is less self-evident than it first appears, and is a matter of confusion and controversy within the profession, particularly in regard to modern architecture."@en ,

		"La futurolog\\u00EDa es definida por Gaston Berger (uno de los fundadores de la disciplina), como la ciencia basada en el m\\u00E9todo cient\\u00EDfico que estudia el futuro para comprenderlo y poder influir en \\u00E9l.En ocasiones, el t\\u00E9rmino futurolog\\u00EDa hace referencia a otras disciplinas no basadas en el m\\u00E9todo cient\\u00EDfico como, por ejemplo, la astrolog\\u00EDa o la ciencia ficci\\u00F3n.La Organizaci\\u00F3n para la Cooperaci\\u00F3n y el Desarrollo Econ\\u00F3micos (OCDE) define la futurolog\\u00EDa como el conjunto de tentativas sistem\\u00E1ticas para observar e integrar a largo plazo el futuro de la ciencia, la tecnolog\\u00EDa, la econom\\u00EDa y la sociedad con el prop\\u00F3sito de identificar las tecnolog\\u00EDas emergentes que probablemente produzcan los mayores beneficios econ\\u00F3micos o sociales.Por otra parte, la futurolog\\u00EDa es una disciplina y un conjunto de metodolog\\u00EDas orientadas a la previsi\\u00F3n del futuro. "@es ,
		"La futurologia \\u00E8 il tentativo di prevedere, con un approccio scientifico, il futuro pi\\u00F9 o meno remoto dell\'umanit\\u00E0. Il termine futurologo talvolta descrive anche consulenti di management che aiutano aziende ed altre organizzazioni a comprendere una serie di andamenti e tendenze globali, ad operare la gestione del rischio e a conoscere potenziali opportunit\\u00E0 di mercato."@it ,
		"A futurologia \\u00E9 a tentativa de prever, com uma abordagem cient\\u00EDfica, o futuro mais ou menos remoto da humanidade, tendo como objetivo abordar os v\\u00E1rios cen\\u00E1rios poss\\u00EDveis do futuro. Apesar de uma elevada exatid\\u00E3o em pontos espec\\u00EDficos, o trabalho de um futur\\u00F3logo n\\u00E3o \\u00E9 indicar o que vai acontecer, mas sim o que poder\\u00E1 acontecer."@pt ,
		"Futures studies (also called futurology) is the study of postulating possible, probable, and preferable futures and the worldviews and myths that underlie them. There is a debate as to whether this discipline is an art or science. In general, it can be considered as a branch of the social sciences and parallel to the field of history. History studies the past, futures studies considers the future."@en ,
		"Die Zukunftsforschung oder Futurologie (lateinisch futurum \\u201EZukunft\\u201C und -logie) ist die \\u201Esystematische und kritische wissenschaftliche Untersuchung von Fragen m\\u00F6glicher zuk\\u00FCnftiger Entwicklungen\\u201C \\u201Eauf technischem, wirtschaftlichem und sozialem Gebiet\\u201C. Sie verwendet unter anderem Methoden, Verfahren und Techniken, wie sie von der Prognostik entwickelt wurden (und werden) und verbindet qualitative und quantitative Methoden."@de ,
		"La futurologie a pour ambition d\\u2019aborder les diff\\u00E9rents sc\\u00E9narios possibles de l\\u2019avenir. Sous l\'influence de l\'anglais (futures research), le terme tend avec difficult\\u00E9 \\u00E0 remplacer celui de \\u00AB prospective \\u00BB en France.La futurologie est cens\\u00E9e proc\\u00E9der \\u00E0 partir des donn\\u00E9es technologiques, \\u00E9conomiques ou sociales du pass\\u00E9 et du pr\\u00E9sent, et affirme se fonder sur des techniques et des mod\\u00E8les scientifiques."@fr ,

dbr:Independence_movement_in_Puerto_Rico	rdfs:label	"Independence movement in Puerto Rico"@en ,
		"Movimiento independentista de Puerto Rico"@es ;
	rdfs:comment	"El movimiento de independencia de Puerto Rico hace referencia a las diversas iniciativas, a trav\\u00E9s de la historia de la isla, para obtener la independencia, primero de Espa\\u00F1a y despu\\u00E9s de los Estados Unidos."@es ,
		"The Independence Movement in Puerto Rico refers to initiatives by inhabitants throughout the history of Puerto Rico to obtain independence for the island people. First from the Spanish Empire, and since 1898, from the United States. A wide variety of groups, movements, political parties, and organizations have worked for Puerto Rican Independence over the centuries.A spectrum of autonomous, Nationalist, and Independence sentiments and political parties exist on the island."@en .

		"Il disegno industriale (dall\'inglese industrial design) \\u00E8 l\'uso sia di arti applicate che di scienze applicate al fine di migliorare estetica, ergonomia, funzionalit\\u00E0 e/o usabilit\\u00E0 di un prodotto, e si pu\\u00F2 occupare anche del miglioramento della commerciabilit\\u00E0 o persino della produzione."@it ,

		"Industri\\u00EBle vormgeving, ook wel industrieel ontwerp, productontwikkeling, productdesign of (industrial) design genoemd, is het ontwikkelen van producten die industrieel in massa- of serieproductie worden vervaardigd."@nl ,
		"Industrial design is a process of design applied to products that are to be manufactured through techniques of mass production. Its key characteristic is that design is separated from manufacture: the creative act of determining and defining a product\'s form takes place in advance of the physical act of making a product, which consists purely of repeated, often automated, replication."@en ,
		"El dise\\u00F1o Industrial es una actividad que tiene que ver con el dise\\u00F1o de productos seriados y/o industriales, que podemos diferenciar en dos tipos : bienes de consumo y bienes de capital. Es una de las m\\u00FAltiples herramientas que busca mejorar las cualidades de los productos industriales, poniendo \\u00E9nfasis en la forma y la funci\\u00F3n, con un enfoque prioritario hacia el usuario."@es .
dbr:Installation_art	rdfs:label	"Installation art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Installation art is an artistic genre of three-dimensional works that are often site-specific and designed to transform the perception of a space. Generally, the term is applied to interior spaces, whereas exterior interventions are often called public art, land art or intervention art; however, the boundaries between these terms overlap."@en .

		"D\\u00E1-se o nome de international style ou estilo internacional \\u00E0 arquitetura funcionalista praticada na primeira metade do s\\u00E9culo XX em todo o mundo. N\\u00E3o existe grande rigidez quanto ao uso da express\\u00E3o em si: n\\u00E3o \\u00E9 incomum us\\u00E1-la ao referir-se ao movimento moderno como um todo (e vice-versa)."@pt ,
		"De Internationale Stijl is een aanduiding voor een stroming in de architectuur (en de binnenhuisarchitectuur) in de periode van circa 1930 tot circa 1970. De term is afkomstig van de titel van het boek The International Style, geschreven door Philip Johnson en Henry-Russell Hitchcock. De stijl is ontstaan uit het Nieuwe Bouwen. Die stijl legde reeds de nadruk op zaken als functionaliteit, strakke vormen, moderne constructietechnieken en afwezigheid van versieringen."@nl ,
		"Der Internationale Stil (englisch [The] International Style) ist eine Str\\u00F6mung der klassischen modernen Architektur, die oft mit dieser gleichgesetzt wird. Die Entwicklung des Internationalen Stils begann um 1922 in Europa, sp\\u00E4ter verbreitete er sich in der ganzen Welt. Als Gegenbewegung kann der kritische Regionalismus angesehen werden."@de ,
		"Le Style international est un courant architectural qui s\'est \\u00E9panoui entre les ann\\u00E9es 1920 et la fin des ann\\u00E9es 1980 dans le monde entier. Ce style, qui marque l\'arriv\\u00E9e des id\\u00E9es du Mouvement moderne aux \\u00C9tats-Unis, notamment par l\'interm\\u00E9diaire de Philip Johnson au MoMA \\u00E0 New York et de Ludwig Mies van der Rohe \\u00E0 Chicago, r\\u00E9sulte du mariage des id\\u00E9es de l\'\\u00E9cole du Bauhaus et des techniques de construction en acier et en verre des \\u00C9tats-Unis."@fr ,
		"Styl mi\\u0119dzynarodowy \\u2013 pr\\u0105d architektury modernistycznej, z kt\\u00F3rym cz\\u0119sto jest ona uto\\u017Csamiana, rozwijaj\\u0105cy si\\u0119 od oko\\u0142o 1922 w Europie, a p\\u00F3\\u017Aniej na ca\\u0142ym \\u015Bwiecie."@pl ,
		"Se conoce como Estilo Internacional a un conjunto de arquitecturas que comparten las caracter\\u00EDsticas formales m\\u00E1s puristas del Movimiento Moderno y, en menor medida, las funcionalistas. El nombre, que triunf\\u00F3 en el mundo anglosaj\\u00F3n como sin\\u00F3nimo de Movimiento Moderno y que, como en s\\u00ED mismo indica, lo consider\\u00F3 un estilo, proviene de una exposici\\u00F3n de arquitectura europea y americana que tuvo lugar en el MoMA en 1932, organizada por Henry-Russell Hitchcock y Philip Johnson."@es ,

		"The International Style is the name of a major architectural style that is said to have emerged in the 1920s and 1930s, the formative decades of modern architecture, as first defined by Americans Henry-Russell Hitchcock and Philip Johnson in 1932, with an emphasis more on architectural style, form and aesthetics than the social aspects of the modern movement as emphasised in Europe."@en .

dbr:Interstitial_art	rdfs:label	"Interstitial art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Interstitial art is a term first coined in the 1990s, and increasingly popularized in the early 2000s, that refers to any work of art whose basic nature falls between, rather than within, the familiar boundaries of accepted genres or media, thus making the work difficult to categorize or describe within a single artistic discipline."@en .

		"Die Irokesen, Eigenbezeichnung Haudenosaunee (\\u201ELeute des Langhauses)\\u201C, sind nordamerikanische Indianer, die einer gemeinsamen Sprachfamilie angeh\\u00F6ren. Die irokesischen Sprachgruppen bewohnten ein zusammenh\\u00E4ngendes Gebiet rund um den Ontario-, Huron- und Eriesee in den heutigen Staaten New York und Pennsylvania sowie in Teilen von Alabama und Georgia (USA) und im s\\u00FCdlichen Ontario und Qu\\u00E9bec (Kanada)."@de ,
		"The Iroquois  (/\\u02C8\\u026Ar\\u0259kw\\u0254\\u026A/ or /\\u02C8\\u026Ar\\u0259kw\\u0251\\u02D0/), also known as the Haudenosaunee /\\u02C8ho\\u028Ad\\u0259n\\u0275\\u02C8\\u0283o\\u028Ani/, are a historically powerful and important northeast Native American confederacy."@en ,

		"Les Iroquois (ou Haudenosaunee) connus aussi par l\'expression Cinq-Nations comprennent effectivement cinq et puis plus tard six nations am\\u00E9rindiennes de langues iroquoises vivant historiquement dans le nord de l\'\\u00C9tat de New York aux \\u00C9tats-Unis au sud du lac Ontario et du fleuve Saint-Laurent. 		"Gli Irochesi sono una popolazione di nativi americani originariamente stanziata tra gli attuali Stati Uniti e il Canada che si riferiscono a loro stessi con il nome di Haudenosaunee ovvero Popolo della Lunga Casa.Storicamente diedero vita a una confederazione di nazioni (trib\\u00F9) nota come Lega irochese, Confederazione irochese o Sei Nazioni (originariamente Cinque Nazioni).Le trib\\u00F9 che nel 1570 diedero origine alle Cinque Nazioni furono i Cayuga, i Mohawk, gli Oneida, gli Onondaga e i Seneca."@it ,
		"Os iroqueses (em ingl\\u00EAs e franc\\u00EAs: Iroquois, pronunciado irocu\\u00E1) ou Haudenosaunee foram um grupo nativo norte-americano que vivia em torno da regi\\u00E3o dos Grandes Lagos, primariamente no sul de Ont\\u00E1rio, uma prov\\u00EDncia do Canad\\u00E1, e no nordeste dos Estados Unidos."@pt ,
		"Los iroqueses o haudenosaunee (en lenguas iroquesas: Gente de la casa larga )? son nativos de Am\\u00E9rica del Norte. El pueblo iroqu\\u00E9s surgi\\u00F3 alrededor de la regi\\u00F3n de los Grandes Lagos, inicialmente en el sur de Ontario, una provincia de Canad\\u00E1, y en el noreste de los Estados Unidos de Am\\u00E9rica. Los iroqueses eran inicialmente n\\u00F3madas. Hasta el siglo XVII formaron lo que actualmente se llama Confederaci\\u00F3n Iroquesa."@es ,
		"De Irokezen, Iroquois of Haudenosaunee vormen een confederatie van vijf en later zes taalkundig en etnisch aan elkaar verwante volken in Noord-Amerika. In dit verband spreken we dan ook van \\"The Six Nations\\" (de zes naties). De Iroquois noemen zichzelf gezamenlijk Haudenosaunee, letterlijk vertaald, \\"volk van het langhuis\\". De oorspronkelijke vijf naties zijn van oost naar west: Mohawk (Kanien\\u2019kehaka), Oneida (Onyota\\u2019a:ka), Onondaga (Onoda\\u2019gega), Cayuga (Gayugaho:no) en Seneca (Ondowahgah)."@nl .

	rdfs:comment	"El arte cin\\u00E9tico es una corriente de arte en que las obras tienen movimiento o parecen tenerlo. Es una tendencia de las pinturas y las esculturas contempor\\u00E1neas creadas para producir una impresi\\u00F3n de movimiento. El arte cin\\u00E9tico y el arte \\u00F3ptico son corrientes art\\u00EDsticas basadas en la est\\u00E9tica del movimiento. Est\\u00E1 principalmente representado en el campo de la escultura donde uno de los recursos son los componentes m\\u00F3viles de las obras."@es ,
		"Kinetische Kunst ist eine k\\u00FCnstlerische Ausdrucksform, in der die Bewegung als integraler \\u00E4sthetischer Bestandteil des Kunstobjekts Beachtung findet. Auch dann, wenn sich das Objekt scheinbar ver\\u00E4ndert, weil sich der Betrachter bewegt (Carlos Cruz-Diez) oder auch eine Illusion eine Bewegung vort\\u00E4uscht (Youri Messen-Jaschin). Daher gilt die Op-Art manchen Betrachtern als kinetische Kunst.Die kinetische Kunst wurde in den 1950er und 1960er-Jahren popul\\u00E4r."@de ,
		"A arte cin\\u00E9tica, \\u00E9 uma corrente das artes pl\\u00E1sticas que explora efeitos visuais por meio de movimentos f\\u00EDsicos ou ilus\\u00E3o de \\u00F3ptica ou truques de posicionamento de pe\\u00E7as.Artistas como Marcel Duchamp (1887-1968), Alexander Calder (1898-1976), Vasarely (1908), Jesus Raphael Soto (1923), Yaacov Agam (1928), Jean Tinguely (1925), Pol Bury (1922) e o brasileiro Abraham Palatnik (1928), s\\u00E3o apontados como expoentes desta linguagem."@pt ,

		"Kinetic art is art from any medium that contains movement perceivable by the viewer or depends on motion for its effect. Canvas paintings that extend the viewer\'s perspective of the artwork and incorporate multidimensional movement are the earliest examples of kinetic art. More pertinently speaking, kinetic art is a term that today most often refers to three-dimensional sculptures and figures such as mobiles that move naturally or are machine operated."@en ,
		"L\'arte cinetica \\u00E8 una corrente artistica nata negli anni venti e successivamente sviluppatasi negli anni cinquanta e anni sessanta che si propone di introdurre il movimento nell\'opera artistica.Nell\'arte cinetica il movimento pu\\u00F2 essere fisico, come nelle sculture cinetiche di Jean Tinguely, nei mobile di Alexander Calder o nelle prospettive mobili di Gianni Colombo oppure virtuale, come nei dipinti Op art di Bridget Riley, di Yaacov Agam, nelle illusioni ottiche di Alberto Biasi o nelle \\"superfici a testura vibratile\\" di Getulio Alviani.Anche se alcuni critici hanno cercato di suddividere l\'arte cinetica in diverse categorie, chiamate \\"arte programmata\\", \\"optical art\\" o simili, il comune denominatore \\u00E8 sempre un rapporto attivo fra l\'opera d\'arte e lo spettatore, con l\'immagine che si modifica in s\\u00E9 o in seguito allo spostarsi nello spazio di chi guarda.L\'origine di questo movimento deriva dall\'esaurirsi delle esperienze astratte informali ed ha come necessaria premessa l\'azzeramento operato dagli artisti di Azimuth: Enrico Castellani, Agostino Bonalumi e Piero Manzoni.La vera diffusione ed il massimo successo di questo tipo di arte si \\u00E8 avuta negli anni \'60 anche se alcune intuizioni gi\\u00E0 strutturate, quali quelle di Bruno Munari che nel 1952 scrive il \\"Manifesto del macchinismo\\" erano precedenti.I pi\\u00F9 grandi successi si ebbero nelle mostre organizzate a Zagabria chiamate \\"Nove Tendencije\\", nella mostra \\"arte programmata\\" presso l\'Olivetti a Milano nel 1962, sino ad arrivare all\'apice della popolarit\\u00E0 mondiale con la mostra \\"The Responsive Eye\\" al MoMa di New York nel 1965. "@it ,

dbr:Maximalism	rdfs:label	"Massimalismo (arte)"@it ,
		"Maximalismo"@es ,
		"Maximalism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The movement of maximalism in reference to the arts was founded by the artist and filmmaker Daryush Shokof in 1990 in Cologne, Germany. Maximalism vis-a-vis the arts is a new way of creating art. Many common elements are shared in the art works by artists who participate in the maximalist movement. The movement was initiated by Daryush Shokof as he wrote in his one-man show catalog of paintings at Galleria Verlato in Milano, Italy in 1990; \\"Unbalancing the chaos = Balance = Life = Maximalism\\"."@es ,
		"In the arts, maximalism, a reaction against minimalism, is an esthetic of excess and redundancy. The philosophy can be summarized as \\u201Cmore is more\\u201D contrasted with minimalist motto \\"less is more\\"."@en ,
		"Massimalismo \\u00E8 un termine usato nelle arti, tra cui la letteratura, l\'arte visiva, la musica e varie altre per spiegare un movimento o tendenza di che comprende tutti i fattori multiuso dell\'espressionismo, e nasce come un movimento artistico opposto al minimalismo; il massimalismo infatti celebra la ricchezza e l\'eccesso, ed ogni opera pu\\u00F2 contenere riferimenti ironici, erotici, culturali o di critica sociale, come si evince dai dipinti massimalisti."@it .
dbr:Miniature_art	rdfs:label	"Miniature art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Miniature art or model art is a genre that focuses on art (especially painting, engraving and sculpture) in much-smaller-than-usual sizes. Miniature art societies, such as the World Federation of Miniaturists (WFM), provide applicable definitions of the term. An often-used definition is that a piece of miniature art is capable of being held in the palm of the hand, or that it covers less than 100 cm\\u00B2."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"La arquitectura neocl\\u00E1sica es un estilo arquitect\\u00F3nico que produjo el movimiento neocl\\u00E1sico que comenz\\u00F3 a mediados del siglo XVIII, por una reacci\\u00F3n contra el estilo barroco de ornamentaci\\u00F3n naturalista as\\u00ED como por el resultado de algunos rasgos clasicistas nacidos en el barroco tard\\u00EDo. Se prolong\\u00F3 durante el siglo XIX, confluyendo a partir de entonces con otras tendencias, como la arquitectura historicista y el eclecticismo arquitect\\u00F3nico."@es ,
		"Met neoclassicistische architectuur wordt bedoeld de architectuurstijl die, in lijn met de bredere kunststroming van het neoclassicisme, een terugkeer naar de idealen van de oude Griekse en Romeinse bouwkunst voorstond. Het neoclassicisme in de bouwkunst ontstond enerzijds als een reactie op de zwierige vormen van de barok- en rococo-architectuur, anderzijds als een voortzetting van de classiciserende tendensen in de bouwkunst van de tweede helft van de 18e eeuw (Lodewijk XVI-stijl)."@nl ,
		"Neoclassical architecture is an architectural style produced by the neoclassical movement that began in the mid-18th century. In its purest form it is a style principally derived from the architecture of Classical antiquity, the Vitruvian principles and the architecture of the Italian architect Andrea Palladio.In form, Neoclassical architecture emphasizes the wall rather than chiaroscuro and maintains separate identities to each of its parts."@en ,
		"Por arquitetura neocl\\u00E1ssica (AO 1945: arquitectura neocl\\u00E1ssica) entende-se o estilo arquitet\\u00F3nico que, em linha com a tend\\u00EAncia art\\u00EDstica universal do neoclassicismo, resulta da recupera\\u00E7\\u00E3o da gram\\u00E1tica formal da antiguidade cl\\u00E1ssica grega e romana."@pt ,

		"L\\u2019architecture n\\u00E9o-classique est un courant architectural proc\\u00E9dant du n\\u00E9o-classicisme de la seconde moiti\\u00E9 du XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle et du d\\u00E9but du XIXe si\\u00E8cle. 	rdfs:comment	"Neoclassicismo \\u00E8 il nome dato ad una tendenza culturale sviluppatasi in Europa tra il XVIII ed il XIX secolo."@it ,
		"Het neoclassicisme was aan het eind van de 18e en het begin van de 19e eeuw een stroming in de kunst, waarin opnieuw de vermeende puurheid van de klassieken werd nagestreefd. Men richtte zich daarbij met name op de (bouw)kunst van de oude Grieken en Romeinen. Beroemde neoclassicistische kunstenaars zijn de Franse schilders Jacques Louis David en Jean Auguste Dominique Ingres, en de in Rome werkzame beeldhouwers Antonio Canova en Bertel Thorvaldsen."@nl ,
		"El t\\u00E9rmino Neoclasicismo (del griego -\\u03BD\\u03AD\\u03BF\\u03C2 neos, el lat\\u00EDn classicus y el sufijo griego -\\u03B9\\u03C3\\u03BC\\u03CC\\u03C2 -ismos) surgi\\u00F3 en el siglo XVIII para denominar de forma peyorativa al movimiento est\\u00E9tico que ven\\u00EDa a reflejar en las artes los principios intelectuales de la Ilustraci\\u00F3n, que desde mediados del siglo XVIII se ven\\u00EDan produciendo en la filosof\\u00EDa, y que consecuentemente se hab\\u00EDan transmitido a todos los \\u00E1mbitos de la cultura."@es ,

		"O neoclassicismo  foi um movimento cultural nascido na Europa em meados do s\\u00E9culo XVIII, que teve larga influ\\u00EAncia na arte e cultura de todo o ocidente at\\u00E9 meados do s\\u00E9culo XIX. Teve como base os ideais do iluminismo e um renovado interesse pela cultura da Antiguidade cl\\u00E1ssica, advogando os princ\\u00EDpios da modera\\u00E7\\u00E3o, equil\\u00EDbrio e idealismo como uma rea\\u00E7\\u00E3o contra os excessos decorativistas e dram\\u00E1ticos do Barroco."@pt ,
		"Neoclassicism (from Greek \\u03BD\\u03AD\\u03BF\\u03C2 n\\u00E8os and \\u03BA\\u03BB\\u03B1\\u03C3\\u03C3\\u03B9\\u03BA\\u03CC\\u03C2 klassik\\u00F2s classicus) is the name given to Western movements in the decorative and visual arts, literature, theatre, music, and architecture that draw inspiration from the \\"classical\\" art and culture of Ancient Greece or Ancient Rome."@en ,

		"Klassizismus bezeichnet als kunstgeschichtliche Epoche den Zeitraum etwa zwischen 1770 und 1840. Der Klassizismus l\\u00F6ste den Barock bzw. das Rokoko ab. Eine Form des Klassizismus ist das Biedermeier. Die Epoche wurde in der Malerei und Literatur von der Romantik begleitet und in der Architektur vom Historismus abgel\\u00F6st.Im Verh\\u00E4ltnis zum Barock kann der Klassizismus als k\\u00FCnstlerisches Gegenprogramm aufgefasst werden. Gegen Ende des 18."@de .

		"Pan-Africanism is an ideology and movement that encourages the solidarity of Africans worldwide. It is based on the belief that unity is vital to economic, social, and political progress and aims to \\"unify and uplift\\" people of African descent. The ideology asserts that the fate of all African peoples and countries are intertwined."@en ,
		"Panafrikanisme is een filosofie die terrein won tijdens de Afrikaanse onafhankelijkheidsstrijd."@nl ,
		"La parola panafricanismo fu inventata nel 1900 dall\'avvocato di Trinidad Henry Sylvester Williams che convoc\\u00F2 a Londra una conferenza per \\"protestare contro il furto di terre nelle colonie, la discriminazione razziale e discutere in generale dei problemi dei neri\\".In generale la parola ha due significati collegati fra loro: Un movimento che promuove l\'unit\\u00E0 politica e il sentimento di identit\\u00E0 comune tra i paesi africani (in particolare quelli dell\'Africa nera) e si sforza di costruire istituzioni che rendano effettiva questa unit\\u00E0. "@it ,
		"Panafrikanismus (griechische Vorsilbe \\u03C0\\u1FB6\\u03BD pan \\u201Aalles\\u2018) bedeutet \\u201Edie Einheit aller schwarzen/afrikanischen Menschen weltweit, unabh\\u00E4ngig von ihrer Ethnie oder Nationalit\\u00E4t\\u201C, d. h. der Menschen, deren Vorfahren durch die atlantische und die arabische Versklavung mit Gewalt aus Afrika weggebracht wurden und nun in den USA, in der Karibik und Lateinamerika und auch in Teilen des Mittleren Ostens und S\\u00FCdasiens leben.Die bedeutsamsten Zentren des Panafrikanismus waren London, New York und Paris."@de ,

		"El panafricanismo o pan-africanismo es un movimiento pol\\u00EDtico, filos\\u00F3fico, cultural y social, que promueve el hermanamiento africano, la defensa de los derechos de las personas africanas y la unidad de \\u00C1frica bajo un \\u00FAnico Estado soberano, para todos los africanos, tanto de \\u00C1frica como de las di\\u00E1sporas africanas."@es ,
		"Le panafricanisme est une id\\u00E9e politique et un mouvement qui promeut et encourage la pratique de la solidarit\\u00E9 entre les africains o\\u00F9 qu\'ils soient dans le monde.  Le panafricanisme est \\u00E0 la fois une vision sociale, culturelle et politique d\'\\u00E9mancipation des africains et un mouvement qui vise \\u00E0 unifier les africains du continent et de la diaspora africaine  en une communaut\\u00E9 africaine globale."@fr ,

	rdfs:comment	"Le saint-simonisme est une doctrine socio-\\u00E9conomique et politique dont l\'influence fut d\\u00E9terminante au XIXe si\\u00E8cle. Elle tient son nom de Claude Henri de Rouvroy, comte de Saint-Simon (1760-1825). Son disciple ou partisan est qualifi\\u00E9 de \\u00AB Saint-Simonien \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"Saint-Simonianism was a French political and social movement of the first half of the 19th century, inspired by the ideas of Claude Henri de Rouvroy, comte de Saint-Simon (1760\\u20131825).Saint-Simon\'s ideas, expressed largely through a succession of journals such as l\'Industrie (1816), La politique (1818) and L\'Organisateur (1819\\u201320)  centered on a perception that growth in industrialization and scientific discovery would have profound changes on society."@en ,
		"Il sansimonismo \\u00E8 stato un movimento socialista francese della prima met\\u00E0 del XIX secolo. Il movimento prende il nome dal suo ideatore  il conte Henri de Saint-Simon, il centro di questo movimento fu l\'\\u00C9cole polytechnique."@it ,
		"El sansimonismo fue el movimiento ideol\\u00F3gico con fines pol\\u00EDticos fundado por los seguidores del socialista ut\\u00F3pico Henri de Saint-Simon despu\\u00E9s de la muerte de \\u00E9ste en 1825. En Francia constituy\\u00F3 la primera experiencia pr\\u00E1ctica de socialismo, aunque se discute si sus propuestas fueron realmente socialistas."@es ,
		"Het saint-simonisme dankt zijn naam aan de grondlegger ervan, graaf de Saint-Simon. Claude Henri de Saint-Simon (1760-1825), graaf de Rouvroy, was een vroege socialist, voorloper van Karl Marx. Zijn leer, die tot het \'utopisch socialisme\' wordt gerekend, werd het saint-simonisme genoemd."@nl ,

	rdfs:comment	"Der Salon de Paris (franz\\u00F6sisch f\\u00FCr Pariser Salon) war eine regelm\\u00E4\\u00DFige Kunstausstellung, die von K\\u00F6nig Ludwig dem XIV. im Jahre 1667 initiiert wurde, um den offiziellen h\\u00F6fischen Kunstgeschmack zu propagieren. Im 19. Jahrhundert war der Salon Mittelpunkt und B\\u00FChne des franz\\u00F6sischen Kunstbetriebes. So wurden w\\u00E4hrend des Pariser Salons des Jahres 1855 beispielsweise 891.682 Besucher gez\\u00E4hlt und 1880 stellten 5184 K\\u00FCnstler 7289 Exponate aus."@de ,
		"Il Salon fu un\'esposizione periodica di pittura e scultura, che si svolse al Louvre di Parigi, con cadenza biennale fino al 1863 ed annuale in seguito (decreto imperiale del 13 novembre 1863), dal XVII al XIX secolo.Il Salon nasce nel 1667 con la prima esposizione organizzata dall\\u2019Accademia reale, riservata solamente ai membri dell\'Accademia stessa."@it ,
		"O Sal\\u00E3o de Paris (em franc\\u00EAs, Salon de Paris) foi fundado em 1667 na capital francesa para exibir obras de arte, especialmente pinturas, dos membros da Academia Real de Pintura e EsculturaA exposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o foi chamada de Sal\\u00E3o pelo fato de ter sido organizada no Salon d\'Apollon, do Museu do Louvre. Ocorreu anualmente at\\u00E9 1736 e bienalmente at\\u00E9 a Revolu\\u00E7\\u00E3o Francesa, quando voltou a ser organizada anualmente."@pt ,

		"The Salon (French: Salon), or rarely Paris Salon (French: Salon de Paris), beginning in 1667 was the official art exhibition of the Acad\\u00E9mie des Beaux-Arts in Paris. Between 1748 and 1890 it was the greatest annual or biennial art event in the Western world. At the 1761 Salon, thirty-three painters, nine sculptors, and eleven engravers contributed. From 1881 onward, it has been managed by the Soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 des Artistes Fran\\u00E7ais."@en ,
		"El Sal\\u00F3n de Par\\u00EDs fue la exposici\\u00F3n de arte oficial de la Academia de Bellas Artes de Par\\u00EDs (Francia), que se celebr\\u00F3 a partir de 1725. Entre 1748 y 1890 fue el acontecimiento art\\u00EDstico anual o bienal m\\u00E1s importante del mundo. Desde 1881 lo organiz\\u00F3 la Soci\\u00E9t\\u00E9 des Artistes Fran\\u00E7ais."@es ,
		"Salon \\u2013 czasowa wystawa, prezentowana publicznie, przedstawiaj\\u0105ca dorobek wsp\\u00F3\\u0142czesnych artyst\\u00F3w. 		"Le Salon de peinture et de sculpture est une manifestation artistique se d\\u00E9roulant \\u00E0 Paris depuis le XVIIIe si\\u00E8cle, qui exposait les \\u0153uvres des artistes agr\\u00E9\\u00E9es par l\'Acad\\u00E9mie des beaux-arts.D\'abord nomm\\u00E9e \\u00AB Salon de l\'Acad\\u00E9mie royale des beaux-arts \\u00BB, \\u00E0 la R\\u00E9volution elle prend le nom de \\u00AB Salon de peinture et de sculpture \\u00BB et se d\\u00E9mocratise en s\'ouvrant aux artistes de toutes origines sous l\'impulsion des peintres Jacques-Louis David et Jean-Bernard Restout.Elle redevient le \\u00AB Salon de l\'acad\\u00E9mie royale \\u00BB sous la Restauration, et reprend son nom de \\u00AB Salon de peinture et de sculpture \\u00BB sous la Deuxi\\u00E8me R\\u00E9publique, jusqu\'en 1881 o\\u00F9 elle prend le nom de \\u00AB Salon des artistes fran\\u00E7ais \\u00BB, destin\\u00E9 \\u00E0 pr\\u00E9senter l\'art officiel. "@fr .
dbr:Small_press	rdfs:label	"Small press"@nl ,
		"Independent-Verlag"@de ,
		"Small press"@en ,
		"Small press"@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"Small press is een alternatieve DIY-stroming in de stripwereld die ontstond in de jaren negentig met het wegvallen van de grote stripbladen. De small-pressproducten zijn meestal kleine boekjes die aspirant-striptekenaars, veelal op eigen kosten en in zeer kleine oplages, drukken (lees: eigenhandig kopi\\u00EBren) en op de markt brengen."@nl ,
		"La d\\u00E9nomination am\\u00E9ricaine small press (pluriel small presses) (\\u00AB petit \\u00E9diteur \\u00BB, litt. petite presse) est souvent utilis\\u00E9e pour d\\u00E9crire les \\u00E9diteurs qui ont des ventes annuelles inf\\u00E9rieures \\u00E0 un certain niveau."@fr ,
		"Independent-Verlag (auch \\u201EKleinverlag\\u201C oder \\u201EMinipresse\\u201C) bezeichnet einen kleinen, meist jungen Verlag, der unabh\\u00E4ngig von Konzernen ist. Der Begriff wurde urspr\\u00FCnglich f\\u00FCr kleine Musiklabels verwendet und bezieht sich auf die \\u00F6konomische Ebene und auf eine \\u00C4sthetik, die das Streben der gro\\u00DFen Verlage nach Massenerfolgen und Umsatzmaximierung ablehnt \\u2013 es ist kein Imprint-Verlag.Insbesondere die Kurt-Wolff-Stiftung f\\u00F6rdert die Kultur unabh\\u00E4ngiger Verlage."@de ,
		"A small press is a publisher with annual sales below a certain level. Commonly, in the United States, this is set at $50 million, after returns and discounts."@en .

		"Southern Tang (Chinese: \\u5357\\u5510; pinyin: N\\u00E1n T\\u00E1ng; also referred to as Nantang), later known as Jiangnan (\\u6C5F\\u5357), was one of the Ten Kingdoms in south-central China created following the Tang Dynasty from 937\\u2013976. Southern Tang replaced the Wu Kingdom when Li Bian (a.k.a. Xu Zhigao) deposed the emperor Yang Pu.The capital was located in Jinling (also known as Xidu), located in present-day Nanjing in Jiangsu Province."@en ,
		"\\u5357\\u5510\\u5927\\u5510\\u5510\\u306E\\u4F4D\\u7F6E\\u5357\\u5510\\u3068\\u4E94\\u4EE3\\u5341\\u56FD\\u5357\\u5510\\uFF08\\u306A\\u3093\\u3068\\u3046\\u3001937\\u5E74 - 975\\u5E74\\uFF09\\u306F\\u3001\\u4E94\\u4EE3\\u5341\\u56FD\\u6642\\u4EE3\\u306B\\u6C5F\\u5357\\u306B\\u5272\\u62E0\\u3057\\u305F\\u56FD\\u3067\\u3042\\u308A\\u3001\\u5341\\u56FD\\u306E\\u4E00\\u3064\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u9996\\u90FD\\u306F\\u91D1\\u9675\\uFF08\\u73FE\\u5728\\u306E\\u5357\\u4EAC\\uFF09\\u3002\\u56FD\\u53F7\\u306F\\u5358\\u306B\\u5510\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u304C\\u3001\\u5510\\u3068\\u540D\\u4E57\\u3063\\u305F\\u4ED6\\u306E\\u653F\\u6A29\\u3068\\u533A\\u5225\\u3059\\u308B\\u305F\\u3081\\u306B\\u3001\\u7279\\u306B\\u3053\\u306E\\u56FD\\u306E\\u540D\\u3092\\u5357\\u5510\\u3068\\u3044\\u3046\\u3002\\u5341\\u56FD\\u306E\\u4E2D\\u3067\\u306F\\u6700\\u5927\\u306E\\u52E2\\u529B\\u3092\\u8A87\\u3063\\u305F\\u304C\\u3001\\u83EF\\u5317\\u306E\\u5F8C\\u5468\\u3084\\u5317\\u5B8B\\u306B\\u653B\\u3081\\u7ACB\\u3066\\u3089\\u308C\\u3066\\u6EC5\\u4EA1\\u3057\\u305F\\u3002\\u6587\\u5316\\u7684\\u30FB\\u7D4C\\u6E08\\u7684\\u306B\\u306F\\u5927\\u3044\\u306B\\u7E41\\u6804\\u3057\\u3066\\u3044\\u305F\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Tang du Sud (en chinois: \\u5357\\u5510, aussi appel\\u00E9 Nantang), plus tard connu sous le nom de Jiangnan (\\u6C5F\\u5357), \\u00E9tait l\'un des Dix Royaumes du centre-sud de la Chine  cr\\u00E9\\u00E9 \\u00E0 la chute de la dynastie Tang entre 937 et 975. Ce royaume a remplac\\u00E9 le royaume Wu quand Li Bian (alias Xu Zhigao) d\\u00E9posa l\'empereur Yang Pu.La capitale du royaume est situ\\u00E9e \\u00E0  Jinling (\\u00E9galement connu sous le nom de  Xidu), situ\\u00E9e dans l\'actuelle Nanjing, province du Jiangsu."@fr .
dbr:Teatro_Campesino	rdfs:label	"Teatro Campesino"@es ,
		"Teatro Campesino"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"El Teatro Campesino (\\"farmworkers\' theater\\"), is a theatrical troupe founded in 1965 as the cultural arm of the United Farm Workers with the \\"full support of Cesar Chavez.\\" The original actors were all farmworkers, and El Teatro Campesino enacted events inspired by the lives of their audience. Early performances were on flat bed trucks in the middle of the fields in Delano, California, and the theater is now located in San Juan Bautista, California."@en ,
		"Teatro campesino se llama tanto al modelo teatral como al grupo de teatro callejero que, nacido en 1965 como guerrilla pac\\u00EDfica en la huelga de agricultores mexicanos en California, evolucion\\u00F3 a partir de 1970 hacia planteamientos profesionales y contenidos religiosos, nacionalistas y pol\\u00EDtico-humanitarios. Su l\\u00EDder, desde su creaci\\u00F3n, fue Luis V\\u00E1ldez."@es .

		"L\'area delle arti visive (o arti visuali) \\u00E8 estremamente ampia. In effetti \\u00E8 definibile cos\\u00EC qualunque forma artistica che abbia come risultato un oggetto visibile. Altre arti quali il teatro, la musica o l\'opera, costituiscono invece categorie a s\\u00E9 stanti di tipo figurativo, pur con confini non sempre ben definiti; vedi ad esempio la body art o l\'arte interattiva, o anche il cinema, che pu\\u00F2 incorporare differenti forme artistiche."@it ,

		"Sztuki wizualne \\u2013 nazwa obejmuj\\u0105ca r\\u00F3\\u017Cne dziedziny tw\\u00F3rczo\\u015Bci artystycznej, kt\\u00F3re odbierane s\\u0105 przez widza poprzez wzrok (st\\u0105d ich nazwa \\u2013 wizualny oznacza wzrokowy, dostrzegalny, z \\u0142ac. videre \\u2013 widzie\\u0107). Kategoria stosowana jest zatem wobec tradycyjnych dziedzin (takich jak malarstwo czy rze\\u017Aba), ale tak\\u017Ce wobec nowych zjawisk (np. performance, instalacja), kt\\u00F3rych nie obejmowa\\u0142y tradycyjne terminy sztuki pi\\u0119kne czy sztuki plastyczne."@pl ,
		"The visual arts are art forms such as ceramics, drawing, painting, sculpture, printmaking, design, crafts, photography, video, filmmaking and architecture. Many artistic disciplines (performing arts, conceptual art, textile arts) involve aspects of the visual arts as well as arts of other types."@en ,

		"Beeldende kunst is de vorm van kunst waarbij het beeldende (de afbeelding) voorop staat. Een afbeelding in de zin van een uitbeelding, die een platte of een ruimtelijke vorm kan aannemen met een zichtbaar resultaat. In Engelssprekende landen spreekt men over visual arts. Deze kunstvorm werd ook wel eens plastische kunst genoemd, maar dat is een gallicisme ontstaan uit de Franse term arts plastiques. Dat geeft aan dat de gemaakte werken plastisch, dat wil zeggen tastbaar zijn."@nl .

		"Yugoslavism  refers to nationalism or patriotism centred upon the Yugoslavs - an identity referring to a united singular South Slav people and the South Slav populated territories of southeastern Europe. Yugoslavism has historically advocated the union of all South Slav populated territories now composing Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Montenegro, Serbia (and the disputed region of Kosovo), Slovenia, and Macedonia."@en ,
		"Jugoslawizm (ruch jugos\\u0142owia\\u0144ski) \\u2013 ruch kulturalno-polityczny istniej\\u0105cy od XIX w., maj\\u0105cy na celu zjednoczenie S\\u0142owian po\\u0142udniowych."@pl ,
		"El yugoslavismo (en serbocroata: jugoslavenstvo, en serbio: \\u0458\\u0443\\u0433\\u043E\\u0441\\u043B\\u043E\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u043E) es un concepto que se refiere al nacionalismo o patriotismo centrado en los yugoslavos, identidad en referencia a un \\u00FAnico y singular pueblo de eslavos del sur y los territorios eslavos del sur poblados del sureste de Europa."@es .

		"\\u4E0D\\u6761\\u7406\\uFF08\\u3075\\u3058\\u3087\\u3046\\u308A\\uFF09\\u306F\\u3001\\u4E0D\\u5408\\u7406\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3053\\u3068\\u3001\\u3042\\u308B\\u3044\\u306F\\u5E38\\u8B58\\u306B\\u53CD\\u3057\\u3066\\u3044\\u308B\\u3053\\u3068\\u3092\\u6307\\u3059\\u3002\\u82F1\\u8A9E\\u306E absurd\\u3001\\u30D5\\u30E9\\u30F3\\u30B9\\u8A9E\\u306E absurde\\u3001\\u30C9\\u30A4\\u30C4\\u8A9E\\u306E Absurdit\\u00E4t \\u306E\\u8A33\\u3002\\u3053\\u308C\\u3089\\u306F\\u3044\\u305A\\u308C\\u3082\\u30E9\\u30C6\\u30F3\\u8A9E\\u306E absurdus \\u3092\\u8A9E\\u6E90\\u3068\\u3059\\u308B\\u3002\\u3053\\u306E\\u30E9\\u30C6\\u30F3\\u8A9E\\u306E\\u610F\\u5473\\u306F\\u300C\\u4E0D\\u5354\\u548C\\u306A\\u300D(cf. 		"Het absurdisme is een filosofische stroming waarin wordt gesteld dat het leven in essentie geen betekenis heeft, het onmogelijk is rationeel te verklaren waarom er leven is en dat iedere poging om de essentie van het heelal te ontrafelen gedoemd is te mislukken. Volgens absurdisten is het menselijk lijden het resultaat van vergeefse pogingen door individuen om reden of betekenis in de absurde kloof van het bestaan te vinden. Het idee van absurdisme wordt weerspiegeld in diverse kunstvormen."@nl ,
		"En philosophie et en litt\\u00E9rature, l\'absurde est un d\\u00E9calage entre l\'attente de l\'homme et l\'exp\\u00E9rience qu\'il fait du monde, dans quelque domaine de l\'activit\\u00E9 humaine qu\'il s\'exprime. Il r\\u00E9sulte donc de la contradiction d\'un syst\\u00E8me par le fait."@fr ,
		"Absurdismus ist eine Philosophie welche besagt, dass die Anstrengungen der Menschheit einen Sinn im Universum zu finden unweigerlich fehlschlagen m\\u00FCssen (und daher absurd sind), da kein solcher Sinn existiert, zumindest in Bezug auf die Menschheit. Das Wort \\u201Eabsurd\\u201C in diesem Kontext meint dabei nicht \\u201Elogisch unm\\u00F6glich\\u201C, sondern eher \\u201Ef\\u00FCr Menschen unm\\u00F6glich\\u201C.Der Absurdismus hat Bez\\u00FCge zum Existentialismus und zum Nihilismus."@de ,
		"In philosophy, \\"the Absurd\\" refers to the conflict between (1) the human tendency to seek inherent value and meaning in life and (2) the human inability to find any. In this context absurd does not mean \\"logically impossible\\", but rather \\"humanly impossible\\"."@en ,
		"Absurdyzm \\u2013 pogl\\u0105d uznaj\\u0105cy rzeczywisto\\u015B\\u0107 za absurdaln\\u0105, a ludzkie dzia\\u0142ania maj\\u0105ce na celu zrozumienie rzeczywisto\\u015Bci za nie mog\\u0105ce osi\\u0105gn\\u0105\\u0107 swego celu. Jest zwi\\u0105zany z nihilizmem i egzystencjalizmem."@pl ,
		"Em filosofia, \\"O Absurdo\\" se refere ao conflito entre a tend\\u00EAncia humana de buscar significado inerente \\u00E0 vida e a inabilidade humana para encontrar algum significado. Nesse contexto \\"absurdo\\" n\\u00E3o significa \\"logicamente imposs\\u00EDvel\\", mas sim \\"humanamente imposs\\u00EDvel\\"."@pt ,
		"La filosof\\u00EDa del absurdo, llamada en ocasiones absurdismo, establece los esfuerzos realizados por un ser. Convirti\\u00E9ndose incongruentemente en un ser el cual yace buscando el contexto de la verdad absoluta dentro del universo. Dichas b\\u00FAsquedas tienden a fracasar ya que no existe tal significado (al menos en relaci\\u00F3n al hombre), caracteriz\\u00E1ndose as\\u00ED por su escepticismo en torno a los principios universales de la existencia."@es ,
