		"Katharevousa (Greek: \\u039A\\u03B1\\u03B8\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B5\\u03CD\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1, (Modern Greek: /ka\\u03B8a\\u02C8revusa/, lit. \\"pure [language]\\"), is a form of the Modern Greek language conceived in the early 19th century as a compromise between Ancient Greek and the Demotic Greek of the time. Originally, it was widely used both for literary and official purposes, though seldom in daily language."@en ,
		"Catar\\u00E9vussa (em grego: \\u03BA\\u03B1\\u03B8\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B5\\u03CD\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1, transl. kathar\\u00E9vussa, lit. \\"l\\u00EDngua purificada\\") \\u00E9 uma forma do idioma grego criada no in\\u00EDcio do s\\u00E9culo XIX por Adam\\u00E1ntios Kora\\u00EDs (1748-1833). Korais rejeitava a influ\\u00EAncia bizantina na l\\u00EDngua grega e era um cr\\u00EDtico \\u00E1cido da ignor\\u00E2ncia do clero e sua submiss\\u00E3o ao Imp\\u00E9rio Otomano. A kathar\\u00E9vussa foi concebida para expurgar do grego os aportes estrangeiros sem, por\\u00E9m, voltar ao grego antigo."@pt ,
		"Kathar\\u00E9vousa, kazar\\u00E9vusa o cazar\\u00E9vusa (en griego: \\u03BA\\u03B1\\u03B8\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B5\\u03CD\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1, [ka\\u03B8a\'\\u027E\\u025Bvusa], literalmente \\u00ABlengua pura\\u00BB) es una variante culta y arcaizante del griego moderno. La kathar\\u00E9vousa se concibi\\u00F3 en el siglo XIX como un intento de \\u00ABpurificar\\u00BB la lengua de los barbarismos que se hab\\u00EDan ido introduciendo desde \\u00E9poca medieval, sobre todo desde la descomposici\\u00F3n del imperio bizantino y la dominaci\\u00F3n otomana. Su primer promotor importante fue el l\\u00EDder revolucionario Adamantios Korais (1748\\u20131833)."@es ,
		"La katharevousa (in greco \\u039A\\u03B1\\u03B8\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B5\\u03CD\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1, IPA: [ka\\u03B8a\\u02C8r\\u025Bvu\\u02CCsa]) \\u00E8 stata una variante artificiale pianificata naturalistica, arcaizzante e purista, della lingua greca, creata agli inizi del XIX secolo sulla base dell\'antico dialetto attico da Adamantios Korais e utilizzata come lingua ufficiale della Grecia fino al 1976.La katharevousa mirava a eliminare o minimizzare le variazioni che aveva subito la lingua greca nel periodo bizantino e, successivamente, sotto la dominazione ottomana, e a cercare di ricreare una forma adeguatamente modernizzata di greco antico ripristinando sia termini che strutture grammaticali antiche.Fu adottata come lingua ufficiale del Regno di Grecia (resosi indipendente dall\'Impero ottomano nel 1832), con l\'intento di sostituire la dhimotik\\u00EC (in greco: \\u03B4\\u03B7\\u03BC\\u03BF\\u03C4\\u03B9\\u03BA\\u03AE), il greco parlato dalla popolazione, e fu al centro della questione della lingua greca. "@it ,
		"\\u041A\\u0430\\u0444\\u0430\\u0440\\u0435\\u0301\\u0432\\u0443\\u0441\\u0430 (\\u0433\\u0440\\u0435\\u0447. \\u03BA\\u03B1\\u03B8\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B5\\u03CD\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1 \\u2014 \\u00AB\\u0447\\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u0430\\u044F\\u00BB) \\u2014 \\u043A\\u043E\\u043D\\u0441\\u0435\\u0440\\u0432\\u0430\\u0442\\u0438\\u0432\\u043D\\u0430\\u044F \\u0440\\u0430\\u0437\\u043D\\u043E\\u0432\\u0438\\u0434\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u044C \\u0433\\u0440\\u0435\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u0430, \\u043A\\u043E\\u0442\\u043E\\u0440\\u0430\\u044F \\u0431\\u044B\\u043B\\u0430 \\u0432 \\u0413\\u0440\\u0435\\u0446\\u0438\\u0438 XIX \\u0438 XX \\u0432\\u0435\\u043A\\u043E\\u0432 \\u043E\\u0441\\u043D\\u043E\\u0432\\u043D\\u044B\\u043C \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u043E\\u043C \\u0433\\u043E\\u0441\\u0443\\u0434\\u0430\\u0440\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0430, \\u043E\\u0431\\u0449\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u0436\\u0438\\u0437\\u043D\\u0438 \\u0438 \\u0447\\u0430\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438 \\u043B\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u044B."@ru ,
		"Die heute als Katharevousa [ka\\u03B8a\\u02C8revusa] (\\u039A\\u03B1\\u03B8\\u03B1\\u03C1\\u03B5\\u03CD\\u03BF\\u03C5\\u03C3\\u03B1 \\u201Adie Reine [Sprache]\\u2018) bezeichnete Form des Griechischen wurde im 19. Jahrhundert zun\\u00E4chst auf Basis der griechischen Volkssprache (Dimotiki), sp\\u00E4ter eher nach dem Ideal des klassischen Attisch entwickelt, als man die Notwendigkeit einer modernen Staats- und Bildungssprache feststellte und die gesprochene Volkssprache f\\u00FCr die Zwecke des neu zu gr\\u00FCndenden griechischen Staates nicht als ausreichend erachtete."@de .

	rdfs:comment	"Eine Marionette ist eine Gliederpuppe, die von einem Marionettenspieler mit Hilfe von F\\u00E4den bewegt wird, die an den einzelnen Gliedern befestigt sind. Das Baumaterial war fr\\u00FCher in der Regel Holz. F\\u00FCr die K\\u00F6pfe wurde h\\u00E4ufig Lindenholz verwendet, da es eine feine Maserung aufweist, weich genug ist, um einfach bearbeitet zu werden, und hart genug, um langlebig stabil und bruchfest zu bleiben."@de ,

		"Fantoche, marionete ou marioneta, origina-se do termo marionette que vem do frances. Constitui-se numa forma de entretenimento para adultos e crian\\u00E7as. Quem manipula uma marionete \\u00E9 um titereiro."@pt ,

		"Une marionnette \\u00E0 fils ou fantoche est une marionnette contr\\u00F4l\\u00E9e par des fils qui relient les diff\\u00E9rentes parties de son corps (t\\u00EAte, bras, jambes, torse\\u2026) \\u00E0 un support en bois nomm\\u00E9 croix d\'attelle ou contr\\u00F4le. Elle est donc manipul\\u00E9e par le dessus.L\'ensecret est la technique utilis\\u00E9e pour relier la marionnette \\u00E0 fils \\u00E0 son contr\\u00F4le."@fr ,
		"A marionette is a puppet controlled from above using wires or strings depending on regional variations.  A marionette\'s puppeteer is called a marionettist. Marionettes are operated with the puppeteer hidden or revealed to an audience by using a vertical or horizontal control bar in different forms of theatres or entertainment venues. They have also been used in films and on television. The attachment of the strings varies according to its character or purpose."@en ,
		"Marioneta (palabra usada a menudo para nombrar al conjunto de la familia de los t\\u00EDteres, nombre espa\\u00F1ol del teatro de mu\\u00F1ecos) es, en su definici\\u00F3n m\\u00E1s t\\u00E9cnica e hist\\u00F3rica, una figurilla hecha de diversos materiales (madera, pasta, trapo, metal, pl\\u00E1stico, etc.) que manipulada gracias a un conjunto de hilos o cuerdas cobra movimiento."@es ,

		"El georgismo \\u2014com\\u00FAnmente llamado as\\u00ED por Henry George, su m\\u00E1s conocido te\\u00F3rico\\u2014 o geo\\u00EDsmo, a veces confundido con la geonom\\u00EDa (una ciencia), es una filosof\\u00EDa pol\\u00EDtica e ideolog\\u00EDa econ\\u00F3mica por la que uno es due\\u00F1o de aquello que logre crear, pero todo aquello que es proporcionado por la naturaleza, sobre todo la tierra, pertenece a toda la humanidad por igual."@es ,
		"Het geo\\u00EFsme of georgisme (naar de Amerikaans econoom Henry George) is een politieke en economische ideologie. Centraal in het gedachtegoed is het eigendomsprincipe dat stelt dat priv\\u00E9-eigendom het gevolg is van menselijke arbeid en creatie, maar dat de natuurlijke hulpbronnen, inclusief alle grond, aan de mensheid als geheel toebehoren."@nl ,
		"Il georgismo, da Henry George (1839-1897), \\u00E8 una filosofia ed una ideologia economica che sostiene che ognuno abbia il diritto di appropriarsi di ci\\u00F2 che crea attraverso il proprio lavoro, ma che ogni cosa che si trova in natura, principalmente la terra, appartenga in maniera egalitaria a tutta l\'umanit\\u00E0. La filosofia georgista \\u00E8 legata all\'idea della tassa unica sul valore della terra."@it ,

		"\\u4E54\\u6CBB\\u4E3B\\u4E49\\u662F\\u4E00\\u79CD\\u7ECF\\u6D4E\\u610F\\u8BC6\\u5F62\\u6001\\uFF0C\\u7531\\u4EA8\\u5229\\u00B7\\u4E54\\u6CBB\\u63D0\\u51FA\\u3002"@zh ,
		"Georgism (also known as geoism and geonomics) is an economic philosophy holding that the economic value derived from land, including natural resources and natural opportunities, should belong equally to all residents of a community, but that people justly own value that they fairly create.  The Georgist paradigm offers solutions to social and ecological problems, relying on principles of land rights and public finance which attempt to integrate economic efficiency with social justice."@en .

dbr:Augustan_poetry	rdfs:label	"Poes\\u00EDa augusta"@es ,
		"Augustan poetry"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"See also Augustan literature (ancient Rome).In Latin literature, Augustan poetry is the poetry that flourished during the reign of Caesar Augustus as Emperor of Rome, most notably including the works of Virgil, Horace, and Ovid. In English literature, Augustan poetry is a branch of Augustan literature, and refers to the poetry of the 18th century, specifically the first half of the century.  The term comes most originally from a term that George I had used for himself."@en ,

		"Die Br\\u00FCcke (\\"Il Ponte\\") \\u00E8 stato un gruppo di artisti dell\'avanguardia tedesca formatosi a Dresda il 7 giugno 1905, fu l\'origine di un pi\\u00F9 vasto e localmente diversificato movimento denominato Espressionismo tedesco caratterizzato, a differenza delle analoghe proposizioni francesi, da atteggiamenti di decisa opposizione politica e sociale."@it ,
		"Die Br\\u00FCcke (El Puente) es la tendencia art\\u00EDstica de un grupo de pintores alemanes expresionistas reunidos en Dresde entre 1905 y 1913.La pintura del grupo Die Br\\u00FCcke es una de las primeras expresiones de las vanguardias del siglo XX. Busca experimentar e innovar, pero  tambi\\u00E9n efectuar una protesta contra academicismos y ciertos \\u00ABablandamientos\\u00BB y rebuscamientos t\\u00EDpicos de la Belle \\u00C9poque."@es ,
		"Die Br\\u00FCcke (The Bridge) was a group of German expressionist artists formed in Dresden in 1905, after which the Br\\u00FCcke Museum in Berlin was named. Founding members were Fritz Bleyl, Erich Heckel, Ernst Ludwig Kirchner and Karl Schmidt-Rottluff. Later members were Emil Nolde, Max Pechstein and Otto Mueller. The seminal group had a major impact on the evolution of modern art in the 20th century and the creation of expressionism.Die Br\\u00FCcke is sometimes compared to the Fauves."@en ,
		"Die Br\\u00FCcke war eine expressionistische K\\u00FCnstlergruppe (auch KG Br\\u00FCcke genannt), die am 7. Juni 1905 in Dresden von den vier Architekturstudenten Ernst Ludwig Kirchner, Fritz Bleyl, Erich Heckel und Karl Schmidt-Rottluff gegr\\u00FCndet wurde und als ein Wegbereiter des deutschen Expressionismus gilt. Weitere Mitglieder der K\\u00FCnstlergruppe wurden Max Pechstein, Otto Mueller und Cuno Amiet, kurzzeitig auch Emil Nolde und Kees van Dongen."@de ,
		"Die Br\\u00FCcke, tamb\\u00E9m conhecido simplesmente como Br\\u00FCcke, (do alem\\u00E3o, A ponte), refere-se a um grupo art\\u00EDstico alem\\u00E3o inserido no movimento expressionista. Foi fundado a 7 de Junho de 1905 em Dresden por um grupo de estudantes de arquitectura da Escola T\\u00E9cnica de Dresden, Ernst Ludwig Kirchner, Fritz Bleyl, Erich Heckel e Karl Schmidt-Rottluff."@pt ,
		"\\u00AB\\u041C\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u00BB (\\u043D\\u0435\\u043C. Die Br\\u00FCcke) \\u2014 \\u0433\\u0440\\u0443\\u043F\\u043F\\u0430 \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u043E\\u0432 \\u0432 \\u0413\\u0435\\u0440\\u043C\\u0430\\u043D\\u0438\\u0438 \\u0432 1905\\u20141913 \\u0433\\u043E\\u0434\\u0430\\u0445, \\u0432\\u044B\\u0441\\u0442\\u0443\\u043F\\u0438\\u0432\\u0448\\u0438\\u0445 \\u043E\\u0441\\u043D\\u043E\\u0432\\u043E\\u043F\\u043E\\u043B\\u043E\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u0430\\u043C\\u0438 \\u043D\\u0435\\u043C\\u0435\\u0446\\u043A\\u043E\\u0433\\u043E \\u044D\\u043A\\u0441\\u043F\\u0440\\u0435\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u043E\\u043D\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C\\u0430."@ru ,
		"Die Br\\u00FCcke was een kortstondig bestaande beweging in de beeldende kunst (1905-1913), gevormd door een groep expressionistische kunstenaars uit de Duitse stad Dresden."@nl ,
		"Die Br\\u00FCcke (niem. Most, inne nazwy Br\\u00FCcke lub KG Br\\u00FCcke) \\u2013 ugrupowanie niemieckich artyst\\u00F3w ekspresjonist\\u00F3w, kt\\u00F3re powsta\\u0142o w Dre\\u017Anie w 1905 roku. Za\\u0142o\\u017Cone zosta\\u0142o przez czterech student\\u00F3w architektury: Fritza Bleyla, Ericha Heckela, Ernsta Ludwiga Kirchnera i Karla Schmidt-Rottluffa. P\\u00F3\\u017Aniej do\\u0142\\u0105czyli do nich: Emil Nolde i Max Pechstein (1906) oraz Otto Mueller (1910).Cz\\u0142onkowie grupy poszukiwali nowych form artystycznej ekspresji, stoj\\u0105cych w opozycji do tradycji akademickiej tamtego czasu."@pl .

	rdfs:comment	"O candombe \\u00E9 uma dan\\u00E7a com atabaques t\\u00EDpica da Am\\u00E9rica do Sul. Tem um papel significativo na cultura do Uruguai dos \\u00FAltimos duzentos anos. Foi reconhecido pela Organiza\\u00E7\\u00E3o das Na\\u00E7\\u00F5es Unidas para a Educa\\u00E7\\u00E3o, a Ci\\u00EAncia e a Cultura como Patrim\\u00F4nio Oral e Imaterial da Humanidade. \\u00C9 uma manifesta\\u00E7\\u00E3o cultural originada a partir da chegada dos escravos da \\u00C1frica ao continente sul-americano. Em menor medida, existem manifesta\\u00E7\\u00F5es de candombe no Brasil e Argentina."@pt ,
		"Le candombe est un genre musical d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 dans la r\\u00E9gion de l\'Uruguay. Certains musicologues pr\\u00E9tendent qu\'il trouve son origine dans les rythmes de l\'Afrique bantoue.Le Candombe est essentiellement l\'expression de la communaut\\u00E9 noire de Montevideo (Uruguay). On en trouve traditionnellement des  expressions dans l\'ensemble de l\'Uruguay et parfois en l\'Argentine."@fr ,
		"Urspr\\u00FCnglich ist der Candombe eine folkloristische Tanzbewegungsform der Afro-Lateinamerikaner in Montevideo und Buenos Aires. Der Candombe in Uruguay wurde im September 2009 auf die Repr\\u00E4sentative Liste des immateriellen Kulturerbes der Menschheit der UNESCO aufgenommen und z\\u00E4hlt somit zum Immateriellen Kulturerbe der Menschheit.In Montevideo erklingen auch heute noch an jedem Samstagnachmittag die Trommeln des Candombe."@de ,
		"\\u30AB\\u30F3\\u30C9\\u30F3\\u30D9\\u3068\\u306F\\u592A\\u9F13\\u3092\\u57FA\\u306B\\u3057\\u305F\\u30A6\\u30EB\\u30B0\\u30A2\\u30A4\\u306E\\u97F3\\u697D\\u69D8\\u5F0F\\u3067\\u3042\\u308B\\u3002\\u30AB\\u30F3\\u30C9\\u30F3\\u30D9\\u306F\\u30E2\\u30F3\\u30C6\\u30D3\\u30C7\\u30AA\\u306E\\u30A2\\u30D5\\u30EA\\u30AB\\u7CFB\\u4F4F\\u6C11\\u306B\\u3088\\u3063\\u3066\\u958B\\u59CB\\u3055\\u308C\\u3001\\u30D0\\u30F3\\u30C8\\u30A5\\u30FC\\u30FB\\u30A2\\u30D5\\u30EA\\u30AB\\u7CFB\\u306E\\u30C9\\u30E9\\u30E0\\u3092\\u57FA\\u306B\\u3001\\u30E8\\u30FC\\u30ED\\u30C3\\u30D1\\u4EBA\\u3068\\u3001\\u30BF\\u30F3\\u30B4\\u306E\\u606F\\u9063\\u3044\\u306E\\u5F71\\u97FF\\u304B\\u3089\\u306A\\u3063\\u3066\\u3044\\u308B\\u30022009\\u5E74\\u3001\\u300C\\u30AB\\u30F3\\u30C9\\u30F3\\u30D9\\u3068\\u305D\\u306E\\u793E\\u4F1A\\u30FB\\u6587\\u5316\\u7684\\u7A7A\\u9593\\u300D\\u304C\\u30E6\\u30CD\\u30B9\\u30B3\\u7121\\u5F62\\u6587\\u5316\\u907A\\u7523\\u306B\\u767B\\u9332\\u3055\\u308C\\u305F\\u3002"@ja ,
		"Candombe \\u2013 styl muzyki oparty na b\\u0119bnach (tambores). Candombe powsta\\u0142o w Montevideo i jest charakterystyczne dla grupy afro-urugwajczy\\u00F3w; oparte jest na stylu b\\u0119bnienia charakterystycznym dla plemion bantu w \\u015Brodkowej i po\\u0142udniowej Afryce. Candombe mia\\u0142o wp\\u0142yw na rozw\\u00F3j tanga argenty\\u0144skiego.Milongon jest rodzajem wolnego candombe.W 2009 roku muzyka candombe i jej przestrze\\u0144 spo\\u0142eczno-kulturowa zosta\\u0142a wpisana na list\\u0119 niematerialnego dziedzictwa UNESCO."@pl ,
		"Candombe is een op percussie gebaseerde muziekstijl, die zich heeft ontwikkeld onder de voornamelijk Afro-Uruguayaanse bevolking van Montevideo. Voor veel uitvoerenden is het niet alleen een muziekstijl, maar ook een levensvorm, een gemoedstoestand, een cultuur."@nl ,
		"El candombe es una manifestaci\\u00F3n cultural de origen negroafricano. Tiene un papel significativo en la cultura de Uruguay de los \\u00FAltimos doscientos a\\u00F1os, fue reconocido por UNESCO como Patrimonio Cultural Inmaterial de la Humanidad. Es una manifestaci\\u00F3n cultural originada a partir de la llegada de esclavos de \\u00C1frica. Existen en menor medida, manifestaciones propias de candombe en Argentina y Brasil."@es ,
		"Candombe is an Uruguayan music and dance style originating with African slaves. It is considered an important aspect of the culture of Uruguay and was recognized by UNESCO as a World Cultural Heritage of humanity. To a lesser extent, Candombe is practiced in Argentina [Paraguay) and Brazil. In Argentina, it can be found in  Buenos Aires, Santa Fe, Paran\\u00E1, and Corrientes. In Paraguay is continued  this tradition in Kamba Kua(Camba Cua) in Fernando de la Mora near  to Asuncion."@en .

"@es ,

dbr:Fantastique	rdfs:label	"Fantastique"@zh ,

		"\\u0424\\u0430\\u043D\\u0442\\u0430\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u043A\\u0430"@ru ,

	rdfs:comment	"Lo Fantastique es un g\\u00E9nero o subg\\u00E9nero literario, sin duda pr\\u00F3ximo del g\\u00E9nero fant\\u00E1stico (o fantas\\u00EDa), y que puede definirse como la intrusi\\u00F3n de lo sobrenatural en un marco realista, o sea, aparici\\u00F3n y desarrollo de hechos inexplicables aunque en teor\\u00EDa con algun, lo fantastique b\\u00E1sicamente est\\u00E1 presente vacilando entre la aceptaci\\u00F3n de lo sobrenatural como tal, y una tentativa de explicaci\\u00F3n racional."@es ,
		"The Fantastique is a French term for a literary and cinematic genre that overlaps with science fiction, horror, and fantasy.The fantastique is a substantial genre within French literature.  Arguably dating back further than English language fantasy, it remains an active and productive genre which has evolved in conjunction with anglophone fantasy and horror and other French and international literature."@en ,
		"Le fantastique est un registre litt\\u00E9raire qui se caract\\u00E9rise par l\\u2019intrusion du surnaturel dans le cadre r\\u00E9aliste pour un r\\u00E9cit. Selon le th\\u00E9oricien de la litt\\u00E9rature Tzvetan Todorov (voir son essai Introduction \\u00E0 la litt\\u00E9rature fantastique), le fantastique se distingue du merveilleux par l\'h\\u00E9sitation qu\'il produit entre le surnaturel et le naturel, le possible ou l\'impossible et parfois entre le logique et l\'illogique."@fr ,
		"Il fantastico \\u00E8 un genere di narrazione basato sulla rappresentazione di elementi e situazioni immaginarie che esulano dall\'esperienza quotidiana, straordinarie, che si ritiene non si verifichino (molto probabilmente) nella realt\\u00E0 comunemente sperimentata. Elementi che possono definire una situazione fantastica sono l\'intervento del soprannaturale o del meraviglioso, come la magia o una invenzione tecnologica futuribile."@it ,

		"Die Generaci\\u00F3n del 98 (deutsch Generation von 98) war eine literarische Bewegung in Spanien.Der Begriff geht auf Azor\\u00EDn zur\\u00FCck, der ihn in einer Artikelserie, \\u201ELa Generaci\\u00F3n de 1898\\u201C von 1913 verwendete, und spielt auf die desastr\\u00F6se Niederlage Spaniens im Spanisch-Amerikanischen Krieg und die daraus folgende angespannte soziale und politische Situation an.  Denn am 25. April 1898 hatte Spanien den USA den Krieg erkl\\u00E4rt."@de ,
		"A Gera\\u00E7\\u00E3o de 98 (Generaci\\u00F3n del 98 em espanhol) \\u00E9 a denomina\\u00E7\\u00E3o atribu\\u00EDda a um grupo de escritores, ensa\\u00EDstas e poetas espanh\\u00F3is que se viram profundamente afetados pela crise moral, pol\\u00EDtica e social na Espanha subsequente \\u00E0 derrota militar na Guerra Hispano-Americana e a consequente perda de Porto Rico, Cuba e Filipinas em 1898."@pt ,
		"Pokolenie 1898 (hiszp. Generaci\\u00F3n del 98) \\u2013 generacja pisarzy i my\\u015Blicieli hiszpa\\u0144skich, urodzonych pomi\\u0119dzy 1864 a 1880 rokiem, po\\u0142\\u0105czonych pokoleniowym do\\u015Bwiadczeniem hiszpa\\u0144skiej kl\\u0119ski w wojnie z USA i utraty hiszpa\\u0144skich kolonii. Wydarzenie to wywo\\u0142a\\u0142o og\\u00F3lnonarodow\\u0105 atmosfer\\u0119 zniech\\u0119cenia i samokrytyki, a u m\\u0142odego pokolenia potrzeb\\u0119 odpowiedzi na podstawowe pytania filozoficzne."@pl ,
		"The Generation of \'98 (also called Generation of 1898 or (in Spanish) Generaci\\u00F3n del 98 or Generaci\\u00F3n de 1898) was a group of novelists, poets, essayists, and philosophers active in Spain at the time of the Spanish\\u2013American War (1898).The name Generaci\\u00F3n del 98 was coined by Jose Mart\\u00EDnez Ruiz, commonly known as Azor\\u00EDn, in his 1913 essays titled \\"La generaci\\u00F3n de 1898\\", alluding to the moral, political, and social crisis in Spain produced by the disaster and the loss of the colonies of Cuba, Puerto Rico, and the Philippines after defeat in the Spanish\\u2013American War that same year. "@en ,
		"Con il termine Generazione del \'98 (Generaci\\u00F3n del 98) si indica un gruppo di intellettuali spagnoli dei primi del XX secolo. L\'allusione all\'anno 1898 per indicare questo gruppo \\u00E8 dovuta alla guerra ispano-americana combattuta in quell\'anno tra Stati Uniti e Spagna, che cost\\u00F2 a quest\'ultima la perdita delle sue ultime colonie d\'oltremare, cio\\u00E8 Cuba, Porto Rico e Filippine."@it ,
		"La derni\\u00E8re d\\u00E9cennie du XIXe si\\u00E8cle connut une activit\\u00E9 litt\\u00E9raire d\\u00E9bordante en Espagne. Les auteurs de la g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ration de 98 (Generaci\\u00F3n del 98), comme ils furent surnomm\\u00E9s, \\u00E9taient d\\u00E9termin\\u00E9s \\u00E0 r\\u00E9\\u00E9valuer la vie culturelle du pays et essayer de la revitaliser. C\'est l\'\\u00E9poque \\u00E0 laquelle l\'Espagne, perdant ses derni\\u00E8res colonies, se rendit soudainement compte qu\'elle n\'\\u00E9tait plus ce qu\'elle fut."@fr ,

		"La generaci\\u00F3n del 98 es el nombre con el que se ha reunido tradicionalmente a un grupo de escritores, ensayistas y poetas espa\\u00F1oles que se vieron profundamente afectados por la crisis moral, pol\\u00EDtica y social desencadenada en Espa\\u00F1a por la derrota militar en la guerra hispano-estadounidense y la consiguiente p\\u00E9rdida de Puerto Rico, Guam, Cuba y las Filipinas en 1898."@es ,

		"Wegen der Vielzahl der Sprachen, die in Indien gesprochen und geschrieben werden, kann von der indischen Literatur nur im Plural gesprochen werden. Die indischen Literaturen z\\u00E4hlen zu den \\u00E4ltesten literarischen Traditionen der Welt. Die klassische Sanskrit-Dichtung wurde im Mittelalter durch mehrere vom Volk gesprochene mittelindische Prakrit-Sprachen abgel\\u00F6st.Unter Moghul-Einfluss kam ab dem 16. Jahrhundert die vorwiegend in Urdu verfasste islamische Lyrik des Ghasel hinzu."@de ,
		"La litt\\u00E9rature indienne est riche et si on compte les contes et les \\u00E9pop\\u00E9es, serait parmi les plus anciennes au monde[\\u00E9vasif]. L\'Inde compte 22 langues dites nationales et 2 langues officielles, une grande quantit\\u00E9 d\'\\u0153uvres a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 produite, dans ces diff\\u00E9rentes langues, au fil du temps. Les formes orale et \\u00E9crite sont aussi importantes l\'une que l\'autre.La litt\\u00E9rature traditionnelle hindoue tient une grande place dans la culture indienne."@fr ,

		"La letteratura indiana si compone di tutte quelle opere prodotte nel subcontinente indiano fino al 1947 e dalla creazione della Repubblica dell\'India in poi, che riconosce ufficialmente 22 lingue.Le prime opere della letteratura indiana furono trasmesse oralmente. La letteratura sanscrita comincia con i Veda, una collezione di inni sacri composti tra il 2000 a.C. e il IV secolo a.C., e con i poemi epici Mah\\u0101bh\\u0101rata e Ramayana."@it ,

		"Indian literature refers to the literature produced on the Indian subcontinent until 1947 and in the Republic of India thereafter. The Republic of India has 22 officially recognized languages.All dates about the ancient Indian literature are not only uncertain, but are contested. European scholars from the 18th century onwards estimated dates of various texts based on methods that Indian scholars consider arbitrary. The earliest works of Indian literature were orally transmitted."@en ,

		"Escola de Nova Iorque (New York School), grupo informal e associado ao chamado Expressionismo abstrato \\u00E9 o nome dado a um grupo de artistas dos EUA, ativo a partir de meados dos anos 40 at\\u00E9 finais dos anos 50, de modo relativamente aut\\u00F4nomo da Arte Europeia, e que viria a afirmar a presen\\u00E7a norteamericana no contexto art\\u00EDstico mundial.A New York School era formada por poetas, pintores, dan\\u00E7arinos e m\\u00FAsicos experimentais."@pt ,
		"The New York School  (synonymous with abstract expressionist painting) was an informal group of American poets, painters, dancers, and musicians active in the 1950s and 1960s in New York City. They often drew inspiration from surrealism and the contemporary avant-garde art movements, in particular action painting, abstract expressionism, jazz, improvisational theater, experimental music, and the interaction of friends in the New York City art world\'s vanguard circle."@en ,
		"L\'\\u00C9cole de New York fait r\\u00E9f\\u00E9rence \\u00E0 un groupe artistique informel de po\\u00E8tes, peintres, danseurs et musiciens, actifs \\u00E0 New York dans les ann\\u00E9es 1950-60, se r\\u00E9clamant de l\'inspiration du surr\\u00E9alisme et des mouvements d\'avant-garde, en particulier l\'action painting, l\'expressionnisme abstrait, la musique exp\\u00E9rimentale, le jazz, l\'improvisation th\\u00E9\\u00E2trale."@fr ,
		"Die New York School war eine Gruppe amerikanischer Maler und Dichter in New York, die sich seit Anfang der 1940er Jahre kristallisierte. Als wichtige K\\u00FCnstler der ersten Generation gelten Arshile Gorky, Hans Hofmann, Adolph Gottlieb, Willem de Kooning und Jackson Pollock. 1946 pr\\u00E4gte der New Yorker Kunstkritiker Robert Coates den Begriff Abstrakter Expressionismus."@de .

		"Pol\\u00F4nia Jovem"@pt ;
	rdfs:comment	"Young Poland (Polish: M\\u0142oda Polska) was a modernist period in Polish visual arts, literature and music, covering roughly the years between 1890 and 1918. It was a result of strong aesthetic opposition to the earlier ideas of Positivism which followed the suppression of the 1863 January Uprising against the occupying army of Imperial Russia. M\\u0142oda Polska promoted trends of decadence, neo-romanticism, symbolism, impressionism and art nouveau."@en ,
		"Jong Polen (M\\u0142oda Polska) was een nationalistische groep componisten, musici en kunstenaars in Polen, opgericht door de componisten Ludomir R\\u00F3\\u017Cycki en Grzegorz Fitelberg in 1905. De term \'Jong Polen\' dook al eerder op, in 1890, als aanduiding van een \'trend\', maar de groep als zodanig bestond pas vanaf 1905."@nl ,
		"Pol\\u00F4nia Jovem (em polon\\u00EAs: M\\u0142oda Polska) \\u00E9 um per\\u00EDodo modernista da arte, da literatura e da m\\u00FAsica polonesa que cobriu cerca dos anos desde 1890 at\\u00E9 1918. Ele foi um dos efeitos da forte oposi\\u00E7\\u00E3o \\u00E0s ideias do positivismo e promoveu os car\\u00E1teres da decad\\u00EAncia, do neo-romantismo, do simbolismo, do impressionismo e do Art Nouveau."@pt ,

	rdfs:comment	"Via\\u021Ba Rom\\u00E2neasc\\u0103, originally Via\\u021Ba Rom\\u00EEneasc\\u0103 (Romanian for \\"The Romanian Life\\"), is a monthly literary magazine published in Romania. Formerly the platform of the left-wing traditionalist trend known as Poporanism, it is at present one of the Writers\' Union main venues.The magazine, dedicated to literary and scientific issues, was published from March 1906 to August 1916 and from September 1920 to September 1940, first in  Ia\\u0219i and then, after 1930, in Bucharest."@en ,
		"Via\\u0163a rom\\u00E2neasc\\u0103 (pol. \\u017Cycie rumu\\u0144skie) \\u2013 rumu\\u0144skie czasopismo o profilu literackim i naukowym, ukazuj\\u0105ce si\\u0119 w okresie od marca 1906 do sierpnia 1916 i od wrze\\u015Bnia 1920 do wrze\\u015Bnia 1930 w Jassach, a od 1930 do wrze\\u015Bnia 1940 w Bukareszcie. 	rdfs:comment	"L\'occidentalisme est un courant de pens\\u00E9e n\\u00E9 dans l\'Empire russe dans la premi\\u00E8re moiti\\u00E9 du XIXe si\\u00E8cle.Il recouvre une multitude de th\\u00E9ories (aussi bien lib\\u00E9rales que socialistes, ou anarchistes) dont le point commun est de consid\\u00E9rer que la Russie est arri\\u00E9r\\u00E9e et que c\'est l\'Occident qui doit lui servir de mod\\u00E8le de d\\u00E9veloppement.La conviction de l\'inf\\u00E9riorit\\u00E9 de la Russie par rapport \\u00E0 l\'Europe occidentale \\u00E9tait largement r\\u00E9pandue dans un pays o\\u00F9 les tsars (en particulier Pierre le Grand et Catherine II) et les classes dirigeantes avaient \\u00E9cart\\u00E9 les valeurs et institutions russes pour adopter, souvent rapidement et brutalement, celles de l\'Occident."@fr ,
		"Westernizers (Russian: \\u0417\\u00E1\\u043F\\u0430\\u0434\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A, zapadnik) were a group of 19th century intellectuals who believed that Russia\'s development depended upon the adoption of Western European technology and liberal government. In their view, western ideas such as industrialisation needed to be implemented throughout Russia in order to make it a more successful country."@en ,

Od lat 60. XIX w."@pl ,
		"Der Begriff Westler (russisch \\u0417\\u0430\\u043F\\u0430\\u0434\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A, zapadnik) ist eine Umschreibung f\\u00FCr eine politisch-publizistische Richtung im Russland des 19. Jahrhunderts, die in den 1840er Jahren aufgrund der Auseinandersetzung mit den Slawophilen entstand. Vergleichbar mit den Urbanen in Ungarn, traten die Vertreter der Westler f\\u00FCr einen engen Anschluss Russlands an die westeurop\\u00E4ische Kultur ein. 		"Abstraction-Cr\\u00E9ation est un collectif d\'artistes form\\u00E9 \\u00E0 Paris en 1931 pour contrer l\'influence du puissant groupe des surr\\u00E9alistes dirig\\u00E9 par Andr\\u00E9 Breton. Auguste Herbin, Jean H\\u00E9lion et Georges Vantongerloo fond\\u00E8rent le groupe pour promouvoir l\'art abstrait apr\\u00E8s la tendance de la repr\\u00E9sentation dans les ann\\u00E9es 1920. L\'existence de ce groupe commence r\\u00E9ellement en 1932 et se termine en 1936. Une revue-cahier fut \\u00E9dit\\u00E9e, Abstraction-Cr\\u00E9ation, imprim\\u00E9e \\u00E0 Paris par Les Tendances nouvelles."@fr ,
		"Abstraction-Cr\\u00E9ation \\u2013 mi\\u0119dzynarodowa grupa abstrakcjonist\\u00F3w za\\u0142o\\u017Cona w 1931 w Pary\\u017Cu i stanowi\\u0105ca kontynuacj\\u0119 dzia\\u0142alno\\u015Bci grupy Cercle et Carr\\u00E9. Za\\u0142o\\u017Cyciele, Auguste Herbin i Georges Vantongerloo, wyznaczyli sobie cel promowania sztuki abstrakcyjnej poprzez grupowe wystawy. Do stowarzyszenia do\\u0142\\u0105czy\\u0142o wielu uznanych artyst\\u00F3w, m.in. Naum Gabo, Wasilij Kandinskij, Piet Mondrian, Alexander Calder."@pl ,
		"Abstra\\u00E7\\u00E3o-Cria\\u00E7\\u00E3o (em franc\\u00EAs, Abstraction-Cr\\u00E9ation) foi uma associa\\u00E7\\u00E3o internacional de artistas pl\\u00E1sticos estabelecida em Paris em 1931, com a proposta de superar a arte figurativa e apoiar o exerc\\u00EDcio da criatividade no campo do abstracionismo. A associa\\u00E7\\u00E3o publicou cinco anu\\u00E1rios entre 1932 e 1936 e organizou diversas exposi\\u00E7\\u00F5es, chegando a congregar cerca de 400 artistas, a maioria da Europa e dos Estados Unidos."@pt ,
		"Abstraction-Cr\\u00E9ation was a loose association of artists formed in Paris in 1931 to counteract the influence of the Surrealist group led by Andr\\u00E9 Breton.Founders Theo van Doesburg, Auguste Herbin, Jean H\\u00E9lion and Georges Vantongerloo started the group to foster abstract art after the trend turned to representation in the 1920s.A non-prescriptive group of artists were involved, whose ideals and practices varied widely: Albert Gleizes, Franti\\u0161ek Kupka, Piet Mondrian, Jean Arp, Marlow Moss, Naum Gabo, Alberto Magnelli, Barbara Hepworth, Ben Nicholson, Kurt Schwitters, Wassily Kandinsky, Wolfgang Paalen, Th\\u00E9o Kerg, Taro Okamoto, Paule V\\u00E9zelay, Hans Erni, Bart van der Leck, Leon Tutundjian and John Wardell Power.Five Cahiers (yearbooks) were published between 1932-36 entitled Abstraction-cr\\u00E9ation: Art non-figuratif; a reprint edition of the Cahiers was published by the Arno Press, New York in 1968. "@en ,
		"Abstraction-Cr\\u00E9ation was een, op initiatief van de Belg Georges Vantongerloo, op 12 februari 1931 in Parijs opgerichte internationale groep kunstenaars, die van groot belang is geweest voor de ontwikkeling van de moderne kunst. Andere oprichters waren Auguste Herbin (voorzitter), Theo van Doesburg (vicevoorzitter), Jean H\\u00E9lion (penningmeester), Hans Arp, L\\u00E9on Arthur Tutundjian, Albert Gleizes, Franti\\u0161ek Kupka, Georges Valmier (commissieleden), Antoine Pevsner en Naum Gabo."@nl .

		"Political satire is a significant part of satire that specializes in gaining entertainment from politics; it has also been used with subversive intent where political speech and dissent are forbidden by a regime, as a method ofPolitical satire is usually distinguished from political protest or political dissent, as it does not necessarily carry an agenda nor seek to influence the political process. While occasionally it may, it more commonly aims simply to provide entertainment."@en .

		"La culture populaire repr\\u00E9sente une forme de culture dont la principale caract\\u00E9ristique est d\'\\u00EAtre produite et appr\\u00E9ci\\u00E9e par le plus grand nombre, \\u00E0 l\'oppos\\u00E9 d\'une culture \\u00E9litiste ou avant-gardiste qui ne toucherait qu\'une partie ais\\u00E9e et/ou instruite de la population. Elle ne doit pas \\u00EAtre confondue avec la culture de masse ou la culture m\\u00E9diatique ."@fr ,
		"Popular culture or pop culture is the entirety of ideas, perspectives, attitudes, images, and other phenomena that are within the mainstream of a given culture, especially  Western culture of the early to mid 20th century and the emerging global mainstream of the late 20th and early 21st century. Heavily influenced by mass media, this collection of ideas permeates the everyday lives of the society."@en ,
		"Der Begriff Popkultur (von lateinisch populus \\u201AVolk\\u2018) oder Popul\\u00E4rkultur bezeichnet kulturelle Erzeugnisse und Alltagspraktiken, die vor allem seit dem 20. Jahrhundert im Zuge der gesellschaftlichen Modernisierung als Massenkultur Verbreitung finden. Die Etablierung des Massenkonsums seit dem sp\\u00E4teren 19. Jahrhundert spielt daf\\u00FCr eine Rolle.Der Begriff Popul\\u00E4rkultur hat sich auch als allgemeinerer und neutraler Ersatz f\\u00FCr die \\u00E4ltere Bezeichnung \\u201EVolkskultur\\u201C durchgesetzt."@de ,

		"El t\\u00E9rmino cultura popular hace referencia al conjunto de patrones culturales y manifestaciones art\\u00EDsticas y literarias creadas o consumidas preferentemente por las clases populares (clase baja o media sin instrucci\\u00F3n acad\\u00E9mica, o en la antig\\u00FCedad \\"la plebe\\") por contraposici\\u00F3n con una cultura acad\\u00E9mica, alta u oficial centrada en medios de expresi\\u00F3n tradicionalmente valorados como superiores y generalmente m\\u00E1s elitista y excluyente."@es ,
		"Popcultuur (afkorting van \'populaire cultuur\') is de in de jaren zestig in de westerse landen ontstane subcultuur, die zich afzette tegen overgeleverde normen en waarden en die daaraan uiting gaf door afwijkende kleding en haardracht. De popmuziek vormde daarbij een belangrijk medium om gevoelens en idee\\u00EBn uit te dragen.Popcultuur is een zeer breed begrip."@nl ,

		"This article is about the Spanish Renaissance of the 15th-16th centuries.See Renaissance of the 12th century for the earlier Renaissance in Spain.The Spanish Renaissance refers to a movement in Spain, emerging from the Italian Renaissance in Italy during the 14th century, that spread to Spain during the 15th and 16th centuries."@en ,
		"Renacimiento espa\\u00F1ol es la expresi\\u00F3n empleada para designar a la influencia y al desarrollo que se dio en Espa\\u00F1a del movimiento art\\u00EDstico y cient\\u00EDfico originado en Italia en el  siglo XV, y que se fue expandiendo por el resto de Europa Occidental en el s. XVI, conocido como Renacimiento."@es ,
		"De Spaanse renaissance is een periode in de 15e en 16e eeuwse Spaanse geschiedenis die haar naam ontleent aan de invloed die Spanje vanaf de 15e eeuw onderging van de renaissance die in Itali\\u00EB begon. Een van de bekendste kunstenaars uit deze periode was de schilder El Greco.Tegen het einde van de 15e eeuw was er ook onder Spaanse kunstenaars en intellectuelen een nieuwe aandacht ontstaan voor de kunsten, wetenschappen en literatuur van de Grieks-Romeinse oudheid."@nl ,
		"Il Rinascimento spagnolo \\u00E8 l\'insieme delle manifestazioni culturali ed artistiche sorte in Spagna, soprattutto nel corso del XVI secolo, per l\'influenza del Rinascimento italiano. Si tratt\\u00F2 di un\'adesione lenta, condizionata dalle tradizioni locali e dotata di caratteri propri."@it .

		"The Boston School was a group of Boston-based painters active in the first three decades of the twentieth century. Often classified as American Impressionists, they had their own regional style, combining the painterliness of Impressionism with a more conservative approach to figure painting and a marked respect for the traditions of Western art history. Their preferred subject matter was genteel: portraits, picturesque landscapes, and young women posing in well-appointed interiors."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"The Cleveland School refers to the flourishing local arts community of Northeast Ohio during the period from 1910 to 1960. It was so named in 1928 by Elrick Davis, a journalist with the Cleveland Press."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"La cultura hacedora, cultura del hacedor, cultura fabricante o cultura maker es una cultura o subcultura contempor\\u00E1nea que representa una extensi\\u00F3n basada en la tecnolog\\u00EDa de la cultura DIY (h\\u00E1galo-usted-mismo)."@es ,
		"Gli artigiani digitali, o \\"maker\\", costituiscono un movimento culturale contemporaneo che rappresenta un\'estensione su base tecnologica del tradizionale mondo del fai da te. Tra gli interessi tipici degli artigiani digitali vi sono realizzazioni di tipo ingegneristico, come apparecchiature elettroniche, realizzazioni robotiche, dispositivi per la stampa 3D, e apparecchiature a controllo numerico."@it ,
		"The maker culture is a contemporary culture or subculture representing a technology-based extension of DIY culture that intersects with hacker culture which is less concerned with physical objects (opposed to software) and the creation of new devices (opposed to tinkering with existing ones)."@en ,

		"L\'affiche est un support de publicit\\u00E9 ou de propagande destin\\u00E9 \\u00E0 \\u00EAtre vu dans la rue et plus g\\u00E9n\\u00E9ralement dans les espaces publics. Imprim\\u00E9e sur papier, sur du tissu ou des supports synth\\u00E9tiques, elle adopte des dimensions variables, pouvant aller jusqu\'\\u00E0 plusieurs m\\u00E8tres. Elle gagne ses lettres de noblesse \\u00E0 la fin du XIXe si\\u00E8cle avec des illustrateurs comme Jules Ch\\u00E9ret ou Alphonse Mucha et des peintres comme Toulouse-Lautrec, qui ne d\\u00E9daignent plus y avoir recours comme moyen d\'expression."@fr ,
		"Ein Plakat ist ein gro\\u00DFer, in der Regel mit Text und Bild bedruckter Bogen aus Papier, der an einer Plakatwand, einem Plakatreiter, einer Litfa\\u00DFs\\u00E4ule oder einer anderen geeigneten Fl\\u00E4che in der \\u00D6ffentlichkeit angebracht wird, um eine Botschaft zu \\u00FCbermitteln. Seinem Wesen nach ist das Plakat eine Mitteilung an eine anonyme Gruppe von Empf\\u00E4ngern. Der Absender kann nicht unmittelbar kontrollieren, ob seine Botschaft den einzelnen Empf\\u00E4nger erreicht und wie dieser darauf reagiert."@de ,

		"A poster is any piece of printed paper designed to be attached to a wall or vertical surface. Typically posters include both textual and graphic elements, although a poster may be either wholly graphical or wholly text. Posters are designed to be both eye-catching and informative. Posters may be used for many purposes.  They are a frequent tool of advertisers (particularly of events, musicians and films), propagandists, protestors and other groups trying to communicate a message."@en ,

		"Cartaz (tamb\\u00E9m chamado p\\u00F3ster (portugu\\u00EAs europeu) ou p\\u00F4ster (portugu\\u00EAs brasileiro) \\u00E9 um suporte, normalmente em papel, afixado de forma que seja vis\\u00EDvel em locais p\\u00FAblicos. Sua fun\\u00E7\\u00E3o principal \\u00E9 a de divulgar uma informa\\u00E7\\u00E3o visualmente, mas tamb\\u00E9m tem sido apreciada como uma pe\\u00E7a de valor est\\u00E9tico. Al\\u00E9m da sua import\\u00E2ncia como meio de publicidade e de informa\\u00E7\\u00E3o visual, o cartaz possui um valor hist\\u00F3rico como meio de divulga\\u00E7\\u00E3o em importantes movimentos de car\\u00E1ter pol\\u00EDtico ou art\\u00EDstico."@pt ,
		"Cartel es un soporte de la publicidad. Consiste en una l\\u00E1mina de papel, cart\\u00F3n u otro material que se imprime con alg\\u00FAn tipo de mensaje visual (texto, im\\u00E1genes y todo tipo de recursos gr\\u00E1ficos) que sirve de anuncio para difundir una informaci\\u00F3n o promocionar un (bien o servicio) producto (econom\\u00EDa) (dab), un evento, una reivindicaci\\u00F3n o cualquier tipo de causa. 	rdfs:comment	"Purismus, aus dem Adjektiv pur (lat. purus = rein, unverf\\u00E4lscht, ehrlich) bedeutet in der \\u00C4sthetik ein Schwergewicht auf dem Klaren, Genauen, Regelm\\u00E4\\u00DFigen, auch Unverf\\u00E4lschten. Puristische Str\\u00F6mungen folgen oft auf Wellen des Manierismus und des Eklektizismus, die zum Beispiel ein \\u00DCberborden des Ornamentalen mit sich bringen.Im engeren Sinn ist der Purismus eine Richtung der Kunst und Architektur des 20. Jahrhunderts."@de ,
		"Le purisme, mouvement post-cubiste, est un courant d\'artistes repr\\u00E9sentant des objets de la vie quotidienne. C\'est une forme de cubisme. Am\\u00E9d\\u00E9e Ozenfant et Le Corbusier sont les th\\u00E9oriciens du purisme.En 1918, Le Corbusier signe le manifeste Apr\\u00E8s le cubisme, o\\u00F9 il pr\\u00E9conise avec Ozenfant un retour \\u00E0 l\'ordre. Leur mouvement est initi\\u00E9 par l\'ouvrage La peinture moderne, publi\\u00E9 \\u00E0 Paris en 1925."@fr ,
		"Purismo es la denominaci\\u00F3n de un movimiento art\\u00EDstico franc\\u00E9s de la \\u00E9poca de las vanguardias hist\\u00F3ricas (la primera mitad del siglo XX)."@es ,

,
		"Na arte, o purismo foi um movimento que defendia uma pintura sem valores emocionais, racional e rigorosa. Sem subjetividade e qualidades decorativas. O movimento foi fundado por Am\\u00E9d\\u00E9e Ozenfant, pintor e escritor, e Le Corbusier (Charles Edouard Jeanneret), em 1918. Os dois se consideravam os criadores do Cubismo Puro.Existe uma simplifica\\u00E7\\u00E3o das formas, geometriza\\u00E7\\u00E3o."@pt ,
		"Purism, referring to the arts, was a movement that took place between 1918\\u20131925 that influenced French painting and architecture. Purism was led by Am\\u00E9d\\u00E9e Ozenfant and Charles Edouard Jeanneret (Le Corbusier). Ozenfant and Le Corbusier created a variation of Cubist movement and called it Purism."@en ,
		"Puryzm \\u2013 kierunek w malarstwie powsta\\u0142y z kubizmu syntetycznego, nawi\\u0105zuj\\u0105cy r\\u00F3wnie\\u017C do neoplastycyzmu i konstruktywizmu.Rozwin\\u0105\\u0142 si\\u0119 w latach 1916-1925, jego tw\\u00F3rcami byli Ozenfant i Le Corbusier. Stworzyli oni program czystej formy, porz\\u0105dkuj\\u0105cej wizj\\u0119 rzeczywisto\\u015Bci na miar\\u0119 \\"wieku maszyny\\". Stosowano pastelow\\u0105 gam\\u0119 barwn\\u0105 i kompozycj\\u0119 z\\u0142o\\u017Con\\u0105 z p\\u0142askich, p\\u0142ynnie zrytmizowanych form geometrycznych."@pl ,

		"Il Purismo \\u00E8 un movimento artistico nato in Francia attorno agli anni venti come reazione alle tendenze decorative del Cubismo e come tentativo di creare un\'arte chiara, ordinata, espressione della moderna civilt\\u00E0 delle macchine."@it ,
		"Purisme was een latere vorm van kubisme, die werd bedacht en toegepast door de Franse schilder Am\\u00E9d\\u00E9e Ozenfant en de architect Charles-Edouard Jeanneret (Le Corbusier). Ook de aanvankelijk kubistische schilder Fernand L\\u00E9ger ontplooide zich later actief binnen het Purisme. Purisme verwierp de decoratieve trend van kubisme, en was meer gericht op een terugkeer naar heldere, geordende vormen. Jeanneret en Ozenfant schreven voor het eerst over purisme in hun boek After Cubism uit 1918."@nl .

		"Skamander was a Polish group of experimental poets founded in 1918 by Julian Tuwim, Antoni S\\u0142onimski, Jaros\\u0142aw Iwaszkiewicz, Kazimierz Wierzy\\u0144ski and Jan Lecho\\u0144.Initially unnamed, in December 1919 it adopted the name Skamander, after the Scamander River in Asia Minor."@en ,

Sie setzte sich f\\u00FCr den Gebrauch der allt\\u00E4glichen Sprache in der Poesie ein, verk\\u00FCndete aber ansonsten ein \\u201EProgramm der Programmlosigkeit\\u201C."@de ,

		"L\'\\u00E9cole florentine est une des \\u00E9coles italiennes de peinture qui  se d\\u00E9veloppe  du XIIIe au XVIe si\\u00E8cle \\u00E0 Florence ; on lui attribue traditionnellement les principes m\\u00EAmes de la Renaissance italienne, rompant avec le go\\u00FBt byzantin r\\u00E9gnant dans toute l\'Europe, comme le fit Giotto, figure embl\\u00E9matique de la naissance de ce courant de renouveau artistique \\u00E0 Florence.Bien que Giorgio Vasari place \\u00E0 Florence l\'origine de la Renaissance artistique italienne, les historiens de l\'art comme Roberto Longhi, consid\\u00E8rent que plusieurs des capitales italiennes, comme Bologne, Ferrare, Urbino, Venise, Milan, Bari, P\\u00E9rouse, Padoue, Naples, Palerme et Ravenne, ont contribu\\u00E9, ensemble (par leurs \\u00E9changes nombreux) au renouveau artistique de cette p\\u00E9riode."@fr ,

		"Florentine painting or the Florentine School refers to artists in, from, or influenced by the naturalistic style developed in Florence in the 14th century, largely through the efforts of Giotto di Bondone, and in the 15th century the leading school of Western painting. Some of the best known artists of the Florentine school, including other arts, are Filippo Brunelleschi, Donatello, Michelangelo, Fra Angelico, Botticelli, Lippi, Masolino, and Masaccio."@en ,

		"Village Prose (Russian: \\u0414\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043F\\u0440\\u043E\\u0437\\u0430, or \\u0414\\u0435\\u0440\\u0435\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u043B\\u0438\\u0442\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0442\\u0443\\u0440\\u0430) was a movement in Soviet literature beginning during the Khrushchev Thaw, which included works that focused on the Soviet rural communities. dbr:Dirty_realism	rdfs:label	"R\\u00E9alisme sale"@fr ,
		"Realismo sujo"@pt ,
		"Realismo sucio"@es ,
		"Realismo sporco"@it ,
		"Dirty realism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Con realismo sporco (dall\'inglese dirty realism) si designa un movimento letterario sorto negli Stati Uniti negli anni settanta-ottanta che, in linea generale, pretende di ricondurre la narrazione (specialmente il racconto breve) ai suoi elementi fondamentali.Si tratta di una filiazione del minimalismo che ha caratteristiche peculiari."@it ,
		"El realismo sucio (\\u00ABDirty realism\\u00BB) es un movimiento literario estadounidense desarrollado sobre todo en los a\\u00F1os 1970 que pretende reducir la narraci\\u00F3n (especialmente el relato corto) a sus elementos fundamentales.Se trata de una derivaci\\u00F3n del minimalismo que tiene caracter\\u00EDsticas propias. Al igual que aqu\\u00E9l, el realismo sucio se caracteriza por su tendencia a la sobriedad, la precisi\\u00F3n y una parquedad extrema en el uso de las palabras en todo lo que se refiera a descripci\\u00F3n."@es ,
		"Dirty Realism, ou Realismo sujo \\u00E9 um movimento liter\\u00E1rio norte-americano nascido em 1970, em que a narrativa \\u00E9 despojado de suas caracter\\u00EDsticas fundamentais.Este movimento \\u00E9 um derivado do minimalismo. No minimalismo, o realismo sujo \\u00E9 caracterizado por uma economia de palavras e um foco na descri\\u00E7\\u00E3o superf\\u00EDcial. Autores que trabalham dentro do g\\u00EAnero, como o brasileiro Renan M. Rossi (Carnivale), tendem a afastar-se de adv\\u00E9rbios e preferem permitir que o contexto dite os significados."@pt ,
		"Dirty realism is a term coined by Bill Buford of Granta magazine to define a North American literary movement. Writers in this sub-category of realism are said to depict the seamier or more mundane aspects of ordinary life in spare, unadorned language. The term formed the title of the Summer 1983 edition of Granta, for which Buford wrote an explanatory introduction:\\"Dirty Realism is the fiction of a new generation of American authors."@en ,
		"Le r\\u00E9alisme sale (de l\'anglais : dirty realism) repr\\u00E9sente un mouvement litt\\u00E9raire am\\u00E9ricain qui \\u00E9mergea dans les ann\\u00E9es 1970-1980, dont le terme fut lanc\\u00E9 en 1983 par Bill Buford du magazine litt\\u00E9raire Granta pour d\\u00E9finir ce mouvement.Les \\u00E9crivains d\\u00E9crits comme \\u00AB r\\u00E9alistes sales \\u00BB (de l\'anglais : dirty realists) d\\u00E9peindraient avec somme de d\\u00E9tails les plus sordides ou les plus quelconques aspects de la vie ordinaire en utilisant un langage simple et sans ornement."@fr .

		"Poetic realism was a film movement in France of the 1930s. More a tendency than a movement, poetic realism is not strongly unified like Soviet Montage or French Impressionism but were individuals who created this lyrical style. Its leading filmmakers were Pierre Chenal, Jean Vigo, Julien Duvivier, Marcel Carn\\u00E9, and, perhaps the movement\'s most significant director, Jean Renoir."@en .

	rdfs:comment	"Dau al Set (\\u00AB D\\u00E9 sur le sept \\u00BB) est un groupe artistique catalan d\'avant-garde n\\u00E9 \\u00E0 Barcelone autour de la revue homonyme (octobre 1948). Son seul titre (en Catalan, le d\\u00E9 sur le sept) annon\\u00E7ait d\\u00E9j\\u00E0 le caract\\u00E8re de rupture du groupe.Ses fondateurs sont le po\\u00E8te Joan Brossa, les peintres Antoni T\\u00E0pies, Joan Pon\\u00E7, Joan-Joseph Tharrats et Modest Cuixart et le philosophe Arnau Puig."@fr ,
		"Dau al Set (Catalan pronunciation: [\\u02C8daw \\u0259\\u026B \\u02C8s\\u025Bt]), the first post-World War II artistic movement in Catalonia, was founded in Barcelona in October 1948 by poet Joan Brossa.  The avant-garde group had connections to the Surrealist and Dadaist movements and stressed the importance of both the conscious and unconscious in their works."@en ,
		"Dau al Set [\\u02C8daw \\u0259\\u026B \\u02C8s\\u025Bt] (Katalanisch f\\u00FCr \\u201AW\\u00FCrfel, der eine Sieben zeigt\\u2018) war eine spanische K\\u00FCnstlergruppe, deren Mitglieder katalanische K\\u00FCnstler und Schriftsteller waren. Die Gruppe wurde 1948 in Barcelona gegr\\u00FCndet. Die Gr\\u00FCndungsmitglieder waren die Maler und K\\u00FCnstler Modest Cuixart, Joan Pon\\u00E7, Juan Jos\\u00E9 Tharrats, und Antoni T\\u00E0pies, der Philosoph Arnau Puig und der Dichter Joan Brossa, der den Gruppennamen kreierte und die Gruppe wesentlich inspirierte."@de ,
		"Dau al Set es un grupo art\\u00EDstico vanguardista espa\\u00F1ol de Catalu\\u00F1a creado alrededor de la revista hom\\u00F3nima en Barcelona, en septiembre de 1948. Su propio t\\u00EDtulo (en espa\\u00F1ol \'La s\\u00E9ptima cara del dado\') ya delata su car\\u00E1cter rupturista.Sus miembros fundadores fueron el poeta Joan Brossa (que cre\\u00F3 el nombre del grupo y la revista), el fil\\u00F3sofo Arnau Puig y los pintores Joan Pon\\u00E7 (director de la revista), Antoni T\\u00E0pies, Modest Cuixart y Joan-Josep Tharrats (editor e impresor de la misma)."@es ,
		"Dau al Set [\\u02C8daw \\u0259\\u026B \\u02C8s\\u025Bt] sono un gruppo artistico catalano d\'avanguardia creato nell\'ottobre 1948 a Barcellona intorno all\'omonima rivista."@it ,
		"O Dau al Set \\u00E9 o nome de um grupo art\\u00EDstico da vanguarda catal\\u00E3, criado em torno da revista com o mesmo nome, em Barcelona, em Outubro de 1948. O seu t\\u00EDtulo, que significa A S\\u00E9tima Face do Dado, mostra j\\u00E1 o seu car\\u00E1cter de ruptura.Os seus membros fundadores foram Joan Brossa, poeta, criador do nome do grupo e da revista, Arnau Puig, fil\\u00F3sofo, e os pintores Joan Pon\\u00E7 (director da revista), Antoni T\\u00E0pies, Modest Cuixart e Joan-Josep Tharrats (editor e impressor da revista)."@pt .

dbr:Return_to_order	rdfs:label	"Ritorno all\'ordine"@it ,
		"Return to order"@en ,
		"Retour \\u00E0 l\'ordre"@fr ,
		"Return to order"@nl ;
	rdfs:comment	"Le Retour \\u00E0 l\'ordre est un mouvement artistique europ\\u00E9en, de l\\u2019entre-deux-guerres, caract\\u00E9ris\\u00E9 par une r\\u00E9interpr\\u00E9tation de l\\u2019id\\u00E9al classique.N\\u00E9 au lendemain de la  Premi\\u00E8re Guerre mondiale, ce mouvement \\u2013 o\\u00F9 les artistes et les intellectuels expriment leur volont\\u00E9 de renouer avec un art susceptible d\'incarner, par l\'\\u00E9loge du classicisme, le \\u00AB g\\u00E9nie \\u00BB des nations dont l\'ordre et la hi\\u00E9rarchie ont \\u00E9t\\u00E9 boulevers\\u00E9s lors du dernier conflit arm\\u00E9 - prend le pas sur les \\u00AB exc\\u00E8s \\u00BB de l\'avant-gardisme international, jusqu\'alors dominant : d\\u00E8s lors, il envahit le champ des arts plastiques et de l\'architecture et influence de nombreux artistes tels  Picasso,  Braque, Ludwig Mies van der Rohe ... "@fr ,
		"Return to order (van het Franse retour \\u00E0 l\'ordre) was een Europese kunsttendens die volgde na de Eerste Wereldoorlog en die zich afzette tegen de extreme avant-garde in de kunst van de periode tot ongeveer 1918 en in plaats daarvan haar inspiratie haalde uit de meer traditionele kunst."@nl ,
		"The return to order was a European art movement that followed the First World War, rejecting the extreme avant-garde art of the years up to 1918 and taking its inspiration from traditional art instead.  The movement was a reaction to the War.  Cubism was partially abandoned even by its creators, Braque and Picasso, and Futurism, which had praised machinery, violence and war, was rejected by most of its adherents."@en ,
		"Ritorno all\'ordine \\u00E8 stata una corrente artistica europea successiva alla prima guerra mondiale, un movimento pittorico che ripropose la centralit\\u00E0 della tradizione e della storia, del classicismo e della fedelt\\u00E0 figurativa, del racconto e della celebrazione aulica, rifiutando gli estremismi dell\'Avanguardia che aveva dominato fino al 1918 e ritornando quindi ad un tipo di ispirazione tradizionale.Questo movimento fu una reazione alla guerra e subito abbandon\\u00F2 il Cubismo, facendolo rigettare persino dai suoi primari inventori, Braque e Picasso. "@it .

dbr:Feminist_art_movement	rdfs:label	"Feminist art movement"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The feminist art movement refers to the efforts and accomplishments of feminists internationally to produce art that reflects women\'s lives and experiences, as well as to change the foundation for the production and reception of contemporary art. dbr:Garip	rdfs:label	"Garip"@en ,
		"Garip"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"Garip (t\\u00FCrkisch f\\u00FCr seltsam oder fremdartig) war eine t\\u00FCrkische Dichtergruppe. Alternativ wurde diese Str\\u00F6mung auch Erste Neue (t\\u00FCrkisch Birinci Yeni) genannt.Sie bestand aus Orhan Veli, Oktay Rifat und Melih Cevdet, die schon seit ihrer Oberschulzeit befreundet waren. Dabei war Orhan Veli der bekannteste Vertreter der Gruppe. Nach dessen Tod 1950 entwickelten die beiden verbliebenen Freunde ihren Stil individuell weiter und begannen auch Romane und Theaterst\\u00FCcke zu schreiben."@de ,
		"Garip (Turkish: strange, peculiar / poor, forlorn) was a group of Turkish poets. The group was also known as the First New Movement. It was composed of Orhan Veli, Oktay Rifat and Melih Cevdet, who had been friends since high school. The name \\"Garip\\" signalled a break with the conventional, decadent style of Turkish poetry and literature at the time. Garip poets used vernacular speech and surrealist elements in their poems."@en .

dbr:Modular_constructivism	rdfs:label	"Modular constructivism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Modular constructivism is a style of sculpture that emerged in the 1950s and 1960s and was associated especially with Erwin Hauer and Norman Carlberg. It is based on carefully structured modules which allow for intricate and in some cases infinite patterns of repetition, sometimes used to create limitless, basically planar, screen-like formations, and sometimes employed to make more multidimensional structures."@en .

dbr:American_realism	rdfs:label	"American realism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"American realism was a style in art, music and literature that depicted contemporary social realities and the lives and everyday activities of ordinary people. The movement began in literature in the mid-19th century, and became an important tendency in visual art in the early 20th century. Whether a cultural portrayal or a scenic view of downtown New York City, American realist works attempted to define what was real."@en .
dbr:Christian_Gnosticism	rdfs:label	"\\u0413\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u0447\\u0435\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u0435 \\u0445\\u0440\\u0438\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u0430\\u043D\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u043E"@ru ,
		"Christian Gnosticism"@en ,
		"Gnosticismo crist\\u00E3o"@pt ,
		"Gnostiek"@nl ;
	rdfs:comment	"De gnostiek is een verzamelnaam voor een brede waaier aan religieuze stromingen binnen het vroege christendom. De term gnostiek is etymologisch afkomstig van het Griekse woord voor kennis, gnosis (\\u03B3\\u03BD\\u03C9\\u03C3\\u03B9\\u03C2). In de gnostiek kreeg gnosis de speciale betekenis van mystieke kennis over de verborgen aard van de werkelijkheid en van de mens. De gnostiek onderscheidde zich daarmee van het confessionele christendom dat zich baseerde op geloof."@nl ,
		"The term Gnosticism is used by scholars with a wide variety of meanings and levels of specificity. Sometimes the term refers only to those Sethians who used the term gnostikoi to describe themselves. Sometimes it is used more broadly to include Valentinians, followers of Basilides, and others. Likewise, one scholar may consider Simon Magus a gnostic, where another considers him a proto-gnostic."@en ,

dbr:Mono-ha	rdfs:label	"Mono-ha"@fr ,
		"\\u3082\\u306E\\u6D3E"@ja ,
		"Mono-ha"@en ,
		"Mono-Ha"@it ;
	rdfs:comment	"Mono-Ha \\u00E8 il nome comunemente attribuito ad una corrente artistica, ed al gruppo dei suoi appartenenti, che hanno operato in Giappone tra la fine degli anni sessanta e l\'inizio degli anni settanta.Sebbene radicalmente differenti e diversificati tra loro, il lavoro di ciascun artista del Mono-Ha \\u00E8 caratterizzato da alcune caratteristiche comuni quali: l\'impiego di materiali naturali, l\'assimilazione di alcuni aspetti dell\'Occidente, la sfida al concetto tradizionale di arte."@it ,
		"Mono-ha (\\u3082\\u306E\\u6D3E) is the name given to group of 20th-century Japanese artists. The Mono-ha artists explored the encounter between natural and industrial materials, such as stone, steel plates, glass, light bulbs, cotton, sponge, paper, wood, wire, rope, leather, oil, and water, arranging them in mostly unaltered, ephemeral states. The works focus as much on the interdependency of these various elements and the surrounding space as on the materials themselves."@en ,
		"Mono-ha est le nom d\'un groupe d\\u2019artistes japonais du XXe si\\u00E8cle, bien qu\'il y ait d\\u00E9bat pour savoir si Mono-ha est un mouvement artistique ou une partie du mouvement de l\'art conceptuel. dbr:Navajo_weaving	rdfs:label	"Navajo weaving"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Navajo rugs and blankets (Navajo: diyog\\u00ED) are textiles produced by Navajo people of the Four Corners area of the United States. Navajo textiles are highly regarded and have been sought after as trade items for over 150 years. Commercial production of handwoven blankets and rugs has been an important element of the Navajo economy."@en .

		"Het Armeens (\\u0540\\u0561\\u0575\\u0565\\u0580\\u0565\\u0576, Hayer\\u0113n) is de Indo-Europese taal die in Armeni\\u00EB door de overgrote meerderheid van de bevolking gesproken wordt. De taal wordt ongeveer door 6 miljoen mensen gesproken, niet alleen in Armeni\\u00EB, maar ook in Nagorno-Karabach en de Armeense Diaspora, zoals Frankrijk en de Verenigde Staten.Het Armeens heeft een eigen alfabet, ontwikkeld door St. Mesrop Masjtots."@nl ,
		"The Armenian language (classical: \\u0570\\u0561\\u0575\\u0565\\u0580\\u0567\\u0576; reformed: \\u0570\\u0561\\u0575\\u0565\\u0580\\u0565\\u0576 [h\\u0251j\\u025B\\u02C8\\u027E\\u025Bn] hayeren) is an Indo-European language spoken by the Armenians. It is the official language of the Republic of Armenia and the self-proclaimed Nagorno-Karabakh Republic. It has historically been spoken throughout the Armenian Highlands and today is widely spoken in the Armenian diaspora."@en ,

		"Die armenische Sprache (armenisch: \\u0540\\u0561\\u0575\\u0565\\u0580\\u0565\\u0576, traditionelle Rechtschreibung: \\u0540\\u0561\\u0575\\u0565\\u0580\\u0567\\u0576 - Hajeren) ist ein Zweig der indogermanischen Sprachen.Man unterscheidet drei Sprachformen des Armenischen: Altarmenisch (\\u0533\\u0580\\u0561\\u0562\\u0561\\u0580 \\u2013 auch Grabar genannt), das seit dem 5. 		"El idioma armenio (en armenio, \\u0570\\u0561\\u0575\\u0565\\u0580\\u0565\\u0576 \\u056C\\u0565\\u0566\\u0578\\u0582, AFI: [h\\u0251j\\u025B\\u0279\\u025Bn l\\u025Bzu], hayeren lezu \'lengua armenia\', abreviado como hayeren \'armenio\') es una lengua indoeuropea hablada por los armenios. 	rdfs:comment	"La Repubblica del Benin (italiano Ben\\u00ECn; francese /be\\u02C8n\\u025B\\u0303/) \\u00E8 uno Stato dell\'Africa Occidentale, precedentemente conosciuto con il nome di Dahomey. 		"Benin (/b\\u0268\\u02C8ni\\u02D0n/ b\\u01DD-NEEN or /b\\u0268\\u02C8n\\u026An/ b\\u01DD-NIN; French: B\\u00E9nin), officially the Republic of Benin (French: R\\u00E9publique du B\\u00E9nin) and formerly Dahomey, is a country in West Africa. It is bordered by Togo to the west, by Nigeria to the east and by Burkina Faso and Niger to the north. A majority of the population live on its small southern coastline on the Bight of Benin, part of the Gulf of Guinea in the northernmost tropical portion of the Atlantic Ocean."@en ,

		"Benin, officieel de Republiek Benin, is een land in Afrika. Het grenst in het westen aan Togo, in het noordwesten aan Burkina Faso, in het noordoosten aan de Republiek Niger in het oosten aan Nigeria. In het zuiden ligt het aan de Baai van Benin, onderdeel van de Golf van Guinee. Tot 1975 was het land bekend onder de naam Dahomey. De Republiek Dahomey werd op 1 augustus 1960 onafhankelijk van Frankrijk."@nl ,
		"Benin [be\\u02C8ni\\u02D0n] (frz. B\\u00E9nin [be\\u02C8n\\u025B\\u0303]) ist ein Staat in Westafrika. Die Bezeichnung steht in Tradition zum historischen K\\u00F6nigreich Dahomey, das bis zur Eroberung durch die Franzosen Ende des 19. Jahrhunderts den s\\u00FCdlichen Teil des modernen Staates und des Nachbarstaates Togo umfasste."@de ,

		"Konkani is een Indo-Arische taal hoewel veel woorden afgeleid zijn van de Dravidische talen. De taal wordt gesproken in de gebieden Goa, Maharashtra, Karnataka en Kerala in India, door de Konkani.Door de invloed van westerse talen (Portugees, Engels) bestond de mogelijkheid dat het Konkani zou uitsterven. In het begin van de eenentwintigste eeuw werd het door zo\'n 3,6 miljoen mensen gesproken."@nl ,

		"Le konkani est une des 22 langues officielles parl\\u00E9es en Inde, par plus de 7 millions, dans le nord et le centre de la bande c\\u00F4ti\\u00E8re du Maharashtra, entre la c\\u00F4te de Konkan (d\'o\\u00F9 son nom) et les gh\\u00E2ts occidentaux, langue officielle \\u00E0 Goa au Karnataka, au Dadra et Nagar Haveli et au Kerala. Dans la partie sud de sa zone d\'extension, il est appel\\u00E9 gom\\u00E2ntak\\u00EE."@fr ,
		"Konkani (K\\u014D\\u1E45ka\\u1E47\\u012B) is an Indo-Aryan language belonging to the Indo-European family of languages and is spoken along the western coast of India. It is one of the 22 scheduled languages mentioned in the 8th schedule of the Indian Constitution and the official language of the Indian state of Goa. The first Konkani inscription is dated 1187 A.D."@en ,
		"O concani (pron\\u00FAncia portuguesa AFI: [k\\u0254nka\'ni:]) ou concanim, ou ainda conc\\u00E2nio, a que os portugueses chamavam canarim  (devan\\u00E1gari: \\u0915\\u094B\\u0902\\u0915\\u0923\\u0940 ko\\u1E43ka\\u1E47\\u012B; canar\\u00E1: \\u0C95\\u0CCA\\u0C82\\u0C95\\u0CA3\\u0CBF; malaiala: \\u0D15\\u0D4A\\u0D02\\u0D15\\u0D23\\u0D40) \\u00E9 uma l\\u00EDngua indo-ariana falada na \\u00CDndia. Come\\u00E7ou por ser um vern\\u00E1culo do s\\u00E2nscrito, com corrup\\u00E7\\u00E3o inevit\\u00E1vel de algumas palavras."@pt ,
		"El idioma konkan\\u00ED o konkani (dev\\u00E1nagari: \\u0915\\u094B\\u0902\\u0915\\u0923\\u0940, malabar: \\u0D15\\u0D4A\\u0D02\\u0D15\\u0D23\\u0D40, canar\\u00E9s: \\u0C95\\u0CCA\\u0C82\\u0C95\\u0CA3\\u0CBF, alfabeto latino: konknni) es una de las lenguas nacionales de la India, que pertenece a la familia indoeuropea de lenguas. Es una lengua indo-aria, y es hablada en la costa oeste de la India llamada Konkan."@es ,
		"Konkani (\\u0915\\u094B\\u0902\\u0915\\u0923\\u0940) ist urspr\\u00FCnglich ein Dialekt des Marathi, der haupts\\u00E4chlich in Goa gesprochen wird. Er hat jedoch einen Ausbauprozess durchgemacht und kann deshalb als eigene Sprache gelten. Da Goa mehr als 400 Jahre eine portugiesische Kolonie war, hat Konkani viele portugiesische Ausdr\\u00FCcke aufgenommen. Es sind aber auch Einfl\\u00FCsse der Sprachen des Nachbarstaats Karnataka (Kannada) und Elemente des Hindi bemerkbar, sowie Einfl\\u00FCsse aus dem Englischen."@de ,

	rdfs:comment	"Rusland (Russisch: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u044F, Rossija), officieel de Russische Federatie (Russisch: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0424\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F, Rossijskaja Federatsija), is een land dat geografisch gedeeltelijk gelegen is in Europa (Europees Rusland) en gedeeltelijk in Azi\\u00EB. Het is echter vanuit politiek perspectief Europees omdat de belangrijkste delen ervan in het Europese deel liggen en ruim 70% van de bevolking hier woont. Moskou is de grootste stad, de hoofdstad en het economisch hart van Rusland."@nl ,

Com 17 075 400 de quil\\u00F4metros quadrados, a R\\u00FAssia \\u00E9 o pa\\u00EDs com maior \\u00E1rea do planeta, cobrindo mais de um nono da \\u00E1rea terrestre. \\u00C9 tamb\\u00E9m o nono pa\\u00EDs mais populoso, com 142 milh\\u00F5es de habitantes."@pt ,
		"Rusia (en ruso: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u044F, romanizaci\\u00F3n: Ross\\u00EDya) o la Federaci\\u00F3n Rusa (formalmente: Federaci\\u00F3n de Rusia; en ruso: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0424\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F, romanizaci\\u00F3n: Ross\\u00EDiskaya Feder\\u00E1tsiya) es el pa\\u00EDs m\\u00E1s extenso del mundo. La Federaci\\u00F3n de Rusia cuenta con una superficie de 17 125 246 kil\\u00F3metros cuadrados, equivalente a la novena parte de la tierra firme del planeta, y con gran variedad de relieves y entornos naturales."@es ,
		"Russia (/\\u02C8r\\u028C\\u0283\\u0259/; Russian: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0301\\u044F, tr. Rossiya; IPA: [r\\u0250\\u02C8s\\u02B2ij\\u0259]), also officially known as the Russian Federation (Russian: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0301\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0424\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0301\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F, tr. It is a federal semi-presidential republic. At 17,075,400 square kilometres (6,592,800 sq mi), Russia is the largest country in the world, covering more than one-eighth of the Earth\'s inhabited land area."@en ,
		"Russland (russisch \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u044F [r\\u0250\\u02C8s\\u02B2ij\\u0259] 12px Aussprache?/i, Transkription Rossija) bzw. die Russische F\\u00F6deration (oder seltener Russl\\u00E4ndische F\\u00F6deration; russisch \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0424\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F, 12px Aussprache?/i, Transkription Rossijskaja Federazija) ist ein f\\u00F6derativer Staat im nord\\u00F6stlichen Eurasien und fl\\u00E4chenm\\u00E4\\u00DFig der gr\\u00F6\\u00DFte der Erde. 		"La Russie, en forme longue la F\\u00E9d\\u00E9ration de Russie, en russe \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u044F (Rossi\\u00EFa) prononciation et \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0424\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F (Rossi\\u00EFska\\u00EFa Federatsi\\u00EFa) prononciation, est le plus vaste pays de la plan\\u00E8te. Sa population est estim\\u00E9e \\u00E0 environ 146,5 millions d\\u2019habitants en 2014. Le pays est \\u00E0 cheval sur l\\u2019Asie du Nord (74,7 % de sa superficie) et sur l\\u2019Europe (25,3 % de sa superficie)."@fr ,

		"La Federazione Russa (in russo: \\u0420\\u043E\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u0439\\u0441\\u043A\\u0430\\u044F \\u0424\\u0435\\u0434\\u0435\\u0440\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F?, traslitterato: Rossijskaja Federacija, ), chiamata comunemente anche Russia, \\u00E8 un paese transcontinentale che si estende tra l\\u2019Europa e l\\u2019Asia, il pi\\u00F9 vasto stato del pianeta con una superficie di 17 075 400 km\\u00B2 (per oltre la met\\u00E0 quasi disabitato).Confina con Norvegia, Finlandia, Estonia, Lettonia, Lituania, Polonia, Bielorussia, Ucraina, Georgia, Azerbaigian, Kazakistan, Cina, Corea del Nord e Mongolia; come la Cina \\u00E8 lo stato al mondo con il maggior numero di stati limitrofi (14), considerando anche stati con ridotto riconoscimento internazionale gli stati confinanti con la Russia diventano 16 (vanno aggiunti Abcasia e Ossezia del Sud entrambe riconosciute dalla Russia). "@it .

		"Reino Unido (em ingl\\u00EAs: United Kingdom - UK), oficialmente Reino Unido da Gr\\u00E3-Bretanha e Irlanda do Norte(em ingl\\u00EAs: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland), \\u00E9 um Estado soberano insular localizado em frente \\u00E0 costa noroeste do continente europeu. O Reino Unido inclui a ilha da Gr\\u00E3-Bretanha, a parte nordeste da ilha da Irlanda, al\\u00E9m de muitas outras ilhas menores. A Irlanda do Norte \\u00E9 a \\u00FAnica parte do Reino Unido com uma fronteira terrestre, no caso, com a Rep\\u00FAblica da Irlanda."@pt ,
		"Het Verenigd Koninkrijk, officieel het Verenigd Koninkrijk van Groot-Brittanni\\u00EB en Noord-Ierland, afgekort VK (Engels: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, afgekort UK, informeel Britain) is een land en een staat in West-Europa met ongeveer 63,7 miljoen inwoners, gelegen tussen de Noordzee en de Atlantische Oceaan."@nl ,
		"The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, commonly known as the United Kingdom (UK) or Britain, is a sovereign state in Europe. Lying off the north-western coast of the European mainland, the country includes the island of Great Britain\\u2014a term also applied loosely to refer to the whole country\\u2014the north-eastern part of the island of Ireland and many smaller islands."@en ,

Para otras acepciones, v\\u00E9ase Us (desambiguaci\\u00F3n), USA (desambiguaci\\u00F3n) y EUA (desambiguaci\\u00F3n).Los Estados Unidos (en ingl\\u00E9s: United States), oficialmente los Estados Unidos de Am\\u00E9rica (en ingl\\u00E9s: United States of America), son un pa\\u00EDs soberano constituido en rep\\u00FAblica federal constitucional compuesta por 50 estados y un distrito federal."@es ,
		"De Verenigde Staten, officieel de Verenigde Staten van Amerika, afgekort VS (Engels: United States of America, afgekort USA of US), zijn een federatie van 50 staten en het District of Columbia, grotendeels in Noord-Amerika gelegen. Twee van de vijftig staten, Alaska en Hawa\\u00EF, grenzen niet aan de andere staten. Tot het land behoren ook diverse eilandgebieden in de Cara\\u00EFbische Zee en de Grote Oceaan. De Verenigde Staten zijn het op twee na grootste land ter wereld in bevolking, na China en India."@nl ,

		"Les \\u00C9tats-Unis, en forme longue les \\u00C9tats-Unis d\'Am\\u00E9rique, en anglais United States et United States of America, sont un pays situ\\u00E9 en Am\\u00E9rique du Nord. Politiquement, les \\u00C9tats-Unis sont une r\\u00E9publique constitutionnelle f\\u00E9d\\u00E9rale \\u00E0 r\\u00E9gime pr\\u00E9sidentiel compos\\u00E9e de cinquante \\u00C9tats, dont quarante-huit sont adjacents et forment le Mainland. Celui-ci est encadr\\u00E9 par l\'oc\\u00E9an Atlantique \\u00E0 l\'est et l\'oc\\u00E9an Pacifique \\u00E0 l\'ouest, et se trouve bord\\u00E9 au nord par le Canada et au sud par le Mexique."@fr ,
		"Estados Unidos da Am\\u00E9rica (em ingl\\u00EAs: United States of America; pronunciado: [ju\\u02D0\\u02C8na\\u026A.t\\u0259d \\u02C8ste\\u026A\\u02A6 \\u0259v \\u0259\\u02C8m\\u025B.\\u027B\\u026A.k\\u0259]), ou simplesmente Estados Unidos (11px? United States), s\\u00E3o uma rep\\u00FAblica constitucional federal composta por 50 estados e um distrito federal. A maior parte do pa\\u00EDs situa-se na regi\\u00E3o central da Am\\u00E9rica do Norte, formada por 48 estados e Washington, D.C., o distrito federal da capital."@pt ,
		"The United States of America (USA), commonly referred to as the United States (U.S.) or America, is a federal republic composed of 50 states, a federal district, five major territories and various possessions. The 48 contiguous states and Washington, D.C., are in central North America between Canada and Mexico. The state of Alaska is located in the northwestern part of North America and the state of Hawaii is an archipelago in the mid-Pacific."@en ,

		"Dresden (12px Aussprache?/i, obersorbisch Drje\\u017Ed\\u017Aany, von altsorbisch dre\\u017E\\u010Fany \\u201ESumpf-\\u201C oder \\u201EAuwald-Bewohner\\u201C) ist die Landeshauptstadt des Freistaates Sachsen. Laut st\\u00E4dtischem Melderegister ist sie mit 542.155 Einwohnern (30. Juni 2015) nach Leipzig die zweitbev\\u00F6lkerungsreichste s\\u00E4chsische Stadt und die zw\\u00F6lftst\\u00E4rkste Kommune Deutschlands.Als Sitz der s\\u00E4chsischen Landesregierung und des Landtags sowie zahlreicher Landesbeh\\u00F6rden ist die Stadt politisches Zentrum des Landes."@de ,

		"Dresde (Dresden en allemand , et Drje\\u017Ed\\u017Aany en sorabe) est une ville-arrondissement d\\u2019Allemagne, capitale et ville la plus peupl\\u00E9e de la Saxe. Elle se situe dans le bassin de Dresde, entre les parties sup\\u00E9rieures et m\\u00E9dianes de l\\u2019Elbe et la plaine d\\u2019Allemagne du nord.En 2013, elle compte 530 754 habitants."@fr ,
		"Dresden (German pronunciation: [\\u02C8d\\u0281e\\u02D0sd\\u0259n]; Upper Sorbian: Drje\\u017Ed\\u017Aany) is the capital city of the Free State of Saxony in Germany. It is situated in a valley on the River Elbe, near the Czech border.Dresden has a long history as the capital and royal residence for the Electors and Kings of Saxony, who for centuries furnished the city with cultural and artistic splendor. The city was known as the Jewel Box, because of its baroque and rococo city center."@en ,
		"Dresde (en alem\\u00E1n: Acerca de este sonido Dresden ; en espa\\u00F1ol \\u00E1urico: Dresda) es la capital del estado federado de Sajonia, en Alemania. Limita al noroeste con el distrito de Mei\\u00DFen, al noreste con el de Bautzen y al sur con el de S\\u00E4chsische Schweiz-Osterzgebirge. Dresde se encuentra justo en el centro de la conurbaci\\u00F3n hom\\u00F3nima. Situada en el centro de Europa, constituye un nudo de transportes fundamental a la vez que un centro econ\\u00F3mico de gran importancia."@es ,
		"Dresda (in tedesco Dresden , in sorabo Drje\\u017Ed\\u017Aany) \\u00E8 una citt\\u00E0 extracircondariale di 531.806 abitanti della Germania, capitale del Land della Sassonia e capoluogo del distretto direttivo (Direktionsbezirk) omonimo.Sorge sul fiume Elba, la cui valle era inserita nella lista dei patrimoni dell\'umanit\\u00E0 dell\'UNESCO, per poi esserne tolta nel 2009, in seguito alla costruzione del ponte a quattro corsie Waldschl\\u00F6sschen."@it .

	rdfs:comment	"Net.art (net dot art) est un terme invent\\u00E9 par Pitz Schultz en 1995[r\\u00E9f. souhait\\u00E9e] et repris par un petit groupe d\'artistes pour d\\u00E9signer leurs pratiques artistiques sur internet.  Ces artistes ainsi que Pit Schultz \\u00E9taient pr\\u00E9sents sur la liste Nettime et partageaient un int\\u00E9r\\u00EAt commun pour l\'art. Ce groupe s\'est rencontr\\u00E9 physiquement en janvier 1996 lors du festival Next Five Minutes \\u00E0 Amsterdam."@fr ,
		"Si definisce net.art un\'opera d\'arte creata con, per e nella rete Internet.Esistono per\\u00F2 diverse tipologie di lavori digitali che seppur creati per la rete non possono essere definiti opere di net art. Per questo motivo  \\u00E8 necessario rintracciare alcuni elementi essenziali che rendono riconoscibile un\'opera di Net. Art."@it ,
		"net.art refers to a group of artists who have worked in the medium of Internet art since 1994. The main members of this movement are Vuk \\u0106osi\\u0107, Jodi.org, Alexei Shulgin, Olia Lialina, and Heath Bunting (irational.org, Daniel Garc\\u00EDa And\\u00FAjar, Heath Bunting, Rachel Baker and Minerva Cuevas)."@en ,
		"Net.art, tambi\\u00E9n llamado net(dot)art o arte.en.red, puede referirse a un g\\u00E9nero de producciones art\\u00EDsticas realizadas ex profeso en y para la red internet, o a un movimiento espec\\u00EDfico de artistas de origen europeo que introdujeron ciertas pr\\u00E1cticas art\\u00EDsticas en la d\\u00E9cada de los noventa coincidiendo con el desarrollo de la WorldWideWeb.En tanto g\\u00E9nero, el net.art es una de las formas de arte interactivo habilitadas por los soportes digitales, y las pr\\u00E1cticas comunicativas generadas por ellos.La denominaci\\u00F3n net.art designa las pr\\u00E1cticas art\\u00EDsticas que apuntan a una experiencia est\\u00E9tica espec\\u00EDfica de internet como soporte de la obra, y dialogan o exploran pr\\u00E1cticas comunicativas en la cibercultura.En ese sentido, Allex Galloway introdujo el t\\u00E9rmino (web) site specificity, para referirse a esa especificidad del net.art:El gran reto del net.art es demostrar autonom\\u00EDa. "@es .
