		"Lautpoesie"@de ;
	rdfs:comment	"La poesia sonora \\u00E8 una forma di espressione artistica interdisciplinare, dove la vocalit\\u00E0, talora applicata alla scrittura, talora svincolata da essa, svolge un ruolo di primo piano, connettendosi anche con forme espressive visive, gestuali, musicali.La poesia sonora pu\\u00F2 essere collocata a pieno titolo nel quadro delle ricerche intermediali, ovvero, come teorizzato da Dick Higgins nel 1961, quelle forme espressive nelle quali le diverse discipline artistiche si intrecciano in una struttura unica e inscindibile cos\\u00EC come avviene per la poesia visuale. "@it ,
		"Lautpoesie (auch akustische oder phonetische Poesie bzw. Dichtung) ist eine Gattung der modernen Lyrik, die auf sprachlichen Sinn ganz oder zu einem erheblichen Teil verzichtet. Analog zur abstrakten Malerei versucht die Lautpoesie, die Sprache nicht in abbildender beziehungsweise inhaltlich-bezeichnender Funktion, sondern rein formal als Lautmaterial anzuwenden."@de ,
		"Sound poetry is an artistic form bridging literary and musical composition, in which the phonetic aspects of human speech are foregrounded instead of more conventional semantic and syntactic values; \\"verse without words\\". By definition, sound poetry is intended primarily for performance."@en ,
		"La po\\u00E9sie sonore est une discipline po\\u00E9tique du XXe si\\u00E8cle. Le terme a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 utilis\\u00E9 la premi\\u00E8re fois en 1958, dans un texte sign\\u00E9 de Jacques Villegl\\u00E9 et Fran\\u00E7ois Dufr\\u00EAne, \\u00E0 propos d\'Henri Chopin. Henri Chopin, exposant en 1967 ce qu\'est la po\\u00E9sie sonore, a expliqu\\u00E9 qu\'il est possible de la diviser en deux groupes : ceux qui sont dans la \\u00AB pr\\u00E9f\\u00E9ration simple de la voix \\u00BB et ceux qui usent \\u00AB des ressources du magn\\u00E9tophone \\u00BB."@fr ,
		"Poes\\u00EDa fon\\u00E9tica es una forma de creaci\\u00F3n po\\u00E9tica basada en los recursos sonoros de la lengua. Antes de que se inventara la escritura, la poes\\u00EDa se transmit\\u00EDa mediante la declamaci\\u00F3n."@es ,
		"Poesia fon\\u00E9tica \\u00E9 uma forma de composi\\u00E7\\u00E3o po\\u00E9tica na qual os aspectos fon\\u00E9ticos da linguagem humana s\\u00E3o priorizados em rela\\u00E7\\u00E3o aos valores sem\\u00E2nticos e sint\\u00E1ticos mais convencionais, podendo, inclusive, n\\u00E3o usar palavras e tendendo a uma aproxima\\u00E7\\u00E3o com a composi\\u00E7\\u00E3o musical. \\u00C9 sin\\u00F4nimo ou se confunde com Poesia sonora ou Sonorista, Poesia f\\u00F4nica, Poesia auditiva ou Poesia ac\\u00FAstica, podendo fazer parte de uma s\\u00E9rie de manifesta\\u00E7\\u00F5es distintas com caracter\\u00EDsticas em comum."@pt ,
		"Een klankdicht is een gedicht waarbij de betekenis geheel is losgelaten en alleen de klank een rol speelt. Het klankdicht wordt wel als de meest extreme vorm van de atonale po\\u00EBzie beschouwd."@nl .

		"Als Russische Nonkonformisten werden die K\\u00FCnstler bezeichnet, die von 1953 bis 1986 (vom Stalins Tod bis zum Aufbruch von Perestroika und Glasnost) als Gegenbewegung zum Sozialistischen Realismus in Literatur, bildender Kunst und Musik in der Sowjetunion wirkten.In der russischen Sprache werden deren  Werke auch als Inoffizielle Kunst, Zweite Avantgarde, Andere Kunst, Alternative Kunst oder U-Bahn-Kunst bezeichnet."@de ,
		"The term Soviet Nonconformist Art refers to art produced in the former Soviet Union from 1953-1986 (after the death of Joseph Stalin until the advent of Perestroika and Glasnost) outside of the rubric of Socialist Realism.  Other terms used to refer to this phenomenon are \\"unofficial art\\" or \\"underground art.\\""@en .

dbr:Divisionism	rdfs:label	"Divisionism"@en ,
		"Dywizjonizm"@pl ,
		"Divisionismo"@es ,
		"Divisionnisme"@fr ,
		"Divisionismo"@pt ,
		"Divisionismo (pittura)"@it ;
	rdfs:comment	"Le divisionnisme (aussi appel\\u00E9 chromo-luminarisme) est une th\\u00E9orie picturale correspondant \\u00E0 un style qui consiste \\u00E0 appliquer sur un support de petites taches de couleur pure juxtapos\\u00E9es."@fr ,
		"El divisionismo (tambi\\u00E9n conocido como el cromoluminarismo) fue el estilo caracter\\u00EDstico en la pintura neoimpresionista, definido por la separaci\\u00F3n de colores en puntos individuales que interact\\u00FAan \\u00F3pticamente.Por requerir que el visor combine los colores \\u00F3pticamente en vez de mezclar los pigmentos f\\u00EDsicamente, los divisionistas creyeron que lograban la luminosidad m\\u00E1xima posible cient\\u00EDficamente."@es ,
		"O divisionismo tamb\\u00E9m designado por cromoluminarismo, refere-se a uma teoria ou a um estilo de pintura neo-impressionista, que separa as cores em pequenos pontos ou pinceladas de cor pura. A aplica\\u00E7\\u00E3o destes pontos na tela, leva a que seja o observador a misturar visualmente as cores e, assim, a \\"construir\\" a pintura. Em vez de as cores serem misturadas na palete, como at\\u00E9 ent\\u00E3o, aquelas s\\u00E3o aplicadas directamente na tela."@pt ,
		"Dywizjonizm (fr. division = podzia\\u0142) \\u2013 metoda malarska zapocz\\u0105tkowana przez tw\\u00F3rc\\u00F3w impresjonizmu, rozwini\\u0119ta przez neoimpresjonist\\u00F3w w tzw. pointylizm. Powstanie metody dywizjonizmu wi\\u0105\\u017Ce si\\u0119 z artystycznymi poszukiwaniami Claude\'a Moneta. Dywizjonizm polega na ograniczeniu palety barw widma s\\u0142onecznego. Farby nak\\u0142adane s\\u0105 plamami \\u201Eczystych\\u201D kolor\\u00F3w, kt\\u00F3re, obserwowane z pewnej odleg\\u0142o\\u015Bci, mieszaj\\u0105 si\\u0119 w siatk\\u00F3wce oka widza, tworz\\u0105c kolory uzupe\\u0142niaj\\u0105ce."@pl ,
		"Il divisionismo fu uno stile derivato dal Neo-Impressionismo caratterizzato dalla separazione dei colori in singoli punti o linee che interagiscono fra di loro in senso ottico; per tali motivi pu\\u00F2 essere definito come una variante specifica del Puntinismo. Il divisionismo non pu\\u00F2 essere definito un movimento pittorico, perch\\u00E9 non vi sono regole scritte da rispettare per dipingere con questo stile."@it ,
		"Divisionism (also called Chromoluminarism) was the characteristic style in Neo-Impressionist painting defined by the separation of colors into individual dots or patches which interacted optically.By requiring the viewer to combine the colors optically instead of physically mixing pigments, Divisionists believed they were achieving the maximum luminosity scientifically possible."@en .

dbr:Hartlib_Circle	rdfs:label	"Hartlib Circle"@en ,
		"C\\u00EDrculo de Hartlib"@es ;
	rdfs:comment	"Se denomina C\\u00EDrculo de Hartlib a una red de correspondencia establecida en el per\\u00EDodo 1630 a 1660, entre Samuel Hartlib y su red de relaciones. La red se extend\\u00EDa por Europa Occidental y Central, y era liderada por Samuel Hartlib, un hombre dedicado a la informaci\\u00F3n con sede en Londres. Hartlib trabaj\\u00F3 junto con John Dury, un personaje itinerante que abogaba por unificar a los protestantes."@es ,
		"The Hartlib Circle was the correspondence network set up in Western and Central Europe by Samuel Hartlib, an intelligencer based in London, and his associates, in the period 1630 to 1660. Hartlib worked closely with John Dury, an itinerant figure who worked to bring Protestants together."@en .

dbr:Spin_art	rdfs:label	"Spin Art"@de ,
		"Spin art"@fr ,
		"Spin art"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Spin art is an art form that primarily uses paint, a canvas and a spinning platform. It is primarily used to entertain and expose children to the process of art creation, although it can be enjoyed by people of all ages."@en ,
		"Le spin art ou spin painting est un proc\\u00E9d\\u00E9 pictural utilisant la force centrifuge pour r\\u00E9partir de la peinture sur un support. On retrouve cette technique dans le monde scolaire comme dans l\'art contemporain."@fr ,
		"Spin Art, auch Swirl Art, ist eine abstrakte Maltechnik, die insbesondere von Kindern angewendet wird. Die kreativen Spielzeuge erschienen unter verschiedenen Namen wie Swirl \'N\' Paint, Swirl Art, spin-art-device oder auch einfach Malger\\u00E4t.Das Spielzeug besteht aus einem Drehteller, auf dem eine meist postkartengro\\u00DFe, wei\\u00DFe Pappe befestigt wird. Au\\u00DFen befindet sich eine runde oder rechteckige h\\u00F6here Umrandung. Der Drehteller wird per Motor in Rotation gebracht."@de .

		"La Scapigliatura (von ital. scapigliare: die Haare zerzausen) war die Bezeichnung f\\u00FCr eine Gruppe vorwiegend lombardischer K\\u00FCnstler und Schriftsteller in Mailand zwischen 1860 und 1880.Wie auch andere europ\\u00E4ische K\\u00FCnstlergruppen jener Jahre (etwa den Impressionisten) forderte sie eine Erneuerung der Kunst. In Anlehnung an die Pariser Boh\\u00E8me wurde der b\\u00FCrgerliche Lebensstil abgelehnt. Unzweifelhaft ist auch der Einfluss franz\\u00F6sischer Schriftsteller wie Charles Baudelaire und Gustave Flaubert."@de ,
		"Scapigliatura (Italian: [skapi\\u028E\\u028Ea\\u02C8tu\\u02D0ra]) is the name of an artistic movement which developed in Italy after the Risorgimento period (1815\\u20131871). The movement included poets, writers, musicians, painters and sculptors. The term Scapigliatura is the Italian equivalent of the French \\"boh\\u00E8me\\" (bohemian), literally meaning \\"unkempt\\" or \\"dishevelled\\"."@en .

dbr:Pseudorealism	rdfs:label	"Pseudorealism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Pseudorealism, also spelled pseudo-realism, is a term used in a variety of discourses, connoting any artistic and dramatic technique, or work of art, film and literature based on non-realistic ideas but intended to be received by the viewer as based on reality.The term Pseudorealism has a parallel in mathematical field of representation theory where, a (pseudo real)  or Quaternionic representation is a group representation that is equivalent to its complex conjugates."@en .

		"Yonkoma manga (4\\u30B3\\u30DE\\u6F2B\\u753B, \\"four cell manga\\", or 4-koma for short), a comic-strip format, generally consists of gag comic strips within four panels of equal size ordered from top to bottom. (They also sometimes run right-to-left horizontally or use a hybrid 2x2 style, depending on the layout requirements of the publication in which they appear.)  Though the word yonkoma comes from the Japanese, the style also exists outside of Japan in other Asian countries as well as in the English-speaking market."@en ,

		"The Kailyard school of Scottish fiction (1880-1914) was developed in the last decades of the 19th century as a reaction against what was seen as increasingly coarse writing representing Scottish life complete with all its blemishes. It has been considered to be an overly sentimental representation of rural life, cleansed of real problems and issues that affected the people, but proved for a time extremely popular."@en ,
		"Le mouvement Kailyard est un mouvement de la litt\\u00E9rature \\u00E9cossaise apparu \\u00E0 la fin du XIXe si\\u00E8cle en r\\u00E9action au naturalisme pr\\u00E9sentant la vie \\u00E9cossaise sous ses aspects les plus crus. Son nom est issu du scots kailyaird ou kailyard, qui d\\u00E9signe un petit carr\\u00E9 de choux adjacent \\u00E0 une ferme.Le mouvement a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 vu comme une repr\\u00E9sentation exag\\u00E9r\\u00E9ment sentimentale de la vie rurale, expurg\\u00E9e des v\\u00E9ritables probl\\u00E8mes affectant la population."@fr .

dbr:Graphic_arts	rdfs:label	"Artes gr\\u00E1ficas"@es ,
		"Graphische Kunst"@de ,
		"Graphic arts"@en ,
		"Arts graphiques"@fr ,
		"\\u30B0\\u30E9\\u30D5\\u30A3\\u30C3\\u30AF\\u30FB\\u30A2\\u30FC\\u30C8"@ja ;
	rdfs:comment	"A type of fine art, graphic art covers a broad range of art forms. Graphic art typically is two-dimensional and includes calligraphy, photography, drawing, painting, printmaking, lithography, typography, serigraphy (silk-screen printing), computer graphics, and bindery. Graphic art also consists of drawn plans and layouts for interior and architectural designs. The responsibility for effective communication also falls under the auspices of the graphic designer."@en ,

		"Artivist (artivista en castellano) es una palabra \\"portmanteau\\" que combina \\"arte\\" y \\"activismo\\". El Artivismo se ha desarrollado en los a\\u00F1os recientes al mismo tiempo que las protestas en contra de la globalizaci\\u00F3n y los conflictos armados emergieron y proliferaron. En muchos de los casos los artivistas tratan de empujar agendas pol\\u00EDticas con la idea del arte. 		"Vergangenheitsbew\\u00E4ltigung is a composite German word with individual and collective significance that describes processes of coming to terms with the past (Vergangenheit = past; Bew\\u00E4ltigung = overcome [the negative, repressed and incriminating, mental injuries and guilt]), which is perhaps best rendered in English as \\"struggle to overcome the [negatives of the] past\\". It is a key term in the study of post-1945 German literature and culture."@en ,
		"Vergangenheitsbew\\u00E4ltigung hat individuelle und kollektive Bedeutung. Bew\\u00E4ltigt werden m\\u00FCssen Negatives, Verdr\\u00E4ngtes und Belastendes, seelische Verletzungen und Schuldgef\\u00FChle."@de ,
		"Vergangenheitsbew\\u00E4ltigung is een samengesteld Duits woord waarmee de Duitse worsteling wordt aangeduid om in het reine te komen met het (meestal nationaalsocialistische) verleden. (Vergangenheit = verleden; Bew\\u00E4ltigung = in het reine komen met, overmeestering). De Duitse term Geschichtsaufarbeitung (verwerking van het verleden) heeft betrekking op hetzelfde proces, maar wordt minder vaak gebruikt."@nl ,

		"Vergangenheitsbew\\u00E4ltigung est un mot allemand qui d\\u00E9signe le moyen de g\\u00E9rer le pass\\u00E9. 	rdfs:comment	"Chromotherapy, sometimes called color therapy, colorology or cromatherapy, is an alternative medicine method, which is considered pseudoscience. Chromotherapists claim to be able to use light in the form of color to balance \\"energy\\" lacking from a person\'s body, whether it be on physical, emotional, spiritual, or mental levels."@en ,
		"La cromoterapia, conocida tambi\\u00E9n como la terapia del color, es una t\\u00E9cnica empleada en medicina alternativa cuyo objetivo es la curaci\\u00F3n de ciertas enfermedades a trav\\u00E9s del uso de colores.La cromoterapia o terapia del color pertenece a las t\\u00E9cnicas o pr\\u00E1cticas nueva era (new age), al igual que la proyecci\\u00F3n astral, la visualizaci\\u00F3n guiada, la iridolog\\u00EDa, la reflexolog\\u00EDa, el shiatsu y la sanaci\\u00F3n con pir\\u00E1mides y cristales.De acuerdo con la cromoterapia, los colores ejercen influencias emocionales en las personas, permitiendo generar un estado que facilite la sanaci\\u00F3n de enfermedades y restablecer los desequilibrios que producen dichos padecimientos.La cromoterapia funciona aplicando una luz con un color que corresponda al color de una enfermedad, infecci\\u00F3n, virus, hongos, bacterias, y par\\u00E1sitos."@es ,

		"La cromoterapia \\u00E8 una medicina alternativa che fa uso dei colori come terapia per la cura delle malattie.L\'utilizzo dei colori \\u00E8 normalmente regolato da principi comuni, analoghi a quelli che portano a scegliere il colore dell\'abito da indossare o la tinta delle pareti di casa per abbinarli a una determinata personalit\\u00E0 e favorire o contrastare un certo stato d\'animo."@it ,

		"Cromoterapia \\u00E9 a pr\\u00E1tica da utiliza\\u00E7\\u00E3o das cores na cura de doen\\u00E7as. 		"\\u0413\\u0443\\u0442\\u0430\\u0439 (\\u044F\\u043F. \\u5177\\u4F53, \\u00AB\\u041A\\u043E\\u043D\\u043A\\u0440\\u0435\\u0442\\u043D\\u043E\\u0441\\u0442\\u044C\\u00BB) \\u2014 \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u0435\\u0441\\u0442\\u0432\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0435 \\u043D\\u0430\\u043F\\u0440\\u0430\\u0432\\u043B\\u0435\\u043D\\u0438\\u0435 \\u0438 \\u0430\\u0441\\u0441\\u043E\\u0446\\u0438\\u0430\\u0446\\u0438\\u044F \\u0445\\u0443\\u0434\\u043E\\u0436\\u043D\\u0438\\u043A\\u043E\\u0432 \\u0432 \\u043F\\u043E\\u0441\\u043B\\u0435\\u0432\\u043E\\u0435\\u043D\\u043D\\u043E\\u0439 \\u042F\\u043F\\u043E\\u043D\\u0438\\u0438."@ru ,
		"Grupo Gutai (\\u5177\\u4F53, pode ser traduzido com \\"incorpora\\u00E7\\u00E3o\\") foi um grupo de artistas japoneses do p\\u00F3s-guerra."@pt ,
		"Gutai (\\u5177\\u4F53, Gutai?, ao\\u00FBt 1954 - mars 1972) est un mouvement artistique d\'avant-garde japonais.Le terme vient de gu, \\u00AB instrument \\u00BB et tai, \\u00AB corps \\u00BB, son adverbe gutaiteki, \\u00AB concret \\u00BB, \\u00AB incarnation \\u00BB, qui s\'oppose donc \\u00E0 l\'abstrait, c\'est-\\u00E0-dire \\u00E0 l\'art abstrait."@fr ,
		"The Gutai group (\\u5177\\u4F53) is the first radical, post-war artistic group in Japan. It was founded in 1954 by the painter Jiro Yoshihara in Osaka, Japan, in response to the reactionary artistic context of the time. This influential group was involved in large-scale multimedia environments, performances, and theatrical events and emphasizes the relationship between body and matter in pursuit of originality. The movement rejected traditional art styles in favor of performative immediacy."@en .

dbr:Dutch_and_Flemish_Renaissance_painting	rdfs:label	"Renascimento flamengo"@pt ,
		"Pieno Rinascimento fiammingo e olandese"@it ,
		"Renaissance flamande"@fr ,
		"Dutch and Flemish Renaissance painting"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Il pieno Rinascimento fiammingo e olandese \\u00E8 una fase dell\'arte europea databile essenzialmente tra la fine del XV e il XVI secolo."@it ,
		"Le terme de renaissance flamande d\\u00E9signe la r\\u00E9ponse apport\\u00E9e au XVIe si\\u00E8cle dans les Pays-Bas m\\u00E9ridionaux au renouveau pictural amen\\u00E9 par la renaissance italienne."@fr ,
		"No norte da Europa, a Renascen\\u00E7a se materializou em torno da vis\\u00E3o do realismo intenso da obra de Albrecht D\\u00FCrer. Nos Pa\\u00EDses Baixos, os pintores seguiram o impulso setentrional para a observa\\u00E7\\u00E3o precisa e para o naturalismo, no \\u00E2mbito das paisagens e retratos. Assim como na It\\u00E1lia, a Renascen\\u00E7a setentrional terminou com o Maneirismo, que durou uma gera\\u00E7\\u00E3o a mais que na It\\u00E1lia."@pt ,
		"Dutch and Flemish Renaissance painting represents the 16th century response to Italian Renaissance art in the Low Countries. These artists, who span from the Antwerp Mannerists and Hieronymus Bosch at the start of the 16th century to the late Northern Mannerists such as Hendrik Goltzius and Joachim Wtewael at the end, drew on both the recent innovations of Italian painting and the local traditions of the Early Netherlandish artists. Antwerp was the most important artistic centre in the region."@en .

		"L\\u2019ind\\u00E9pendantisme kurde d\\u00E9signe l\'ensemble des discours politiques pr\\u00F4nant la cr\\u00E9ation d\'un \\u00C9tat kurde autonome ou ind\\u00E9pendant, le Kurdistan. Ces discours sont notamment tenus par des partis politiques, des groupes menant une lutte arm\\u00E9e et des associations \\u00E0 vocation culturelle."@fr ,
		"Kurdayet\\u00EE, auf Deutsch in etwa \\u201EKurdismus\\u201C, ist ein vor allem im Irak verwendeter Begriff f\\u00FCr kurdisches Nationalbewusstsein. Er bedeutet im weitesten Sinne, dass Kurdistan auf eine lange Besiedlungsgeschichte zur\\u00FCckblickt, Kurden eine Nation sind und sie deshalb das Recht auf politische Selbstbestimmung haben."@de .

dbr:Tubism	rdfs:label	"Tubism"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Tubism is a term coined by the art critic Louis Vauxcelles in 1911 to describe the style of French artist Fernand L\\u00E9ger.  Meant as derision, the term was inspired by  L\\u00E9ger\'s idiosyncratic version of Cubism, in which he emphasized cylindrical shapes.  The style was developed by L\\u00E9ger in his paintings of 1909\\u20131919, such as Nudes in the Forest (1909-10) and The Card Players (1917)."@en .

dbr:New_Khmer_Architecture	rdfs:label	"New Khmer Architecture"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"The term New Khmer Architecture was coined by authors Helen Grant Ross and Darryl Leon Collins to describe an architectural movement in Cambodia during the 1950s and 1960s. The style blended elements of the Modern Movement with two distinctly Cambodian traditions: the grand tradition of Angkor, and the vernacular tradition of ordinary people\'s houses. The Kingdom of Cambodia gained independence from France in 1953."@en .

		"The Danish Golden Age covers the period of creative production in Denmark, especially  during the first half of the 19th century. Although Copenhagen had suffered from fires, bombardment and national bankruptcy, the arts took on a new period of creativity catalysed by Romanticism from Germany."@en ,
		"La Edad de Oro danesa es el per\\u00EDodo de producci\\u00F3n creativa en Dinamarca, especialmente durante la primera mitad del siglo XIX. In der Neuzeit gewannen seit der Renaissance die Abformungen lebender Menschen in Gips zunehmend an Bedeutung als Modelle f\\u00FCr Abg\\u00FCsse (zum Beispiel in Bronze im Wachsausschmelzverfahren) und zu Studienzwecken. 		"Le Lifecasting est un processus de cr\\u00E9ation d\'une copie en trois dimensions d\'un corps humain vivant au moyen de mat\\u00E9riel de moulage versant sp\\u00E9cial et le mat\\u00E9riau de moulage.Dans certains cas rares, le lifecasting est \\u00E9galement l\'utilisation d\'animaux vivants. Les plus courants sont les installations d\'h\\u00E9bergement sont torses, des mains et des visages, des ventres de femmes enceintes, bien qu\'il soit possible de copier n\'importe quelle partie du corps."@fr ,
		"Lifecasting is the process of creating a three-dimensional copy of a living human body, through the use of molding and casting techniques. In rare cases lifecasting is also practiced on living animals. The most common lifecasts are of torsoes, pregnant bellies, hands, faces, and gentalia and it is possible for an experienced lifecasting practitioner to copy any part of the body. Lifecasting is usually limited to a section of the body at a time, but full-body lifecasts are achievable too."@en .

		"Il concettismo, o conceptismo in spagnolo, \\u00E8 uno stile letterario caratteristico della letteratura barocca spagnola della fine del XVI secolo al XVII secolo, del quale Alonso de Ledesma fu l\\u2019iniziatore.Lo scrittore gesuita Graci\\u00E1n ha teorizzato, in l\'Agudeza y arte del ingenio (Acutezza e arte dell\'ingegno, 1647), questo misticismo del pensiero, caratterizzato da un ritmo rapido, un vocabolario semplice, diretto da metafore piene d\\u2019ingegno e di giochi di parole, il cui principale rappresentante fu il poeta Quevedo. "@it ,
		"Conceptismo of conceptisme is een literaire beweging van de Spaanse barok. Het is een semantisch rijke en geconcentreerde stijl die werd gebruikt in de late 16e eeuw en in de 17e eeuw."@nl ,
		"Le conceptisme, conceptismo en espagnol, est un style litt\\u00E9raire caract\\u00E9ristique de la litt\\u00E9rature baroque espagnole de la fin du XVIe au XVIIe si\\u00E8cle et dont Alonso de Ledesma fut l\'initiateur. Francisco de Quevedo en a \\u00E9t\\u00E9 le plus grand repr\\u00E9sentant."@fr ,
		"Conceptismo is a literary movement of the Baroque period of Portuguese and Spanish literature. It began in the late 16th century and lasted through the 17th century.Conceptismo is characterized by a rapid rhythm, directness, simple vocabulary, witty metaphors, and wordplay."@en ,
		"El conceptismo es una corriente de la literatura  que se basa en la asociaci\\u00F3n ingeniosa entre palabras e ideas. Su m\\u00E1ximo te\\u00F3rico contempor\\u00E1neo, Baltasar Graci\\u00E1n, en la Agudeza y arte de ingenio, define el \\u00ABconcepto\\u00BB como: Un acto del entendimiento que expresa la correspondencia que se halla entre los objetosEl conceptismo se caracteriza por la concisi\\u00F3n de la expresi\\u00F3n y la intensidad sem\\u00E1ntica de las palabras, que se cargan de significados, adoptando varios sentidos."@es ,
		"Conceptismo, tamb\\u00E9m chamado de conceitismo, \\u00E9 uma vertente liter\\u00E1ria do estilo barroco surgida em meados do s\\u00E9culo XVII na Espanha."@pt ,
		"Konceptyzm (w\\u0142. concetto \\u2013 \\u015Bwietny, wyszukany pomys\\u0142) \\u2013 g\\u0142\\u00F3wny pr\\u0105d w poezji baroku, cechuj\\u0105cy si\\u0119 d\\u0105\\u017Ceniem do nieustannego zadziwiania, zaskakiwania i zaszokowania czytelnika. Koncept to wyszukany, oryginalny  i niespodziewany pomys\\u0142, na kt\\u00F3rym oparty jest utw\\u00F3r poetycki, zar\\u00F3wno pod wzgl\\u0119dem budowy jak i tre\\u015Bci. Poetyk\\u0119 konceptyzmu mo\\u017Cna okre\\u015Bli\\u0107 mianem poetyki kontrastu. Zami\\u0142owanie do niego zaznaczy\\u0142o si\\u0119 w doborze skojarze\\u0144, puent czy trop\\u00F3w, takich jak antytezy, oksymorony, paradoksy."@pl .

		"\\u0413\\u043E\\u043D\\u0433\\u043E\\u0440\\u0438\\u0437\\u043C"@ru ;
	rdfs:comment	"Il Culteranesimo o Culteranismo o Gongorismo \\u00E8 un\'estetica del Barocco spagnolo nell\'ambito pi\\u00F9 generale del Concettismo, con il quale divide l\'intenzione di rarefare e calibrare l\'espressione separandola dall\'equilibrio e chiarezza dei classici, ma con il procedimento opposto, cio\\u00E8 dilatando il significato in una maggiore espressione estetica, non per chiarire il messaggio mediante il procedimento della parafrasi, ma piuttosto per impressionare e confondere con il labirintico, il sensoriale e l\'evanescente dell\'espressione, ed applicarsi fondamentalmente al genere lirico e al verso invece che alla prosa.Lo stile culterano \\u00E8 un\'amplificazione non parafrastica in quanto non pretende esplicare ma dilettare con l\'esercizio intellettuale dell\'enigma. "@it ,
		"El culteranismo es una corriente literaria del barroco espa\\u00F1ol dentro de la m\\u00E1s general del conceptismo, con el cual comparte la intenci\\u00F3n de intensificar la expresi\\u00F3n separ\\u00E1ndola del equilibrio y claridad cl\\u00E1sica, pero en lugar de la condensaci\\u00F3n de significados propia del conceptismo m\\u00E1s caracter\\u00EDstico, aboga por la per\\u00EDfrasis embellecedora y la elusi\\u00F3n del vocabulario com\\u00FAn, utilizando para ello latinizaci\\u00F3n de la sintaxis y el l\\u00E9xico mediante el hip\\u00E9rbaton y los cultismos, las met\\u00E1foras puras, y las per\\u00EDfrasis alusivas a menudo con referentes de la mitolog\\u00EDa cl\\u00E1sica. "@es ,
		"Denomina-se culteranismo ou cultismo o aspecto do barroco voltado para o jogo de palavras, para o rebuscamento da forma, para a ornamenta\\u00E7\\u00E3o estil\\u00EDstica, para o preciosismo ling\\u00FC\\u00EDstico, para a erudi\\u00E7\\u00E3o minuciosa. Retrata-se a realidade de modo indireto, real\\u00E7ando mais a maneira de representar que propriamente o apresentado."@pt ,
		"Culteranismo is a stylistic movement of the Baroque period of Spanish history that is also commonly referred to as Gongorismo (after Luis de G\\u00F3ngora)."@en ,

		"Le cultisme ou cult\\u00E9ranisme, estilo culto ou culteranismo en espagnol, est l\\u2019un des styles litt\\u00E9raires de la p\\u00E9riode baroque espagnole qui, s\\u2019opposant au conceptisme de Quevedo (bien qu\'en r\\u00E9alit\\u00E9 il s\'en rapproche fortement parfois par ses recours), se caract\\u00E9rise par une profusion ornementale de m\\u00E9taphores, un vocabulaire opulent, un ordre syntactique complexe, de multiples m\\u00E9taphores pr\\u00E9cieuses, au service d\\u2019un contenu extr\\u00EAmement conventionnel.P\\u00E9joratif, le terme de cult\\u00E9ranisme, forg\\u00E9 d\\u2019apr\\u00E8s \\u00AB luth\\u00E9ranisme \\u00BB pour comparer ses adeptes \\u00E0 des h\\u00E9r\\u00E9tiques de l\\u2019authentique po\\u00E9sie, semble avoir \\u00E9t\\u00E9 utilis\\u00E9 pour la premi\\u00E8re fois par l\\u2019humaniste espagnol Bartolom\\u00E9 Jim\\u00E9nez Pat\\u00F3n (1569-1640), d\\u00E9signe en r\\u00E9alit\\u00E9 un type de rh\\u00E9torique d\\u00E9j\\u00E0 en cours dans le mani\\u00E9risme.Le cult\\u00E9ranisme est une branche de l\\u2019esth\\u00E9tique baroque espagnole plus g\\u00E9n\\u00E9rale que le conceptisme avec lequel il a en commun la complication du sens de l\\u2019\\u0153uvre litt\\u00E9raire, non par la concision et la concentration de la signification, comme il \\u00E9tait de coutume, mais au contraire par l\\u2019atomisation et l\\u2019ordonnancement sous forme d\\u2019\\u00E9nigme pour exercer la culture et l\\u2019intelligence par le d\\u00E9codage d\\u2019une mani\\u00E8re plus d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9e et sensorielle. "@fr .

dbr:Lightpainting	rdfs:label	"Lightpainting"@en ;
	rdfs:comment	"Lightpainting is an art form developed by artist Stephen Knapp and introduced in 2002. Lightpainting (one word) is not to be confused with light painting (two words), the latter of which is a photographic process recording traces of light on film or digital media to create images that must be reproduced in printed or transparency form."@en .

		"O neorrealismo foi uma corrente art\\u00EDstica de meados do s\\u00E9culo XX, com um car\\u00E1cter ideol\\u00F3gico marcadamente de esquerda / marxista, que teve ramifica\\u00E7\\u00F5es em v\\u00E1rias formas de arte (literatura, pintura, m\\u00FAsica) mas atingiu o seu expoente m\\u00E1ximo no Cinema neorrealista, sobretudo no realismo po\\u00E9tico franc\\u00EAs e no neorrealismo italiano.Com o mesmo nome, mas com distin\\u00E7\\u00E3o, pode ser observada uma Teoria das rela\\u00E7\\u00F5es internacionais."@pt ,
		"Le N\\u00E9or\\u00E9alisme est un mouvement litt\\u00E9raire et cin\\u00E9matographique qui s\'est d\\u00E9velopp\\u00E9 en Italie (et au Portugal) dans les ann\\u00E9es 1940 et 1950. Cet article traite du n\\u00E9or\\u00E9alisme dans son ensemble. Pour un article plus complet sur le mouvement cin\\u00E9matographique, voyez N\\u00E9or\\u00E9alisme (cin\\u00E9ma)."@fr ,
		"Het neorealisme is een internationale beweging die halverwege de jaren vijftig van de twintigste eeuw ontstond in Engeland en Amerika. Naast het neorealisme wordt ook de term poptical-art gebruikt. Het neo-realisme zien we terug in de schilderkunst, journalistiek, literatuur, film etc. Onveranderlijk is de \'gewone mens\' en het \'gewone leven\' het onderwerp. In 1960 krijgt poptical-art navolging in Frankrijk onder de term Nouveau R\\u00E9alisme."@nl ,
		"In art, neorealism was established by the ex-Camden Town Group painters Charles Ginner and Harold Gilman at the beginning of World War I.  They set out to explore the spirit of their age through the shapes and colours of daily life. Their intentions were proclaimed in Ginner\\u2019s manifesto in New Age (1 January 1914), which was also used as the preface to Gilman and Ginner\\u2019s two-man exhibition of that year."@en .
dbr:Quito_School	rdfs:label	"Quito School"@en ,
		"Escuela Quite\\u00F1a"@es ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Quito School (Escuela Quite\\u00F1a) is a Latin American artistic tradition that constitutes essentially the whole of the professional artistic output developed in the territory of the Royal Audience of Quito \\u2014 from Pasto and Popay\\u00E1n in the north to Piura and Cajamarca in the south \\u2014 during the Spanish colonial period (1542-1824). It is especially associated with the 17th and 18th centuries and was almost exclusively focused on the religious art of the Catholic Church in the country."@en ,

dbr:Rouen_School	rdfs:label	"School van Rouen"@nl ,
		"Scuola di Rouen"@it ,
		"Rouen School"@en ,
		"\\u00C9cole de Rouen"@fr ;
	rdfs:comment	"The Rouen School (L\'\\u00C9cole de Rouen) is a term used for artists or artisans born or working in Rouen, or for all artistic products from Rouen, such as Rouen faience of the 16th to 18th centuries. The term was first used in 1902 by Ars\\u00E8ne Alexandre in his catalogue to an exhibition by Joseph Delattre in the galerie Durand-Ruel in Paris."@en ,
		"L\'\\u00C9cole de Rouen est l\'expression utilis\\u00E9e pour regrouper sous une m\\u00EAme \\u00E9tiquette des artistes ou artisans rouennais. Elle est aussi d\'usage \\u00E0 propos de tout ensemble de productions originaire de la ville de Rouen, comme la fa\\u00EFence des XVIe et XVIIIe si\\u00E8cles."@fr ,
		"De School van Rouen (Ecole de Rouen) is de benaming voor een groep kunstschilders aan het einde van de negentiende eeuw en de eerste helft van de twintigste eeuw, werkzaam in of afkomstig uit Rouen. De term werd voor het eerst gebruikt in 1902 door de criticus Ars\\u00E8ne Alexandre in de catalogus van een expositie van deze schilders te Parijs."@nl ,
		"La Scuola di Rouen (in francese \\u00C9cole de Rouen) \\u00E8 un termine usato per indicare la corrente pittorica di artisti o artigiani nati o che hanno lavorano a Rouen. Sotto questa denominazione figurano tutti i prodotti artistici di Rouen, come le Rouen faience dal sedicesimo al diciottesimo secolo.Il termine fu coniato nel 1902 da Ars\\u00E8ne Alexandre nel suo catalogo di una mostra di Joseph Delattre nella galleria di Paul Durand-Ruel a Parigi."@it .
